		details:
			"► \nAbout\nApplied \n\nApplied\nMaterials is the leader in materials engineering solutions used to produce\nvirtually every new chip and advanced display in the world. Our expertise in modifying\nmaterials at atomic levels and on an industrial scale enables customers to\ntransform possibilities into reality. At Applied Materials, our innovations\nmake possible the technology shaping the future.\n\n \n\n► Your Opportunity\n\nThis role is\nfor candidate having a bachelor’s or master’s degree with strong academic\nbackground in (one of areas) of material science & engineering, chemical\nengineering, electrical engineering (specialization in VLSI/chip design),\nmetallurgy with specialization in material science. Candidates alternatively\ncan have educational background in sciences as Physicist, Chemist etc.\n\nCandidate should be self-starter and can work with\nminimal guidance and knows how to navigate cross-functionally. They demonstrate\na system thinking approach to their assignments and can synthesize information\nto take effect action. They can apply their fundamental theories, principles,\nand concepts to solve real world problems. \n\n► Roles & Responsibility \n\n· \nCollect data,\nanalyze, and compile reports on basic process engineering experiments, within\nsafety guidelines\n\n· \nPerform hardware\ncharacterization on basic systems, within safety guidelines\n\n· \nTroubleshoot basic\nproblems, perform Root Cause Analysis, and resolve basic process engineering\nissues\n\n· \nMeasure film\nproperties and organize data/reports for review\n\n· \nGenerate internal\ndocumentation for products, presentations, and technical reports\n\n· \nInteract with\ncustomers to resolve basic process engineering issues/problems under direct\nsupervision\n\n· \nWork with engineers,\nvendors, and suppliers, under direct supervision\n\n· \nBecome familiar with\nthe process of implementing new technology, products, and analytical\ninstrumentation\n\n· \nWork on system\nengineering projects that have a substantial mix of electrical, mechanical,\nphysics, algorithms and software design utilizing expertise in technical area\nof specialty.\n\n· \nPerform tests and\nprovide feedback to product engineering and software on new designs and ongoing\nengineering improvements.\n\n· \nProblem\nidentification and troubleshooting engineering problems in field of technical\nexpertise, including serviceability and manufacturability.\n\n· \nWork with System\nIntegration during the assembly and final testing of all products.\n\n· \nReview all external\nequipment interfaces, analyze architecture ideas, and insure they are up to\ndate and documented.\n\n· \nInterface with other groups on issues,\nranging from Facility, HW, SW, C&F, Service to Business Value End to End.\n\n \n\nTravel:\n\n75% travel required\n\nEligibility Criteria: \n\n Must\n have 7 CGPA or 70% and above in X, XII, UG & PG\n\n \n\n \n\nFunctional Knowledge\n\n Demonstrates conceptual knowledge of theories, practices, and\n procedures within a discipline \n\n \n\nBusiness Expertise\n\n Applies general knowledge of business developed through education or\n experience \n Recommends best\n practices to improve products, processes, or services.\n\n \n\nLeadership\n\n Individual contributor; accountable for developing technical\n contribution\n Ability to\n influence others independent of level and function, including external\n partners.\n Strong\n decision-making skills and record of good judgments.\n\n \n\nProblem Solving\n\n Uses existing procedures to solve standard problems; analyzes information\n and standard practices to make judgments\n Thinks\n strategically to solve problems and resolve issues to manage speed of\n execution.\n Leads others to\n solve complex problems; uses sophisticated analytical thought to exercise\n judgment and identify innovative solutions.\n\n \n\nImpact\n\n Has limited impact on own work team; works within standardized\n procedures and practices to achieve objectives and meet deadlines\n Impacts the\n achievement of customer, operational, project or service objectives; work\n is guided by mindset of innovation and commercialization of product ideas.\n\n \n\nInterpersonal Skills\n\n Exchanges straightforward information, asks questions and checks for\n understanding\n Communicates\n difficult concepts and negotiates with others to adopt a different point\n of view.\n\n \n\nQualification\n\nBachelor’s Undergraduate and/or master’s degree in material\nscience & engineering, chemical engineering,\nelectrical engineering (specialization in VLSI/chip design), metallurgy\nengineering with specialization in material science. Candidates alternatively\ncan have educational background in sciences as Physicist, Chemist, or similar\nfields.",
