		details:
			"Role: Operations Research Scientist – ILocation: BangaloreAbout usMeesho - Every story here begins with a spark of ambition and a touch of entrepreneurial magic. We’re not just a platform, we’re your partner in transforming dreams into reality.Our MissionDemocratising internet commerce for everyone - Meesho (Meri shop) started with a single idea in mind to be an e-commerce destination for the next billion Indian consumers and enable 100 million small businesses to succeed online. We provide sellers with a range of industry-first benefits such as zero commission and an affordable shipping cost., growing their business by tapping the company’s massive customer base, state-of-the-art tech infrastructure, pan-India logistics at cost through third-party logistics providers and in-house logistics arm Valmo in an 'Everyday Low Cost' channel for sellers. Affordable, relatable merchandise mirroring local markets has helped us make inroads with first-time internet users in the country. We cater to an underserved and unique customer base and cover serviceable pincode in the country. Our unique business model and continuous innovation has enabled us to become the first Indian horizontal E-commerce company.About the Data Science TeamOur Data Science team is the Avengers to Meesho’s S.H.I.E.L.D 🛡. And why not? We are the ones who assemble during the toughest challenges and devise creative solutions, building intelligent systems for millions of our users who are looking at a thousand different categories of products. We’ve barely scratched the surface, and have amazing challenges in charting the future of commerce for Bharat.Supply Chain Network Optimization is an integral part of the VaLMo Data Science team that operates at the heart of VaLMo's vision, developing innovative, data-driven solutions that directly impact millions of users. We're not just solving today's problems; we're thinking long term to build models and frameworks that will define the future of our business. This team uses a wide variety of engineering and advanced applied mathematical techniques (OR, ML, DL, MILP etc) techniques to study and solve niche problems in supply chain across the entire value chain (network design, first/last mile optimization)Our typical day involves dealing with optimizing the VaLMo network, identifying the precise ETA at every single node of the network. As a Data Scientist, you will navigate uncharted territories with us, discovering new paths to creating solutions for our users.🔍 You will be at the forefront of interesting challenges and solve unique customer problems in an untapped market.But wait – there’s more to us. Our team is huge on having a well-rounded personal and professional life. When we aren't nose-deep in data, you will most likely find us belting “Summer of 69” at the nearest Karaoke bar, or debating who the best Spider-Man is: Maguire, Garfield, or Holland? You tell us ☺💼 About the RoleAs a Operation Research Scientist - I, you won’t just crunch numbers — you’ll design solutions, build scalable models,and push boundaries.You’ll work across product and tech teams to:● Develop cutting-edge optimization techniques for complex non-linear and integer programming problems.● Designing and implementing applied mathematical models to address complex business problems.● Apply OR models for efficiently managing VaLMo network● Predict demand patterns and key business metrics● Predict ETA at node level in VaLMO networkEligibility Criteria:This role is open only to students from the 2026 batch pursuing M.Tech and M.Sc programs in IEOR.Required Skills & Experience:● Strong fundamentals in Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and Statistics● Proficiency in Python, SQL, and frameworks like PyTorch or TensorFlow● Solid understanding of hypothesis testing, linear algebra, and model evaluation techniques● Strong analytical mindset with the ability to draw insights from complex or unstructured data● At least one internship experience related to Data Science or related fields reflected in the resumeCompensation offered -Total CTC (INR): 60,00,000 per annumFixed Compensation: 24,00,000 per annum●Joining Bonuses:○Year 1: INR 7,50,000○Year 2: INR 8,50,000○Year 3: INR 9,50,000○Year 4: INR 10,50,000Other Perks and Benefits:●Flexible work hours and a healthy work-life balance.●Regular team outings, fun activities, and engagement in various clubs.●Opportunity to work with a diverse and talented team, exposure to different business verticalsand the chance to make a significant impact. 🎯 Join usThis isn’t just a job — it’s your chance to build for Bharat, experiment at scale, and grow alongside one ofIndia’s most innovative startups.",
