		details:
			'Qualification : B.Tech./M.Tech.in Aerospace, Mechanical, Electrical, Electronics,As a Propulsion System Engineer, you will be contributing towards various aircraft programs on system design, development and integration aspects while collaborating and interfacing with engine manufacturers, multiple design offices and stakeholders.The various activities to be performed are: Consolidate Engine System Requirements with the different internal stakeholders.Contribute to Integration activities with engine manufacturer and Airbus team relative to Engine system: Design reviews, Interfaces definition, architecture optimization.Understand the system design of Engine Interface function in order to analyse the design change / modifications to launching the necessary actions to identify the root causesContribute to innovation of our Products and support TRL (Technical Readiness Level) maturity gates.Define and validate functional requirements and interface requirements for the integration (systems, mechanical, hydro-mechanical, thermal and Multiphysics) of the Powerplant System which encompasses Engine and/or Propeller structure, Nacelle and equipment (pump, heat exchanger, valve, tank, pipe, etc.).Contribute to the certification by supporting the delivery of the Powerplant Certification dossier.Deliver Technical Specification to suppliers of the components.Perform Verification and Validation activities to ensure there are no regressions and compliance with the set of the Powerplant requirements.Analysis of the in-service queries to identify potential impact (airworthiness, reliability, cost etc.), launching the necessary actions to identify the root causesSupport Powerplant industrialization, Entry Into Service and In-Service operation.Develop competences relative to System Engineering and MBSEJob Disclaimer & NotificationsWe bring to the notice of all concerned that Airbus Group India Pvt. Ltd (hereinafter referred to as "AIG") follows a fair and merit-based employee selection and recruitment practice.Airbus Group India does not:● Send job offers from free email services including but not limited to Gmail, Rediffmail, Yahoomail, Hotmail and others● Authorize anyone to either collect money or arrive at any monetary arrangement in return fora job at AIG● Charge / accept any form of consideration or security deposit from job seekers and applicantsduring any stage of the selection and/ or recruitment process● Request for your credit card number or bank account numberIt has come to our attention that fake job offers under the aegis of Airbus India or Airbus Group India Pvt. Ltd. have been circulated by unauthorized personnel. On receipt of an interview call for any job at AIG, the candidate may take some measures such as visiting the official website or career site of Airbus to get the contact details to enquire with the Human Resources department of Airbus India regarding such jobs and/or the interview details and any other relevant informationFor further information on Airbus India Careers, please click here. Please check www.airbus.com to get the contact details and enquire with the company to confirm if any information that you have received is genuine; do not respond to any fraudulent communication. AIG will not be responsible to anyone acting on an employment offer not directly made by Airbus Group India Pvt Ltd. anyone making an employment offer in return for money or other type of gain is not authorized by AIG and is not offering an approved job. AIG reserves the right to take legal action, including criminal action, against such individuals/entities**Airbus is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and is committed to create an inclusive and diverse work environment. AGI selects job applicants (internal and external) on the basis of suitability for the job, and irrespective of gender, marital status, age, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, nationality, religion, ethnicity or differently abled/ (dis)ability. )',
