		details:
			'As an Industrial Design & Architecture Engineer, you will be supporting the Top Company Objectives of improving the design of plants, stations to support the Industrial system in the ramp up for existing programs and create a robust and resilient Industrial system for future generation of Aircraft. The profile involves working with the Industrial DMU, preparing related methodology documentation. Defining, developing and deploying the Industrial systems and digital twin capabilities in the frame of digital manufacturing and Industry 4.0. Creating best practices to assist the Industrial teams from conceptual design through the finished industrial system.The individual gets the opportunity to work on the entire spectrum of programs from the existing Airbus Aircraft fleet (A320, A330 , A350) to the Zero-E programs.Required skills and experience:Digital Manufacturing & Industry 4.0: Experience as a Digital Manufacturing Engineer to work on Industry 4.0 technologies and reach the ambition towards digital twin. The Scope of activities involves:Design Plant Layouts as per different rate of production along with 3D simulations for logistics and Human path validation.Iterate on alternate solutions and execute trade off with different simulation Industrial KPIs.Define forward and inverse kinematics to conceptualize new Jig designs and perform 3D Flow SimulationAutomate Industrial system design with Robotics simulations (Material handling, spot welding, Arc Welding).Ergonomic analysis and evaluation for health and safety of workers.Design change, release process and Configuration Management within industrial setup.Augmented / Virtual Reality for station and Jig design validation.Manufacturing Engineering: Use ME Shopfloor Knowledge/Experience to implement Lean manufacturing while designing/improving Industrial system. Use Industrial Engineering principles in order to define the best suitable layout with most optimized processes which will adhere to the target Takt.Build sequence Creation/validation.Good level of GD&T knowledge to understand and implement industrial tolerancing.Knowledge on reading design / manufacturing drawings to understand or design 2D/3D Layouts, Jigs and Tools.Develop NC Programming and Simulation to deploy on the shop floor.Industrial Architecture: Technically lead development projects from conceptual phase of R&T (of tomorrow) projects until implementation fostering co-design approachStakeholder management to drive architecture projects to meet requirements reaching best performance Capture and analyze stakeholder needs, defining architectural solutions to meet or exceed customer expectationsAlign architecture strategy with the organization\'s business goals and long-term strategic planningBest to have Airbus product knowledge of different programs along with basic knowledge on Structural assembly and Systems design (Electrical System Integration/ Mechanical System Integration)It is not expected for one person to have all the above skillset. The job requires the basic level of understanding of the above.The Job role would also give exposure to different career paths under the perimeter of the Industrial system such as Industrial Digital Mockup, Ergonomist (Health & safety), Robotic Simulation, Jigs & Tools design plus its tolerancing. If you are looking for a healthy working environment, young and an enthusiastic team with great growth opportunities this team is a great place to be.TOOL SKILLS:3DExperience Delmia or any similar Tools. CATIA Google Workspace (Presentation, docs,etc)VericutEDUCATION:B.Tech. / B.E. / M.Tech. / M.E. in Mechanical / Industrial / ProductionSOFT SKILLS:Ability to work independently & in a team in a transnational environment.Assertive communication and interpersonal skills.Willingness to learn new skills, self-development.Ability to work in multiple projects and drive innovation initiatives.Strong problem solving and logical thinking ability.Effective decision-making capabilities.Job Disclaimer & NotificationsWe bring to the notice of all concerned that Airbus Group India Pvt. Ltd (hereinafter referred to as "AIG") follows a fair and merit-based employee selection and recruitment practice.Airbus Group India does not:● Send job offers from free email services including but not limited to Gmail, Rediffmail, Yahoomail, Hotmail and others● Authorize anyone to either collect money or arrive at any monetary arrangement in return fora job at AIG● Charge / accept any form of consideration or security deposit from job seekers and applicantsduring any stage of the selection and/ or recruitment process● Request for your credit card number or bank account numberIt has come to our attention that fake job offers under the aegis of Airbus India or Airbus Group India Pvt. Ltd. have been circulated by unauthorized personnel. On receipt of an interview call for any job at AIG, the candidate may take some measures such as visiting the official website or career site of Airbus to get the contact details to enquire with the Human Resources department of Airbus India regarding such jobs and/or the interview details and any other relevant informationFor further information on Airbus India Careers, please click here. Please check www.airbus.com to get the contact details and enquire with the company to confirm if any information that you have received is genuine; do not respond to any fraudulent communication. AIG will not be responsible to anyone acting on an employment offer not directly made by Airbus Group India Pvt Ltd. anyone making an employment offer in return for money or other type of gain is not authorized by AIG and is not offering an approved job. AIG reserves the right to take legal action, including criminal action, against such individuals/entities**Airbus is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and is committed to create an inclusive and diverse work environment. AGI selects job applicants (internal and external) on the basis of suitability for the job, and irrespective of gender, marital status, age, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, nationality, religion, ethnicity or differently abled/ (dis)ability. )',
