			"Required Domain Expertise (skills):M.Tech: Aerospace Engineering / Mechanical EngineeringGood logical reasoning, analytical skills,( Data Analytics preferable)Basic understanding of Aircraft design and sub-systems. Job scope (Tasks & accountabilities):To support the design and development of Overall Aircraft level target weights and to track aircraft weight evolution throughout the development phase for MSI (Mechanical system installation) or ESI (Electrical System Installation) perimeter Develop mass models for loads calculation, inertia models for aircraft simulation for different configurations and support special requestsWork closely with Architects and adapt, suggest weight saving ideas and access the robustness of weight and CG.Prepare and present Status weight evolution and Outlook weight evolution to the Chief engineering team.Validate the Supplier reports provided by Risk Sharing Partners (RSP) and communicate the findings.Help the Quality team on future Technical Development CapabilityAssessment/Conformity Audit (TDCA) for any supplier.Drive the designers, risk sharing partners of Airbus and vendors for the design with respect to weight targets.Prepare the estimation for Prototype and section weighing and validate if necessary.Calculate weight and CG impact for Customer modifications, Service bulletins, Weight repercussions & Technical repercussionsAlert Weight and Balance (W&B) Specialist on any important discrepancy between Estimated, Calculated, and Weighed values and verify that corrections are applied.Above all to drive innovation and bring new technology adaptation to aircraft design. Tools: Catia V5, PDM systems, Programming skills (PYTHON or MATLAB preferable) Soft skills:Agile and reliable, interested in working in a transnational empowered teamAbility to communicate effectively and efficiently Flexibility & adaptabilityAbility to challenge the status quoAbility to accept responsibility of taskCapacity to innovate & make proposal for improvements",
