		details:
			"Required Education: ● B.Tech. / M.Tech. in Aerospace, Mechanical, Electrical, Electronics, Instrumentation and Control As an Associate Engineer, you'll contribute to pioneering research, technology development, and complex problem-solving across various aerospace domains. You'll play a crucial part in exploring new concepts, developing innovative solutions, and applying advanced engineering principles to both legacy and next-generation aerospace systems.The various activities to be performed are: Contribute to the design, development, and optimization of cutting-edge aerospace components and systems.Perform complex engineering analysis, solve challenging technical problems, and propose innovative solutions.Utilize and apply advanced engineering tools and methodologies for design, analysis, and validation.Participate in technology maturation projects, from concept generation through feasibility studies and prototyping.Collaborate effectively with interdisciplinary engineering teams, including R&D, design, manufacturing, and test.Simulation Development Environment applications development based on AGILE methodologyPrepare and present technical reports, documentation, and recommendations to internal and external stakeholders.Stay abreast of industry trends, scientific advancements, and new engineering techniques.Conduct research and analysis on emerging technologies and advanced concepts relevant to aerospace systems.Required skills and expertise: - Basic aerospace domain knowledge - Experience in simulation and modeling of behavioral and/or physical systems (e.g. using Matlab, Simulink)- Experience with programming in C, C++, Matlab, java, C #, Python.- Strong problem solving and logical thinking ability - Strong interpersonal and communication skills - Flexibility and adaptability - Ability to work well in a team environmentJob Disclaimer & NotificationsWe bring to the notice of all concerned that Airbus Group India Pvt. Ltd (hereinafter referred to as \"AIG\") follows a fair and merit-based employee selection and recruitment practice.Airbus Group India does not:● Send job offers from free email services including but not limited to Gmail, Rediffmail, Yahoomail, Hotmail and others● Authorize anyone to either collect money or arrive at any monetary arrangement in return fora job at AIG● Charge / accept any form of consideration or security deposit from job seekers and applicantsduring any stage of the selection and/ or recruitment process● Request for your credit card number or bank account numberIt has come to our attention that fake job offers under the aegis of Airbus India or Airbus Group India Pvt. Ltd. have been circulated by unauthorized personnel. On receipt of an interview call for any job at AIG, the candidate may take some measures such as visiting the official website or career site of Airbus to get the contact details to enquire with the Human Resources department of Airbus India regarding such jobs and/or the interview details and any other relevant informationFor further information on Airbus India Careers, please click here. Please check www.airbus.com to get the contact details and enquire with the company to confirm if any information that you have received is genuine; do not respond to any fraudulent communication. AIG will not be responsible to anyone acting on an employment offer not directly made by Airbus Group India Pvt Ltd. anyone making an employment offer in return for money or other type of gain is not authorized by AIG and is not offering an approved job. AIG reserves the right to take legal action, including criminal action, against such individuals/entities**Airbus is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and is committed to create an inclusive and diverse work environment. AGI selects job applicants (internal and external) on the basis of suitability for the job, and irrespective of gender, marital status, age, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, nationality, religion, ethnicity or differently abled/ (dis)ability. )",
