		details:
			"EDUCATION: B.Tech/B.E/M.Tech/M.E in Mechanical/Aerospace/Industrial EngineeringThe job requires defining, developing and deploying industrial systems in the frame of digital manufacturing and Industry 4.0. You will collaborate with industrial engineers for creating, delivering and standardizing discrete event simulation models of existing and future manufacturing Lines/Plants and FALs to balance production rate across processes, understand material flow, determine buffer requirements and maximize factory throughputYou will be responsible for creating 3D Digital Mock-Ups of plants and prepare related methodology documentation and best practices to assist the Industrial teams from conceptual design through the finished industrial system. Additionally, assist in defining, developing and deploying these Industrial systems and digital twin capabilities You will secure the consideration of industrial aspects in the Aircraft definition, manage the design of the Industrial System in synchronization with the Aircraft design, increasing maturity throughout early development. It is applicable to all new Projects and Programs, including derivatives and major modifications of an existing Product/Program.You will be creating Industrial MBSE and related methodology documentation and best practices to assist the Industrial teams from conceptual design through the finished industrial system. You will work independently on the digital manufacturing tools and techniques on 3DExperience, for activities such as: Producing Routing , As-Prepared BoM, ISOI & Updating Work Order, Build Process and M-BOM definition. Preparing Work Instructions.You will be programming robotic systems and troubleshooting. Support Virtual commissioning activity across different Airbus Plant. Documenting robotic application development or changes.",
		info: "WORLD OF AIRBUSAirbus has always been at the forefront of innovating new technologies, with apioneering spirit that has redefined the aerospace industry. Our products bring peoplecloser together, helping them unite and progress. We strive to continually push theboundaries on what is possible to safeguard our world for future generations.Airbus shares a long-standing relationship of collaboration and symbiotic growth withIndia. For more than 50 years, technology and know-how from the company havecatalyzed the growth of India’s civil aviation sector and supported the modernisation ofits armed forces. \"Make in India\" is at the heart of Airbus strategy in India with thecompany constantly increasing the country's contribution to its global product portfolio.Airbus' local footprint in sourcing, engineering, innovation, maintenance and trainingservices is a testament to our commitment to developing the local ecosystem.MEDICAL INSURANCEThe employee and up to a maximum of five dependent family members (Employee +Spouse/same gender partner + 2 *Children below 26 years + 2 Parents/In Laws) arecovered for expenses towards hospitalization (including domiciliary) of more than 24 hoursunder a family floater Mediclaim Insurance Policy. Medical Insurance base policy is 10Lakhs & Employee voluntary top up is 10 Lakhs. Total up to 20 lakhs.BENEFITSACCIDENT INSURANCE POLICYAll employees of Airbus India are covered under a Group Personal Accident Policy, in caseof any unfortunate event of injuries or death due to an accident. The Personal Accidentcoverage would be twice of CTC (Minimum INR 25 Lakhs).All employees of Airbus are covered under a Group life term insurance policy. This policyalso provides critical illness cover to employees and hence in case of specific illnesses asdefined in policy, an employee can avail the money from insurance company for treatment.Employees are entitled to an amount up-to twice CTC / min 25 Lakhs and criticalillness cover for additional 10 LakhsHEALTHCARE & EMPLOYEE WELLNESSAirbus provides Health care and Employee wellness program for each employee and theirfamily members.Healthcare online portal, for all our employees and their dependants.Annual Master Health check-up for an employee and their spouse/same genderpartner.Doctor’s visit at officeDietician’s visit at officeLIFE INSURANCE POLICYINSURANCE & EMPLOYEE WELLNESSLEAVES & HOLIDAYSWORK-LIFE BALANCE SUPPORTType of Leave Days AllottedEarned Leaves 20 Working days per annumSick/Casual Leave 12 Working days per annumMaternity Leave 26 Weeks (Also applicable for adoption)Paternity Leave 25 Calendar days (Also applicable for adoption)Compassionate LeaveMarriage: 5 days for own wedding; 1 day for siblings’ weddingBereavement:5 days - death of a parent/spouse/same gender partner10 days - death of a child2 days - death of a sibling/parent-in-law/grandparentSeniority(Completion of service)3 years - 1 day of leave5 years - 2 days of leave10 years - 3 days of leaveYear End Closing 6 Working days per annumNational & Festival Holidays 10 Working days per annumPlease Note: For employees joining during the calendar year, the leave is calculated on a pro-rata basis for the first year according to thedate of joining & calculated on the number of days of service up to December 31. The leaves earned during each year of service will becredited to the employee leave account only on 1st January of the subsequent year. Each new employee will receive a credit of earnedleave on pro-rata basis upon completion of their probation period as an exception.We follow a hybrid mode of working with minimum 60% working days being in office.Depending on your team and business requirements, WFH days would be decided.",
