			"1. \nJob Description – Manager\n(Chemical/Process)\n\nReliance New Energy Limited\n\nReliance is building the world's most comprehensive, integrated, and\nfuture-ready New Energy ecosystem to drive India's journey towards energy\nindependence and global sustainability leadership. As part of our strategic\ncommitment, Reliance has pledged to achieve Net-Zero Carbon status by 2035 —\none of the most ambitious climate goals globally.\n\nWe aim to enable India’s shift from an energy-importing nation to a global\nclean-energy powerhouse and empower MSMEs, startups, academia and industry\npartners to participate in the green-tech ecosystem. Our New Energy Giga\nComplex spans Navi Mumbai, Jamnagar, Dahej, Kutch and Bengaluru with full-stack\nengineering, commissioning, R&D, and operations capability.\n\nWork Locations (Full-time office): Navi Mumbai, Jamnagar, Dahej, Kutch,\nBengaluru and PAN-India project sites.\n\nJob Role\n\nManager – Team\nMember (Chemical/Process) Engineering\nProject Execution | Technology Deployment | New Energy Manufacturing\n\nRole Summary\n\nContribute to\nengineering, commissioning, scale‑up, and optimization of cutting‑edge New\nEnergy facilities including Solar PV, Hydrogen systems, Electrolysers, Energy\nStorage, Power Electronics, and Advanced Materials. Work in multi‑disciplinary\nenvironments supporting commissioning, operations, safety, quality, and\ntechnology deployment.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n• Process\ndesign, simulation (Aspen/HYSYS), PFDs, P&IDs, mass‑energy balances\n\n• Electrolyser,\nhydrogen, chemical, and polymer process studies\n\n• Commissioning\nsupport, HAZOP, safety and energy efficiency\n\n• Vendor\nevaluation, FAT/SAT, SOP creation\n\nSkills & Knowledge\n\n• Reaction\nengineering, thermodynamics, battery chemical knowledge\n\n• Exposure to\nhydrogen/fuel cell systems preferred\n\n• Strong data\ninterpretation and plant engineering skills\n\nQualifications\n\nM.Tech\nin relevant domain\n• Minimum CGPA: 8.0 (no backlogs)\n• 10th, 12th & UG: ≥ 60%",
