			"Resume filtering | Aptitude test (00:50) | Case study (01:30) | Personal interview (01:00)",
		details:
			"Organisation\n& Team Description\n\nShell Lubricants Supply Chain (LSC) EMEA\norganisation covers more than 115 countries across Europe, Middle East and\nAfrica. We provide ~1 Billion liters of lubricant per year to customers ranging\nfrom the world’s largest car manufacturers to small independent workshops,\nnational utility companies to wind farms across the B2C and B2B customer\ngroups. \n\n \n\nThe Supply Chain Optimisation &\nDevelopment team, of which the Digital & Automation team is a part of, is\naccountable for all capital expenditure (~$80M per year) across EMEA. Within LSC,\nthis team invests in the future of our assets, which consists of a network of 9\nlubricants and grease manufacturing locations, to become modern, flexible, and\nadaptable to future customer needs. \n\n \n\nThe Automation Analyst is a member\nof the Digital & Automation team. The team is accountable for identifying,\ndefining and implementing structural end to end digital and automation\nopportunities that create value for Shell. Driven by a dynamic landscape, automation,\nrobotics, and data play pivotal roles for LSC EMEA.\n\nThe role reports into the Digital &\nAutomation Manager.\n\nRole Description\n\nAre you a data science enthusiast\nwith a knack for supply chain optimisation, statistical analysis, and artificial\nintelligence? If so, keep reading! \n\nAs an Automation Analyst, you’ll be analysing and optimising our supply chain\nprocesses within LSC EMEA. You will be provided the opportunity to make a\nsignificant impact on our operations. This role involves working with data,\nmodeling material flows, and optimization towards the most fit-for-purpose\nsolutions. You’ll be using simulation software to identify the most optimal capital\nexpenditure (CAPEX) investments, which will help to improve our supply chain\ncompetitiveness. For example, we’re significantly investing in automated mobile\nrobots (AMR) across our sites. Typical questions the team addresses are; \n\n· \nWhat are the\nbest possible routes for the AMRs to navigate around our sites?\n\nand \n\n· \nHow many AMRs do\nwe need to avoid bottlenecks or risk congestion? And what should be the speed\nof our warehouses to match AMR capacity?\n\n \n\nBy applying your modeling expertise you\nwill be supporting the team to get the right answers.\n\n \n\nBut there’s more! Over the years a\nlot of effort has gone into consistently collecting data-points across our\nsupply chain, all integrated into one data platform. Though there’s more to do we\n see immense opportunities that are waiting\nto be explored. As an Automation Analyst you will be looking at opportunities\nto streamline and automate operations and processes. To do so you will be developing\nand deploying models in Python or Spark, depending on the size of the data. You’d\nbe pivotal in bringing data closer to our decision-makers, enabling them to\nmake informed decisions quickly. For example, by developing conversational AI\ninterfaces that allow to query the data in natural language, making insights\neasily accessible and understandable for anyone.\n\n \n\nAll in all, as an Automation\nAnalyst, you’ll be building and deploying your own models, as well as applying\nyour modelling expertise to further advance our automation efforts across\nvarious parts of our supply chain! \n\n You will be expected To\n\nAnalyse data:\n\n· \nConduct in-depth analyses of\nexisting processes to identify potential areas for automation\n\n· \nRun simulations to help design the\nideal automation lay-out of our sites\n\n· \nModel & simulate to identify the\noptimal CAPEX investments in LSC EMEA\n\n· \nRecommend the best automation investment\nbased on cost-benefit analysis\n\nDevelop and deploy models:\n\n· \nDevelop and deploy models using\nprogramming languages such as Python or Spark \n\n· \nDeploy models into production\nenvironments and monitor their performance\n\n \n\nCollaborate with cross-functional\nteams:\n\n· \nEngage with various teams to\nidentify automation opportunities\n\n· \nFacilitate meetings with teams to\ndiscuss progress and address challenges\n\n \n\nRequirements\n\nExcellent analytical & problem-solving skills\n\n Background in Applied Mathematics/Physics,\n Econometrics, Data Science and Artificial Intelligence Technology,\n Electrical/Mechanical Engineering, Robotics, Systems & Control,\n Transport, Infrastructure and Logistics \n \n Proven experience in supply chain analysis and modelling\n (preferred) \n Proficiency in data modeling and simulation tools\n \n Proficiency in programming languages such as\n Python or Spark\n\nOpportunity & project delivery in a supply chain environment\n\n Ability to analyse and translate complex\n opportunities into clear value propositions\n Ability to recognize links between opportunities/projects\n with the skill to develop overviews \n High personal drive and delivery focus; result\n oriented\n\n \n\nStrong stakeholder management skills\n\n Interpersonal and influencing skills\n Strong communication skills, with the ability to\n convey complex concepts to non-technical stakeholders \n Open minded, challenging others and own\n assumptions and output.\n\n \n\nAnd most importantly, enthusiasm for\ninnovation and technology adoption in manufacturing processes! If you do not\npossess all skills listed above don’t be put off, we invite you to explain us\nhow you plan to leverage your skills to achieve our goals. \n\nDesirable Skills to possess\nor develop\n\nCommercial\nAcumen\n\n· Commercial mindset to improve efficiency and competitiveness\n\n· External focus, innovation, agility and speed\n\nMindset & Behaviors \n\n Foster a culture of curiosity to inspire others to think outside\n the box\n Work independently and as part of a team in a fast-past environment",
		info: "",
		reqs: "",
