			"Associate Product Manager\n\nAt Kelp we are welcoming applications from all\nthose who are enthusiastic about their skillset and are keen to make a huge\nimpact\n\nWe are going to trust you with\n\n· Collaborating with cross-functional teams across\ngeographies for requirement gathering, planning, and project implementation.\n\n· Translating business needs into detailed user\nstories and functional specifications for developers and QA teams.\n\n· Leading User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for new\nfeatures and ensuring successful deployment.\n\n· Defining and monitoring KPIs related to product\nusage, customer behavior, and system performance.\n\n· Gathering, analyzing, and interpreting usage data\nto derive insights that improve user experience.\n\n· Supporting the automation of internal processes for\ndata collection and performance tracking.\n\n· Acting as the communication hub between business\nstakeholders and technical teams to ensure alignment and timely execution.\n\nOur ideal candidate\nwill be someone with\n\n· Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with\nthe ability to break down complex business processes.\n\n· Hands-on experience working in Agile environments\nand familiarity with agile tools.\n\n· The ability to write clear, concise functional\nrequirements and communicate effectively across technical and non-technical\nteams.\n\n· Excellent verbal and written communication skills,\nwith a knack for presentations and stakeholder alignment.\n\n· A highly organized, detail-oriented mindset with a\nstrong sense of ownership and accountability.\n\n Bonus Points, if you\n\n Have\n experience working with international clients or teams.\n Are\n proficient in data analysis tools like Excel, R, or Python.\n Have\n experience with data visualization platforms such as Power BI or Tableau.Have previously contributed to improving user\nexperience based on data and feedback.",
