		details:
			"Purpose of Role We are seeking passionate AI Trainee Engineers (Frontend / Backend) eager to dive deep into AI-driven \nsolution and product development. This role goes far beyond traditional coding — it’s a rare opportunity to \nwork hands-on with real-world Gen AI / Agentic AI systems, exploring advanced LLMs, NLP pipelines, and \nRAG architectures for solving complex healthcare analytics problems. You will work with senior AI engineers \nand researchers to develop real-world NLP systems for enterprise use cases tailored to the Pharmaceutical \nIndustry. Responsibilities • Experience in using different open-source libraries Pandas, Tensorflow, PyTorch. Research and \nexperiment with cutting-edge GenAI and Agentic AI models for real-world use cases • Collaborate in building scalable AI-based applications — from intuitive frontends to efficient \nbackends • Work on data extraction, NER, text summarization, and semantic search problems using advanced \nNLP tools • Integrate LLMs (OpenAI, Gemini, Cohere, DeepSeek, etc.) into custom applications for Chatbots, \nQuestion Answering, and Document Understanding • Apply prompt engineering, embedding techniques, and RAG strategies for building intelligent AI \nagents • Clean and structure unstructured text data from varied sources like PDFs, PPTs, and web pages using \ntools like PyMuPDF, PDFMiner, Tesseract, BeautifulSoup, Selenium, etc • Contribute to the AI infrastructure stack involving vector databases (Pinecone, FAISS, ChromaDB), \ntransformer models (BERT, T5, RoBERTa), and backend APIs Required Skills & Technologies • Strong fundamentals in Python and libraries like: \nPandas, Tensorflow, PyTorch, Transformers, Keras, PDFPlumber, PyPDF2, Selenium, BeautifulSoup, \nPython-pptx, Tesseract, etc • Experience/knowledge of: \no NER, Text Cleaning, Summarization, QA, Topic Modeling \no Transformers & Fine-tuning LLMs \no RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) \no Prompt Engineering for LLMs \no Vector stores: Pinecone, FAISS, ChromaDB • Understanding of frontend/backend development and willingness to work in full-stack setupsQualifications Required • Degree: BE/BTech/MTech/MCA in Computer Science, Data Science, or related fields. • Freshers (0–3 years) from CDAC (DAI, DBDA, DAC) or equivalent AI/ML-focused certifications \nencouraged to apply • Strong analytical mindset and willingness to work on real AI problems in the healthcare domain • Bonus: Exposure to Pharma/Life Sciences/Clinical or RWE data",
