			"Electrical Engineer – Electrification & Power Conversion Systems (PhD)Position OverviewWe at Caterpillar are seeking Electrical Engineers with a PhD to lead advanced research and development in electrification and power conversion systems. This role focuses on system-level engineering, control strategy development, and component design. You will work on cutting-edge technologies—including batteries, fuel cells, and Power conversion system—and help integrate them into Caterpillar’s electrified solutions.You will contribute to pioneering solutions for battery energy storage, renewable integration, and power electronics, while documenting research findings, filing patents, and mentoring junior engineers.Key ResponsibilitiesSystem-Level Engineering & Integration•Model and simulate power conversion systems to meet system requirements and application functionalities.•Conduct power system studies (dynamic and steady-state) using tools like PSS®E, PSCAD, and PowerFactory.•Perform grid connection studies to evaluate the performance of renewables, battery energy storage systems (BESS), and their controls.•Support electrical system integration, ensuring seamless interaction between components, subsystems, and control architecture.•Implement Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL) and Product-in-the-Loop (PIL) simulations to validate system performance and control strategies.Control Strategy & Software Modeling•Define controller requirements, identify subsystems, and develop control strategies for inverters, converters, and chargers.•Develop user-defined dynamic models in tools such as PSS®E and PowerFactory.•Work with MATLAB/Simulink for control system modeling and simulation.Caterpillar: Confidential GreenComponent & Motor Design•Design and evaluate electrical components including wiring harnesses, connectors, and protection systems.•Contribute to motor design and validation, including selection, control strategy development, and performance verification.Testing, Validation & Evaluation•Execute component testing and validation to ensure reliability, safety, and compliance with performance standards.•Evaluate new technologies, products, and processes for performance and feasibility.Collaboration & Communication•Communicate technical findings with cross-functional teams, suppliers, and stakeholders.•Contribute to the design and maintenance of innovative products and systems.•Publish research findings in peer-reviewed journals and present at international conferences.•Mentor junior engineers and interns on advanced modeling and design methodologies.Required Qualifications•PhD in Electrical Engineering, Power Systems, or related field with strong research background in electrification technologies.•Proven track record of publications, patents, or significant contributions in power electronics, energy storage, or renewable integration.•Expertise in MATLAB/Simulink, dynamic modeling, and multiphysics simulation.•Hands-on experience with PSS®E, PSCAD, PowerFactory, and HIL/PIL setups.•Strong analytical, scientific writing, and communication skills.Preferred Qualifications•Experience in industry-academia collaboration, sponsored research projects, or grant writing.•Familiarity with emerging technologies in electrification and power conversion.•Programming skills (Python, MATLAB) for automation and data processing.Mechanical Design Engineer – Electrification and Energy SolutionsPosition OverviewWe at Caterpillar are seeking highly capable and detail-oriented Mechanical Design Engineers (PhD Only) with a strong foundation in structural design, mechanical simulation, and product development. The successful candidates will be responsible for designing and analysing mechanical components and assemblies for advanced energy systems, including battery packs, hydrogen fuel cells, and power conversion equipment such as EV chargers and inverters.Candidates must demonstrate a solid academic background, with project or thesis work that includes measurable outcomes, such as validated simulation results, prototype development, or published findings. This role requires proficiency in CAD modeling, FEA-based simulation tools, and the ability to deliver robust, manufacturable mechanical designs.Key Responsibilities•Design and develop mechanical components and assemblies for energy systems, ensuring structural integrity, manufacturability, and compliance with performance requirements.•Perform structural analysis using simulation tools to evaluate stress, strain, deformation, fatigue, and vibration characteristics.•Create and manage 3D CAD models, assemblies, and detailed engineering drawings using industry-standard software.•Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless integration of mechanical designs with electrical and thermal subsystems.•Conduct design reviews, tolerance stack-up analysis, and manufacturability assessments.•Drive prototype builds and mechanical testing; perform root-cause/failure analysis and corrective actions.•Document design processes, analysis results, and engineering decisions in a clear and structured format.Caterpillar: Confidential GreenRequired Qualifications•PhD in Mechanical Engineering, Aerospace Engineering, Materials Science, or a related field.•Strong record of research publications, patents, or significant contributions to mechanical design innovation.•Demonstrated experience in academic projects or thesis work with quantifiable results, such as validated simulations, experimental data, or prototype performance.•Proficiency in CAD software (e.g., SolidWorks, CATIA, Siemens NX, Creo).•Hands-on experience with FEA tools (e.g., ANSYS Mechanical, Abaqus, COMSOL).•Background in materials selection, joining methods, and manufacturing processes.•Understanding of DFM/DFA, GD&T, and engineering standards.•Excellent analytical reasoning, scientific writing, and communication skills.Preferred Qualifications•Exposure to mechanical design in battery systems, fuel cell housings, power electronics packaging, or thermal management systems.•Experience with Multiphysics simulation, thermal-structural coupling, or dynamic analysis.•Familiarity with design optimization techniques and material selection strategies.•Programming/scripting skills (e.g., Python, MATLAB) for automation and data processing.•Knowledge of prototype development, mechanical testing methodologies, and failure analysis.•Industry-academia collaboration experience and mentoring graduate students.",
