			"Product Designer (Campus Hire)About People InteractiveWe’re an Indian consumer internet company behind some of the most trusted matchmaking and relationship platforms:Shaadi.com – the world’s leading matchmaking platform helping over 8 million people find loveSangam.com – focused on community-based matchmakingVIPShaadi.com – a premium matchmaking experience for HNIsAstroShaadi.com – astrology-led matchmaking powered by insightsOur products touch millions of lives every month. We design with empathy, powered by data and technology, to help people build meaningful connections.Role OverviewAs a Product Designer (Growth), you’ll design experiences that attract, activate, and retain users across our platforms. You’ll learn how design drives measurable growth—through better onboarding, smoother conversions, engaging reactivations, and smarter monetization flows.You’ll work closely with Product Managers, Engineers, and Data Analysts to design and test ideas that make our products grow faster and our users happier.What You’ll DoDesign and improve key growth touchpoints such as signup, onboarding, profile completion, and subscription flows.Collaborate on A/B tests and experiments to optimize conversion and retention.Use user insights and analytics to design for measurable impact.Create scalable design assets, frameworks, and flows that enable quick experimentation.Learn to evaluate design success using growth metrics like conversion rate, retention, and LTV.What We’re Looking ForFinal-year students or recent graduates in Design, HCI, Interaction Design, or related fields.Strong foundation in UX, interaction, and visual design.Proficiency in Figma and prototyping tools.Willingness to learn and adapt new tools like AI & critical thinkingCuriosity about how design can influence growth and business outcomes.Portfolio or academic projects that demonstrate clear design thinking and user understanding.Bonus PointsInternship or project experience in consumer or subscription-based products.Interest in conversion optimization, engagement design, or personalization.Understanding of how A/B testing and experimentation work.Why Join UsWork on products that impact millions of users globally.Learn directly from senior designers and growth leaders.Gain exposure to real growth metrics and data-driven design decisions.Be part of a design culture that values creativity, experimentation, and measurable impact.",
