			"Team TE2A MMC Tech\n\n \n\nMMC is seeking candidates for the following position based in\nthe Noida office:\n\n \n\nSenior Software ENGINEER\n\n \n\nWhat can you expect?\n\nJoin\nour cutting-edge Innovation team expansion into India, where you'll work as a\npart of squads building innovative AI applications using the latest tools and\ntechnologies.\n\n· \nThe\nopportunity to be an early contributor to a fast-evolving area with significant\nexecutive focus.\n\n· \nThe\nchance to geek out on initiatives such as Hackathons and be part of the broader\nMMC Tech ecosystem.\n\n· \nTo be\npart of our strategic tech hub that delivers industry-leading digital solutions\nfor clients and colleagues. \n\n· \nBe part of a team driven by a\nstart-up culture but backed by a giant To\nbe part of our strategic tech hub that delivers industry-leading digital\nsolutions for clients and colleagues. \n\n \n\nWhat is in it for you?\n\n Standard\n MMC Salary Package\n Standard\n MMC Colleague Benefits\n Huge\n landscape to learn & work on new technologies and apply your skills\n\nWe will count on you to:\n\n· Collaborate\nwith counterparts in the Dublin, Cluj and Noida innovation centres.\n• Develop prototypes in such a way they can be productionised.\n\n· Be a\ncollaborative developer comfortable in an Agile environment.\n\n· Be a\nlifelong learner with an appetite for improving your craft, introducing change,\nand collaborating with like-minded colleagues.\n\n· Identify\nand implement improvement opportunities.\n\n· Create\nand maintain best practice development frameworks and establish standards, e.g.\nPrompt Engineering.\n\n· Develop\npractices and guidelines to improve consistency and reuse of solutions.\n\n· Implement\nLLM integrations and RAG pipelines that consider latency, cost, and safety.\n\n· Contribute\nto data preprocessing, labeling/annotation workflows and evaluation of model\noutputs.\n\n· \nHelp\ninstrument model monitoring and testing (performance, drift, and safety\nchecks).\n\nWhat you’ll get to do:\n\n• \nDesign and architect innovative, modern digital experiences.\n\n• \nBuild, support and mentor effective teams.\n\n• \nWrite code alongside your development team.\n\n• \nWork with state-of-the-art technologies to solve genuine, real-world\nproblems.\n\n• \nBuild strong relationships with software engineering team.\n\n• \nEnjoy working in a diverse, dynamic, collaborative, transparent,\nenvironment where everyone's ideas and opinions are equally valued.\n\nWhat you need to have: \n\n· Experience\nwith a modern frontend framework — ideally React (Vue, Angular are good too).\n\n· Practical\nexperience of NestJS / NodeJS or similar stack.\n\n· Experience\nwith or knowledge of Python (including libraries for data/AI workflows).\n\n· A\ncreative, problem-solving approach to your work.\n\n· Exposure\nto core machine learning concepts (basic supervised/unsupervised learning,\nprobability/statistics, linear algebra).\n\n· Familiarity\nwith at least one deep learning framework (e.g., PyTorch or TensorFlow) and\ncommon ML libraries (e.g., scikit-learn).\n\n· Awareness\nof transformer models and the Hugging Face ecosystem (transformers library,\ntokenizers).\n\n· Basic\nunderstanding of embeddings and vector search concepts.\n\n· Comfortable\nworking with RESTful APIs\n\n Willingness to\n learn MLOps fundamentals (model packaging, containerization, and\n deployment on cloud/Kubernetes).\n\n \n\nWhat makes you stand out?\n\n• \nStrong knowledge of RESTful APIs.\n\n• \nPractical experience of Kubernetes and/or\nMongoDB.\n\n• \nKnowledge on LLMs.\n\n• \nKnowledge on prompt engineering techniques.\n\n• \nKnowledge on RAG.\n\n• \nFamiliarity with LangChain, LlamaIndex or\nsimilar orchestration/agent libraries for LLM applications.\n\n• \nExperience or familiarity with cloud model APIs\nand services (OpenAI, Azure OpenAI, AWS Sagemaker, GCP Vertex AI) and basic\nGPU/cloud concepts.\n\n• \nPersonal or academic projects demonstrating\nLLM/AI work (GitHub links, Kaggle, hackathon projects).\n\n• \nPersonal or academic projects using embeddings\nand vector databases.\n\n• \nParticipation in ML coursework, internships, or\ncompetitions.",
