		details:
			"Associate Product Manager Location: Pune, India (Onsite)Company: TruckX Technologies Pvt. LtdAbout TruckXTruckX Technologies Pvt Ltd. is a fast-growing technology company building modern tools for the trucking and logistics ecosystem in the US. We specialize in telematics, fleet management, dispatch automation, and AI-powered productivity platforms.While we run multiple product lines across ELDs, dashcams, fleet SaaS, and compliance management, this role is specifically focused on our next-generation AI platform Hey Bubba! for carriers - an intelligent AI assistant that helps commercial fleets find loads, negotiate, plan trips, automate paperwork, and run their business efficiently.Role OverviewWe’re looking for a highly motivated Associate Product Manager (APM) who is detail-oriented, analytical, and passionate about building intuitive AI products. You will work closely with engineering, design, data, and operations teams to drive execution, validate features, run product-level testing, and ensure high-quality releases.This is a hands-on role ideal for someone early in their PM career who wants to learn fast, take real ownership, and help shape a cutting-edge AI product used by thousands of truckers across the US.Key ResponsibilitiesWork closely with engineering to break down features, clarify requirements, resolve edge cases, and support technical tradeoff decisions throughout the development cycle.Own end-to-end product-level testing for mobile, web, backend, and AI flows—creating test cases, validating builds, identifying defects, and ensuring release quality.Drive AI-related feature development, ensuring model outputs, workflows, and interactions are accurate, consistent, and aligned with user needs.Collaborate with Engineering, design, data, and operations to deliver smooth user experiences, maintain cross-team alignment, and ensure readiness for releases.Document product requirements, workflows, and release notes clearly and maintain high-quality internal product communication.Conduct deep user, market, and workflow research to understand carrier and fleet problems, validate hypotheses, and translate findings into clear product decisions.Analyze data and metrics across product usage, funnels, and performance, using analytical tools (Mixpanel, GA, SQL basics, or similar) and automating recurring reports or dashboards where possible.What We’re Looking For0 - 1 years of experience in Product Management, QA, Business Analysis, or a related role.Strong understanding of product requirements, testing processes, and usability.Ability to break down complex workflows into simple, actionable steps.Excellent analytical skills and attention to detail.Strong communication and documentation skills in English.Ability to work in a fast-paced, iterative startup environment.Technical curiosity and willingness to dive deep into AI workflows, backend logic, and data-driven decision making.Nice-to-HaveExperience in AI, logistics, freight-tech, or SaaS platforms.Exposure to mobile app testing, voice interfaces, or workflow automation.Basic understanding of APIs, data flows, and system behaviors.Why Join UsWork on one of the most ambitious AI platforms in the US trucking industry.Solve real problems for carriers, fleet owners, and owner-operators.Be part of a team where your work has direct impact and ownership.Growth-focused environment with mentorship, autonomy, and rapid skill development.Competitive compensation and the opportunity to grow into a full Product Manager role.",
		info: "-",
		reqs: "",
		url: "https://campus.placements.iitb.ac.in/applicant/job/12738",
