			"Resume filtering | Technical test (90 minutes) | Technical interview (45 minutes) | Personal interview (45 minutes) | HR Interview",
		details:
			"About LOHUM LOHUM is India’s largest producer and processor of sustainable critical minerals, and one of the largest globally outside of China. Our business spans manufacturing, processing, and recycling, with an annual capacity exceeding 50,000 metric tonnes.We produce high-value materials such as Lithium, Cobalt, Nickel, Copper, Platinum Group Metals, and Rare Earths, as well as value-added products like catalysts, alloys, magnets, and cathode active materials. With aggressive expansion underway, LOHUM is building a reliable, resilient, and de-risked critical minerals supply chain to power India’s National Critical Minerals Mission and the global clean energy transition.Role Summary We are seeking a highly analytical and detail-oriented Policy & Strategy Associate to join our growing Strategy and Policy team. This role plays a key part in shaping LOHUM’s medium- and long-term strategic direction in a rapidly evolving landscape of geopolitics, technology, supply chains, and climate policy.The Associate will conduct macro-economic modelling and market analysis, track global and domestic policy developments, and assess their strategic implications for LOHUM. The role also involves supporting policy advocacy, building datasets, and developing thought-leadership and position papers that strengthen LOHUM’s voice across the critical minerals and clean-tech ecosystem.Key Responsibilities Economic Analysis & Forecasting: Macro-economic assessments, market modelling, and long-term demand/supply forecasts.Policy Tracking & Impact: Monitor domestic and global policy developments and evaluate implications for LOHUM.Strategy Development: Support strategic planning by analysing market, regulatory, and geopolitical shifts to identify risks and opportunities.Advocacy & Submissions: Prepare policy briefs, regulatory submissions, and presentations for government stakeholders.Research & Thought Leadership: Engage with industry and academia through research publications and datasetsQualifications & Skills Relevant Experience: 2–3 years of professional work in government, consulting firms, market research firms, or think-tanks. We are open to candidates of other backgrounds provided you can demonstrate relevant experience.Economic Modelling and Analysis Skills: Candidates will be tested comprehensively on these.Technical Proficiency: Proficient with Microsoft Office, especially Excel, PowerPoint, and Word. Proficiency in data analysis tools like Python or R would be looked at favourably.Attention to Detail: Demonstrated commitment to high-quality, accurate, and well-structured outputs.Communication: Strong written and verbal communication skills in English and Hindi. We will make you write A LOTEducation: Degree in Economics, Finance, Public Policy, or related fields; candidates with engineering/technical backgrounds and relevant experience are also encouraged to apply.Government Engagement: Experience building relationships and working with senior bureaucrats and political stakeholders would be considered a bonus.",
