			"Resume filtering | Case Study Assignment | Interview 1 | Interview 2 | Interview 3",
		details:
			"About Lohum\n\nLOHUM is India’s largest producer and\nprocessor of sustainable critical minerals—and among the biggest globally\noutside China. Powering the clean energy revolution, Lohum manufactures,\nprocesses, and recycles over 50,000 metric tonnes annually, producing essential\nmaterials like Lithium, Cobalt, Nickel, Copper, and Rare Earths, along with\nadvanced products such as catalysts, alloys, magnets, and cathode active\nmaterials. As India’s largest lithium-ion battery recycler with a 90% market\nshare, Lohum is building a secure and circular supply chain for critical\nminerals that fuels the energy transition.\n\nWith nine facilities across India and\ninternational operations in the UAE and Africa, Lohum combines large-scale\noperations with deep R&D. Its breakthrough NEETM™ (Extraction &\nTransformation Method) recovers over 95% of materials with 99.5%+ purity,\nsetting new standards for sustainable innovation. Backed by 100 researchers\nacross 11 specialized labs, Lohum invests heavily in developing next-generation\nmaterials, AI, and membrane technologies. Partnering with 200+ global leaders\nincluding Tata, Samsung, Panasonic, and Glencore, Lohum stands at the forefront\nof redefining the future of clean energy and circular critical minerals.\n\nAtoms, Bits, Coulombs (ABC) Program:\n\nHow do you leverage technology to make real,\ntangible things in a fast, inexpensive, and energy-efficient manner?\n\nThis is the defining question of our age.\n\nLOHUM seeks to cultivate a generation of\nleaders to tackle this very problem through the ABC Program. We are looking for\nsmart, young, and talented folks who can think of solutions from A, B, and Cs\ni.e. first principles.\n\nA year in the ABC Program:\n\nABC Fellows will undergo a rigorous 12-month\ntraining itinerary.\n\nThey will get exposure to multiple\n\nFunctions - Engineering, Production, R&D,\nOperations, Business,\n\nBusiness verticals - Recycling, Refining,\nEnergy Storage, Software\n\nThis will be achieved through a series of\n3-to-6-month time-bound projects.\n\nEach of these projects will be under the\nguidance of an experienced mentor\n\nAt the end of the 12 months, the ABC Fellows\nwill be assigned permanent roles based on their inclination and performance.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n1. Drive the assigned projects to logical\nconclusions within the given time frame.\n\n2. Analyze learnings from each of the projects\nand recommend next steps.\n\n3. Develop an understanding of how the company\nfunctions.\n\n4. Engage with cross-functional teams to drive\ninnovative solutions.\n\n5. Learn extensively from experts and\nproactively develop skills & knowledge-base.\n\nRequired Skills:\n\n1. Strong technical expertise in one or more\nareas of engineering and/or sciences.\n\n2. Thinking - logical, from first principles,\nrigorous but being open to new ideas.\n\n3. Being data-oriented.\n\n4. Ability to work independently.\n\n5. The ability to comprehend aspects both\nbelow and above your operational layer.\n\n6. Excellent spoken and written communication.\n\n7. Versatility for multi-disciplinary\ncooperation & cross-functional collaboration. \n\n Candidate Learning:\n\nExposure to and understanding of\n\n1. Global Critical Minerals Value Chain\n\n2. Chemical Processes and Scaling Challenges\n\n3. Energy Storage Industry\n\n4. Lithium-ion Battery Circular Economy\n\n5. International Business (and potential\nopportunities to travel and live across India and the world)",
