		details:
			"Role OverviewThe Senior Faculty will be responsible for delivering high-quality coaching for JEE aspirants in their respective subject(s)—Physics, Chemistry, or Mathematics. The role demands advanced subject expertise, innovative teaching methods, and the ability to inspire students to achieve their academic goals.Key ResponsibilitiesTeaching & Content DeliveryPlan and deliver engaging lessons aligned with the JEE syllabus.Simplify complex concepts using innovative teaching techniques and real-world examples.Foster a student-centric learning environment and adapt teaching methods based on student feedback.Content DevelopmentDesign and review study materials, practice problems, and test papers.Stay updated with JEE trends to ensure relevance in teaching materials.Mentoring StudentsProvide personalized guidance to students to address their academic strengths and weaknesses.Monitor student performance and share actionable feedback with students and parents.Examinations & AssessmentsConduct regular tests and evaluations to track progress.Analyze test performance data to refine teaching strategies.CollaborationWork closely with the Academic Head and fellow faculty members to enhance the learning experience.Participate in faculty meetings, training sessions, and brainstorming workshops.",
