			"Resume Shortlisting for Technical Test | Pre-Placement Talk (30 mins) | UX Online Technical Test (24 Hrs) | Group discussion (20 mins/group) | Technical interview (60 mins) | Manager Interview (30 Mins) | HR Interview (30 Mins)",
		details:
			"Job SummaryThe Engineering Development Group (EDG) at MathWorks is a leadership development program designed to nurture talent from diverse technical and design backgrounds. As a User Experience (UX) focused EDG team member, you will collaborate with the MathWorks UX organization to build your leadership, technical, and customer engagement skills through hands-on projects, mentoring, and coaching.You will gain deep exposure to MathWorks products and user workflows, contribute to cross-functional initiatives, and prepare for a full-time role as a UX Designer or UX Researcher, helping craft world-class experiences for engineers and scientists worldwide.Important: Before appearing for the interview, you must select your preferred UX function: either UX Design or UX Research. This ensures alignment with project focus and evaluation criteria.ResponsibilitiesDepending on your selected UX function (either UX Designer or UX Researcher), you will focus on the following specific responsibilities:UX DesignAs a UX-focused EDG team member, you’ll contribute to meaningful design and research projects while supporting customers technically. This blend of work builds your skills in usability, accessibility, and inclusive design, while fostering continuous learning and domain expertise in MATLAB and Simulink. You’ll collaborate across teams, communicate design decisions clearly, and stay current with emerging UX practices.Drive high-impact UX projects across development teams to strengthen technical and professional skills.Collaborate with stakeholders to understand requirements and design complete, user-centered experiences.Apply design principles through concepts, wireframes, prototypes, and polished UI, grounded in interaction, visual design, and information architecture.Promote best practices in usability, accessibility, and inclusive design across teams and workflows.Provide expert technical support for complex issues in MATLAB, Simulink, and the broader MathWorks product suite.Demonstrate leadership by mentoring others and contributing to process improvements and team growth. UX ResearchAs a UX-focused EDG team member, you’ll contribute to meaningful design and research projects while supporting customers technically. This blend of work builds your skills in usability, accessibility, and inclusive design, while fostering continuous learning and domain expertise in MATLAB and Simulink. You’ll collaborate across teams, communicate design decisions clearly, and stay current with emerging UX practices.Lead and contribute to high-impact UX research projects across development teams to strengthen technical and professional skills.Conduct foundational, generative, and evaluative research using diverse methods like interviews, usability testing, surveys, diary studies, and card sorting.Identify pain points and study workflows to inform strategy, validate solutions, and guide product direction through personas, journey maps, and UX metrics.Evangelize customer perspectives and promote research-driven decision-making across teams.Provide expert technical support for complex issues in MATLAB, Simulink, and the broader MathWorks product suite.Demonstrate leadership by mentoring others, initiating process improvements, and deepening domain expertise.Minimum QualificationsA bachelor's degree and 3 years of professional work experience (or a master's degree, or equivalent experience) is required.Additional QualificationsMaster’s or PhD degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Design, or a related field, with a specialization in Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) or similar disciplines.Experience with design or research tools, such as:Design: Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD, AxureResearch: UserZoom, OptimalWorkshop, Morae, MiroA portfolio or research case studies that showcase your projects and contributions (linked in your resume).Experience crafting or evaluating user experiences in technical/engineering domains.Familiarity with programming languages (e.g., MATLAB, R, Python, C++, Java, JavaScript).What You’ll GainHands-on experience shaping the future of MathWorks products used by engineers and scientists worldwide.A strong foundation in user-centered design and research practices.Technical depth in MATLAB, Simulink, and the MathWorks ecosystem.Mentorship and career development to transition into a full-time UX Designer or UX Researcher role.",
		info: "Overall compensation includes a one-time payment of joining bonus, relocation bonus and hybrid work equipment allowance and other benefits. All the above figures detailed are subjected to taxes as per India Income tax act.    Students need to review interview track information before registering for the process. They will not be allowed to alter or change the interview track once they complete the registration process.   To make a conscious choice for Job Location – students must carefully go through the focus areas for Bangalore and Hyderabad detailed in the job description.   Students should have access to a camera-enabled laptop and good internet connectivity for a smooth interviewing experience.   The complete process will be held virtually using Microsoft Teams platform, they must download the app before the recruiting process, the web application doesn’t work.",
