		details:
			"SEDEMAC\nMechatronics Limited\n\nLead Engineer,\nManufacturing Engineering\n\nAbout the Job:\n\nSEDEMAC is expanding its manufacturing engineering capabilities to\nsupport advanced mechatronic products such as gearboxes and electric motors. As\n“Engineer, Manufacturing Engineering”, you will join a team that is actively\nshaping and strengthening SEDEMAC’s manufacturing engineering practices.\n\nThis is an exciting opportunity for sharp and enthusiastic engineers\nwho want to learn how designs become manufacturable products at scale. You\ndon’t need prior production know-how—we will guide you. What matters most is\nyour curiosity, problem-solving ability, and willingness to build expertise in manufacturing\ndomain.\n\nMajor Responsibilities:\n\n· \nSupport new product\ndevelopment by helping prototypes transition smoothly into production-ready\nproducts.\n\n· \nLearn and contribute to\nDesign for Manufacturability (DFM) and Design for Assembly (DFA) reviews, while\nassisting in the preparation of process documents such as flow charts, work\ninstructions, and quality checklists.\n\n· \nCollaborate with suppliers\nand production teams during trial runs, tooling validations, and fixture\ndevelopment to ensure robust manufacturing processes.\n\n· \nAudit supplier processes\nand help define detailed production steps covering fabrication, inspection, and\nassembly.\n\n· \nParticipate in root cause\nanalysis (RCA) of production issues, support implementation of corrective\nactions, and contribute fresh ideas for improvement.\n\n· \nEngage in continuous\nimprovement initiatives focused on quality, cost, and efficiency, applying\nstructured methods like statistical analysis to monitor and optimize processes.\n\n· \nContribute to reliability\nengineering by analysing failure modes, recommending design/process\nimprovements, and ensuring products meet lifecycle and durability requirements.\n\n· \nWork with design and\nquality teams to perform reliability assessments and implement preventive\nmeasures for long-term product performance.\n\n· \nAssist in the development\nand improvement of manufacturing test setups, including end-of-line testers, to\nensure every product shipped meets performance and quality standards.\n\n· \nCapture and document\nlessons learned to strengthen SEDEMAC’s manufacturing know-how and develop\ninternal best practices.\n\nDesired Technical\nSkills:\n\n· Strong fundamentals in Physics, Mathematics, and\nMechanical/Electro-Mechanical concepts.\n\n· Exposure to common manufacturing processes such as\ncasting, machining, moulding, sheet metal, and assembly.\n\n· Ability to interpret engineering drawings;\nfamiliarity with GD&T is desirable.\n\n· Comfort with CAD tools (Creo or equivalent) and\nproficiency in Excel; exposure to Python scripting is an advantage.\n\n· Awareness of product development and quality\nframeworks (PPAP, APQP, PFMEA, SPC, MSA) through academics or projects is a\nplus.\n\n· Familiarity with quality and problem-solving tools\n(5 Whys, Fishbone, Pareto) and basic Lean/Six Sigma practices (Kaizen, 5S) is a\nplus.\n\nDesired\nSoft Skills:\n\n· Strong analytical ability to find root causes and\npropose practical solutions.\n\n· Clear, concise communication with design,\nproduction, and supplier teams.\n\n· Proactive and self-driven, eager to learn and\nimprove manufacturing practices.\n\n· Ability to balance quality, cost, and delivery\ntimelines in decision-making.\n\n· Professional work ethic with a sense of ownership\nand accountability.\n\nInformation on Selection Process:\n\n• \nThe\nselection process will include multi-phased tests plus interviews\n\n• \nThere\nwill be a focus on evaluation of the candidate’s understanding of technical,\nanalytical & logical skills\n\nEducation:\n\n• \nPhD in Mechanical,\nManufacturing Sciences, Production, Mechatronics only.\n\n \n\n \n\nExperience:\n\n \n\n· \nNA\n\nAbout SEDEMAC\n\nAt\nits core, SEDEMAC is the convergence of talented engineers committed to the\ndevelopment and large-scale deployment of innovative control technologies and\nproducts. As one of the fastest-growing Tier-1 suppliers in the automotive\nspace, we work with vehicle, motor, and engine manufacturers who are leaders in\ntheir own space to deliver fundamental control solutions with real-world\nimpact. Our engineer-led organization prides itself on creating technology\npropositions and taking them from the drawing board to high-volume production\nwith operational excellence. We foster a culture that values creativity,\nhonesty, and respect—where ideas are judged by their merit, not by hierarchy.\nWith a strong foundation and ambitious growth plans, SEDEMAC is uniquely positioned\nto shape the future of controls.\n\nJob Location: Pune",
		info: "1: We will be using Superset from this year. The applications will be opened on Superset and the eligible students should apply on the platform.2: The online aptitude and technical tests will be conducted on campus in our presence using Mettl platform. The arrangements should be made accordingly.3: The Technical and HR interview will be conducted on campus.INFRASTRUCTURE REQUIREMENTS:Online Test Platform: Mettl (Video proctored). It is expected that the tests should be conducted in the classroom / auditorium in our invigilation. The arrangements should be made accordingly. All students should be instructed to carry the hard copy of any govt. id proof for the tests. This is a requirement for registration on Mettl platform for the tests.",
