		details:
			"Job Description: Operations Research Scientist I : ORMAE is looking for Operations Research Scientist with good analytics background to deliver solutions for complex problems of our clients. OR Scientist I Should have a scientific mindset and interest in Operation Research algorithms like routing optimization, mathematical modeling, meta-heuristics, heuristics, forecasting, simulation model, inventory optimization. (S)he should have supply chain management background along with advanced analytics experience. (S)He should have strong interest and ability to solve mathematical modelling including LP tools like Cplex, Gurobi, AIIMS, GAMS, AMPL. Programming experience in Python/Java/C#/ C++/R of the optimization algorithm is preferred including background in data structures, graph theory, object oriented programming. Exposure to Supply Chain Guru, Anylogic is preferred Education: B.E./B.Tech./M.S./M.E./M.Tech/Dual/MSc/Ph.D. in Operations Research, Statistics, Computer Science (with operations research experience), Industrial Engineering, Decision Science, Mechanical Engineering, Statistics, Mathematics, Business Analytics, Information Technology or any other Quantitative Specialization. Agreement: : One has to stay committed and work for a minimum of 3 years from the Date of Joining with the company Penalty Clause: If any new joiner leaves before completing 3 years from his/her date of joining with us, they will be required to pay Rs 6 Lakhs to ORMAE. This policy is in place because we invest significantly in their training and provide them the opportunity to work on international projects with a Fortune 500 customer, which will enhance their skills and position them as top OR Scientists in the industry Full Time Employee Salary, Perks & Benefits: Salary for B.E./B.Tech./M.S./M.E./M.Tech/Dual/BSc/MSc/Ph.D and other Quantitative Specialisation : 12 LPA (Fixed) + 1 LPA (Variable Performance Pay) Training: You will have to undergo an initial 3-month training period, during which you will receive a stipend of ₹30,000 per month. On successful completion of the training, you will be promoted to the role of OR Scientist 1 with a CTC of ₹13 LPA (₹12 LPA fixed + ₹1 LPA performance-based variable pay). Compensation: For 1st Year - Annual CTC will be 12 lacs per annum fixed CTC, plus 1 lac per annum that will be performance based bonus. For subsequent years there will be an increment based on performance. Work with young and energetic team and exposure to work with direct client including fortune 500 worldwide companies. Learning Benefits: A lifetime opportunity to sum up in 3 years of your learning and knowledge with Machine Learning, Operations Research and Advanced Analytics. Insurance Benefits – Group Medical Insurance- 5 / 10 Lacs, Wellness Program - Employee Assistance Program, Employee Training Programme, Parental Support - Maternity & Paternity Benefit Program Mobility Benefits - Travel & Reimbursement Policy Retirement Benefits - Employee PF Contribution, Flexible PF Contribution, Leave Encashment. What is in it for you: Meritocracy based Career Progression Global Exposure Live wire Environment Great Technical cross training & mentorship Happening start up - in the garden city of Bengaluru Come join us, let do something great!!",
		info: "Penalty Clause: If any new joiner leaves before completing 3 years from his/her date of joining with us, they will be required to pay Rs 6 Lakhs to ORMAE. This policy is in place because we invest significantly in their training and provide them the opportunity to work on international projects with a Fortune 500 customer, which will enhance their skills and position them as top OR Scientists in the industry. Full Time Employee Salary, Perks & Benefits: Salary for B.E./B.Tech./M.S./M.E./M.Tech/Dual/BSc/MSc/Ph.D and other Quantitative Specialisation : 12 LPA (Fixed) + 1 LPA (Variable Performance Pay) Training: You will have to undergo an initial 3-month training period, during which you will receive a stipend of ₹30,000 per month. On successful completion of the training, you will be promoted to the role of OR Scientist 1 with a CTC of ₹13 LPA (₹12 LPA fixed + ₹1 LPA performance-based variable pay). Compensation: For 1st Year - Annual CTC will be 12 lacs per annum fixed CTC, plus 1 lac per annum that will be performance based bonus. For subsequent years there will be an increment based on performance. Work with young and energetic team and exposure to work with direct client including fortune 500 worldwide companies.",
		reqs: "Minimum CGPA: 6Penalty Clause: If any new joiner leaves before completing 3 years from his/her date of joining with us, they will be required to pay Rs 6 Lakhs to ORMAE. This policy is in place because we invest significantly in their training and provide them the opportunity to work on international projects with a Fortune 500 customer, which will enhance their skills and position them as top OR Scientists in the industry Training: You will have to undergo an initial 3-month training period, during which you will receive a stipend of ₹30,000 per month. On successful completion of the training, you will be promoted to the role of OR Scientist 1 with a CTC of ₹13 LPA (₹12 LPA fixed + ₹1 LPA performance-based variable pay). Compensation: For 1st Year - Annual CTC will be 12 lacs per annum fixed CTC, plus 1 lac per annum that will be performance based bonus. For subsequent years there will be an increment based on performance. Work with young and energetic team and exposure to work with direct client including fortune 500 worldwide companies. As discussed, we request you to kindly waive off the Corporate Registration Fee since our participation will be virtual.",
