		details:
			"About Skyroot AerospaceSkyroot Aerospace is India’s leading private space launch vehicle company, founded with the vision of “Opening Space for All.” We are pioneering India’s private space revolution by developing cutting-edge launch vehicle technologies that enable cost-effective and reliable access to space. Our team is driven by innovation, technical excellence, and a shared passion for space exploration and engineering breakthroughs.Role Overview - (Mechanical/ Aerospace / Industrial Engineering)We are looking for highly motivated engineering graduates to join our growing engineering teams. You will work on challenging, multidisciplinary projects that contribute directly to the design, development, testing, and production of next-generation space systems.This opportunity offers a platform to apply core engineering knowledge to real-world aerospace applications, working alongside some of the best minds in the industry. Roles and ResponsibilitiesParticipate in design, analysis, and validation of engineering systems and components.Support development, manufacturing, integration, and testing activities across multiple domains.Work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to solve complex engineering challenges.Contribute to continuous improvement, optimization, and innovation in product development.Ensure compliance with aerospace quality, safety, and reliability standards. Must-Have QualificationsB.Tech / B.E. (Final year or recent graduate) in Mechanical, Aerospace, Aeronautical, or Industrial Engineering.Core Engineering Fundamentals:a. Mechanical Engineering: Mechanics of Materials, Vibrations, Thermodynamics, Heat and Mass Transfer, Turbomachineryb. Aerospace / Aeronautical Engineering: Flight Dynamics, Aerodynamics, Propulsion, Aerospace Structuresc. Industrial Engineering: Operations Research, Supply Chain ManagementStrong analytical and problem-solving abilitiesProficiency in programming languages such as Python, C/C++ for data analysis, automation, and simulation scriptingProficiency in CAD and engineering analysis/simulation softwareExcellent teamwork, communication, and a proactive learning attitudeGenuine passion for aerospace and innovation-driven engineering Why Join Skyroot Aerospace?Be part of India’s first private company to build and launch space vehicles.Work on end-to-end development of real space systems with a young and dynamic team.Mentorship from experienced engineers and scientists, including ISRO alumni.Collaborative, high-growth environment where your ideas and work have real impact. Location: Hyderabad, TelanganaEmployment Type: Full-timeEligible Disciplines: Mechanical / Aerospace / Aeronautical / Industrial Engineering Role Overview - Avionics EngineeringWe are seeking highly motivated and technically strong graduates to join our Avionics team. You will work on end-to-end development of flight-critical electronic systems, embedded software, and electrical integration that power our space launch vehicles.This role provides an exceptional opportunity to apply your electronics and software expertise to real-world aerospace applications in a fast-paced, innovation-driven environment.Roles and ResponsibilitiesContribute to the design and development of embedded systems, electronics hardware, and software for flight and ground systems.Work on hardware design, PCB development, firmware programming, and system testing.Support integration and validation of avionics systems including sensors, controllers, and power distribution.Participate in data acquisition, telemetry, and control system development for launch vehicles.Collaborate across teams (mechanical, propulsion, systems) to ensure seamless system-level performance.Ensure compliance with aerospace quality, safety, and reliability standards. Must-Have QualificationsB.Tech / B.E. (Final Year or Recent Graduate) in Electronics and Communication, Electrical, or Instrumentation Engineering.Strong fundamentals in electronics, control systems, embedded systems, and circuit design.Proficiency in C/C++ or Python, and exposure to microcontrollers, FPGAs, or embedded platforms.Knowledge of electrical schematics, PCB tools, or simulation software (MATLAB, LTSpice, etc.).Strong analytical, problem-solving, and debugging skills.Excellent teamwork, communication, and a passion for technology and aerospace innovation.Why Join Skyroot Aerospace?Work on cutting-edge avionics that power India’s private space missions.Collaborate with experienced engineers, scientists, and ISRO alumni.Opportunity to see your designs and code literally take flight.A learning-driven, collaborative culture focused on engineering excellence and innovation. Location: Hyderabad, TelanganaEmployment Type: Full-timeEligible Disciplines: Electronics and Communication / Electrical / Instrumentation Engineering Role Overview - Mission & GNCWe are seeking highly motivated and technically strong graduates to join our Mission and Guidance, Navigation & Control (GNC) teams. You will work on end-to-end development of Trajectory design, GNC algorithms, flight software and perform various mission studies for launch vehicles.This role provides an exceptional opportunity to apply your flight dynamics, control system design, sensor fusion and electronics expertise to real-world aerospace applications in a fast-paced, innovation-driven environment.Roles and ResponsibilitiesWork on the design and development of Launch Vehicle Mission design, GNC algorithms and software, six Degree of Freedom launch vehicle models and mission simulations.Support integration and validation of GNC software in the flight computer through simulations and ground tests.Perform mission studies to ensure the robustness of the software and safety of the launch vehicle.Collaborate across teams (mechanical, propulsion, avionics) to ensure seamless system-level performance.Ensure compliance with aerospace quality, safety, and reliability standards.Must-Have QualificationsB.Tech / B.E. (Final Year or Recent Graduate) in Aerospace Engineering, Electrical and Electronics Engineering or Instrumentation and Control Engineering.Strong fundamentals in flight mechanics, control systems, sensor fusion and embedded software development.Proficiency in C/C++, MATLAB and Python, and exposure to microcontrollers, FPGAs, or embedded platforms.Strong analytical, problem-solving, and debugging skills.Excellent teamwork, communication, and a passion for technology and aerospace innovation.Why Join Skyroot Aerospace?Work on cutting-edge Mission Design and GNC systems that power India’s private space missions.Collaborate with experienced engineers, scientists, and ISRO alumni.Opportunity to see your designs and code literally take flight.A learning-driven, collaborative culture focused on engineering excellence and innovation. Location: Hyderabad, TelanganaEmployment Type: Full-timeEligible Disciplines: Aerospace Engineering/ Electrical and Electronics Engineering/ Instrumentation and Control Engineering.",
