		details:
			"About Skyroot AerospaceSkyroot Aerospace is India’s leading private space launch vehicle company, founded with the vision of “Opening Space for All.” We are pioneering India’s private space revolution by developing cutting-edge launch vehicle technologies that enable cost-effective and reliable access to space. Our team is driven by innovation, technical excellence, and a shared passion for space exploration and engineering breakthroughs.Role OverviewAs an Experienced Business Analyst, you will:· Lead strategic market analyses by building models, identifying growth opportunities, and forecasting trends.· Develop detailed business cases and proposals to support investment and operational decisions.· Optimize processes: analyze workflows, pinpoint inefficiencies, and implement improvements.· Drive cross-functional initiatives—partnering with engineering, finance, and operations to ensure alignment and execution.· Create and maintain interactive dashboards for real-time business insights.· Mentor interns and junior analysts on analysis frameworks and best practices.What You BringYou blend analytical expertise with practical business acumen. You interpret complex datasets, translate findings into strategic recommendations, and communicate them effectively to stakeholders. You take initiative, lead projects end-to-end, and elevate team performance through mentoring and collaboration.Technical Proficiencies· Advanced Excel modelling and VBA for complex analyses.· Expertise in BI tools (Power BI, Tableau) and SQL for data extraction and visualization.· Strong statistical analysis, forecasting, and scenario modelling skills.· Experience with AI-driven analytics and prompt engineering workflows.· Exceptional report writing and executive presentation capabilities.Qualifications:Final Year Engineering Graduate only 2026Key Attributes· Strategic Mindset: You see the big picture and align analyses to long-term objectives.· Collaboration & Influence: You communicate clearly and build consensus across teams.· Adaptability: You thrive in ambiguity and pivot quickly as priorities shift.· Ownership: You take accountability for deliverables and drive results without handholding.· People who have been in organising committees of the college festivals or part of student senate with an eagerness to improve the business understanding and develop into techno-commercial leaders are preferred.",
