		details:
			"Work with Qualcomm's Platform Architecture (QPA) team on next generation System-on-chip (SoC) for smartphone, tablet, automotive, machine-learning accelerators and other product categories. Candidate will be involved in architecture and/or micro-architecture of various subsystems and interfaces of the SoCs, e.g. reset, boot, power management, security, access control, debug services, various processing subsystems like CPU, DSP, GPU and AI Accelerator subsystems etc. Candidate will be working closely with cross-functional teams - hardware, software and product/test engineering etc. - in analyzing power, performance, area trade-offs, HW/ SW interfaces and re-usability of various IPs/ Cores. He/ She will also be involved in creating/ using architectural models and tools to help perform architectural analysis and architectural validation of choices made thereof. Possible Assignments Depending on Area of Expertise & relevant Experience (if applicable) The successful candidate will -Be part of Qualcomm Platform Architecture TeamWork with Hardware and Software teams to understand the design requirements, specification and interface details.Innovation is the theme of team in which you would be involved in latest technologies viz: ARMv9, RISC-V, SMMUv3, LPDDR5/6, PCIE Gen5, Leading tech-node etcValidate architecture/ microarchitecture models for multiple peripherals, interconnects and IPs for Qualcomm SoC platforms.Work with team to integrate these models to the SoC platform and validate IP/ System Level use cases.Mobile platform security, Secure Boot, Secure Storage, Access Control, Secure Debug, DDR protection, Key management, CertificationsPerform area, power, performance trade-offs and analysis of HW/SW re-usability requirements for IP/Cores and complete SoC & Competitive AnalysisDirectly apply computer architecture knowledge of CPUs, GPUs, DSPs, ML Accelerators, cache coherency, virtual memory, etc.;Collaborate within a rapidly growing and world-class computer architecture team! Preferred Qualifications: (the more the better):Exposure to digital design, VLSI, computer architecture, HDL languages, Scripting languagesGood understanding of SoC Design, Verification, post-Si Validation and Modelling.Good understanding of interfaces and on-chip interconnectsProgramming Languages: Verilog/ SystemVerilog, C/ C++, Perl/ Python/ TclProcessor Architecture, preferably ARM or RISC-V, cache coherency, virtual memoryDSP Architecture/Algorithm Design/OptimizationEmbedded Systems, Linux/Android ExperienceApplied cryptography, HW implementation of public and symmetric key cryptography primitives and computationDesired: SystemC, Assembly language programming for MCUs and/or DSPGood Communication skills, ability to convey information clearly and accurately Career Path in Qualcomm Platform Architecture (QPA) TeamQualcomm is working on the cutting-edge innovation in smartphone, automotive, IOT & machine-learning accelerators. Excellent opportunity to define, drive and design SOC, IP and systems solutions for new architectures.As part of Qualcomm Platform Architecture team, candidate would get hands-on working exposure to next gen products definition and area, power, performance trade-offs analysis. System level architecture/ micro-architecture of system use-cases.Candidate would have immense opportunity to enhance his/her technical skills and opportunity to solve complex problems, innovation, patents & recognition.Career path include, Systems Engineer, Senior Systems Engineer/Architect, Technology Architecture Lead or Product Architecture Lead etc.,This candidate will be in a highly visible position with an excellent opportunity to influence Qualcomm's technical direction, to lead the industry and change the world!",
