			"Aptitude test (90) | Technical interview (45) | Technical interview (45)",
		details:
			"We are looking for a motivated and detail-oriented Data Analyst to join our vibrant and fast-growing Data Analytics team. This role is an excellent opportunity for recent graduates who are eager to begin their career in data analytics and contribute to impactful business decisions.Key Responsibilities:•Collect, clean, and preprocess data from various internal and external sources.•Analyse datasets to identify trends, patterns, and insights that support business strategies.•Build and maintain dashboards and reports using tools such as Excel, Power BI, or Tableau.•Collaborate with cross-functional teams to support data-driven decision-making across product, credit, and operations.•Perform basic statistical analysis to interpret data and provide actionable insights.•Assist in evaluating product performance, tracking KPIs, and supporting analytical initiatives.•Participate in A/B testing, performance tracking, and other analytical experiments.•Contribute to process improvements by identifying gaps and recommending data-backed solutions.What we’re looking for:•Bachelor’s degree in technology or a related field.•Proficiency in SQL and MS Excel; working knowledge of Python or R.•Familiarity with data visualization tools such as Power BI or Tableau.•Strong analytical mindset, attention to detail, and problem-solving ability.•Ability to present data insights clearly through reports, charts, and dashboards.Career Progression PathWe are committed to supporting continuous development and offering a transparent growth pathway for all new joiners. The career progression for this role is structured as follows:Analyst Trainee — On JoiningRole Focus:•Learn foundational analytics skills, tools, and processes•Support basic data cleaning, reporting, and dashboard updates•Work closely with senior team members to understand business data and reporting needsDevelopment Goals:•Build competency in Excel, SQL, and data visualization tools•Gain hands-on experience with internal systems and workflows•Demonstrate reliability, learning agility, and attention to detailAnalyst - After Successful Completion of Probation (6 Months)Role Focus:•Independently manage routine analysis and reporting•Identify trends, validate data accuracy, and present insights•Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirementsDevelopment Goals:•Strengthen analytical problem-solving capability•Develop end-to-end ownership of assigned dashboards/reports•Improve communication and presentation of data insightsSenior Analyst - Upon Completion of 2 YearsRole Focus:•Lead complex analysis projects with minimal supervision•Mentor Analyst Trainees and Analysts•Design scalable dashboards, data models, and automation solutions•Provide thought leadership and influence data-driven decision-makingDevelopment Goals:•Build advanced skills (Python, cloud data tools, statistical modelling, etc.)•Take ownership of high-impact analytics initiatives•Develop leadership and stakeholder-management capabilitiesAbout Kissht:Kissht, a Great Place to Work® certified organization, is a consumer-first credit app that is transforming the landscape of consumer credit. As one of the fastest-growing and most respected FinTech companies, Kissht is a pioneer in data and machine-based lending. With over 15 million customers, including 40% from tier 2 cities and beyond, we offer both short and long-term loans for personal consumption, business needs, and recurring expenses.Founded by Ranvir and Krishnan, alumni of IIT and IIM, and backed by renowned investors like Endiya Partners, the Brunei Investment Authority, and the Singapore Government, Kissht is synonymous with excellence in the industry. Join us and be a part of a dynamic, innovative company that is changing the future of financial technology.",
