		details:
			"Quantitative Research - SingaporeAbout Graviton Research Capital: What began as a small team of passionate researchers and technologists in 2014 has grown into a dynamic firm where innovation and collaboration are at the heart of everything we do. We leverage quantitative analysis and insights across complex financial markets, enabling us to thrive in some of the most demanding and competitive environments.We are proud to have some of the most accomplished quantitative researchers and technologists globally, each operating with strategic autonomy within specialized trading teams. These teams explore diverse strategies across asset classes, driven by their unique processes and insights. This synergy of independence and shared innovation allows us to adapt swiftly, push boundaries and continuously evolve.Our journey is defined by shared ambition and a constant drive to transform the possibilities of quantitative trading.The Role: As a Quantitative Researcher, you will play a pivotal role in shaping trading strategy design and execution. This is a high-impact, research-driven position where you’ll:Design, develop, and implement high-frequency trading strategies based on quantitative research and statistical analysis.Analyze large volumes of market data to identify trading signals, patterns, and anomalies.Build and refine predictive models using machine learning and statistical techniques to enhance trading algorithms.Monitor and evaluate the performance of trading strategies, making necessary adjustments to improve profitability and reduce risk.Work closely with traders, technologists, and other quantitative researchers to integrate strategies and ensure seamless execution.Stay updated with the latest research in quantitative finance, machine learning, and high-frequency trading to incorporate best practices and innovative approaches.Your Skills & Talents:Degree in a highly analytical field, such as Engineering, Mathematics, or Computer Science.8+ CGPA with no backlogsSkills:Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, C++.Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with experience in statistical analysis and machine learning.Familiarity with financial markets, trading mechanisms, and algorithmic trading.Experience with high-performance computing and data processing technologies.Personal Attributes:Strong attention to detail and ability to work under pressure.Excellent communication skills and ability to collaborate effectively in a team environment.Self-motivated with a passion for financial markets and quantitative research.Good to have skills:Internship/experience with high-frequency trading systems and infrastructure.Knowledge of market microstructure and high-frequency trading strategies.Familiarity with low-latency programming and optimization techniques.Why GravitonImpact from Day One: Your work directly influences live trading performance.Elite Mentorship: Learn from some of the best researchers and engineers in the industry.Tech-First Culture: Access to world-class infrastructure, HPC clusters and cutting-edge tools.Flat Hierarchy: No bureaucracy - just an environment that rewards bold ideas and measurable impact.Exceptional Rewards: Market-leading compensation with performance-based growth opportunities.Total Rewards:CTC of SGD 133,200 per annum + discrete bonus + medical coverage. Graviton will also cover airfare and hotel accommodation for up to 14 days during the onboarding period.",
		info: "Total Rewards:CTC of SGD 133,200 per annum + discrete bonus + medical coverage. Graviton will also cover airfare and hotel accommodation for up to 14 days during the onboarding period.Why Graviton:Exceptional Rewards: Market-leading compensation with performance-based growth opportunities.Comprehensive Perks:Competitive payAnnual international team outingFully covered commuting expensesBest-in-class health insuranceCatered breakfasts and lunches with a well-stocked kitchenFour weeks of annual leave plus market holidaysGym and sports club membershipsRegular social events, clubs, and after-work partiesImpact from Day One: Your work directly influences live trading performance.Elite Mentorship: Learn from some of the best researchers and engineers in the industry.Tech-First Culture: Access to world-class infrastructure, HPC clusters, and cutting-edge tools.Flat Hierarchy: No bureaucracy—just an environment that rewards bold ideas and measurable impact.",
