			"Technical test (1:30) | Aptitude test (1:30) | Technical interview (1 hr) | Personal interview (30 mins)",
		details:
			"Department Brief:The Technology infrastructure department is responsible for the design, implementation, and maintenance of the \norganization's IT infrastructure. This includes the physical components of the IT environment, such as servers, storage devices, \nnetworking, security equipment. The IT infrastructure department also manages the software that runs on these devices, \nsuch as operating systems, applications, and security software. Technology infrastructure department plays a critical role in \nensuring the availability, performance, and security of the organization's IT systems. They work closely with other IT \ndepartments, such as the Application and the Operations, to ensure that the organization's Technology infrastructure is \nreliable and secure. Technology Infrastructure department is also responsible for designing, developing, planning and \nimplementing changes to the IT infrastructure and maintain scripts to automate IT infrastructure that involves tasks such as \nprovisioning servers, configuring network devices, deploying applications, upgrading hardware and software, and migrating \nto new technologies.Roles & Responsibilities:You will be responsible to design develop and maintain scripts to automate IT infrastructure that involves tasks such as \nprovisioning servers, configuring network devices, and deploying applications. The Trainee will play crucial role in \nunderstanding the requirements for automation and will be exposed to cutting-edge technologies such as Python, Ansible, \nCI/CD and UI Development. Developing and maintaining of automation scripts for IT infrastructure which involves tasks such as provisioning \nservers, configuring network devices, and deploying applications. Collaborating with different stakeholder which involves software developers, system administrators, and security \nengineers to understand the requirement and automate the manual tasks.Troubleshooting automation issues that involve debugging scripts, identifying, and resolving errors etc.Documenting automation scripts and processes that involves creating concise and crisp documents so that other \nteam members can understand and re-use. Managing pipeline created for application deployment Managing Automation tools",
