			"Technical test (1:30) | Aptitude test (1:30) | Technical interview (1 hr) | Personal interview (1 hr)",
		details:
			"Who we are A homegrown brand with a global vision, NSE is counted as one of the world’s largest exchanges and a catalyst for driving\nIndia’s economic growth. NSE was the first exchange in India to implement electronic or screen-based trading which began\nits operations in 1994; a pioneer in technology which ensures the reliability and performance of its systems through a culture\nof innovation and investment in technology. NSE operates a market ecosystem to bring in transparency & efficiency. Brief Introduction of EPR DepartmentThe Economic Policy and Research (EPR) function, a part of the Business Development department, is the research and\nanalytical arm of NSE. The EPR team, headed by the Chief Economist, is responsible, among other things, for bringing out\nNSE’s monthly flagship publication called NSE Market Pulse—a one-of-its-kind, one-stop document that extensively tracks\nthe Indian economy and markets. The publication is well appreciated and widely referred to by stakeholders across the board\nincluding Government, Regulators, Practitioners and Academia. The EPR team works in close collaboration with SEBI, as well\nas internal departments of the exchange including Business Development, Products, Listing, Technology, Regulations and\nIndices for providing analytical support.What you will be doing The role requires contribution towards building NSE’s reputation as a thought leader by undertaking research on economy\nand securities markets and assisting in policy advocacy. It would provide him/her the opportunity to work in at least four\nbroad areas namely macroeconomics, financial markets, corporate governance & ESG and specifically quantitative finance.\nThe research on high-frequency orders and trades data will help the candidate understand the nuances of how an exchange\nworks and build his/her skills in working on big, one-of-its-kind data.You will be responsible forMacro and financial market research\n• Assist the team in carrying out research and data analysis for the flagship monthly publication, NSE Market Pulse.\n• Closely track developments in the securities market and issues in India and abroad on a continuous basis and\nanalyse their linkages and potential impact.\n• Assist the team in holding webinars/round-table discussions/seminars around crucial macro-economic issues and\nother topics of interest to the exchange and prepare research reports out of it.\n• Work/interact with top-notch academic institutions and think tanks on collaborative projects\nMarket microstructure/quantitative finance research:\n• Work alongside other researchers of NSE’s research projects in the field of data science, market microstructure,\neconometrics, market liquidity, etc., on NSE’s cloud-based research facility called the NSE Data Room (NDR).\n• Clean, aggregate, and organize tick-by-tick data for research projects in a quick machine-readable format\n• Generate insights on market structure by analysing this data using techniques in the area of statistics,\neconometrics, AI/ML.\n• Document and present the findings of the analysis in a research note/working paper.\n• Collaborating with internal (Technology, Business Development, Surveillance, etc.) and external stakeholders\n(SEBI) to provide analytical support.• Creating tools to analyse data for patterns\n• Stay abreast with current trends/research in the field of financial/securities market and technology involving big\ndata\n• Continuously strengthen and expand capabilities in modern big-data tools, methods, and analytical techniques. Corporate governance:\n• Assist in establishing NSE as a front-runner in the field of corporate governance by holding roundtables, and\nseminars and generating research output.\n• Expand domain knowledge in corporate governance.In-house and outsourced research and dissemination:\n• Collaborate with other departments of NSE on internal projects.\n• Assist in conducting conferences/roundtables/panel discussions on emerging and existing policy and regulatory\nissues.\n• Review commissioned research papers, student research projects, deliverables of research collaborators etc.\n• Look out constantly for consultation papers put out by regulators/ policy makers and promptly prepare highquality draft response.\n• Prepare drafts for speeches, keynote address, notes for panel discussion etc., for senior management, relating to\nsecurities market, corporate governance and economy.\n• Build and maintain appropriate relationships with research and policy making bodies (research institutions in\nIndia and abroad, Government, SEBI, MCA etc).\nExpand research outreach:\n• Work alongside other team members to expand and support the research community in the area of financial\nmarkets.\n• Assist the team in running the research programs at NSE, including the NSE Research Initiative. This would entail\naccess to requisite data on the cloud facility called NSE data room. How Performance will be measuredFinancial Measures: As defined in KRA\nCustomer Measures: As defined in KRA\nLearning and growth Measures: As defined in KRAInternal Processes Measures: As defined in KRAWhat skills and experience you should bring • Strong analytical/quantitative skills\n• Knowledge of programming languages such as R (preferred), Python, Julia, C++\n• Experience in working and dealing with large financial datasets would be an advantage\n• Proficiency in working with Linux-based environments would be an advantage\n• Knowledge of macro/market databases would be an advantage\n• Ability to deliver quality output under stringent timelines with minimal supervision\n• Result orientationWhat we have to offer you• A Dynamic and Inspiring work environment\n• Collaborative and inclusive work culture that values Diversity, Innovation, and Continuous learning\n• Ample of opportunities to work on challenging projects for professional growth and advancement.\n• Support for professional development.\n• Many more Employee Benefits and Perks",
