		details:
			"ROLE TITLE: SCIENTIST-‘B’ (Electronics & Communication Engineering)Key accountabilities:• Understanding product requirements, architecting, a suitable solution aften ananalysis of different alternatives.• Design and/or testing of a board, including PCB design in CAD toolenvironment. The board would typically be a microprocessor based board,with a variety of electrical and optical network interfaces, and could involveRF/DSP/Fibre-optical system components/network processors, etc.• Desing, coding, simulation and testing of FPGA/PLD• Testing of the design and design related procured components eg. Opticalmodules, amplifiers, couplers, etc.• Validation of a product/solution and ensuring its working in the customerenvironment.• Documentation of the design, to facilitate mass production of the design andtechnology transfer.Role requirement behaviors: Team spirit, proficiency towards using latest hardwaredesign and testing toolsROLE TITLE: SCIENTIST- ‘B’ (Computer Science Engineering)Key accountabilities:• Well versed with computer network and system programming having excellentsoftware development skills and problem tackling approach.• Sound base in computer design and architecture.• Basic knowledge in RISC, CISC architecture types, and variants ofprocessors based on Intel, MIPS and Power PC.• In depth knowledge in operating system concepts viz memory management,disk scheduling, multithreading, parallel processing, use of semaphores andtackling different deadlock situations, ways to detect and avoid them optimally.• Developer having decent knowledge in database concepts and normalization,having concrete idea about use of ER diagrams.• Expertise in C/C++/Python/MEAN stack programming and sound knowledgein optimum algorithm and design patterns.• Expertise in objective C & Swift is desirable.• Exposure in J2SE, J2EE, web technologies and Linux environment isdesirable.• Exposure to Basic data science, NLP, Machine Learning, Deep Learning(CNN,RNN,LSTM) is desirableRole requirement behaviors: Analytical thinking, Learning Ability, Teamwork,Continuous Learning",
		info: "",
		reqs: "Eligibility criteria:\n\n \n\n1. \nQualification:\nBE/B.Tech/ME/M.Tech in Computer Science & Engineering or Electronics &\nCommunication Engineering. Where ECE is not a standalone department, Electrical\nEngineering may be considered if demonstrably equivalent to ECE.\n\n2. \nStream continuity: For\nME/M.Tech in EC/CS, BE/B.Tech must also be EC/CS; cross-stream combinations are\nnot considered.\n\n3. \nAcademic thresholds: Minimum\n70% or 7.0/10 CGPA in B.E/B.Tech and in the highest qualification acquired.\nScreening will consider up to 6th semester for UG and up to 2nd semester for\nPG; final eligibility requires overall 70%/7.0 CGPA upon completion.\n\n4. \nAttempts/backlogs: No\nbacklogs; all subjects in every qualification must be cleared in the first and\nsingle attempt.\n\n5. \nNationality: Indian\nnationals only.\n\n \n\nAge criteria (as on 01 August 2026):\n\n \n\nFor BE/BTech:\n\na) GEN/EWS\nCategory : Not exceeding 25\nyears.\n\nb) OBC\nCategory : Not exceeding\n28 years.\n\nc) SC/ST/PH\nCategory :\nNot exceeding 30 years.\n\nFor ME/Mtech:\n\na) GEN/EWS\nCategory : Not exceeding 27\nyears.\n\nb) OBC\nCategory : Not exceeding\n30 years.\n\nc) SC/ST/PH\nCategory :\nNot exceeding 32 years.",
