			"you’ll be our: GET- System Engineer you’ll be based at: IBC Knowledge Park, Bengaluruyou’ll be Aligned with: Head of Hardware, Firmware and System Engineeringyou’ll be a member of: Hardware, Firmware & System Engineering TeamWhat you’ll do at Ather: This role is for an engineer who would take care of validating multiple requirements and constraints on various electro-mechanical systems for electric two wheelers and associated charging infrastructure BEFORE setting them as product specifications. Conceptualize electronic and electro-mechanical systems like dashboards, vehicle control unit, sensors, actuators and chargers for various applications.Translate product requirements into technical specifications for development by Engg teams.Research into existing and new technologies to understand feasibility of productizing them.Build Proof of concepts for quick feasibility checks.Own and specify the interactions between subsystems through solid understanding of the vehicle/CI architecture.Trade off diverse system requirements like functional , safety, reliability, durability, and compliance. Responsible for Interaction and Impact Analysis for any specification change and engineering change. Investigate system level failures because of subsystem malfunction.Define and solve problems from first principles.Gather and analyze the right data to solve problems. Here’s what we are looking for: Solid understanding of electric circuits.Solid understanding of engineering physics.Good understanding of lab equipment.Exposure to firmware.Ability to interpret schematics and read C code.A good team player with interpersonal planning and good communication skills.You bring to Ather: B.Tech/M.Tech with specialization in any Engineering discipline with adequate exposure to physics and some expertise in circuits.",
