		details:
			"You’ll be ourAI DeveloperYou’ll be based atIBC Knowledge Park, Bengaluru, IndiaYou’ll be aligned withAI LeadYou’ll be joining ourDS and AI TeamAbout AtherAt Ather, we are building the future of smart, connected electric vehicles. Our fleet is the backbone of this smart ecosystem, generating a massive, growing stream of data. We are increasingly using this data to power intelligent features and business decisions. We are a fast growing company and our internal systems continue to evolve rapidly to facilitate this growth.About the RoleWe are looking for a highly motivated and skilled developer to join our innovative AI team. You will be responsible for designing and developing intelligent software agents using cutting-edge tools. This role requires familiarity with generative AI and related techniques.What You Will DoWe are looking for a highly motivated and skilled Generative AI Agent Developer to join our innovative team. You will be responsible for designing, developing, and deploying intelligent software agents using cutting-edge tools. AI is an evolving area so your work will not be limited to just tech but will also include working with multiple stakeholders, supporting decisions, building domain expertise, and identifying opportunities and making a business case for it.What We Are Looking ForRequired:Technical skills:Proficiency in Python; comfortable programming without any AI assistanceStrong knowledge of basic LLM concepts such as tokens, context windows, etc.Hands on experience with deep learning modelsExperience of working with various unstructured input, eg. text, images, video, etc.Soft skills:Ability to break large problems down into smaller problemsQuick learner, on tech but also on various business functions in a typical corporate environmentNice to have:Technical skills:Experience of building an AI based system and having users interact with itExperience of evaluating the performance of an AI based system, identifying specific improvements needed, and being able to implement themFamiliarity with advanced LLM concepts such as attention mechanisms, KV caching for inference optimization, etc.Hands-on experience with some LLM related tools and techniques such as Chain-of-Thought (CoT), Tree-of-Thought (ToT), Reflection, ReAct pattern, DSPy, etc.Hands-on experience with some LLM orchestration frameworks, e.g., LangChain / LangGraph, CrewAI, AutoGen, or Agent Development Kit (ADK))Experience in building robust Python based systemsExperience with LLM optimization techniques for deployment, e.g., quantization, pruning, batching, etc.Experience with vector databases, eg., Pinecone, Weaviate, Chroma, Milvus, etc.Experience with model fine tuning, eg. data preparation, LoRA, QLoRA, etc.Soft skillsAbility to drive consensusAbility to prioritise feature requests based on various considerations such as impact, feasibility, effort, etc.Be You, With UsThe Ather story doesn't write itself - our people do. We believe everyone is equal, but not the same. Diversity is our strength, and building an inclusive and equitable workplace begins with acknowledging and embracing our differences.We are an equal opportunity employer, and our team reflects a wide range of identities, experiences, and perspectives - all united by a shared passion to shape the Ather journey.",
