			"you’ll be our: Design Engineer - Hardware Packaging you’ll be based at: IBC Knowledge Park, Bengaluruyou’ll be Aligned with: Manager- Hardware Packagingyou’ll be a member of: Hardware Packaging TeamRole in a nutshell: To design high quality vehicle electronics modules packaging by applying best practices and methods such as DFMEA, DFX, DMAIC, DOE and statistical tolerance analyses. To deliver design definitions for prototype and production modules. To root cause and prevent production and field issuesDesign and development of electronic and electro-mechanical systems like dashboard, controller module, sensors, actuators for various applications.Testing and Validation of systems designed and interactions between them by understanding the vehicle architecture.Responsible for ensuring manufacturability of electronic box build assembly components and drive quality controls.Responsible for Electromechanical Interaction and Impact Analysis and experience in Tolerance stack-up.Participate in and contribute to DFMEA, DFM, DFA, DFC, DFS, DFR, and component selection/derating reviews carry out RCA on field failures and implement/recommend CAPA.Performing Problem solving using industry best practices such as 5-Why analysis, Fishbone diagram, RCA methodologies etc..Any other work assigned by the reporting manager. The responsibilities can be reviewed or changed from time to time as per the guidance of the reporting manager. Here’s what we are looking for: Strong knowledge on engineering fundamentals for applications.Knowledge in manufacturing process for Plastics, sheet metal, machining and casting.Knowledge in fasteners, inserts, surface treatment methodologies, and engineering plastics used for electronic packaging and vehicle peripherals.Basic knowledge on understanding of electronics components will be an added advantage. knowledge on basic tolerance stackup and GD&T is required.Basic knowledge on Thermal design including interface materials and simulation will be an added advantage.Experience with working on SW tools such as NX. Basic understanding of CAE tools such as Ansys/Fluent.A good team player with interpersonal planning and good communication skills.",
