			"Resume filtering | Technical test (02:00) | Technical interview (00:40) | HR Interview (00:40)",
		details:
			"Mission of the programThe goal for our GET program in the Department of Product Ownership is to forge the future leaders of electric mobility. We are seeking a select few to navigate through the complexities of building technology and manufacturing products with a first principles approach, and be at the forefront of driving Ather’s mission. You’ll be ourGET - Department of Product OwnershipYou’ll be based at IBC Knowledge Park, BengaluruYou’ll be aligned withDepartment of Product OwnershipYou’ll be joining ourDepartment of Product OwnershipWhat you’ll do at AtherOver 24 months, you will embark on a high-velocity journey through Ather’s development ecosystem. It is a fully immersive experience to build a product owner from the ground up. Each rotation is a deep dive into a specific function, where you will be given meaningful, technically challenging work that supports critical business prioritiesPhase 1: Engineering and validation - Hands-on understanding of what it takes to build our products - vehicle engineering, powertrain dynamics, battery technology and software. Own a component or part of code and ship it to our customers. Understand the way we build our technology fundamentallyPhase 2: Industrialisation and supply-chain - Work alongside our manufacturing engineering and supply-chain teams to take a design from a prototype to industrialising it for scale. Learn what it takes to work with partner suppliers, and the considerations (financial, operational and technical) at play for manufacturing parts that need to be supplied at scale at utmost reliabilityPhase 3: Financial acumen - get acquainted with financial tools that help to do what it takes to run development operations including budgeting, setting PnL targets, technology benchmarking, zero-based costing, and writing out compelling business cases for pitching newer ideas. Post an assessment at the end of 2 years including technical depth as well as soft skills such as the ability to negotiate, lead without formal authority and being comfortable working with ambiguity, you shall commence work as a Product Owner / Associate Product Owner for one of our modulesAs a Product Owner, you will take charge of a cross-functional development team to define its roadmap in alignment with Ather’s vision and near-term objectives, pitch your roadmap to the upper management to obtain resources to fund your projects, and then get into the weeds with the relevant cross-functional teams and deliver those projects. Along the way, you will have to set priorities, make many micro-decisions in terms of where to take risks and where not to by assessing trade-off’s, decide whether to outsource a certain aspect of the project or do it in-house, negotiate with various stakeholders across the board on specifications / costs / manufacturing strategy / timelines, and inspire your team to achieve exceptional results in a way that is uniquely AtherHere’s what we are looking for Demonstrated ability to think from engineering first principles, ideally through driving inter-disciplinary engineering projects including mechanical, hardware and software aspects. For instance, should be able to link the physics within a lithium ion cell to the economics of running a charging stationWorking with a multi-faceted team, we seek candidates who have a demonstrated interest across various aspects of running a business - finance, marketing, operations - in addition to engineeringDemonstrated leadership potential, strong collaborative skills and high emotional intelligence to earn the trust and respect of colleagues with decades more experience What you bring to Ather Outstanding academic record that demonstrates a deep grasp of core engineering fundamentals Portfolio of hands-on projects that showcase passion for building things. Tell us a completing story about a complex problem you solved not for a grade, but because you were obsessed with finding an answerSelf-starter, with a bias for action, resiliency in the face of setbacks",
		info: "Be You, With UsThe Ather story doesn't write itself - our people do. We believe everyone is equal, but not the same. Diversity is our strength, and building an inclusive and equitable workplace begins with acknowledging and embracing our differences. We are an equal opportunity employer, and our team reflects a wide range of identities, experiences, and perspectives - all united by a shared passion to shape the Ather journey.",
