		details:
			"At Ather, we take pride in ushering the Indian EV movement forward, and we continue to do this by building from scratch. The best part is that we’re just getting started. So, if you believe in taking moonshots, join us. Be the story.You’ll be ourGET - Dept. of Chief EngineeringYou’ll be based atIBC Knowledge Park, BengaluruYou’ll be aligned withDepartment of Chief EngineeringYou’ll be joining ourDepartment of Chief EngineeringWhat you’ll do at AtherWork on engineering problems across multiple disciplines and systems over a period of 2 years by rotating between teams and projects as deemed necessary.Be part of a swimlane (cross-functional team) of one of the above systems/components in one of the above rotation stints.If the work undertaken by the candidate during the 2 year rotation stint is deemed satisfactory across various dimensions of assessment - depth of knowledge in various streams of engineering (mech, elec, software), various components/systems of an Electric Vehicle, basic fundamentals of program management, project delivery etc., the candidate shall be asked to work as a Module Lead/Assistant Module Lead for one of the many modules in our EVs.Here’s what we’re looking forEnthusiastic engineers with a strong first principles understanding of the various streams of engineering - mechanical, electrical and software. Strong first principles backed knowledge of a wide range of disciplines would be an important requirement in the role and hence would be gauged in the interview process.Basic understanding of electric vehicles and the various technologies going into them.Ability to switch between simulation, design, characterization, testing seamlessly to be part of the team that delivers the end system/component.Should be able to work across tools for CAD, Code, Schematic, Datasheets, Diagnostics with minimal supervision.What you bring to AtherA curious mind that can ask the right questions and bring new ideas to the table.A curious mind that can work across disciplines and systems and tie them up (virtually) to understand what it takes to deliver an EV at Ather’s scale.",
