		details:
			"Job Overview:We are seeking highly motivated and adaptable Post Graduate Engineer Trainees (PGETs) to join our dynamic aerospace & defense company. As a PGET, you will embark on a challenging and rewarding journey, gaining hands-on experience and contributing to critical projects across various functions.We are looking for individuals who:• Are passionate about the aerospace & defense industry.• Have a strong desire to contribute to India's technological advancements.• Are eager to learn and grow in a challenging and rewarding environment.As a PGET, you will have the opportunity to:• Work on cutting-edge projects and technologies.• Gain hands-on experience in various functions.• Receive mentorship and guidance from experienced professionals.• Develop your technical and leadership skills.• Build a successful career in the aerospace & defense industry.As an Avionics trainee, you will be, • Responsible to study and understand the system by going through requirements and design documents.• He/she is involved in systems integration, troubleshooting and testing on UAV. • Is required to review the testing of the existing designs and further assist in installation of the same; • Understand requirement properly and identify the appropriate equipment that would rightly fit the requirement compare and conduct analysis amongst the various alternatives available; troubleshoot any issues that come up• Carry cost estimation keeping budget; carry out obsolescence study, suggest and implement the changes in existing design; technical & compliance evaluation of the equipment, vigorous electrical & mechanical laboratory testing of the inputs received from the manufacturer, ensure factory acceptance test and site acceptance test• Develop an integration plan, setup integration facility & integration of equipment procured; carry out flight evaluation along with team; construct verification cross reference matrixRoles may include (but not limited to):1) Understanding of concepts of Avionics standards 2) Familiarity with Aerospace / Avionics design / simulation software3) Knowledge of Aerospace components and Systems 4) Fulfill pre-defined projects for the particular- rotation Skills we are looking for:• Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.• Adaptability to work in a dynamic and fast-paced environment.• Willingness to learn and take on new challenges.Note: The specific role assigned to you as a PGET will depend on your skills, interests, and the organization's requirements. We value flexibility and adaptability, and encourage you to explore various areas within the company to find the best fit for your career aspirations.Join us in shaping the future of aerospace & defense in India!",
