		details:
			"Role: Associate Developer \n\nLocation: Bangalore\n\nCompany\nName: SAP Labs India\n\n \n\n \n\nWhat you\nwill build\n\nWe are part of the Office of the\nCTO (Chief Technology Officer), and therefore we work on topics that directly\nsupport the SAP CTO’s mandate. We investigate front-runner technologies to\nverify, experiment, and create proof-points that inform technical decisions.\nOur work includes technology strategy initiatives such as the North\nStar Architecture,\nalong with related research, investigations, coding experiments, and the\ncreation of Reference Architectures.\n\n \n\nAs a member of our team, you will\nbe responsible for prototyping, building showcases, and experimenting with new\ntechnologies. You will research internal and external products, concepts, and\narchitectures, and contribute to concept and strategy papers as needed. A\nstrong combination of architectural thinking, abstraction skills, and hands-on\ncoding experience is highly valuable for this role.\n\n \n\nYour work will involve:\n\n· Developing tooling and content\n(reference architectures across Data, AI, Platform, Data, AI and Agents) that is published on the SAP Architecture Center \n\n· Exploring emerging technologies\nacross AI and\nAgents, including\n\nNeuro-symbolic AI, Knowledge Graphs, MCP (Model Context Protocol),\nAgent Orchestration, RAG, and other AI-native patterns\n\n· Working\non non-functional aspects such as Security, HA/DR, Performance, and Reliability\n\n· Prototyping and building\nproof-points that influence company-wide strategic decisions\n\n· Contributing\nto concept\nnotes, technical investigations, and strategy documents\n\n \n\n \n\nWhat you\nbring\n\n· \nDegree\nin Computer Science, IT from premier institutes\n\n· \nStrong\nanalytical and problem-solving skills\n\n· \nHands-on\nskills in full-stack engineering (backend/frontend/data/integration/ML\nor GenAI)\n\n· \nKnowledge\nof SAP BTP or public cloud (AWS/Azure/GCP) is a plus\n\n· \nUnderstanding\nor curiosity around Data, AI and agent-based architectures\n\n· \nProficiency\nin one or more programming languages\n\n· \nStrong\npresentation, articulation, and storytelling abilities\n\n· \nCuriosity\nfor emerging technologies and willingness to learn fast\n\n \n\nWhy this\nrole is different\n\nYou will work where research becomes\narchitecture and architecture becomes code, influencing\ntechnology direction across SAP before it reaches product teams.\n\nIf you want to begin your career where strategy\nmeets engineering and experimentation drives decisions, this team is the\nright place.\n\n \n\nWhere you belong\n\nYou will join the Office\nof the CTO (OCTO), the team that\nworks on technology topics relevant to the entire company and product units and,\nin many cases, on ideas before they become mainstream inside SAP. We\nexplore front-runner technologies, run experiments, build proof-points, and\nsupport CTO and Executive Board level strategic projects. A core part of our\nwork is shaping and publishing Reference Architectures that guide how SAP and\nits ecosystem build interoperable and future-ready enterprise solutions. These\narchitectures are externally published via the SAP Architecture Center and are consumed by\ncustomers, partners, and engineering teams across SAP.\n\n \n\nYou will work in an\ninternationally blended team based in India, collaborating closely with peers\nin Germany and the USA. Because our topics are high-impact, strategic,\nand evolve rapidly, continuous learning, fast skill acquisition, and comfort\nwith ambiguity are essential.",
