		details:
			"About Godrej & Boyce Godrej is one of India’s oldest, most trusted and respected brands. Our founders, Ardeshir and Pirojsha Godrej started the journey in 1897 with Engineering excellence and a strong pioneering spirit, towards making India self-reliant. Godrej & Boyce (G&B) positively impacts the lives of one-third of India’s population through its diverse presence across 10 industries – from building complex bespoke engineering solutions to making branded consumer goods like appliances, furniture, locks and security solutions. With over 14,000 committed employees working in 14 diverse businesses offering consumer, office and industrial products & services of the highest quality across India and across the globe. Godrej Appliances Godrej Appliances’ journey began in 1958 with a goal to develop and manufacture a refrigerator in India. The business manufactured India’s first refrigerator and it was momentous, and a big milestone in India’s journey of self-reliance. Today, the business has grown to become one of India’s largest players in the fast-growing home appliances market. With manufacturing facilities in Shirwal, outside of Pune, Maharashtra and Mohali, Punjab which are the first and only manufacturing units in the country to win the coveted Platinum Green Co. certification for the efforts in green manufacturing; and a state-of-the-art R&D centre in Pirangut on the outskirts of Pune. Godrej Appliances has passionately been offering some of India’s most thoughtfully designed appliances because to make people’s lives more convenient and is the only Indian company shortlisted for the Global Cooling Prize, a prestigious global challenge to design a cooling solution with five times less climate impact than the ACs popular today. \n \n \n Job Profile\n \n \n \n \n KRA:-\n \n \n We are on the\n look-out for a product designer, who is passionate about the design\n process, from developing strong conceptual foundations to refining the\n smallest of details with quality and dignity.\n \n You will be\n working closely with a small but motivated team of designers and engineers\n conceptualizing and designing appliances to delight our consumers. \n \n Core\n responsibilities - \n \n \n Conceptualising ideas, converting them into 3D models\n & prototypes\n Product enhancements and customizations\n Design presentations and documentation\n Product development and design support\n \n \n \n \n \n Job\n Description:-\n \n \n The incumbent will be responsible for:\n \n Designing products and their user interfaces using\n participatory and iterative design techniques including observational\n studies, customer interviews, usability testing and other forms of\n requirements’ discovery\n Producing user requirement specifications, personas,\n storyboards, scenarios, design prototypes and design specifications\n Effectively communicate research findings, conceptual\n ideas, detailed design and design rationale both verbally and visually\n Managing design processes, driving decisions,\n tracking issues and assisting in estimating resource needs and schedules\n Working closely with development teams to ensure that\n design specifications are implemented\n \n \n \n \n \n \n Requisite\n Qualification\n \n \n \n \n Essential\n \n \n Master’s in Design \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n Skills\n Required\n \n \n \n \n Special\n Skills Required \n \n \n \n Ideation /conceptualization skills\n Hand sketching skills\n 3D CAD modelling - Rhinoceros, NX, or equivalent\n Illustration skills on Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop\n and XD or equivalent.\n Rendering skills with proficiency in KeyShot or\n equivalent.\n Presentation & communication skills",
