		details:
			"About Godrej & Boyce Mfg. Co Ltd\n\nSince 1897, Godrej Enterprises Group (which includes\nGodrej & Boyce and its affiliates) is a conglomerate that has contributed\nsignificantly to India’s economic growth and self-reliance by providing complex\nengineering, design-led innovation, and sustainable manufacturing solutions.\nFrom the world’s first patented springless lock, and safes to pioneering Indian\nmade typewriters and refrigerators, the conglomerate has also paved the way for\nthe growth of key sectors like aerospace, energy, and security.\n\nGodrej Security Solutions \n\nGodrej Security Solutions, since 1902 has been the\nnation’s first choice when it comes to integrated security solutions for\nfamilies and institutions. \nThe business manufactures vaults, lockers and secure room doors for most of the\nleading public sector and private banks in India and also makes security\nproducts for marine and defence sectors. Godrej Security Solutions have\nprovided surveillance installations in over 45 countries, including the Middle\nEast, South East Asia, Far East Asia, East Africa, USA, Europe and the SAARC\ncountries. \nGodrej Security Solutions is a full-service security solutions organization,\noffering a comprehensive suite for residential, industrial, and business\npremises - providing cutting edge, holistic, integrated surveillance solutions\nthat safeguard not only millions of homes and offices, but also protect\nprestigious institutions like the Reserve Bank of India, the Taj Mahal and\norganizations of national importance. \n\nJob Description – Design – Godrej Security\nSolutions\n\nA) Research on advance barrier materials like - \n\n1) Nano engineered metal composites, \n\n2) Phase - change materials, \n\n3) alloys with self-healing properties,\n\n4) thermal dissipation coating, \n\n5) reactive layers releasing ceramic foams \n\nB) Application of these materials in physical security\nproducts and Marine solutions \n\nC) Stress and thermal simulation, model and simulate\nburglary attempts \n\nD) Sustainability practices in product and process design\n\nSkills Required:\n\nStrong foundation in alloys, lightweight high-strength\nmaterials, heat treatment and failure analysis. Exposure to composites,\nceramics, impact resistance, thermal resistance.",
