			"Resume filtering | Research Prestation round (00:45) | Technical interview (01:00) | HR Interview (00:30)",
		details:
			"Job Description \n\n \n\nAbout us:\nAt Fujitsu AI Lab, we are at the forefront of research, innovation, and product\ndevelopment in areas such as AI (artificial intelligence), Machine Learning\n(ML), and Data Science. Our technologies are integrated into Fujitsu’s products\nand customer systems across sectors like finance, telecommunications,\nmanufacturing, healthcare, and social infrastructure. We are committed to\nshaping the future with cutting-edge AI research, driving advancements in\nfields such as Generative AI, Agentic AI, Graph ML, ML models for complex temporal\nand multimodal data.\n\n \n\nRole\nPurpose:\n\nAs\nan AI Researcher, you will lead groundbreaking research aligned with Fujitsu's\nAI strategy. Your work will directly influence product innovations and the\ndevelopment of novel AI technologies. Additionally, you will drive scientific\nexploration, publish in top-tier conferences and journals, and secure patents\nfor innovative work. \n\n \n\nRoles\nand Responsibilities - Followings are Researcher’s duties:\n\nTechnical Skills\nrequired-\n\n· Advanced\nAI/ML Expertise: Deep\nunderstanding of fundamentals of theoretical machine learning, statistical\ntheory of learning, AI related topics and concepts, and their practical\nimplementation in various domains. \n\n· Up\nto date with the latest in AI algorithms & neural architectures (e.g.,\nattention, transformers, state-space models, etc.), and their application in discriminative\nand generative models, explainable AI, knowledge\nrepresentation, concept discovery & extraction, agentic systems, reasoning,\netc. Prior experience in applying them to one or more of the following\nareas or related topics: natural language (LLMs), human cognition, computer vision,\ngraphs, agents, multi-modal data analytics, time-series, sequence modelling, complex\ntask completion, dynamic optimization etc. \n\n· Proficient\nin AI/ML Programming: Advanced skills in coding, working with\nAI/ML libraries, and familiar with major AI platforms and tools.\n\n· Strong\npublication track in top-tier conferences such as ICML, ICLR, NeurIPS, AAAI,\nIJCAI, AISTATS, SIGKDD, ACL, NAACL etc. For computer vision domain, publications\nin top CV conferences like CVPR, ICCV, ECCV is expected.\n\n· Desirable: Well-informed\nwith latest conceptual advancements in the deployable AI framework (such as AI agents,\nautonomous systems etc.).\n\n \n\nCore\nResearch Leadership\n\n· Identify\nand Frame Research Problems: Brainstorm with other researchers\nto scope new research projects in specified areas. Identifies critical research\nchallenges and develop innovative solutions by differentiating your approaches\nfrom the current state of the art. \n\n· Develop\nAdvanced Technologies: Design new algorithms, neural architectures,\nand computing methodologies. Implement and validate through theoretical and\nexperimental research.\n\n Conduct\n Rigorous Data Analysis: Collect and analyze data to\n draw inferences, support proposed solutions, and demonstrate their\n practical applications.\n\n \n\n \n\nCollaboration\n& Knowledge Sharing\n\n Share\n key findings with internal leadership, including Project Leaders, Research\n Managers, and Project Directors.\n Research\n Publication & IP: Draft and submit patents.\n Author research papers for submission to prestigious AI/ML/CV/NLP\n conferences and journals.\n Academic\n Partnerships: Engage with academic institutions\n and collaborators, expanding Fujitsu’s network and promoting cutting-edge\n AI research.\n\n \n\nIndustry Impact\nand Application\n\n Engage\n with Applied Research Teams: Collaborate\n closely with applied researchers to transform core scientific discoveries\n into practical solutions. Abstract complex research problems from\n real-world challenges.\n Support\n Technology Transition: Facilitate the transfer of\n research outcomes to business units, demonstrating their value to external\n clients and driving real-world impact.\n\n \n\nAdditional\nExpectations\n\n· Scientific\nLeadership: Strong vision for research and the ability to lead\nscientific projects towards impactful breakthroughs.\n\n· Communication:\nExceptional communication, report writing, and presentation skills, with the\nability to translate complex research into understandable and actionable\ninsights.\n\n· Adaptability\nand Growth Mindset: Willingness to learn new fields, explore\nuncharted territories in AI, and develop cross-disciplinary skill sets.\n\n· \nEducation\n& Research Experience: \n\no Ph.D. in AI, Machine Learning, Computer\nScience, or a related field. Research expertise demonstrated\nthrough publication in top AI and ML conferences. \n\no Exceptional\ncandidates finishing MTech/MS, demonstrated through research work, published or\nsubmitted in top ranked conference, development of novel ideas.",
