			"Position Overview\n\nWe are seeking an exceptional PhD Candidate to join our\ncutting-edge research laboratory focused on advancing the frontiers of\nartificial intelligence and machine learning. This position offers an\nopportunity to conduct ground breaking research in multiple domains of AI, with\nemphasis on developing next-generation solutions for fundamental challenges in\nmodern AI systems.\n\nResearch Areas\n\nThe successful candidate will contribute to research in one\nor more of the following areas:\n\nCore Machine Learning & AI:\n\n Reinforcement\n Learning algorithms and applications\n Large\n Language Models with focus on reasoning capabilities and novel\n architectures beyond standard Transformers\n Kernel\n methods and approaches in machine learning\n World\n models for AI systems\n Graph\n theory and non-Euclidean approaches in machine learning\n\nSecurity & Cryptography:\n\n Cryptography-inspired\n machine learning techniques\n Post-quantum\n security in deep learning systems\n Privacy-preserving\n machine learning methodologies\n\nOptimization & Theory:\n\n Advanced\n optimization theory for machine learning\n Design\n and development of adaptive optimizers for deep learning\n Theoretical\n foundations of learning algorithms\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n Research\n Excellence: Conduct independent, high-impact research that advances\n the state-of-the-art in AI and machine learning\n Innovation:\n Generate novel ideas and approaches to solve fundamental problems in AI\n systems\n Implementation:\n Rapidly prototype and implement theoretical concepts into working systems\n Collaboration:\n Work collaboratively within the research team while maintaining\n independent research directions\n Publication:\n Publish research findings in top-tier conferences and journals\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\nEducational Background\n\n PhD\n in Computer Science, Electrical/Electronics Engineering, Industrial\n Engineering, Operations Research, Mathematics, or closely related fields\n Strong\n academic record with evidence of research excellence\n Publications\n in A* conferences like COLT, NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR will be preferred\n\nTechnical Skills\n\n Programming:\n Expert-level proficiency in Python programming\n Machine\n Learning: Deep understanding of machine learning fundamentals, deep\n learning frameworks (PyTorch, TensorFlow), and modern AI architectures\n Mathematics:\n Strong foundation in linear algebra, calculus, probability theory, and\n optimization\n Implementation:\n Proven ability to translate theoretical concepts into efficient, working\n code\n\nResearch Capabilities\n\n Independent\n Thinking: Demonstrated ability to identify and formulate novel\n research problems\n Innovation:\n Track record of generating creative solutions and next-generation ideas\n Problem-Solving:\n Experience in tackling fundamental challenges in AI/ML systems\n Speed\n of Execution: Ability to rapidly move from conceptualization to\n implementation",
