			"Job\nDescription for Software Developer\n\n \n\nJob Title: Software Developer\n\nRole Purpose\n\n \n\nA result-oriented\nSoftware Developer to develop solutions powered by Fujitsu’s new processor,\nwhich help solve real-world challenges facing society and businesses across\ndifferent industries. As a software developer, you are passionate about\ndeveloping solutions and should be comfortable with back-end coding languages,\ntechnologies, frameworks and third-party/opensource libraries. You will play a\nrole in developing innovative advanced solutions and services to support\nbusiness outcomes.\n\n \n\nResponsibilities\n\n· \nImprove and analyze the performance\nof software applications.\n\n· \nEnable and optimize OSS/ISV AI-based\napplications for Fujitsu’s new processor.\n\n· \nDevelop new algorithms for ML/DL\nframeworks, tuning technologies and work on software based on the proposed approaches\nusing AI framework engineering.\n\n· \nDesigning and developing AI\nworkflows, applications, effective APIs and the system architectures\n\n· \nOptimize\nand scale AI/ML frameworks on HPC architectures (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow, JAX)\n\n· \nDevelop\nperformance tuning strategies using vectorization, threading (OpenMP, TBB), or\nSIMD/SVE.\n\n· \nBenchmark performance and memory usage across AI\nworkloads and Contribute to the development of inference pipelines for\nlarge-scale models (LLMs, GNNs, etc.).\n\n· Improve and analyze performance of Generative AI\n& LLM Models for inferencing and fine tuning. \n\n· \nProvide feedback and patches to OSS communities\n(PyTorch, TensorFlow, ONNX, etc.)\n\n· \nDesign Confidential AI Software SDKs for secure\nplatforms on trusted execution environment using Arm Confidential Computing Architecture\n(CCA)\n\n· \nDevelop and validate Scientific ML models (e.g.,\nPINNs, DeepONets, AI Surrogate models) to approximate solutions for physical\nsystems (PDEs, Multiphysics, etc.)\n\n· \nTroubleshooting, debugging, and\nfixing bugs and upgrading software/applications.\n\n· \nWriting technical documentation\n\n \n\nKey Performance Indicators\n\n· \nNumber of software applications\nenabled and optimized for Fujitsu’s new processor.\n\n· \nNumber of software applications\nwith improved performance\n\n· \nDevelopment of new software\ntechnologies\n\n \n\nExperience\n\nYou will be\nable to demonstrate that you have:\n\n· \nMaster’s. in Computer Science,\nComputational Science, Mathematics & Computing or relevant field.\n\n· \nKnowledge and familiarity with\ncommon stacks for software applications\n\n· \nKnowledge of HPC, AI frameworks, or\nsystems programming\n\n· \nUnderstanding of OSS AI Frameworks and\nperformance optimization techniques\n\n· Proficiency\nwith fundamental back-end server-side languages such as Python, C++, C\n\n· \nPreferred experience in AI\nframework or accelerators, performance tuning & optimization techniques\n\n· \nExperience in software development\nin agile approach\n\n· \nExcellent writing, verbal\ncommunication, and teamwork skills\n\n \n\nPreferred Experience\n\nYou will be\nable to demonstrate that you have:\n\n· Knowledge\nin developing and deploying APIs.\n\n· \nKnowledge of Cloud service (Azure/AWS)\nfeatures such as Functions, VM, Container, DevOps (CI/CD)\n\n· \nGreat skills in evaluating\nperformance and security of software applications and delivering solutions\nwhich are efficient and performant.\n\n· \nHPC and computer architecture\nunderstanding.\n\n· \nSkills in AI-related technologies\n\n· \nContributions to OSS AI or HPC\nprojects.\n\n· \nFamiliarity with CPU architecture\ninternals and AI model deployment.\n\n· \nUnderstanding of numerical\ncomputing, linear algebra libraries, and HPC AI optimization.",
