			"Responsibilities:\n\n \n\nl \nResearch\nand design statistical or ML-based trading models.\n\nl \nAnalyze\nterabytes of historical and real-time Market Data.\n\nl \nBacktest\nand simulate strategies using in-house tools and Infrastructure.\n\nl \nMonitor\nand enhance performance of Live Trading Strategies.\n\nl \nCollaborate\nwith technologists to productionize your research.\n\n \n\nRequirements:\n\n \n\nl \nPossess\na degree in a highly analytical field, such as Engineering, Mathematics,\nComputer Science from IITs schools.\n\nl \nExceptional\nanalytical and problem-solving skills.\n\nl \nProficiency\nin programming, particularly in C++ or python.\n\nl \nA\nworking knowledge of Linux/Unix.\n\nl \nA\ncurious mindset and a passion for understanding complex systems.\n\nl \nPassion\nfor problem-solving, quantitative research, and a curiosity about market\nbehavior.\n\nl \nWe\nvalue mathematical rigor and logical reasoning.\n\nl \nHave a\nstrong work ethic & are hardworking\n\nl \nStrong\ncommunication and interpersonal skills.\n\n \n\nWhat We Offer:\n\n \n\nl \nCompetitive\ncompensation with performance bonuses.\n\nl \nAccess\nto world-class research tools and trading infrastructure.\n\nl \nCollaborative,\nflat-structured, and research-first environment.\n\nl \nHands-on\nmentorship from seasoned Quant Traders and technologists.\n\nl \nOpportunity\nto work on live markets and global trading strategies\n\nl \nRegular\noffsites, learning sessions, and a stocked kitchen.\n\n \n\n.",
