			"Resume filtering | Level 1 Hiring Manager (Technical Round) (1 Hour) | Level 2 Project Manager (Technical Round) (1 Hour) | 5 Days Onsite Trial  (45 Hours) | HR Interview (45 Minutes )",
		details:
			"Job Title: Propellant Research Scientist (PhD) — H₂O₂ & Propellant Chemistry\n \n\nLocation: Navi\nMumbai, India (On-site) \n\nCompany: Manastu\nSpace \n\n \n\nAbout Manastu Space \n\n \n\nWe believe that due to limited resources on the planet,\nthere is a need to look out for an alternative to solve our problems, and that\nanother side is space. This option is viable only if we have low-cost and\nsustainable access to space. Manastu Space is working with the exact vision of\nreducing the cost of access to space. \n\n \n\nWe are a Space Safety and\nLogistics Company, using technology to save the Trillion $ Space industry from\nDebris Pollution in Space. We believe that the problems of Earth can be solved\nusing Space. However, the rapid increase in the number of satellites is also\nincreasing the risk of satellite collision, leading to Debris pollution- making\nspace a dangerous place for other satellites as well as astronauts. To prevent\nthis, we are developing an Agile, Safe, Efficient and Affordable Green\nPropulsion System with a new fuel, engine and catalyst for the engine to avoid\nsatellite collision in space and prevent Debris Pollution, which can hence be a\npotential green alternative to the current monopropellant propulsion\ntechnology. \n\nTo aid us in efficiently performing chemical treatment tasks\non various metallic components of our propulsion system we require people with\nan academic background in chemical engineering (preferably with knowledge in\ncorrosion, chemical treatment of metals) and practical experience in chemical\nand materials laboratories. \n\n \n\n About\nthe Role: \n\n Manastu Space is looking for a PhD-level\nresearcher passionate about hydrogen peroxide (H₂O₂) chemistry and long-term\npropellant stability. You’ll work on improving the molecular and practical\nunderstanding of H₂O₂-based propellant systems for next-gen green propulsion. \n\nWhat You’ll Do: \n\n• Lead\nR&D on H₂O₂ stability, decomposition, and molecular behavior. \n\n• Develop\nstabilization strategies and test formulations for long-term storage in the\nsystem. \n\n• Conduct\ncompatibility and material studies for tanks, seals, and coatings for longer\nstorability. \n\n• Build\nanalytical and experimental workflows. \n\n• Collaborate\nacross chemistry and propulsion teams to translate findings into hardware\nsolutions. \n\nYou Bring: \n\n• \nPhD in Chemistry, Physical Chemistry, Chemical\nEngineering, or related field. \n\n• \nHands-on experience with hydrogen peroxide or\noxidiser chemistry. \n\n• Strong\nbackground in reaction kinetics, thermodynamics, and experimental design. \n\n• \nProven analytical and problem-solving skills;\ndata-driven approach. \n\n• Commitment\nto lab safety and best practices for handling oxidisers. Nice to\nHave: \n\n• \nExperience with propellants, stabilisers, or\nenergetic materials. \n\n• Publications\nor patents related to H₂O₂ or propulsion chemistry. \n\n• Familiarity\nwith rheology, viscosity modifiers, or material compatibility tests. \n\n If you are interested in building your career\nin the field of space or would like to explore options in the same, then this\nwould be the best opportunity to give it a shot at our company. Do contact us\nfor more information.",
