			"Resume filtering | L1 Technical Interview with Hiring Manager (01:00) | L2 Meeting with CTO/CEO (01:00) | One Week Trial Assignment (54:00) | HR Interview",
		details:
			"About Manastu Space \n\nWe believe that due to limited\nresources on the planet, there is a need to look out for an alternative to\nsolve our problems, and that another side is space. This option is viable only\nif we have low-cost and sustainable access to space. \n\nManastu Space is working with the\nexact vision of reducing the cost of access to space. We are a Space Safety and\nLogistics Company, using technology to save the trillion‑dollar space industry from debris pollution in orbit.\nWe believe that the problems of Earth can be solved using space. However, the\nrapid increase in the number of satellites is increasing the risk of\ncollisions, leading to debris pollution — making space dangerous for satellites\nand astronauts. To prevent this, we are developing an Agile, Safe, Efficient\nand Affordable Green Propulsion System with a new fuel, engine and catalyst,\nenabling collision avoidance and preventing debris formation. This is a\npotential green alternative to current monopropellant propulsion technologies. \n\nExtending our sustainability\nmission to Earth, Manastu Space is also investing in Sustainable Aviation Fuel\n(SAF) research to support global decarbonization targets. Our SAF initiatives\nfocus on next‑generation\nthermochemical and biochemical pathways, biomass‑to‑liquid routes, e‑fuels, and technologies that\nadvance clean aviation for the future. \n\nJob Description: Scientist / Junior Scientist –\nSustainable Aviation Fuels (SAF) \n\nLocation: Navi Mumbai, India \n\nEmployment Type: Full-time \n\nFunction: Renewable Energy /\nSustainable Fuels R&D \n\nRole Overview \n\nWe are seeking highly skilled and\nqualified, preferably PhD candidates with strong scientific expertise in\nSustainable Aviation Fuels (SAF) to drive research, innovation, and development\nof next-generation renewable aviation fuels. The ideal candidate will have deep\nknowledge of thermochemical/biochemical conversion pathways, fuel synthesis\nchemistry, gasification, and catalytic processes relevant to SAF production. \n\nKey Responsibilities \n\n1. SAF Technology Research &\nDevelopment \n\n-Conduct advanced R&D in\nsustainable aviation fuels (SAF), including biofuels, synthetic fuels,\ngasification, Fischer–Tropsch (FT), Alcohol-to-Jet (ATJ), Powerto-Liquid (PtL),\nBiomass-to-Liquid (BtL), and related conversion technologies \n\n-Design and develop catalysts for\nSAF pathways, including optimization, evaluation, and performance benchmarking\nto achieve high conversion efficiencies \n\n-Independently plan, design, and\nexecute laboratory experiments, while also coordinating work within\ncross-functional R&D teams. \n\n-Perform simulations, kinetic\nmodelling, and process optimization to understand mechanistic behaviour and\nimprove overall process efficiency. \n\n-Develop catalyst structure–activity\ncorrelations by integrating reaction mechanism insights with characterization\nand performance data. \n\n \n\n2. Process & Pilot\nDevelopment \n\n- \nDesign and develop lab-scale reactors, including\nmicrochannel reactors, and support the design, setup, optimization, and\ncommissioning of pilot-scale processes. \n\n- \nApply principles of heat and mass transfer, fluid\ndynamics, and reaction engineering to ensure efficient reactor performance,\nscale-up reliability, and thermal safety. \n\n- \nTranslate laboratory-scale findings into scalable,\nhigh-efficiency processes, ensuring consistency, reproducibility, and\ncost-effective operations. \n\n- \nAssist in TRL upgrades, preparation of safety dossiers,\nconducting safety evaluations, and implementing risk mitigation measures for\ntechnology development and deployment \n\n \n\n3. Cross-functional Collaboration\n\n- Work\nclosely with technical operations, business, and engineering teams to align\nR&D outcomes with organizational goals. \n\n- Provide\ntechnical insights for technology licensors, collaborators and partners. \n\n- Contribute\nto sustainability analysis including lifecycle assessment (LCA) and GHG\nreduction evaluations. \n\n \n\n4. Technology Scouting &\nBenchmarking \n\n- \nIdentify innovations and opportunities globally in SAF,\ne-fuels, CCUS and emerging clean energy technology. \n\n- \nConduct global benchmarking of technologies, processes,\nand sustainability metrics. \n\n \n\n5. Scientific Communication &\nExternal Collaboration \n\n- Present the findings and\nresearch outcome to the Directors, technical team and advisors \n\n-Publish research findings, draft\npatents and represent the organization at conferences and technical forums. \n\n-Collaborate with universities,\nresearch labs, and SAF focused technology groups. \n\n \n\nCore Competencies & Skills \n\n- \nDeep understanding of SAF technology and catalytic\ncarbon conversion processes, along with their thermochemical and biochemical\nconversion pathways. \n\n- \nExpertise in gasification, sustainable syngas\nproduction and conditioning, FT synthesis, and other related processes \n\n-Hands-on experience with syngas\ngeneration from sustainable and energyefficient pathways. \n\n- \nIn-depth knowledge of heterogeneous catalysis and\nproven experience in catalyst development for high-temperature, thermal\ncatalytic processes. \n\n-Ability to operate high-pressure\nand high-temperature reactors such as fixedbed, microchannel, and fluidized-bed\nsystems. \n\n- \nStrong understanding of heat and mass transfer\nprinciples, including their application in reactor design, catalyst performance\nevaluation, scale-up studies, and optimization of thermochemical conversion\nprocesses. \n\n-Extensive knowledge and hands-on\nexperience with advanced analytical, chromatographic, and spectroscopic\ntechniques for comprehensive characterization of fuels, catalysts, and reaction\nintermediates. \n\n-Knowledge of aviation fuel\nstandards, LCA methodologies, carbon capture, hydrogen integration, and GREET\nmodel analysis \n\n- \nProficiency with simulation, process development,\ndesign and data analysis tools such as Aspen Plus / HYSYS / ChemCAD, Origin Pro\n\n-Excellent technical writing\nskills along with a proven track records of research publication in reputed\njournals and patents publication \n\n \n\nEducational and Experience Requirements \n\n-PhD with 0–2 years of experience, or Master’s degree with 4+\nyears of relevant industrial or research experience. \n\n- Hands-on experience preferably\nin SAF/biofuels/synthetic fuels pathway development, or thermochemical\nconversion, catalysis. \n\n \n\nPersonal Attributes \n\n- Strong\nscientific curiosity, analytical mindset and problem-solving orientation. \n\n- Excellent\ncommunication and stakeholder management skills. \n\n-Ability to balance innovation with practical\ntimelines and thrive in a fast-paced environment.",
