		details:
			"Job Title: Linux Systems Administrator – Tools & HPCLocation: MumbaiJob Type: Onsite - Work from officeAbout Neysa:We're a dynamic startup that believes in making technology work for people, not the other way around. Our mission is to enable seamless online experiences that enhance productivity without compromising on life outside screens. We're building the future of AI computing infrastructure, offering supercomputing-level performance for high-end enterprise solutions.About the Role:We are looking for passionate and motivated fresh graduates to join our team as Entry-Level Linux Systems Administrators. This is an excellent opportunity to begin your career in infrastructure management, automation, and high-performance computing (HPC). You will work alongside experienced professionals to gain hands-on exposure to Linux system administration, cloud provisioning, automation tools, and GPU-based computing environments.Key Responsibilities:· Linux Systems Administrationo Assist in installing, configuring, and maintaining Linux systems (RHEL, CentOS, Ubuntu).o Support system upgrades, patching, kernel tuning, and storage configuration.· Automation & Provisioningo Learn and contribute to infrastructure automation using tools like Ansible, Terraform, and Shell/Python scripting.o Support provisioning of infrastructure using tools such as Foreman, MAAS, or Cobbler.· GPU & HPC Technologieso Understand the basics of GPU architecture.o Assist in installation and configuration of NVIDIA drivers and CUDA toolkit.· Virtualization & Cloud Integrationo Work with virtualization platforms such as KVM and Proxmox.o Gain exposure to cloud environments and integration processes.· Documentation & Reportingo Maintain technical documentation including setup guides, configurations, and architecture diagrams.Required Skills and Qualifications:· Education:B.E./B.Tech in Computer Science, Information Technology, Electronics, or related fields (2024/2025 batch).· Technical Skills:o Basic understanding of Linux OS (command-line, file systems, permissions, etc.).o Exposure to scripting languages like Bash, Python, or Perl.o Familiarity with networking concepts (TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, firewalls).o Enthusiastic to learn tools like Ansible, Terraform, and configuration management platforms.· Soft Skills:o Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.o Good communication and teamwork abilities.o Eagerness to learn and adapt to new technologies.Good to Have (Optional):· Basic understanding or academic exposure to:o HPC job schedulers (Slurm, PBS, etc.).o Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC) principles.o GPU/Parallel Computing concepts.o Virtualization tools or cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, etc.).Training & Onboarding:Selected candidates will undergo comprehensive training and mentorship programs to build core competencies in Linux system administration, automation, and HPC environments.Why Join Us?· Work on cutting-edge technologies in system infrastructure and high-performance computing.· Opportunity to build a strong foundational career in DevOps and cloud automation.· Collaborative environment with mentorship from industry experts.Join us in shaping the future of AI computing! We're building a diverse team of innovators who are passionate about solving complex customer challenges while maintaining work-life harmony.",
