		details:
			"Job Title: AI Security Engineer Company: NeysaLocation: ChennaiRole OverviewWe are looking for an AI Engineer with a deep understanding of machine learning andLLM to join our engineering team. This role is for a candidate who can go beyond theoryand leverage their strong foundation in AI to build, test, and experiment with AI systems.You will work with our security engineers to build the next generation of AI-poweredsecurity products and ensure that artificial intelligence is developed and deployedsafely.Key Responsibilities• Build AI Security Solutions: Collaborate closely with security engineers todesign, build, and implement AI and LLM-driven features for our securityproducts.• Develop and Fine-Tune Models: Take ownership of projects involving thedevelopment, fine-tuning, and evaluation of Large Language Models (LLMs)vulnerabilities.• Build AI Agents: Design and implement the core logic for autonomous AI agents,focusing on their reasoning, planning, and tool-interaction capabilities.• Prototype New Features: Rapidly prototype and iterate on new AI-poweredfeatures, translating cutting-edge research into tangible product functionalities.• Experiment and Evaluate: Conduct and document experiments to rigorouslycompare diNerent model architectures, fine-tuning strategies, and agentdesigns, presenting your findings to the team.Required Qualifications• Currently pursuing a Bachelor’s or Master’s in Computer Science, AI, or a relatedfield.• Strong, demonstrable knowledge of AI/ML fundamentals, including variousmodel architectures, training methodologies, and evaluation metrics.• Hands-on experience with LLMs through academic courses, personal projects,or internships (e.g., fine-tuning a model or building agents).• High proficiency in Python and deep familiarity with major AI/ML libraries likePyTorch or TensorFlow, and Hugging Face.• Knowledge of version control systems (e.g., Git).• Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.Preferred Qualifications• Practical experience building or experimenting with AI agents and agenticworkflows. (e.g., using frameworks like LangChain, LlamaIndex).• Experience with MLOps tools (e.g., MLflow) is a plus.• Knowledge of containerization tools like Docker and Kubernetes.• Experience working with REST APIs.• Strong communication and collaboration skills.",
		info: "Work on the Future of AIDive into next-generation projects that push the boundaries of what’s possible. Each challenge is a springboard for industry-changing breakthroughs.Lead with Your IdeasYour insights matter. We trust you to innovate, solve tough problems, and shape how AI transforms businesses worldwide.Flex Your ScheduleWe respect that life doesn’t run on a strict 9-to-5. Structure your workday to match your personal rhythm while staying true to our commitments.Celebrate Moments That MatterEnjoy extra personal holidays on your birthday or anniversary. Because milestones outside of work deserve to be honored.Family FirstTake 15 working days of paternity leave to bond with your newborn. We’re here to support you during life’s most important transitions.Comprehensive CoverageYour well-being is everything. Our health insurance covers you and your loved ones, giving you peace of mind to focus on what you do best.Rewarding Long-Term CommitmentWe recognize the value of loyalty. Gratuity benefits ensure your dedication is appreciated for yearsTop-Tier ToolsWe outfit you with the latest tech and resources, so you can excel in a fast-moving AI environment.A Culture of CollaborationWith open access to leadership and a team that values every voice, you’ll have the support to innovate, learn, and grow—together.",
