		details:
			"Daksh Limited is a high frequency trading firm specializing in automated market making strategies. We strive to be at the forefront of low latency execution, financial modelling and risk management. We are looking for a smart young individual willing to work in a multi-disciplinary role. The role offers the individual an exciting opportunity to learn about financial markets and cutting-edge technologies and to grow with the company. You will learn about the dynamics of automated trading, market microstructure, modelling and pricing financial derivatives, risk management, and the technical skills needed to implement your ideas. We would expect fresh graduates and candidates with 0-3 years of experience to be a good fit. Primary responsibilities : 1. You will be responsible for delivering and controlling end-to-end product\ndevelopment. a. Work directly with traders who have a deep respect for technology. b. Collect and analyze data. c. Prototype solutions and models in order to confirm validity and\neffectiveness of the proposals. d. Develop, test and back-test production ready solutions 2. You will write code for a. New features b. Latency and stability improvements c. Analyzing huge volume of data d. Implementing and testing new design ideas 3. You will be responsible for managing your time and tasks on development,\nanalysis and experimentation. 4. You will be required to keep a variety of systems and technologies up-to-date and\nimprove them for business operations.Requirements : ● Bachelors, Masters, or PhD in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering,\nComputer Science or related technical field ● Understanding of Computer Architecture ● Knowledge of Algorithms and Data structures\n4. Strong Quantitative skills ● Passion and eagerness to learn● Desire to work in a team ● Ability to work in the competitive and fast-paced work environment Coding/IT Skills:1. Ability to work in a Linux environment 2. Ability to write clean, reliable and highly scalable code 3. Experience of development in C++ 4. Experience with high-transaction, low-latency optimisation 5. Some networking experience\n6. Understanding of CPU architecture 7. Understanding of test-driven and data-driven design 8. We extensively use Python as a tool for data mining, analysis and scripting.\nKnowledge of Python is a plus. 9. We use Javascript as a tool for front-end display for traders. Knowledge of\nJavaScript is a plus. What we offer : ● Learn about the top of the class trading system. ● Quick feedback loop. There is nothing like seeing your ideas/solutions make an impact on business real quick. We release early and often to get incremental benefits as they are developed. ● We operate at the bleeding edge of technology, which keeps us on the toe and always excited about technology shaping our business. ● Opportunity to learn as we really believe in sharing knowledge and technology, helping individuals in their personal growth. ● To see and learn up close how financial markets work. ● Getting to know, learn and share ideas and solutions with other smart people.",
