		process:
			"Resume filtering | Interview 1 (01:00) | Interview 2 (01:00) | HR Round (00:45)",
		details:
			'About Niva Bupa \n\nAt Niva Bupa, our purpose is to give every Indian the confidence to access the best healthcare.\nWe are a certified Great Place to Work, covering more than 22 million lives with a network\nof 10,400+ hospitals. Join us as we empower\nour customers to take\ncontrol of their health and live life to the fullest.\n\n The Opportunity \n\nØ Massive Impact: The code\nyou write will directly influence the health and well-being of millions of\nIndians. This is AI with a purpose.\n\nØ True Full-Stack Ownership: Unlike in larger tech firms, you won’t be a cog in\na wheel. You will see your projects all the way from research to production.\n\nØ The Best of Both Worlds: We offer the innovative, fast-paced culture of a\ntech start-up backed by the stability and resources of a market leaderAbout the AI Lab at Niva Bupa (Part of the BUPA Group)At the AI Lab (part of the larger BUPA\ninternational healthcare group and specifically operating within Niva Bupa\nin India), we are building enterprise-grade Generative AI Agentic Systems\nthat power the core of our health insurance operations. Our mission is to\ntransform claims automation, underwriting intelligence, care journeys, sales\nproductivity, and next-gen customer experiences using deep tech.We are looking for a Full-Stack GenAI Engineer\nwho thrives at the intersection of advanced AI (LLMs, Agentic Systems),\nlarge-scale enterprise systems, and direct business impact. This is a rare\nopportunity to build revenue-impacting, cost-transforming AI engines\nwith visibility straight to the CEO.\n\nWhat You\'ll Own (End-to-End Leadership)You will be the technical heartbeat of AI product builds\ninside the AI Lab—designing, architecting, and shipping high-value\nGenAI-powered agents and platforms that directly move the company’s P&L and\nredefine health insurance in India.1. Generative AI Core Engineering & Agent Orchestration· \nArchitect and deploy multi-agent workflows\nusing modern orchestration frameworks (e.g., LangGraph, LlamaIndex, Bedrock,\nVertex AI, Genie) to solve complex, multi-step business problems.· \nDesign and build Retrieval-Augmented\nGeneration (RAG) systems, customized fine-tuned LLMs, high-performance\nembeddings pipelines, and advanced document intelligence solutions.· \nProductionize LLM-based agents for critical\napplications like: claims validation, pre-authorization, sales advisory, care\nmanagement, and internal AI Copilots.· \nLead the productionization of advanced models,\nincluding transformers, diffusion models, and multi-modal models\n(vision, speech) where needed to tackle specialized health-tech challenges.2. Full-Stack Product Engineering· \nOwn the entire UI → API → Model workflow,\nensuring seamless and high-performance integration from front-end to inference.· \nBuild slick, high-throughput user interfaces\nusing modern frameworks (Next.js/Vercel, React, Streamlit) for both\ncustomer-facing and internal operational tools.· \nDevelop robust, scalable backend\nmicroservices (Python/FastAPI, Node.js/Express) optimized for LLM inference\nand serving large-scale data.· \nEngineer resilient and performant data flows\ninto our gold-layer lakehouse to ensure models are trained and grounded\non the highest quality, most secure data.3. Enterprise-Scale LLMOps & Deployment· \nShip models to production with\nuncompromising stability, using modern MLOps tooling (MLflow, CI/CD, Docker,\nKubernetes).· \nAggressively optimize latency, throughput,\ninference cost, and security for all deployed GenAI and LLM services at\nenterprise scale.· \nCreate comprehensive monitoring and\nobservability frameworks specifically tailored for GenAI challenges,\nincluding real-time tracking of:o Model\nDrift & Data Qualityo Hallucination\nRates & Toxicityo Compliance\n& Guardrail Violationso Agent\nDecision Tracing4. Direct Business Impact EngineeringThe AI you build will fundamentally transform the\nbusiness by:· \nDrastically cutting claims processing time\nfrom days to minutes.· \nCreating predictive models that identify cost\ndrivers & leakage in real time.· \nEnabling agents and partners with\nnext-generation AI Copilots for enhanced productivity.· \nDriving underwriting precision and\ndesigning personalized customer journeys across the BUPA/Niva Bupa ecosystem.\n\nWhat You Bring to the TableWe seek an individual who is both a deep technologist\nand a sharp product thinker.Must-Haves· \nStrong fundamentals in algorithms,\ndistributed systems, and applied Machine Learning/Deep Learning.· \nProven hands-on experience with LLM\norchestration and Agent frameworks (e.g., LangChain/LangGraph, LlamaIndex,\nBedrock/Vertex).· \nFull-stack proficiency with modern tooling: React/Next.js\n(or similar) on the front-end combined with Python/FastAPI (or Node.js)\non the back-end.· \nDemonstrated experience deploying and managing\nAI/ML models (especially LLMs) into real, production-level workloads.· \nAbility to thrive in ambiguous, "0 to\n1" environments where you define the product and the architecture.Preferred :· \nExperience working with multi-modal models\n(vision, speech) relevant to healthcare/insurance documentation.· \nDirect experience fine-tuning LLMs or\ntraining custom small models for domain-specific tasks.· \nExposure to the healthcare, insurance, or\nfinancial services domains.· \nA track record of optimizing LLM inference at\nscale (quantization, compilation, specialized hardware).\n\nWhy Niva Bupa’s AI Lab?This is a playground for engineers who want to shape\nthe future of AI + healthcare—not watch it happen.· \nReal Impact: You will build\nenterprise-grade AI engines that directly touch millions of customers and\nredefine how health insurance runs in India.· \nExecutive Backing: Work with a leadership\nteam that fully understands AI, providing real budgets and high architectural\nautonomy.· \nOwnership: You will receive ownership\nlevels equivalent to an early-stage startup, with the security and scale of the\nlarger BUPA group.Your Career Trajectory\n\nFull-Stack GenAI Engineer → Applied AI Architect →\nAI Lab Lead',
