		details:
			"About the Company:\n\nFractal is one of the most prominent providers of Artificial\nIntelligence to Fortune 500® companies. Fractal's vision is to power every\nhuman decision in the enterprise, and bring AI, engineering, and design to help\nthe world's most admired companies. \n\n \n\nFractal's businesses include Crux\nIntelligence (AI driven business intelligence), Eugenie.ai (AI\nfor sustainability), Asper.ai (AI for revenue growth management)\nand Senseforth.ai (conversational AI for sales and customer service).\nFractal incubated Qure.ai, a leading player in healthcare AI for detecting\nTuberculosis and Lung cancer. \n\n \n\nFractal currently has 5500+ employees across\n16 global locations, including the United States,\nUK, Ukraine, India, Singapore, and Australia. Fractal has\nbeen recognized as 'Great Workplace' and 'India's Best Workplaces for\nWomen' in the top 100 (large) category by The Great Place to\nWork® Institute; featured as a leader in Customer Analytics Service\nProviders Wave™ 2021, Computer Vision Consultancies Wave™ 2020 &\nSpecialized Insights Service Providers Wave™ 2020 by Forrester Research Inc., a\nleader in Analytics & AI Services Specialists Peak Matrix 2022 by Everest\nGroup and recognized as an 'Honorable Vendor' in 2022 Magic Quadrant™\nfor data & analytics by Gartner Inc. For more information,\nvisit fractal.ai\n\n \n\nAbout the team\n\n \n\nFractal’s businesses have been involved\nin multiple areas of A.I. research for the past several years and we have\nrecently setup a A.I. Research Lab to focus on the most important\nproblems in A.I. The A.I. Research Lab has worked extensively on the Foundation\nModel /GenAI ecosystem across a wide variety of areas. The team has helped build in-house foundation\n(diffusion) models, has extensively worked on Large Language Model innovations and\nhas built various aspects of Agentic systems that can lead to AGI. The team has\naccess to inhouse GPU-cluster farm along with cloud GPU resources for solving\ncomplex A.I. problems. \n\n \n\nThe A.I. Research Lab will focus on\nfoundational aspects of A.I. research that push the boundaries of what is\npossible and move us towards a world with safe and effective AGI.\n\n \n\nFractal’s A.I. Research team has\nregularly published in top-tier A.I. conferences like NeurIPS, ICLR, AAAI, ICIP\nand others and has been involved in releasing multiple B2C AI products like\nkalaido.ai , Vaidya.ai and marshalgoldsmith.ai. The team has won prestigious\nawards at A.I competitions like HackerCup and AIMO and has also open-sourced\ntrending on Huggingface models with the Fathom model series.\n\n \n\nFractal’s A.I Research team was recently\nselected for the “India AI Mission” to help build reasoning and healthcare\nbased models for India.\n\n \n\nJob\nOverview:\n\n \n\nWe\nare looking for people who can explore new ideas, design and implement\nnext-generation architectures/techniques in image/video, language, audio and\nmultimodal space. You should be motivated to push the boundaries not just in\nstate-of-the-art performance, but also in balancing performance in terms of\ninference speed and compute resource usage. You will collaborate with a\nmultidisciplinary team of researchers, engineers, and data scientists to\ndevelop and deploy practical and scalable solutions to real-world challenges in\nareas such as domain based instruction fine-tuning LLMs, improving text to\nimage and foundational models, building multi-modal foundation models,\nresearching agentic ecosystems to name a few. Your work will have a direct\nimpact on the development of our AI-driven products and services.\n\n \n\nResponsibilities:\n\n· \nImplement\nefficient data pipelines for preprocessing large datasets, including data\naugmentation, tokenization, and distributed training.\n\n· \nCollaborate\non research-to-production transitions, ensuring models are scalable and\nmaintainable in production environments.\n\n· \nBuild A.I. Engineering pipelines for scaling A.I. models to internet\nscale\n\n· \nIntegrate\nAI models into full-stack architectures, including database management\n(SQL/NoSQL like PostgreSQL, MongoDB) for storing user data, model outputs, and\nfeedback loops.\n\n· \nImplement\nCI/CD pipelines for automated testing, deployment, and monitoring of AI-infused\napplications using tools like Jenkins, GitHub Actions, or Kubernetes.\n\n· \nBuild\nbackend services using frameworks like FastAPI, Flask, or Django to expose AI\nmodels via APIs, handling authentication, rate limiting, and error handling.\n\n· \nDevelop\nfrontend interfaces with modern JavaScript frameworks (e.g., React, Vue.js) to\ncreate interactive applications that leverage AI outputs, such as real-time\nchatbots or recommendation systems.\n\n· \nCollaborate with engineering and business\nteams on model deployment and customised training respectively.\n\n \n\nGood\nto Have: \n\n \n\n· \nProficiency in Python (required); experience with\nC++ or Julia for performance-critical components is a plus. \n\n· \nDeep hands-on experience with deep learning\nframeworks: PyTorch (preferred) or TensorFlow/Keras.\n\n· \nFamiliarity\nwith distributed computing tools like Ray, Dask, or Horovod for training on\nmulti-GPU/TPU setups.\n\n· \nAbility to efficiently work on a modern deep\nlearning stack, such as Python, PyTorch, and GPU-enabled compute, eg writing\nnon-trivial custom architecture in Pytorch.\n\n· \nAbility to iterate quickly on open-source\ncode-bases with attention to backwards compatibility, usability, and\nreadability. \n\n· \nCreative, fast-paced executor, detail-oriented,\neager to learn, acquire new skills. \n\n· \nAbility to work effectively in a collaborative\nteam environment and take ownership.\n\n· \nStrong belief in a positive-sum game, valuing\ncooperation and collaboration over zero-sum competition.\n\n \n\nEligibility:\n\n Education: B.tech\n only \n\n Stream: Circuit\n Branch \n\n \n\nPerks\n& Benefits: \n\n· Insurance Benefits, Relocation Benefits,\nGratuity over & above CTC, Employee Assistance Wellness Workshops, Learning & Growth\nOpportunities\n\n· Hybrid Work Environment \n\n· Shuttle & Cab services to office\n(select locations only) \n\n· Unlimited free breakfast, lunch &\nsnacks across our offices \n\n \n\n \n\nJob\nlocation: Mumbai\n\n \n\nJoining:\nJuly\n’26",
