		details:
			"About the Company:Fractal is one of the most prominent providers of Artificial Intelligence to Fortune\n500® companies. Fractal's vision is to power every human decision in the enterprise, and\nbring AI, engineering, and design to help the world's most admired companies.Fractal's businesses include Crux Intelligence (AI driven business intelligence), Eugenie.ai (AI\nfor sustainability), Asper.ai (AI for revenue growth management)\nand Senseforth.ai (conversational AI for sales and customer service). Fractal\nincubated Qure.ai, a leading player in healthcare AI for detecting Tuberculosis and Lung\ncancer.Fractal currently has 5500+ employees across 16 global locations, including the United States,\nUK, Ukraine, India, Singapore, and Australia. Fractal has been recognized as 'Great Workplace'\nand 'India's Best Workplaces for Women' in the top 100 (large) category by The Great Place to\nWork® Institute; featured as a leader in Customer Analytics Service Providers Wave™ 2021,\nComputer Vision Consultancies Wave™ 2020 & Specialized Insights Service Providers Wave™\n2020 by Forrester Research Inc., a leader in Analytics & AI Services Specialists Peak Matrix\n2022 by Everest Group and recognized as an 'Honorable Vendor' in 2022 Magic Quadrant™ for\ndata & analytics by Gartner Inc. For more information, visit fractal.ai About The Team At Fractal, engineers do not just write code, they build intelligence. They design systems that\nlearn, reason, and act; systems that enable the next wave of Agentic and Generative AI for\nglobal enterprises. As an Engineer in our AI Platforms and Solutions team, you will build core AI infrastructure,\nmodel orchestration layers, and agent frameworks that power Fractal’s decision-intelligence\necosystem. Your work will go beyond products you will help create an ecosystem of selflearning agents, scalable data systems, and intelligent experiences that reshape how\nbusinesses think, decide, and act. You’ll collaborate with Fractal’s AI researchers, product engineers, and FDE teams to translate\ncutting-edge AI research into production-grade platforms such as our flagship Cogentiq. You\nwill work on systems that operationalize reasoning, autonomy, and intelligence at scale,\nimpacting millions of lives indirectly through our clients.What You Will Do • Design, develop, test, and scale core AI components, services, and infrastructure\nforming the backbone of Fractal’s platforms and agent ecosystems. • Engineer integrations between large language models (LLMs), reasoning engines, and\ndecision systems. • Implement scalable microservices for agentic orchestration, context management, and\nautonomous task execution. • Collaborate across AI research, product, platform, and FDE teams to move from AI\nconcept to enterprise deployment, translating papers to production. • Contribute to AI platform innovation, including observability, multi-agent\ncoordination, memory architectures, and AI workflow automation. • Participate in AI innovation sprints and hackathons to build prototypes around\nreasoning, tool use, and autonomous collaboration between agents. • Review and optimize code, focusing on performance, scalability, and maintainability in\nhigh-load distributed environments. What You Bring • Strong programming skills in one or more languages : Python, C++, Java, or Go with a\nfocus on clean, efficient, and scalable code. • Deep understanding of data structures, algorithms, OS fundamentals, and\ndistributed systems. • Demonstrated curiosity about AI/ML, Generative AI, and agentic system design • Strong foundation in machine learning, LLMs, deep learning architectures,\nreinforcement learning, or NLP pipelines. • Experience with cloud-native AI systems (GCP, AWS, Azure), container orchestration\n(Kubernetes), and distributed compute frameworks (Ray, Spark, etc.). • Familiarity with LLM fine tuning, Reasoning model tuning, vector databases,\nembeddings, RAG systems, and multi-agent orchestration. • Passion for solving open-ended AI engineering problems: reasoning, planning, and\nhuman-machine collaboration. • Ability to join full-time in 2025. Eligibility: • Education: B.tech in Computer Science, AI, or related engineering field • Stream: Circuit Branch\nPerks & Benefits: • Insurance Benefits, Relocation Benefits, Gratuity over & above CTC, Employee\nAssistance Wellness Workshops, Learning & Growth Opportunities • Hybrid Work Environment\n• Shuttle & Cab services to office (select locations only)\n• Unlimited free breakfast, lunch & snacks across our offices Job location: Mumbai, GGN, Bangalore Joining: Jun/July ’26",
