		details:
			"You will be working with Business Intelligence and Data Analytics (BIDA) team that is dedicated to improving primary healthcare delivery through technology in India. As a Business System Analyst, you will play a crucial role at the intersection of healthtech and public health, helping shape digital visualization tools that improve access, efficiency, and effectiveness in healthcare service delivery.Key Responsibilities:•Act as a bridge between product, technology, and implementation teams•Gather, analyze, and document business and system requirements with a focus on data driven decision making.•Translate public health needs into functional and technical specifications for data models, dashboards, and reports.•Work closely with stakeholders to define user stories, workflows, and system improvements.•Conduct user acceptance testing (UAT) and ensure alignment with end-user needs•Identify and suggest enhancements to improve platform usability and adoption•Support deployment, training, and feedback collection from field implementationsQualifications & Experience:•Education: Bachelor’s or master’s degree in Public Health, Computer Science, Information Systems, or related field•Experience: 0 - 3 years of experience as a BSA or in a similar role, preferably in health tech or edtech or the development or the Data Science sector•Experience working on data analytics initiatives or with public health or public education programs is highly desirable.Key Skills & Competencies:•Strong analytical, critical thinking, and problem-solving skills•Experience in requirement gathering, documentation, and process mapping•Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to work with diverse teams•Hands-on familiarity with Agile methodologies, data visualization tools, Dashboards, and wireframing tools•Understanding of public health systems and government healthcare initiatives in India is an advantage•Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, collaborative, and mission-driven environment",
