		details:
			'We are looking for a skilled AI\nEngineer to design, development and deployment of AI-driven components for\nthe Data-to-Action (D2A) Framework enhancing the DRISHTI and\nSSK health platforms. This is a hands-on technical role requiring\ndeep involvement in coding, model training, and system integration to transform\nDRISHTI+SSK into a proactive health governance tool. Key\nRoles/Responsibilities: \n\n Develop Predictive AI Models:\n \n Build ML\n models for ANC coverage forecasting, disease outbreak\n alerts (e.g., measles via OPD NLP), and fund utilization\n optimization.\n Retrain\n models monthly using new district health data.\n \n Deploy Automated Decision-Support Systems:\n \n Engineer rule-based\n alerts (e.g., "ANC1 < 60% → trigger ASHA\n retraining") integrated into governance dashboards.\n Design real-time\n anomaly detectors for data quality validation (e.g.,\n institutional delivery drops).\n \n Data Triangulation & Validation:\n \n Create\n engines to cross-verify health metrics (e.g., CS rates\n vs. drug stocks) and auto-generate field verification tasks.\n \n API Integration & Scalability:\n \n Establish\n APIs to merge data from Nikshay (TB), POSHAN Tracker (nutrition),\n and supply-chain portals and other health portals.\n Ensure\n seamless deployment across all districts of a state post-pilot.\n \n Documentation & Compliance:\n \n Maintain model performance logs and adhere\n to government data security protocols\n \n\nEssential Experience:· 0-3 yrs of experience in designing,\ntraining, and deploying production-grade AI/ML models.· End-to-end\nAI development (coding → deployment).· Proven\nexperience in healthcare analytics, public health data, or government health\nsystems (e.g., HMIS, Nikshay, NFHS).· Cloud-based ML pipelines (AWS SageMaker/Azure ML)· \nHands-on work with real-time data pipelines, API integrations, and cloud-based AI\ndeployment.Essential Skills:\n\n AI/ML Development:\n \n Proficiency in Python, TensorFlow/PyTorch, scikit-learn.\n Experience in time-series forecasting (e.g., ANC\n coverage predictions) and NLP (e.g., OPD symptom\n clustering).\n \n Data Engineering:\n \n Building real-time anomaly detection systems (±2SD\n outlier flags, cross-validation with GPS/drug stock logs).\n ETL pipelines, data validation\n frameworks, and cloud-based model training (AWS\n SageMaker/Azure ML).\n \n Deployment & Integration:\n \n API-driven integration with health platforms\n (DRISHTI/SSK), HMIS, and supply-chain systems.\n Containerization (Docker) and MLOps for model retraining\n workflows.\n Optimize models for\n low-bandwidth district environments.\n \n\n· \nMaintenance & Validation\n\n \n Monthly model retraining + performance logs.\n Design IVR/field surveys to ground-truth\n AI outputs.\n \n\nAnalytical\n& Soft Skills\n\n Ability to translate health KPIs (ANC coverage, fund utilization)\n into rule-based alert systems.\n Experience in ground-truthing data via\n triangulation (e.g., reconciling CS rates with drug stocks/blood banks).',
