		details:
			"Position OverviewA Program Leader in Central Talent Team will be responsible for developing products, tools and strategy for HR transformation within the organization leading to high-performance through leadership development of staff. The work involves working closely with the organization’s leadership team and will help build capabilities of the Program Leader in designing and implementing products and processes for systemic change within organizations while collaborating with different functions staff and external stakeholders. This position reports to Program Manager- Central TeamPrimary Responsibilities:•Lead the ideation and development of concepts and implementation strategies for organizational HR transformation initiatives.•Support organization’s leadership team in embedding HR transformation initiatives within their big bets•Design and execute comprehensive change management strategies to support successful implementation of key transformation projects.•Establish governance mechanisms and tools to ensure long-term success and ownership of transformation initiatives.•Create clear, targeted communication materials to support change initiatives and ensure alignment across leadership and staff.•Design, implement, and continuously improve the organization’s performance management framework to drive accountability and growth.Required Attributes:•Ability to learn-unlearn-relearn at speed, think analytically and solve problems•Ability to collaborate with and a diverse set of stakeholders•Ability to make effective use of business communication software (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook)•Ability to manage high level of stress and highly ambiguous environmentsEssential Skills and Experiences:•Master's degree in a relevant field, such as Talent Management, Organization Development•1 to 3 years of experience in talent management, talent consulting, or organizational development.•Strong critical thinking and problem-solving skills to analyse complex talent challenges and develop solutions.•Data-driven and analytical mindset, leveraging data to drive decision-making.",
		info: "Comfortable to travel 10-12 days in\na month.\n\n \n\n1. Group Life Term\nInsurance GLTI, covers self\n\n2. Group Personal Accident\nGPA, covers self\n\n3. Group Medical Coverage GMC, this\ncovers dependents): For those who are unmarried self along with parents and for\nthose who are married self, spouse, two children and either of the parents)\n\n4. Gratuity As per the law",
