			"Resume filtering | Group discussion (30mins) | Shark Tank (Case presentation) | Personal interview (30mins each student)",
		details:
			"About the Program – qFly Tech The qFly Tech Leadership Program is a flagship initiative designed to identify, nurture, and accelerate the\ngrowth of high-potential business leaders from top-tier BTech institutes Over a structured 3-year\njourney, selected candidates will undergo cross-functional stints, gain exposure to strategic decisionmaking, and eventually transition into front-end leadership roles—with a clear path toward CXO and\nCEO positions. What You’ll Do As an Applied AI engineer, you will work closely with our pre- and post-sales Customer Experience team by\ndeveloping solutions over the core platform via applications written in TypeScript, JavaScript, Python etc.\nYou will be expected to employ your creativity and expertise to ideate and shape how AI, analytics and\nworkflows are used in customers' processes. Objectives for this role will include: ● Design, develop and implement integrations, automations and customizations to integrate QK offerings\nwith customers’ tech stack and workflows, and ensure successful customer engagements. ● Utilize AI in novel ways to solve customer problems, including Generative AI techniques like prompt\nengineering for foundation large language models (LLMs) to enable great AI agent experience.● Work on semantic search engine fine-tuning for better search accuracy. ● Conduct data analysis, write SQL queries, and build dashboards to share insights and drive decisionmaking.\n● Be proactive in communicating and keeping constant feedback loops to all key stakeholders incl.\nCustomers, Engineering, Product, Customer Success & Support, Revenue, Marketing. ● Learn new tools and guide customers through critical workflows, e.g. integration with code repositories ● Build Snap-ins, workflows, AirSync and AI Agents. Ideal Candidate Qualifications: ● Software engineering degree or equivalent educational or professional experience. ● Hands-on coding experience using TypeScript/JavaScript, Python, APIs, Webhooks, SQL. ● Familiarity with Generative AI technologies including models like GPT-4, prompt engineering and finetuning.\n● Knowledge of vector databases and data embeddings. ● Outstanding communication (written and verbal in English). ● Result-oriented work style, ability to get things done and a learning mindset. ● An endless passion for challenging work that requires high energy, full engagement and a self-founded\nneed for high performance. Eligibility Criteria • 70%+ marks across Class X, XII, UG • Strong analytical, leadership, and communication skills. • Passion for technology, innovation, and business building. • Willingness to relocate and take on diverse challenges. What We Offer • Fast-track career path to CXO roles. (It’s repetitive, so can be deleted) • Direct exposure to board-level strategy and decision-making. • Mentorship from industry veterans and senior executives. • Competitive compensation and performance-linked incentives. • A dynamic, entrepreneurial culture with global opportunities.",
		info: '16LPA\n (Fixed) upto 3 yrs (36 months). \n 36+ months - additional 1 LPA ( 17LPA)\n 48+ months and above - (18LPA)\n Additional one time "MILESTONE BONUS" of Rs. 6,00,000 on\n completion of 3 years.',
