		details:
			"About the Program – qFly The qFly Leadership Programis a flagship initiative designed to identify, nurture, and accelerate the growth of\nhigh-potential business leaders from top-tier BTech/MBA institutions. Over a structured 3-year journey,\nselected candidates will undergo cross-functional stints, gain exposure to strategic decision-making, and\neventually transition into front-end leadership roles—with a clear path toward CXO and CEO positions. Key Responsibilities During the program, associates will: • Rotate across critical business functions including Strategy, Sales, Product, Delivery, Finance, R&D,\nPartnerships and Operations. • Work directly with senior leadership on high-impact projects. • Lead initiatives in digital transformation, client engagement, and market expansion. • Analyze business performance and contribute to growth strategies.• Drive innovation and operational excellence across teams. • Prepare for P&L ownership and customer-facing leadership roles post-program.\nwww.qualitykiosk.com Program Structure • Year 1: Functional rotations with mentorship from business heads. • Year 2: Strategic assignments and leadership shadowing. • Year 3: Ownership of a business vertical or geography. • Post-Program: Transition into a senior front-end role (e.g., Business Unit Head, Country Manager). Eligibility Criteria • 70%+ marks across Class X, XII and 6 CPI and above for UG and PG. • For MBA - Preferably 2 years pre-MBA relevant experience in Technology or Sales. • Strong analytical, leadership, and communication skills. • Passion for technology, innovation, and business building. • Willingness to relocate and take on diverse challenges. What We Offer • Fast-track career path to CXO roles. (It’s repetitive, so can be deleted) • Direct exposure to board-level strategy and decision-making. • Mentorship from industry veterans and senior executives. • Competitive compensation and performance-linked incentives. • A dynamic, entrepreneurial culture with global opportunities.",
