		details:
			"About\nthe Role:You will\njoin our core Research & Product Development Group to build\nnext-generation platforms at the intersection of:\n\n· \nGraph\nAlgorithms & Entity Resolution\n\n· \nOntology\n& Knowledge Representation\n\n· \nDeterministic\n+ Neural Hybrid Architectures\n\n· \nSymbolic\nReasoning + Machine Learning\n\n· \nLarge-scale\nContextual Intelligence Systems\n\nThis is a research-driven product development\nrole, contributing directly to the architecture and algorithms powering our\nDecision Intelligence Platform.Key\nResponsibilities:\n\n· \nDesign\nlarge-scale graph processing and entity-resolution algorithms\n\n· \nBuild\nsemantic/ontology-driven knowledge graph architectures\n\n· \nDevelop\nhybrid symbolic–neural reasoning modules\n\n· \nImplement\ngraph embeddings, GNNs, and representation learning components\n\n· \nWork\nwith large datasets (billions of nodes/edges)\n\n· \nCollaborate\nwith SDE teams to productize R&D outputs\n\n· \nWrite\ninternal technical papers and contribute to publishable researchQualifying\nCriteria:· \nB.Tech from IITs or equivalent top-tier institutions\n\n· \nMinimum CGPA 9.0 OR Top 10% department ranking· \nStrong\nfundamentals in Algorithms, ML/DL, Graph Theory, Probability, NLP or IR· \nOne\nor more of:o Research paper (AAAI, ICML, ICLR,\nNeurIPS, KDD, etc.)o Significant undergraduate research\nproject in graph/ML/IR/NLPo Strong Open-Source contributions\n\no High performance in coding/algorithm\ncompetitionsWhy\nJoin Us?· \nWork\non cutting-edge applied research in graph intelligence &\nsymbolic–neural systems· \nBuild\nfoundational algorithms for our next-gen platform· \nPublication-friendly\nenvironment\n\n· \nFast-paced,\nhigh-talent engineering & research culture",
