		details:
			"As a full-time AUT at ITC, you will play a key\nrole in managing and improving production and engineering operations across\nparameters like cost, quality, technology, productivity, and safety. The role\nmay be factory-based, focusing on areas such as production, maintenance,\nquality and process optimization or involve supply chain and production\nplanning. Depending on the assignment, you could be working on improving plant\nperformance, driving process-improvement or digital-transformation projects,\noptimizing manpower productivity, or planning and executing new factory setups\nand upgrades to existing ones. The role offers opportunities to work with\nadvanced technologies, collaborate with teams across functions\n(techno-managerial role) and engage with agencies/vendors - all while ensuring\nsafety, efficiency, and continuous improvement in operations. This role also\ninvites you to supervise and lead teams comprising of employees, participate\nand represent in collective bargaining and grievance handling, if posted in\nfactories.",
