		details:
			"Job Profile for - B.E/B.Tech- Electrical 1. R&D Vertical Core Technical Skills: - Strong theoretical knowledge of Classical and Modern Control Theory\nlike stability analysis, transfer functions, state-space representation.- Proficiency in MATLAB and Simulink for modelling, simulation, and \ncontrol system design. Calculation of loss in power diodes, Thermal calculation of all power \ncomponents - Preliminary knowledge of a programming language, preferably “C”.- Basic understanding of microcontrollers, microprocessors, and Real Time Operating Systems (RTOS)2. Marine VerticalA strong candidate to handle Marine Marketing and to increase the market share of Medium Engine business.3. Railways Vertical• Sales Engineer• Support to Zonal Manager• Lead Generation• Tender study & preparing quote• Customer Retention3. QualityResponsible for managing customer-reported product issues and driving timely resolution using structured methods such as Fault Tree Analysis (FTA) and the 7-Step problem-solving process. Ensures effective diagnostics, root cause identification, and corrective actions to improve product reliability and customer satisfaction.Job Profile for - B.E/B.Tech Mechanical1. R&D VerticalYou will be assigned to a specific team (e.g., R&D, Simulation, Testing, or \nDesign) and will be responsible for:- Advanced Simulation & Analysis: Performing complex computational fluid dynamics (CFD) analysis \nof in-cylinder combustion, intake/exhaust systems, or after-treatment systems (e.g., SCR, DPF). - Component Design & FEA: Using CAD (like SOLIDWORKS, Creo, or CATIA) and FEA (like \nANSYS or Abaqus) tools to design and analyze the structural integrity and thermal stresses of critical \nengine components (e.g., pistons, cylinder heads, turbochargers). - Performance & Emissions Testing: Assisting in setting up and conducting detailed experiments on \nengine test beds. You will be responsible for analyzing performance, combustion, and emissions data \nusing tools like MATLAB, Python, or specialized engine software (e.g., AVL PUMA, ETAS INCA). - Thermodynamic Modeling: Developing or refining 1D engine simulation models (using tools like \nGT-SUITE or Ricardo WAVE) to predict performance, optimize engine calibration, or evaluate new \nhardware concepts.- Research & Development: Supporting R&D projects focused on future technologies, such as \nalternative fuels (e.g., H2-ICE, biofuels), waste heat recovery, or advanced emission control strategies.- Documentation: Preparing detailed technical reports, analysis summaries, and presenting your \nfindings to the engineering team and management. 2. Defense VerticalResponsible for executing all marketing activities for the Defense vertical of Industrial Business. Conduct execution of all activities such as enquiry generation, preparation of responses, customer communication and finalization of tender.3. Marine VerticalA strong candidate to handle Marine Marketing and to increase the market share of Medium Engine business.4. Construction & Mining VerticalRole 1• Should handle new enquires both application wise and new OEM's and convert leads to sales.• Scout new business opportunities along with Account managers.• Co-ordinations with Customers and Internal stakeholders and should be able to converts leads to actual business.Role 2• Liason with Customer and Internal stakeholder to facilitate new products.• Desk and on field customer visits to conduct research and help frame and execute product strategy.• Coordinate new product development and identify growth potentials and do deep dive in potential growth areas.5. Railway Vertical• Sales Engineer• Support to ZM• Lead Generation• Tender study & preparing quote• Customer Retention3. Quality- Responsible for managing customer-reported product issues and driving timely resolution using structured methods such as Fault Tree Analysis (FTA) and the 7-Step problem-solving process. - Ensures effective diagnostics, root cause identification, and corrective actions to improve product reliability and customer satisfaction.",
