		details:
			"A Candidates will be working on: Structural and thermal simulations using FEA tools. Performing advanced analyses, including: Static and transient analyses for structural and thermal problems. Advanced nonlinear analyses, including geometric, material, and contact nonlinearities. Buckling analysis to evaluate stability under compressive loads. Vibration and fatigue analysis to predict component lifespan under cyclic loading. Modal and harmonic analysis to assess natural frequencies and dynamic response. Preparing and optimizing meshes suitable for high-accuracy simulations. Geometry cleanup and creation for simulation purposes using generic CAD tools.B CFD Analysis: Candidates will work on fluid flow and heat transfer simulations using TCAE software. Perform steady-state and transient CFD analyses for simple systems. Optimize designs based on flow behavior and thermal performance. Post-process CFD results to extract insights such as pressure drops, velocity profiles, and temperature distribution.C Equipment and Machine Design: Candidates will be working on the design of static equipment, such as high-pressure vessels, reactors, agitators, and heat exchangers. Candidates will coordinate with end customers to provide engineering and technical solutions, perform relevant calculations, and create detailed reports and presentations.D Programming and Process Automation: Candidates will be working on writing subroutines in C, Python, or other programming languages to enhance workflows and improve efficiency.E Problem-Solving and Validation: Candidates will be working on hand calculations to validate simulation results. Applying general engineering principles to ensure accurate and reliable solutions.Additional OpportunitiesTravel Opportunities:Candidates may have the chance to travel outside India for presentations and client meetings. A valid passport is therefore preferred.",
