		details:
			"Overview:\n\nTritorc\nis a front runner EPC Company with a global client base ranging from the\nAmericas to the Far East with several branches in the US, the Middle East, South Asia and APAC region. Be at the tip\nof the spear in the world of\ndesigning and developing tools and equipment for the MRO industry. A leader in\nthe bolting and onsite machining industry, Tritorc with a three-decade legacy\nof transformative growth and innovations, now seeks to step up to the next\nlevel. If meticulous preparation and attention to detail with data- driven\ndecisions are your forte, then this position is likely a choice that shall suit\nyour growth as a career professional. \n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nYou are required to display the following traits:\n\nStrategic Leadership: Develop and execute\nthe company's R&D\nstrategy, aligning it with the organization's overall business goals and objectives.\n\nAlong with the basics\nsuch as:\n\n- \nPlanning and Budgeting R&D activities\n\n- Precision machining and programming knowledge.\n\n- Heat Treatment &\nAlloy Steel knowledge\n\n- Monitor team metrics\nand objectives ensuring\nthe meeting of goals\n\n- \nDocument all phases of research and development and Build\nprototypes and testing both in-house\nand on-site.\n\n- Research into identifying materials or solution requirements.\n\n- \nMarket Research and Cost Optimization.\n\n- \nReview existing designs and\ndrive continuous development to improve product quality, performance, and\nreliability.\n\nAdditionally, the R&D Engineer\nshall\n\n- Establish project goals and priorities by collaborating with\nMarketing and Operations.\n\n- Transfer new technologies, products, and manufacturing processes into and out - the company.\n\n- \nDevelop concepts, products, and solutions by coordinating with business units.\nDrive the development of new industrial\ntools and equipment, from concept to commercialization, ensuring they meet or\nexceed industry standards and customer requirements.\n\n- \nResearch, design,\nand evaluate materials, assemblies, processes, and equipment. Stay updated on emerging\ntechnologies, trends, and advancements in the industrial equipment sector and\nevaluate their potential for integration into Tritorc's product portfolio.\n\n-The R&D\nEngineer shall lead development activities to create\nand continually improve new products and processes\nincluding the ones for manufacturing with an adherence to the company\nculture that values,\nconscientious people, you\nshall also ensure.\n\n-Protect the company’s innovations by filing patents and\nstrengthening the IP portfolio.\n\n-Ensure new products carry clear unique selling points (USPs) that\ngive Tritorc a competitive edge in the market.\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nRegulatory Compliance: Ensure\nthat all R&D\nactivities comply with relevant industry\nstandards, regulations, and safety requirements.\n\nCost Management: Optimize\nR&D expenses while\nmaintaining high-quality research\nand product development efforts.\n\nAll of these activities shall be\nfocussed on delivering an\nexperience to the customer that is\nbased on understanding customer expectations on to-be manufactured products.\n\n \n\nRequired Skills & Experience:\n\n- Bachelor's or Master's degree in Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or a related field.\n\n- Minimum of 5 years of experience in research and development, with at least 3 years\nin a leadership role.\n\n- Proven track record\nof successfully launching new products in the industrial equipment sector.\n\n- \nStrong project management skills\nand the ability to lead cross-functional teams.\n\n- \nExcellent problem-solving and analytical skills.\n\n- Knowledge of relevant industry standards and regulations.\n\n- Familiarity with intellectual property management.\n\n- Experience in handling patents and intellectual property, along with\ncreating product USPs.\n\n- Exceptional communication and leadership skills.\n\n- \nInnovative thinker\nwith a passion for staying\nahead of technology trends.\n\n \n\n \n\nWhat we offer:\n\n- Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses.\n\n- Opportunity to lead and shape the future of R&D\nat Tritorc Equipments.\n\n- \nA collaborative and innovative work environment.\n\n- Professional development opportunities and ongoing training.\n\n- \nComprehensive benefits package, including health insurance and retirement plans.\n\n- Access to cutting-edge technology and resources.\n\n- \nWork for a company\ncommitted to sustainability and ethical business\npractices.\n\nIf\nyou are a visionary leader with a passion for innovation, patents, and building\nstrong USPs, we invite you to apply for the position of Research and\nDevelopment Engineer at Tritorc Equipments.\n\nJoin our team and be a part of our\njourney to redefine excellence in the industry.",
