		details:
			"This is a pioneering\nopportunity to become a part of Micron's world-class team as a TAIWAN CENTRAL\nPROBE SUPERVISOR. In this role, you will directly contribute to advancing our\npowerful technology and meticulously crafted processes, ensuring flawless execution\nas we compete in the global market. Your ambition and proven skills will be\ncrucial to our success.\n\nKey Responsibilities:Manufacturing Operations Management: Monitor real-time production, establish\nand execute standard operating procedures, and drive continuous improvement. Coordinate cross-functional resources to ensure smooth production and on-time\ndelivery. Lead capacity planning and optimization initiatives to enhance\nefficiency and overall performance.\nProcess and Solution Development: Design and implement manufacturing execution\nsolutions to improve operational workflows and productivity.RequirementsEducation: Master’s degree in Management, Statistics, or a related field, or\nequivalent experience.\nWorkplace & Shift Arrangement: This role is located in Tainan, Taiwan. Applicants should be prepared to\naccommodate a rotating schedule that includes both day and night shifts.\nCommunication and Management Skills: Demonstrated ability to clearly convey\nobjectives and strategies, effectively coordinate internal and external\nstakeholders, and foster cross-functional collaboration.\nTechnical and Analytical Skills: Proficiency in data analysis tools such as\nExcel and Tableau, with the ability to transform raw data into actionable\ninsights to support production and operational planning.\nProblem-Solving: Strong capability to address challenges and deliver innovative\nsolutions.\nLeadership: Ability to build high-performing teams, create an inclusive and\ncollaborative work environment, and drive talent development for organizational\ngrowth.\nJoin us in Taiwan to be a part of an ambitious team that is determined to make\na significant impact in the industry. Your expertise will drive us toward\nachieving our goals of excellence and innovation.",
