			"Resume filtering | Technical interview (00:30) | Personal interview (00:30)",
		details:
			"As a Metrology Application Engineer at Micron Technology,\nyou will:\n\n Develop, analyze and implement metrology measurement\n techniques in films with a primary focus on lithography overlay, CD-SEM.\n Also need to cover ellipsometry/ scatterometry characterization, modeling;\n XRF, and surface profiling techniques.\n Perform SWR (Special Work Request) lots to assist\n Engineers to complete the evaluations for set-up metrology of recipe of\n newly introduced processes, new process equipment, for process\n improvement, optimization or characterization\n Lead supplier tool CIP activity, assisting in NPI (New\n Product Introduction) transfer activity, defining quality metrics,\n achieving metrology performance, and providing weekly summary updates.\n Be constantly engaged in the Fab operation and\n performing tasks to improve quality, reduce cost, reduce cycle time, and\n improve yield! Detailed analysis of next generation measurement\n capabilities as well as coordinating evolutionary programs.\n\nDeliver reliable and value-adding metrology\napplications to reinforce Micron's technical excellence. Standardize BKM,\nknowledge and way of working to keep the growth of metrology team. We also\nearly engage with TD and MCT for brand-new tech introduction.",
