		details:
			"As an AI Innovation Specialist, you will be responsible for driving innovation through the \ndesign, development, and deployment of AI and data-driven solutions that solve complex \nbusiness problems. You will collaborate with digital, data, and business teams to \ntranslate strategic objectives into scalable AI products, prototypes, and proofs of concept \n(POCs).As a Data Engineer, you are expected to address the following responsibilities: \n \n• AI Solution Innovation, Prototyping, and POCs \no Research and experiment with cutting-edge AI techniques to develop novel \nblueprints that address complex business challenges. \no Rapid Proof-of-Concept models and develop scalable AI solutions that can \nbe implemented in production or new technology systems. \no Participate in translating business problems into technical AI solutions. \no Document experiments, assumptions, and version histories. \no Work on end-to-end solution implementation integrating both technical and \nnon-technical considerations. \n• Innovation-driven Data Engineering and Data Governance Solutions \no Explore and implement modern data technologies (e.g., Delta Lake, Iceberg, \netc.). \no Propose innovative data infrastructure solutions to improve performance, \nscalability, and flexibility. \no Participate in planning and development of data models for advanced \nanalytics, machine learning, or near real-time decision-making. \no Collaborate with cross-functional teams to design and implement end-to\nend scalable data pipelines and solutions. \n• Solution Prototyping and POCs \no Conduct experiments and Proofs of Concept (POCs) to demonstrate AI \nsolutions and validate hypotheses. \no Develop prototypes and simulations to translate findings into tangible \napplications. \n• Data Preparation and Processing \no Collect, transform, and prepare structured and unstructured data for model \ntraining and analytics. \no Support data wrangling tasks using tools like Pandas, NumPy, and basic \nSQL. \no Work closely with data engineers to understand data pipelines and \nintegration points. \n• Ensure Data Quality, Reliability, and Governance \no Implement monitoring and validation processes to ensure data accuracy \nand freshness. \no Ensure adherence to data security, privacy, and compliance (e.g., GDPR, \nHIPAA) as needed. \n• Model Development and Support \no Design and implement AI/ML models to solve complex problems and \noptimize performance. \no Assist in developing, training, and validating machine learning or deep \nlearning models under the guidance of senior engineers. \no Experiment with open-source models (e.g., scikit-learn, TensorFlow, \nPyTorch) and adapt models for specific client applications (e.g., NLP, CV, or \npredictive analytics). \n• Continuous Learning and Contribution \no Stay updated with the latest trends in data engineering, cloud computing, \nand AI/ML innovation. \no Work in cross-functional teams including software developers, domain \nexperts, and project managers to define and refine requirements. \no Contribute to innovation initiatives, hackathons, or R&D projects within the \nfirm \n• Application Engineering and Tools \no Apply programming languages and tools for digital transformation and AI \nsolution deployment. \no Strong hands-on experience with Python, Java, or C# (as per project need). \no Developing Digital solutions using Hyperautomation skills including UiPath, \nBluePrism, Automation Anywhere, etc., and integration with AI, Analytics, \nCloud, and Automation platforms. \no Working knowledge of Microsoft Technologies (Visual Studio/.NET, \nASP.NET, API Integration). \no Exposure to Conversational AI, NLP/NLU models, and Omni-channel \nChatbots. \nPrimary Interactions \n \n• **Internal: ** Collaborate across Data and Digital teams and relevant stakeholders \nbased on project requirements. \n• **External (Depending on Client Project assigned): ** Interface with client-side \nbusiness and technology teams to understand requirements and deliver solutions. \nEngage with third-party vendors, including product and service partners, for project\nspecific needs \nTechnical Skills \n \n \n• Proficiency in languages like Python, Java, or C# with experience in writing clean, \nefficient, and well-documented code. \n• Exposure to databases (SQL/NoSQL), cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure), and Big \nData technologies. \n• Strong programming skills in Python, SQL, or Java/Scala. \n• Knowledge of machine learning algorithms, deep learning, neural networks, NLP, \nand statistical modeling. \n• Understanding of Generative AI concepts, including large language models (LLMs), \nembeddings, and prompt engineering. \n• Understanding of data structures, algorithms, and software engineering practices. \n• Familiarity with CI/CD technologies such as AWS/Microsoft Azure is an advantage. \n• Understanding of AI/ML lifecycle and workflows including data analysis and \nvalidation. \n• Hands-on experience with automation/RPA tools (UiPath, BluePrism, Automation \nAnywhere, etc.) is preferred. \n• Strong understanding of data management for data (structured, semi-structured, \nand unstructured).",
