			"Resume filtering | Aptitude test (02:00) | Technical interview (00:45) | Personal interview (00:45) | Quick Interview",
		details:
			"Nation with NaMo: The Graduate Impact Leadership Program (GILP) 2026Job Description - GILP Campaign AssociateWhen you picture yourself at the beginning of your career, what comes to your mind? A cubicle? A9-to-5 job? Building Excel models to structure financial products? Hustling to launch a product in anew city? Pitching your business idea to potential investors? Working as part of a larger softwareteam on a subset of a project? Researching legal positions and advising clients?We are confident that most likely you will end up doing these things as part of a reputedorganization, working with good people in a steady job. And there is absolutely nothing wrong withthat. If this aligns with your career aspirations, you can stop reading now, and we wish you thebest in your career.However, if this is not quite enough for you, imagine this: Sitting with a senior political leader,understanding local issues and political trends. Brainstorming with your team to design animpactful mass voter outreach campaign. Crafting narratives that shape public opinion andcoordinating the production of ad films that align with your campaign's brand identity. Engaging ingrassroots implementation and enabling direct engagement between senior political leaders andvoters. Analysing data and suggesting course-correction to increase campaign's impact.Witnessing the tangible impact of your work on real people by solving real problems. And doing allthis while supporting Prime Minister Modi and his party in their vision to build a new India.If this vision excites you, we have a role for you. If making a real impact is your priority, wewelcome you to the Graduate Impact Leadership Program (GILP).Our team’s backgroundWe are a diverse team of passionate, talented young individuals on a mission to make India betterthrough our work. We are creating a platform for young professionals to create real impact bysupporting senior political leaders on electioneering, party capability building and governance.Our team members come from some of the most prestigious academic institutions in the country,including IIT Kanpur, IIT Kharagpur, IIT Delhi, IIT Bombay, ISB Hyderabad, NLSIU Bangalore,SRCC, LSR and IIT Guwahati.What does GILP offer?Every year, lakhs of bright minds graduate from top educational institutes in India and enter thecorporate sector, yet the best minds often miss the chance to tackle the nation's most pressingissues. GILP aims to bridge this gap.For college graduates, GILP offers a program where passionate individuals interested innation-building can actively engage with and contribute to the political ecosystem through directinteractions. It is one of the most ambitious talent development initiatives in our field, aligning withthe best global programs in the corporate world.1. Unique Experience: You will get a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to build a fulfilling career inan upcoming space, a chance to work with political stakeholders at all levels to gain in-depthexposure about politics and a real chance to contribute towards solving interesting, unsolvedproblems at scale.2. Accelerated learning & growth: You will be part of a small handpicked team of diverse,passionate and talented individuals who will constantly challenge, support and work with you toachieve extraordinary outcomes.3. Hands-on mentorship: As part of this program, you will be mentored by a team of seasonedprofessionals who have pioneered the evolution of this space and undertaken various electoralcampaigns across the country.4. Competitive remuneration: We understand the value of the talent we have in sustaining oursuccess and we offer competitive remuneration as part of our commitment to our people.About the role - GILP Campaign AssociateStarting in the summer of 2026, Campaign Associates will join various project teams, coordinatingwith senior clients in the political domain. They will be involved in designing, executing andmonitoring multiple election campaigns.Throughout these campaigns, Campaign Associates interact closely with political leaders at theconstituency, district, state and national levels to translate strategic efforts into on-groundexecution across electioneering, party capability building and governance. This role offerssignificant exposure and opportunities but also comes with high expectations for maintainingconfidentiality, demonstrating exemplary client management skills, and delivering strongperformance.Key Responsibilities:1. Campaign Support: Actively contribute ideas and provide operational support for thesuccessful roll-out of diverse campaign initiatives, including preparing notes, SOPs &presentations2. Campaign Coordination: Drive end-to-end management of various campaign activities,ensuring timely & quality execution3. Problem Solving: Identify critical issues, apply strong analytical skills and propose pragmaticsolutions in fast-paced and ambiguous environments4. Operational Excellence: Exhibit a strong bias for action, adapt quickly to dynamic situationsand demonstrate exceptional commitment in a demanding work environment5. Communication & Stakeholder Engagement: Drive clear and structured communication,and manage relationships with internal teams and external stakeholders, including vendors,agencies, and others6. Content & Creative Coordination: Manage end-to-end process of briefing & coordinating withcommunication teams, reviewing and delivering campaign collaterals and creatives inalignment with campaign objectives7. Campaign Monitoring & Performance Tracking: Oversee campaign monitoring & reporting,including call centre coordination and digital ad performance review to track the impact ofcampaign8. Client Management: Under guidance, learn to understand and fulfil client needs to ensureimpactful campaign outcomes and client successDesired Qualifications & Skills:As part of GILP, we are looking for team members at the campaign associate level whodemonstrate the following traits:1. Academic Excellence: Combine an impressive academic record with strong technical skills2. Prioritise Impact: Optimise for impact above everything else3. Structured Problem Solving: Tackle complex situations through effective and structuredproblem solving and out-of-the-box thinking, with the ability to propose practical solutions4. Effective Communication: Possesses strong written and verbal communication skills andinterpersonal skills - both individually and in a group setting5. Detail Oriented: Strong eye for detail and content (including creative content) quality, with theability to coordinate with communication and creative teams6. Initiative and Ownership: Adapt to dynamic and ambiguous situations with a clear bias foraction, and taking end-to-end ownership of tasks to drive their quality and timely closure7. Resilience: Demonstrated ability to thrive in a fast-paced, high-pressure and demanding workenvironment8. Adaptability & Work Ethic:● Exceptional self-drive, passion and a proactive approach to work● Willingness to work, stay and travel extensively across various states in India as perdeployment requirements● Willingness to work long hours and weekends to fulfil campaign demands● Flexibility to undertake ad hoc tasks and adapt to evolving priorities in a dynamicenvironment● Possess uncompromising integrity and ethical principles9. Teamwork: Contribute to the strong team ethic and work towards the success of the entireteam10.Leadership Skills: Display the requisite leadership qualities to take ideas forwardEligibilityTo be eligible to apply for the Campaign Associate position in GILP, you must:1. Be a final-year student at a top engineering, commerce, science, or arts college in the country.2. Be graduating in 2026 from a graduate/undergraduate course (3, 4, or 5-year integratedprograms) at such a college.Please note that postgraduate candidates are not eligible for GILP.",
