		details:
			"About Cadence\n\n \n\nCadence is an AI\nComputational Software and Hardware leader. We are leading the electronic\ndesign automation (EDA) industry, enabling global electronic systems and semiconductor\ninnovation. Our tools and solutions help engineers design innovative products,\nfrom chips to systems, that are shaping the future.\n\n \n\nWe have consistently been\nrecognized among the Fortune 100 Best Companies to Work For and deeply invest\nin our people and their growth.\n\n \n\nWhy Join Us? – Our Vision\nfor NCGs\n\nAt Cadence, we aim to:\n\n \n\n· \nBecome part of your growth journey from the start.\n\n· \nProvide a unique, industry-leading training program\nexposing you to the entire spectrum of the semiconductor design flows enabled\nby Cadence platforms and solutions.\n\n· \nShape you into an early adopter and champion of\nCadence products with practical, gamified, and engaging learning.\n\n· \nWork on the Future - be part of AI, ML and\nInnovation journey at Cadence\n\n· We are\ncommitted to developing your technical expertise, customer handling,\ncommunication, and leadership skills, while instilling a strong, inclusive\nCadence culture. \n\n \n\nNCG Training Program Highlights – \n\n· \n2-3 months of structured training before full-time\nfield deployment\n\n· \nMentor Buddy System for personalized guidance\n\n· \nConnect with industry leaders and Cadence experts\n\n· \nCross-discipline exposure to the semiconductor design\nflows\n\n· \nGet early exposure to how AI/ML is transforming\nchip design industry\n\n· \nWeekly huddles, quizzes, lunch & learns,\nspeaking & hobby clubs\n\n· \nExciting representation opportunities in\nHackathons, Innovation conferences worldwide\n\n· \nFun bonding activities: off-sites, field day trips,\ncultural and CSR activities\n\n \n\nWho Can Apply:\n\n \n\n M.Tech\n Excellent\n academic track record is very important, interest in core field of\n Electronic design is critical.\n Clear\n knowledge on Electronics fundamentals, Analog and Digital concepts are\n important.\n Strong\n fundamentals in analog/digital design, VLSI concepts, scripting\n (Perl/Python/TCL), UNIX/Linux, and EDA tools knowledge is a plus.\n Excellent\n communication, teamwork, and problem-solving skills.\n For\n VLSI positions: Candidates having done VLSI course as part of engineering\n or through training institutes will be added advantage.\n For\n System Design and analysis position: VLSI course mentioned above will not\n be applicable.",
