		details:
			"Edison Engineering Development Program – GE Aerospace\n\n \n\nJob Description Summary\n\n \n\nRotational Engineering Leadership program committed to growing GE's\nentry level, high potential talent-people with a passion for technology, a\ndrive for technical excellence, professional skills and GE values-by\naccelerating their development through intense technical training and a variety\nof business-critical assignments.\n\n \n\nRoles\nand Responsibilities\n\n \n The\n GE Aviation EEDP will prepare you for an exciting career tackling one of\n the world’s toughest challenges – Invent the future of flight, Lift\n People Up & Bring them home safely. As a Aviation EEDP, you\n will:\n Work\n on at least 3 rotations over 2 years in a variety of disciplines/business\n segments, possibly including New Products, Services Technology, Advanced\n Next Gen Technology & Digital Technology\n Receive\n technical training, mentorship, and coaching from world-class\n technologists and experienced technical managers.\n Participate\n in leadership development training with GE program members from other\n business and locations.\n Grow\n your technical expertise in your chosen field and expand your skills in\n new areas.\n Plan\n and perform assigned tasks within the framework of areas’ schedules,\n budget, quality and cost constraints while maintaining accuracy and\n thoroughness\n \n\nRequired\nQualifications\n\n \n Master\n in Engineering/Technology\n At\n least a 7 GPA on a 10 Scale\n \n\nDesired\nCharacteristics\n\n \n Basic\n understanding of engineering and/or manufacturing fundamentals\n Strong\n oral and written communication skills\n Strong\n interpersonal and leadership skills\n High\n self-confidence\n Ability\n to motivate others\n Demonstrated\n scholastic achievements",
