			"Resume filtering | Technical interview (1:00) | Technical Interview (1:00)",
		details:
			"About the positionAurora’s Research department is seeking talented Analysts to join our subscription energy analytics and client-facing services for the Indian power sector, based in our Gurugram office.This position will offer a chance to engage with leading stakeholders in the Indian power market and help to drive forward Aurora’s best-in-class modelling.Your role will be to help analyse and forecast the Indian power market, supported by our proprietary energy market models and analytics software. You will work on policy analysis and investment economics for renewables and other technologies and engage with a client base that includes leading Indian and international energy, financial and governmental organizations.Your role will benefit from tutoring by experienced team members from both Gurugram and Oxford, and allow you to grow into a market expert, delivering market-leading analysis to top clients, and contributing learning to Aurora’s wider global teams.Key responsibilities• Contribute analysis and research to develop Aurora’s view on renewable and conventional assets.• Analyse and understand policy outcomes across India’s energy sector.• Work with Aurora’s best-in-class modelling to develop our views on the future of the Indian energy system.• Communicate findings to a wide range of clients, in-person and online.• Contribute materials to Aurora’s reports, notes and client communicationsWhat we are looking forRequired attributes:• Proven ability to organize and manage time.• Proven ability to interpret and derive insight from complex quantitative data and information.• Ability to communicate clearly and co-operate effectively with both technically and non￾technically stakeholders.• Self-starting, entrepreneurial mind-set, and desire to grow the businessDesirable attributes:• Experience of conducting analysis on power markets, in India or another context.• Experience working on financial markets or project finance.• Demonstrated success in working together with clients.• Competence in advanced data analytics (e.g. Python, R, Matlab, Advanced Excel). What we Offer • The opportunity to substantially influence major decisions in the energy sector• Direct engagement with clients through Aurora conferences, workshops and webinars• The opportunity to grow into a publicly visible industry expert• A fun, informal, collaborative and international work culture • A competitive salary package • Access to regular coaching and mentoring sessions and the opportunity to learn from experienced professionals• Access to the Aurora Academy, our training programme offering a range of opportunities to develop your skills within the responsibilities of your role and within the wider context of the industry• Access to our Employee Assistance Programme (EAP), offering a complete support network that offers expert advice and compassionate guidance 24/7/365, covering a wide range of personal and professional aspects The Company is committed to the principle that no employee or job applicant shall receive unfavourable treatment on grounds of age, disability, gender reassignment, race, religion or belief, sex, sexual orientation, marriage or civil partnership, pregnancy and maternity.About usFrom its academic roots, Aurora Energy Research is a thriving, rapidly growing company, currentlyserving over 600 of the world’s most influential energy sector participants, including utilities, investors, and governments. While we constantly strive to reach new markets and diversify our product portfolio, we are already active across the globe in Asia-Pacific, Latin America, Europe, and North America, working with leading organizations to provide comprehensive market intelligence, bespoke analytic and advisory services, and cutting-edge software. We are a diverse team of experts with vast energy, financial, and consulting backgrounds, covering power, hydrogen, carbon, and fossil commodities. With this, we provide data-driven intelligence to fuel strategic decisions in the global energy transformation.",
		info: "Benefits: Medical InsuranceAll employees in India are eligible for company-paid private medical insurance, which includes their dependents (spouse, two children, parents, or spouse's parents) from day one. This coverage is provided by ICICI Lombard, with Plum serving as the Third-Party Administrator (TPA). The health insurance provides a sum insured of ₹7 lakhs per employee including dependents.Personal Accident InsuranceEmployees are covered under personal accident insurance with a sum insured of up to ₹50,00,000.Group Term Life InsuranceEmployees are covered under term life insurance with a sum insured of up to ₹50,00,000.GratuityAll employees are covered under the Gratuity Act.Saving for Your FutureWe participate in the Employees’ Provident Fund Scheme, which entails a contribution of 12% of your basic wages to the provident fund board. You will also be required to make an equivalent contribution.Learning & DevelopmentWe have a range of training sessions available, both in-person and virtually. Our training encompasses six categories across four levels of knowledge, aligning with participants’ knowledge and experience. The levels of knowledge are: Onboarding, Basic, Intermediate, and Advanced.Employee Assistance Programme (EAP)Health Assured provides 24/7/365 confidential employee and wellbeing support, including counselling support.Wellness SessionsMonthly wellness sessions organised by our Third Party Administrator (Plum).Hybrid WorkingAs part of our commitment to flexible working, we support hybrid working arrangements in line with our Hybrid Working Policy. You can work with your Line Manager to agree what your working pattern will look likeRecognitionWe are committed to ensuring everyone feels valued and appreciated, so we have joined forces with Perkbox. The Perkbox platform gives you access to benefits that suit your individual lifestyle and will help you feel happier and healthier.Office CultureOur office in India office is built to foster great relationships and fun activities like birthday celebrations, snack on Fridays, and more!Find Your CommunityWe are proud of our global and inclusive community. From the Women@Aurora and Aurora Pride group to our Analysts Society and Fun Committee—we have it all!",
