		details:
			"Transforming Enterprises to AI-Native: AI EngineerAbout RhythmsRhythms is building the AI operating system that enables enterprises to become AI-native—fundamentally rethinking how organizations operate, execute, and scale. Founded by entrepreneurs who built and sold Chronus (acquired by Private Equity) and Ally.io (acquired by Microsoft), we've raised one of the largest seed rounds of $26M from top investors including GreenOaks, Madrona, and Accel, alongside CXOs from global technology leaders, earning GeekWire's 2024 Deal of the Year award and named a 2025 finalist for AI Innovation of the Year. Rhythms transform how teams operate by streamlining team operating processes—from meetings and KPI tracking to OKRs and strategic planning. Built on a multi-agent architecture that leverages foundational AI models, our platform seamlessly connects with communication tools like Slack and Teams, project management systems like Jira and Linear, and other work tools teams use daily. We turn meetings into structured workflows, eliminate manual updates with real-time insights, and build organizational memory that grows smarter through patterns, interactions, and knowledge captured across systems.What You'll Do\n\nBuild AI-Native Applications – Design and develop cutting-edge applications using LLMs, agents, and agentic workflows that transform how enterprises operate\nBuild Advanced AI Architectures – Design multi-agent systems, agentic workflows, and implement production AI patterns including RAG, orchestration, and evaluation frameworks\nDevelop Full-Stack Solutions – Create end-to-end applications with Python and React/Next.js, integrating AI capabilities into scalable, robust platforms\nShip Production AI Systems – Build reliable AI systems with focus on real-world performance, evaluation frameworks, and measurable business outcomes\nDeliver Customer Impact – Ship features end-to-end, creating delightful and innovative experiences that enterprise customers depend on dailyWhat We're Looking For\n\nAI-First Mindset – Solid programming skills with genuine passion for AI and eagerness to build with LLMs, agents, and modern AI systems\nEntrepreneurial Spirit – Ownership mentality with drive to take initiative, ship quickly, and learn rapidly from real-world feedback\nStrong Problem Solver – Solid analytical thinking with ability to break down complex problems and build elegant, scalable solutions\nEffective Collaborator – Team player who communicates clearly, shares ideas openly, and works well across different functions\nRelentless Learner – Genuine excitement about AI's cutting edge with drive to explore new models, techniques, and technologies continuouslyWhy Join Rhythms - Your Opportunity to:\n\nLearn from the best: Work with CEO Vetri Vellore (ex-Microsoft VP, serial entrepreneur with successful exits) and engineers from IIT, Stanford, and top-tier institutions\nGrow as an AI engineer: Ship production AI daily, work with cutting-edge tech stack (Cursor, Claude Code), and master building reliable agentic systems at scale\nMake real impact fast: Your code will reach enterprise customers within weeks, not years - see direct feedback and iterate rapidly\nExperience startup culture: AI-native environment, flat structure where better ideas win, and ownership mentality from day one\nBuild your entrepreneurial foundation: Join early with $26M backing - learn how world-class products are built from concept to enterprise scaleAt Rhythms, you'll build the AI systems that power how enterprises operate in the age of artificial intelligence. Join us early where your contributions directly shape the product and your growth is accelerated by working alongside world-class engineers and serial entrepreneurs. You'll ship production AI systems, tackle hard problems in agentic reliability, and gain the experience that sets the foundation for an exceptional career in AI—whether as an engineer or future entrepreneur.Location: Hyderabad, India",
		info: "Working at Rhythms is challenging and demanding - you'll tackle hard problems in making agentic AI reliable for enterprise operations, take on responsibilities beyond typical entry-level roles, and push yourself to grow rapidly. It's also incredibly rewarding: your code impacts thousands of users, you learn from serial entrepreneurs and world-class engineers, and you build the foundation for an exceptional career in AI. If you embrace hard work, thrive on challenges, and want meaningful impact over comfort, we want to hear from you.",
