			"Job Role Summary· The role of this position is to support the process improvement/development in metallurgical process refineries/industries.· Deliver scientific or technical solution through research and developmental program. · Capable for technical ideation & scoping of new R&D projects.· Publications and PresentationsJob Requirements· Master’s degree from the recognized university in the following discipline: Chemical Engineering with good academic & professional records.· Project work preferably in process optimization through experimentation and simulations (such as ASPEN, etc.). Must have· Should have knowledge of chemical processes and equipment: mixing vessels, pressure reactors, separators and classifiers, etc.· Fundamentals of fluid, heat & mass-transfer operations.· Should be willing to work in a team and at plant site. Good presentation and communication skills.· Able to setup and conduct experimentations to arrive at scientific inferences.Good to have· Experience in process industries/ research & development· Experience of process scale-up Stirred tanks, gas scrubbing systems etc.· Conversant with one or more modeling tools such as ASPEN plusExposure to material characterization techniques such as XRF, XRD, etc. is preferrable",
