			"Aptitude test (1) | Group discussion (1) | Technical interview (1) | Personal interview (1) | HR discussion",
		details:
			"Performance Analytics – Associate Consultant (2025)Team: Advisors & Consulting Services – Mastercard ServicesAbout Services within Mastercard:Services within Mastercard is responsible for acquiring, engaging, and retaining customers by managing fraud and risk, enhancing cybersecurity, and improving the digital payments experience. We provide value-added services and leverage expertise, data-driven insights, and execution.Our Advisors & Consulting Services team blends traditional management consulting with Mastercard’s unmatched data, proprietary platforms, and technologies to deliver powerful strategic insights. We work with clients across industries, including banking, payments, retail, and more—to solve critical business challenges and drive measurable results.Make an Impact as an Associate Consultant – Performance AnalyticsAs part of the Performance Analytics track, you’ll work on data-intensive consulting engagements, using Mastercard’s vast data assets and advanced analytics platforms. You’ll partner with a diverse range of clients to translate data into business strategies, apply machine learning models, and build scalable analytical solutions that drive tangible impact.You will:•Collaborate with small teams to solve complex client problems using a mix of consulting frameworks and data science.•Conduct advanced quantitative analysis using tools such as Python, SQL, Pyspark, Hadoop, and Impala.•Synthesize raw data into compelling narratives that influence client strategy, product development, and market positioning.•Contribute to end-to-end solution development – from hypothesis building to testing, validation, and implementation.•Partner with internal product, technology, and consulting teams to co-create scalable data solutions.•Manage multiple client engagements with recurring deliverables across verticals.•Engage in Mastercard’s structured training programs, including data science upskilling, consulting methodologies, and industry-specific tracks.Sample Client Challenges You May Solve•How can a global bank optimize fraud detection strategies compared to industry peers?•What machine learning models can identify customers most likely to churn in a competitive credit card market?•Which market segments show the highest growth opportunities for a technology firm losing share to new entrants?•How can real-time transaction data be used to drive hyper-personalized marketing strategies?Bring Your Passion and ExpertiseWe’re looking for future leaders with a strong mix of business acumen and technical fluency.We value:•Passion: Actively seeks responsibility and takes pride in delivering the highest quality results and recommendations to our clients.•Analytic Excellence: Demonstrates a strong aptitude for structured problem solving and quantitative skills.•Business Interest: Clear interest in the world of business, and intuition for the way that companies make decisions.•Rapid Growth: Eagerness to learn quickly, both through Mastercard's structured training curriculum and organic development opportunities.•Teamwork: Willingness to work within small teams to produce outstanding deliverables, with a will to win attitude.•Integrity: Commitment to Mastercard's values of honesty and integrity with a willingness to embrace and learn from our mistakes.•Diverse Perspective: Brings a unique skillset or approach to the table in every client engagement or internal activity.•Communication: Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with demonstrated leadership abilities.Preferred Qualifications•Outstanding academic achievement (Bachelor’s or Master’s in a quantitative, or technical field: e.g., Statistics, Economics, Engineering, Computer Science, Data Science, or Business Analytics).•Internship or project experience in consulting, analytics, or data-driven problem-solving.•Strong communication skills – both written and verbal – and experience presenting complex insights to non-technical stakeholders.Why Join Mastercard Advisors?•Be part of a global consulting & analytics network with top-tier mentorship.•Work on high-impact projects at the intersection of strategy, technology, and analytics.•Join a culture that champions inclusion, innovation, and integrity.Launch your consulting career at Mastercard and help shape the future of industries around the world.",
