		details:
			"What we want to accomplish and why we need you\nSuki is creating a new category in the health-tech space: the digital assistant. Our product will be the voice user interface for healthcare. What does that mean? Currently, doctors use electronic health record systems to take notes on patient encounters. This is a digital version of the paper charts that you may have seen in your doctor’s office or on TV. These systems can be hard to navigate and time-consuming to manage. Doctors would rather spend that time with patients. We are creating the solution. Doctors that use Suki already spend over 70% less time on administrative tasks, and we’re striving to do even better. Come and join us!We are a user-driven company and are committed to making sure every pixel of our product is in service of the doctor. We’re a team of technologists, clinicians, and industry experts working together to push the limits on technology used in medicine. We’re confident enough to move fast and talented enough not to break things. \nResponsibilities\n \n\nOwn design for essential parts of Suki’s innovative consumer/prosumer Web, mobile apps for doctors, enterprise web apps used by administrators and operations professionals, and buyer experiences like landing pages.\nSweat the details: Lead the charge in optimizing Suki’s fit & finish.\nWork with Suki design colleagues to evolve and apply the team’s design systems to help create a unified look and feel across the company’s suite of products.\nHelp development team members understand best practices for design systems and reusable components.\nWork on designing and prototyping innovative interactions for Suki’s assistant experiences.\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams of product management, engineering, marketing, and executive teams to create beautiful consumer experiences.\nBecome an evangelist for Suki’s design principles within and outside Suki.\n\nQualifications/ Who are we looking for\n\nHybrid UX design and Visual design.\nexperience in design and driven to help make beautiful, polished, super-efficient digital products.\nCan point us to a portfolio of experiences or studies for which you made UX and visual design contributions\nRecent experience leading design for high-quality currently shipping mobile apps or web apps.\nA strong track record of collaboration with cross-functional teams.\nExceptional communication skills for conveying design concepts.\nPast experience with motion design and animation.\nFluency in modern design and prototyping tools like Figma, Protopie, Whimsical, etc.\nPast agency experience is a plus.\nPast experience with branding and marketing is a plus.\nPast experience in designing voice interfaces is a plus.\nThe position is based in Bangalore, India.\n\n \nTell me more about Suki● On a roll: Named by Fast Company as one of the most innovative companies, named Google’s Partner of the Year for AI/ML, named by Forbes as one of the top 50 companies in AI .● Great team: Founded, managed, and backed by successful tech veterans from Google and Apple and medical leaders from UCSF and Stanford. We have technologists and doctors working side-by-side to solve complex problems.● Great investors: We’re backed by Venrock, First Round Capital, Flare Capital, March Capital , and others. With our $55M Series C financing, we have the resources to scale.● Huge market: Disrupting a massive, growing $30+ billion market for documentation, transcription, dictation, and order-entry solutions. Our vision is to become the voice + GUI user interface for healthcare, relieving the administrative burden on doctors instead of adding to it.● Great customers: Our solutions are used in health systems and clinics across the country, supporting clinicians across dozens of specialties. Check out what one of our users says about how Suki has helped his practice.● Impact: You’ll make an impact from day one. You’ll join a team working towards a shared purpose with a culture built upon deep empathy for doctors and passion for making their lives better.\nSuki is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We are dedicated to building a company that fosters inclusion and belonging and reflects the diverse communities we serve across the country. We know we are stronger this way, and we look forward to growing our team with these shared values.",
