		reqs: "The successful candidate must have the ability to meet tight deadlines, have strong interpersonal and communication skills, be detail oriented, and have the ability to work independently and be a self-starter.【Preferred Experience and Skills】Candidates should possess knowledge or experience in one or more of the following areas:- Skills in building dashboards (e.g., Qlik Sense, B-dash, Streamlit, etc.).- Excellent software architecture design skills (must be familiar with Python).- DevOps skills (CI/CD, build processes, infrastructure deployment).- Knowledge of data management middleware such as databases, data lakes, query engines, etc.- Monitoring skills (e.g., error notifications via email or chat).- Experience working in cloud environments.- Fundamental knowledge of Generative AI.In addition to the above, having the following traits and skills would be a plus:- Contribution to Open Source Software Communities.- Understanding of international cultural studies, including Japanese culture.- Any exposure to or proficiency in the Japanese language is welcome.【Ideal Candidate Profile】We are looking for individuals who possess the following mindset and aptitudes:- Strong motivation to contribute to Honda’s AD/ADAS development and emerging domains such as recurring business through data and cloud technologies.- Willingness to quickly respond to customer and market needs, and proactively update operations and products with an agile mindset.- Ability to actively engage and collaborate with people both inside and outside the organization.Language Level: Business English",
