			"Entry | Web Test (1:30) | Technical interview (00:45) | Personal interview (00:45)",
		details:
			"Company Description:Over the years, Honda has consistently created new value and contributed to the joy of living. In every activity, Honda considers what it can do for the people of the world living with hope for a bright future, as well as for the Earth and Society. Honda R&D exists as an agency of Honda and leads the activities of research and development. With a history of more than half a century of cutting-edge research and products, we have accumulated a vast wealth of various technologies and knowledge, which we believe must be utilised to actively contribute to people, the earth, and society. Our mission for the generations to come is to provide new mobility and services while also constantly developing and researching the leading technologies of the times. Honda R&D is embarking on new challenges for the future in a variety of fields, and we want you to be a part of this journey. Domain Description: <Honda R&D Innovative Research Excellence, Honda Innovation Lab, Intelligence and Safety Research (ISR) Domain>Honda R&D ISR Domain is working towards the research and development of technologies that realise intelligent mobility systems for personal cars (i.e., AD and ADAS) and new generation shared mobility. Our concept, which we call “Cooperative Intelligence (CI)”, utilises AI technologies to allow cooperation with the user rather than full automation, which is independent from the user. Our CI systems interact with the user to reduce risk, anxiety and inconvenience, in turn, realising “freedom of door-to-door movement”. We believe that the interaction among the system, the user and the traffic scene, including other road users, should be based on mutual understanding and cooperative action. To achieve this, we consider mobility scenario related computer vision issues (e.g., traffic environment recognition, road user behavior prediction, pedestrian gesture recognition, pedestrian attribute recognition, landmark recognition, high level scene understanding), cooperative action planning (e.g., avoiding deadlock through gentle negotiation with surrounding vehicle by conveying ego-car's intention), and human-machine-communication (e.g., understanding user intention from verbal instructions and gestures, dialogue based on multi-modal context) as some of our core challenges.Job Description:<Responsibilities> The associate will research one or some of the above core challenges. He/she will set technical problems to be solved, find out possible solving approaches, and evaluate them not only in theory but also on a physically working system. In addition, Honda expects him/her to create novel algorithms to provide better performance than the state-of-the-art algorithms in the respective research problem. <Specific Goals> [1st -2nd year] Conduct a feasibility study of traditional and novel approaches for a limited scene. The associate will not only research and execute algorithms but also participate in appropriate data collection and evaluations. [3rd -5th year] The associate will generalise his/her proposed algorithm for wider scenes, and demonstrate it on a prototype (physically working machine) in a public area. *The associate will have a chance to participate in numerous global research activities based on his/her ability and research outputs.",
		info: "Language Level: Whoever is enthusiastic to learn a new language is welcome, although no preliminary knowledge of Japanese is expected. We provide language training support to employees.\nCTC: 9,045,000 JPYCTC Breakdown: ・Basic salary: 6,553,000 JPY ・Allowance(Meal, Commuting, etc): 460,000 JPY・House Rent: 1,032,000 JPY *Guarantee fee will be deducted from salary　 ・JPN language lesson: 1,000,000 JPYTake Home (in Hand): 5,088,000 JPY *After taxGross Taxable Income: 6,553,000 -9,097,000JPY *depend on BonusMonthly Fixed Pay: 546,000 JPY （424,000 JPY *After tax）Bonus: After every 6 months of evaluation (CTC calculations are before tax):1. Output meets the assignments: no incentive (CTC: JPY 9,045,000)2. Outstanding outputs: additional bonus(*after tax) of JPY 636,000 (CTC: JPY 9,045,000+819,000) 3. Supreme outputs: additional bonus(*after tax) of JPY 1,272,000 (CTC: JPY 9,045,000+1,638,000) So maximum CTC a candidate can get after 1 year, depending upon his performance, is JPY 9,045,000+ 1,638,000+ 1,638,000 = 12,321,000JPY Allowances: Commuting allowance,Meal allowance,Allowance Upon Joining(\\150,000, Flight Tickets, Moving Expense, Cost for initial VISA)No overtime allowanceAnnual Paid Leaves:　20 days annuallyBenefits: Employment insurance, Workers’ Accident insurance *Social insurance fee is deducted from salary, Health insurance, Pension InsuranceOfficial Working Hours: Base 8 hours / day",
		reqs: "Preferred Skill Set would be Basic Knowledge or Practical Experience in a few of the following- Machine learning for computer vision, natural language understanding, and multimodal generative AI- Probabilistic Inference- Model-based control (model predictive control, Kalman filter, adaptive control, etc.)In addition to the above, having the following traits and skills would be a plus :-Desire to create technology which would be the world's first and contribute to society- Provide new UX and value to customers through mobility- Proactively challenge new things- Energy to set high goals and go through with them- Ability to proactively communicate one's own ideas and find the best means of problem-solving by involving those around you- Communication skills that can help interact cheerfully with various stakeholders- Desire to work in a multicultural and multilingual environment\n\nWhoever is enthusiastic to learn a new language is welcome, although no preliminary knowledge of Japanese is expected. We provide language training support to employees.",
