		details:
			"About the Role​​You will be part of Accenture Global Tech data science group, an energetic, strategic, high-visibility and high-impact team, to innovate and transform the client’s business using machine learning, advanced analytics and data-driven AI. You will have the unique opportunity to be exposed to a wide diversity of exciting business problems and data and create machine learning methods and data-driven AI solutions to deliver the next generation Accenture AI offerings. The objectives of the team include but are not limited to:​Conceptualizing, designing and developing innovative machine learning / data AI solutions for a wide range of Accenture Operations business towers: Finance & Accounting, Procurement, Cloud, Infrastructure, Customer Analytics, etc.​Integrating the outcomes as real-time analytics to elevate the Accenture’s ability to create value for clients in areas and through means not immediately apparent to clients​Data Scientists in Global Tech follow multiple approaches for project execution from adapting existing assets to Operations use cases, exploring third-party and open-source solutions for speed to execution and for specific use cases to engaging in fundamental research to develop novel solutions. They also leverage the vast global network of Accenture to collaborate with Accenture Tech Labs, Accenture Open Innovation and Accenture Analytics for creating solutions.\n\nBasic Qualification​​​Post-graduate degree (M.Sc. or Dual Degree) in computational science, statistics, mathematics, economics or operations research​Strong statistical programming in Python and R​Solid knowledge of ML/AI methods (supervised/unsupervised, regression, clustering, neural networks, ensembles, stochastic/Bayesian models)​Linux/Unix development experience​Strong written and verbal English communication skills\n\nDesired Skills and experience​​​Experience in ML/statistical models & unstructured data analytics​Strong programming in Python/R​Strong analytical and problem-solving skills​Familiarity with relational DBs & SQL (a plus)​Experience with large datasets & Big Data tools is a plus (e.g., Spark, Hadoop, Hive, Flink)​​Qualification: MSc & MTech/Dual Degree \nRole: Associate Data Scientist​​​​",
