		details:
			"About Landeed\nAt Landeed, we're solving one of India's most fundamental problems: property disputes. With two-thirds of all court cases in India being land-related, we've built India's fastest and most comprehensive property title search engine that retrieves critical legal documents in seconds instead of months.\nWe're not just another startup—we're Y Combinator alumni (S22) backed by top-tier investors including Draper Associates, Bayhouse Capital, and 10x Founders Fund. Having recently raised $5 million in Series X funding, we're scaling rapidly across 24+ Indian states with over 2 million users including property owners, bankers, real estate agents, and developers.\nWhy This Matters\nReal estate represents 84% of Indian household wealth, yet the industry remains plagued by inefficiencies and disputes. We're transforming how property ownership works in India by making title searches 10x faster than traditional methods, building the operating system for property ownership. This isn't just about technology—it's about protecting families' most valuable assets and creating transparency in a $200 billion industry.\nThe Role: Build the Future of Property Technology\nAs an early-stage Software Engineer at Landeed, you'll work directly with our founding team to build products that millions of Indians depend on. You'll be architecting systems that process government data across multiple states, developing AI/ML capabilities that are central to our operations, and creating user experiences that make complex legal processes intuitive.\nWhat You'll Do:\n\nDesign and develop scalable backend systems handling property data from 24+ Indian states\n\nBuild AI/ML solutions for document processing, data extraction, and property analytics\n\nCreate intuitive frontend experiences that make complex legal processes accessible to millions\n\nWork on real-time data pipelines processing government records and legal documents\n\nCollaborate directly with founders on product strategy and technical architecture\n\nShip features that impact over 1 million users and drive business growth\n\nHelp expand our platform to new states and scale our enterprise offerings\n\nWhat We're Looking For\nTechnical Foundation:\n\nStrong programming skills in Python, NextJS, JavaScript, or similar languages\n\nUnderstanding of data structures, algorithms, and system design fundamentals\n\nExperience with databases (SQL), APIs, and cloud platforms (AWS)\n\nFamiliarity with web development frameworks (React, Node.js, Django, etc.)\n\nKnowledge of version control (Git) and software engineering best practices\n\nWhat Sets You Apart:\n\nProblem-solving mindset: You think about real-world impact, not just code\n\nStartup hunger: You thrive in fast-paced environments and want to wear multiple hats\n\nLearning agility: You're excited to dive deep into proptech, legal tech, and government systems\n\nCollaboration: You work well with both technical and non-technical stakeholders\n\nOwnership: You take initiative and drive projects from conception to completion\n\nThe Opportunity: More Than Just a Job\nThis is a wealth-building opportunity at a Y Combinator startup positioned for exponential growth. You'll be among our first 50 employees, giving you:\nDirect Founder Access: Work closely with our founding team who have 7+ years of building together and are on their second YC startup\nMassive Learning: Gain expertise in proptech, AI/ML, government data systems, and scaling startups from 1M to 10M+ users\nCareer Acceleration: Early employees at successful startups often become senior leaders, CTOs, or founders themselves. Our alumni network through Y Combinator provides unparalleled connections\nReal Impact: Your code will help resolve property disputes for millions of families and potentially prevent court cases that currently consume 67% of India's judicial system\nWhy Join Now\n\nTiming: We're post-product-market-fit with strong traction but still early enough for massive upside\n\nFunding: $13+ million raised means stability and resources for growth\n\nTeam: Work with experienced founders who've built successful companies before\n\nMarket: Proptech in India is exploding, and we're the clear leader in title search\n\nTechnology: AI/ML at the core, with greenfield opportunities to build next-gen solution\nLandeed is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusion. We welcome applications from all qualified candidates regardless of race, gender, religion, sexual orientation, or background.",
