		details:
			"Trainee Engineer (Proposal) – Wastewater Treatment & Water RecyclingKey Responsibility Areas (KRA)Position: Trainee Engineer(Proposal) – Wastewater Treatment & Water RecyclingReporting To: General Manager – ProposalsCompany: SFC Environmental Technologies LtdABOUT SFC ENVIRONMENTAL TECHNOLOGIES LTD.Innovating for a Sustainable Tomorrow: SFC Environmental Technologies is at the forefront of tackling critical environmental challenges. We're not just building solutions; we're building a sustainable future. Our advanced technologies, including C-Tech wastewater treatment and OREX solid waste segregation, are setting new industry standards. Be part of a team that's making a real difference.VISION“Be the trusted leader in environmental technologies, continuously innovating to create value, inspiring sustainable change for a better tomorrow.”MISSION“Harnessing technology and human insights to develop and deliver simple, flexible, and cost-effective environmental solutions.”Role OverviewWe are seeking a proactive and detail-oriented Trainee Engineer (Proposal) with 0-2 years of experience. The ideal candidate should have a strong academic background in environmental or civil engineering and a keen interest in proposal engineering for STP/ETP/CETP systems. Familiarity with wastewater treatment technologies such as SBR, A2O, and MBR will be an added advantage. A willingness to learn and contribute to technical proposals and project planning is essential. The key responsibilities of this role include, 1. Tender & Inquiry Management:· Analyze tender documents and project specifications.· Prepare pre-bid queries and attend pre-bid meetings· Summarize technical/commercial expectations from tenders 2. Process Design & Engineering:· Perform process and hydraulic calculations· Develop BOQs for civil, mechanical, piping, and instrumentation· Prepare layouts, PFDs, P&IDs, and hydraulic profiles 3. Cost Estimation & Vendor Coordination:· Invite and evaluate vendor quotations· Estimate CAPEX/OPEX, and optimize design for cost-efficiencySupport in budget preparation and DPR costing4. Proposal & Documentation Preparation:· Draft and submit detailed techno-commercial proposals· Prepare technical data sheets, engineering drawings, and bid annexures· Create Detailed Project Reports with forecasts and treatment philosophies 5. Cross-functional & Stakeholder Coordination:· Liaise with internal teams (Sales, Projects, Design) for proposal inputs· Conduct site visits for data gathering and project understanding· Benchmark competitor offerings and design strategiesKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)1. Proposal Accuracy:· Rate of technical errors or clarifications post-submission2. Bid Turnaround Time:· Percentage of proposals submitted within deadlines3. Design Optimization:· Cost savings through optimized engineering solutions4. Win Rate:· Number of successful bids versus total submissionsAcademic Qualifications· M.Tech in Environmental, Chemical or Civil Engineering with relevant experience.Skills & Competencies Required· 0-2 years of relevant experience in proposal engineering for wastewater projects· Strong knowledge of STP/ETP/CETP technologies and biological treatment processes· Competency in BOQ/BOM preparation, technical documentation, and cost estimation· Familiarity with relevant design software and MS Office tools· Effective communication and project coordination skills· Ability to manage multiple bids simultaneously under tight timelines Reporting Structure & Collaboration• Reports To: General Manager – Proposals• Collaborates With: o Internal departments (Process, Design, Procurement, Projects, Commissioning)o Clients, contractors, and equipment vendorso Drafting and Documentation Teamo Quality & Compliance TeamThe Trainee Engineer (Proposal) – Wastewater Treatment & Water Recycling at SFC Environmental Technologies Ltd. plays a vital role in converting project inquiries and tenders into compelling, accurate, and cost-effective techno-commercial proposals. By integrating process design, cost estimation, and documentation, the Proposal Engineer ensures that each bid aligns with technical standards, client expectations, and financial goals. This role works closely with internal departments, vendors, and clients to develop winning strategies and proposals that drive the company’s growth and support the delivery of sustainable water solutions.",
		info: "About UsSFC Environmental Technologies Ltd. is a leading technology company providing advanced solutions in the environmental sector. We specialize in three key areas: wastewater treatment technology, wastewater recycling and reuse.Our C-Tech technology package includes comprehensive design and engineering, technology installation, and the supply of key equipment and automation solutions, ensuring high efficiency, reliability, and ease of operation for wastewater treatment facilities. In the field of wastewater recycling and reuse, we offer end-to-end solutions using technologies such as MBR, MABR, fibre disc filters, submerged ultrafiltration membranes, and CCRO systems.SFC has also designed, built, and continues to operate India’s longest-running CBG-based integrated solid waste treatment plants in Goa. Our proprietary process, OREX, enables higher gas yield and stable digester performance, setting benchmarks in waste-to-energy solutions.We operate from our head office in Navi Mumbai, with subsidiary offices in Austria and Germany. Our manufacturing infrastructure includes a 200,000 sq. ft. facility in Chakan, Pune, and a membrane manufacturing unit in Czechia.At SFC, we foster a culture rooted in courage, freedom, transparency, accountability, and ownership. We value self-direction and encourage team members to take initiative, think boldly, and consistently deliver beyond expectations.",
