		details:
			"Job Summary: The successful candidate will support the design, development, and implementation of advanced automation/robotics solutions across manufacturing and industrial operations. This role demands a strategic thinker with hands-on expertise in automation technologies, overview of required control systems, and process optimization. The ideal candidate will work to execute / support a cross-functional team, driving innovation, and ensure seamless integration of automation solutions to enhance productivity, safety, and efficiency.Job Responsibilities:• Support automation projects for end-to-end execution of industrial automation initiatives, from concept to commissioning• Architect and implement PLC, SCADA, HMI, and DCS systems tailored to operational needs• Analyze workflows and conceptulize solutions for identified automation opportunities to improve throughput • Collaborate with equipment suppliers and system integrators to ensure timely and cost-effective delivery• Collaboratively work with team of automation engineers and technicians• Ensure all automation systems comply with industry standards and safety regulations• Develop and maintain detailed technical documentation, including schematics, SOPs, and validation protocols• Learn and upskill into diagnosing and resolving automation-related issues• Conduct training sessions for operations and maintenance teams on new systems.• Stay updated on emerging technologies and recommend upgrades to existing systems.Education Required: Master’s Degree (ME) in Electrical, Electronics, Mechatronics, or Industrial EngineeringExperience: 0-2 years industrial experience working with line automation solutions development and commissioningTechnical Knowledge:• Deep knowledge in electrical and instrumentation design - Design robootic converyor, working hands-on experience with industrial robots• Proficiency in PLC programming• Expertise in SCADA systems• Experience with HMI development and customization• Knowledge of industrial communication protocols (Modbus, Profibus, Ethernet/IP).• Familiarity with robotics integration and motion control systems.• Understanding of Industrial IoT (IIoT) and smart manufacturing concepts• Ability to perform system validation and FAT/SAT testing• Experience with data acquisition and analytics platforms.• Proficiency design and simulation tools• Experience in working with Industry best / Eaton preferred hardware vendors (FANUC, KUKA, MIR, ABB, Omron, UR, etc.)",
