		process:
			"Resume filtering | Technical interview (30) | HR Interview (30)",
		details:
			"What you will do:The Engineering and Technology Development Program - Systems Engineering\nchief engineers' office track offers program participants accelerated learning\nexperience for two-years through challenging assignments and curated training\nprogram. This program will provide exposure to aligned roles in the Eaton India\nInnovation Center. \n\n1) Participate in all phases of the product development lifecycle (Requirements, Design, Testing, and Release) following a structured engineering process to ensure quality and reliability.2) Responsible for supporting the deisgn of Mechanism, Arc chute, housing for products like LVAir circuit breaker 3) Collaborate with external and internal customers, such as Product Management, Field Service, Operations and other Engineering teams during the product development life cycle4)Responsible for Design, developemnt and testing of sub system of LV circuit breaker like Mechanism, Arc chute, housing products like LV Air circuit breaker 5) Expertise in design of sheet metal, plastic part design,different sensor selection and its integration. 6)Ability to drive a technology design with a team of engineers both locally and remote7) Leverage Design for Six Sigma for reliable and on time launch of the projectsSkills: • Sound technical understanding of systems engineering concepts\n• High learning agility \n• Creating business proposals, creativity\n\nStrong analytical capability\nGood communication skills in English (verbal and written) to communicate\ninformation effectively to customers, and technical staff.Qualification:M.E. /M.Tech - Embedded/Electronics/Instrumentation/Control\"0-3 Yrs of experience Experience: Experience in electronic hardware design, development, and testing.• Proficiency in schematic capture and PCB layout tools (e.g., Cadence, Altium).• Strong understanding of Analog and Digital circuit design principles.• Familiarity with microcontrollers, sensors, power electronics (Power Supply or SMPS), and wireless communication technologies.• Experience with design for manufacturability and design for testability principles.• Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to work in a collaborative team environment• Experience with embedded systems design and hardware development in High-speed design or mixed signal processing.• Knowledge of electromagnetic compatibility (EMC) and signal integrity (SI) considerations in electronic hardware design.• Familiarity with simulation and modelling tools for electronic circuits (e.g., SPICE, Simulink)",
