		details:
			"Job Summary: \n The primary responsibility of this role is to perform flow &\n thermal analysis of switchgear/UPS/Circuite protection devices/transformer\n & allied electrical products for\n thermal performance prediction. Individual will be required to partner with\n teams located in India, Europe, US & China, understand specific design\n intent, develop, and validate analysis models to substantiate various\n engineering designs. He/She should be conversant with different products\n within the electrical portfolio. Candidate should ensure proper coordination\n and communication with all stakeholders by following project management best\n practices.This position is responsible for handling medium complex\n technologies related to conjugate heat transfer,flow estimtion &\n electronics cooling wherein incumbent is expected to independently handle\n requirements and deliver quality results within stipulated timelines.\n \n The candidate should have strong background in heat transfer,fluid\n mechanics with thorough understanding of CFD analysis fundamentals.He/She\n should proactively look for various opportunities to validate his/her\n analytical predictions with physical testing to constantly mature DP\n capabilities.Job Responsibilities:\n A. Technology Responsibilities:\n • Contribute towards maturing identified technical capabilities aligned to flow, thermal domain from ES amercas portfolio\n \n • Work closely with product\n and analysis experts to Develop and validate\n digital prototypes to mimic product physics and predict key CTQ’s\n \n B. Program Responsibilities:\n • Ensure Analysis First deployment on\n low/medium complex electrical componenets/Assemblies \n • Highlight\n apt technical and schedule risks on assigned\n low/medium complex programs and work towards metigating those\n • Work with SME to\n effectively support simulation request to manage workload\n C. Extended Responsibilities:\n • Participate in ES Americas level initiatives and\n contribute thru solid value add\n • Learn DFSS fundamentals & impliment on\n the programs\n • Embrace continuous improvement initiatives\n and demonstrate consistent increase in “value” from project\n deliverables\n •Create valuable IP to expand innovation envelope\n for organization growthQualification & Skills:\n \n \n Master’s degree in mechanical / aerospace\n \n \n ~0-2 Years\n \n \n CFD, Heat Transfer, Fluid Mechanics,Simulation tool expertise\n \n \n Accountability – Takes\n complete responsibility of assigned tasks and delivers results despite of\n roadblocks \n Passion - Pursues\n everything with drive and motivates others around to contribute towards the\n cause \n Resourceful – Works across the boundaries to get\n the desired things done timely \n Problem Solving - Uses rigorous logic and methods to solve\n difficult problems with effective solutions, Looks beyond the obvious\n solutions and comes up with creative/ innovative proposals\n Learner - Takes\n efforts to upskill self and shares the learnings with broader team\n proactively \n Transparency - Should\n create open and trusting environment in the team\n Please select",
		info: "Perks: Transportation, Medical Insurance, Food coupon, Accommodation for initial 14 days for out stationed candidates",
		reqs: "Mtech - Mechanical/Aerospace - 6.5 & Above CGPA with no live or dead backlogs.",
