		process:
			"Resume filtering | Technical interview (30 Minutes) | Personal interview (30 Minutes)",
		details:
			"JDJob Summary:\n Eaton\n India Innovation Center (EIIC) – Center for Digital Engineering (CDE) has a\n Engineer open position. The primary responsibility of this role is to perform\n simulations of electrical products breakers/switchgear/UPS from MBD (Multi\n Body Dynamics)/vibration/Static technology. Individual will be required to\n partner with local and global teams, understand the design intent, develop\n and validate simulation models to substantiate the engineering designs.\n Individual should have sound knowledge of Mechanical systems, Vibration &\n Mechanics modelling techniques in ADAMS/ANSYS Workbench and allied software.\n \n The primary function for this position includes: \n • Collaborates with technology and\n product teams to define problem statements\n • Understands project requirements\n and solves problems in discussion with local as well as global\n stakeholders.\n • Understand existing simulation\n modeling methodologies & assist to mature further\n • Deploys developed simulation\n methodologies to strengthen “Analysis First” strategy on electrical productsJob Responsibility:\n 1.\n Develops simulation models for MBD/Vibration/Static CTQ to evaluate critical\n performance of electrical products.\n 2. Analyze,Interpret, summarize and communicate simulation results to\n global audience and provide technical and/or design recommendations.\n 3. Delivers deep insights through simulations for robust product\n development to meet performance requirements/ CTQs for electrical\n products.\n 4. Coordinates with stakeholders to understand analysis requirements,\n create analysis approach & solve simple/medium complex problems\n 5. Understand & assist in maturing analysis capability of Structural\n technology domain for electrical productline.\n 6. Engage with product and test engineer to improve analysis models and\n validate analysis approach with test data. \n 7.Demonstrates CI mindset & indentify opportunities to automate\n repetative tasks.Qualification & Skills:\n \n \n 1) MS/ME/M.Tech\n in Mechanical/Automotive engineering\n \n \n 2) 0-2 Years of relevant experience with multinational engineering\n organization.\n \n \n 3) Thorough understanding of dynamic techniques like Fatigue,\n Static, MBD, Vibration analysis methods. Knowledge of Six Sigma (DfSS) is\n preferred. \n \n \n 4) Candidate should have excellent English communication (oral and\n written) and presentation skills and should be a good team player.",
		info: "Perks: Transportation, Food coupon, Accommodation for initial 14 days for out station candidates, Medical Insurance.Guidance: Please prepare according to JD and read about Eaton.",
