		details:
			"NLP Engineer – Augnito\n\nAbout\nUs\n\nAugnito\nis the next gen Voice AI powering the healthcare industry. Augnito empowers\nmedical professionals and streamlined clinical workflows with cloud-based, AI\nspeech recognition that offers ergonomic data entry with 99% accuracy, without\nthe need for voice profile training, from any device, anywhere. \n\nFrom\nthe outset, Augnito was built in close partnership with clinicians, using\nhuman-centered design, to create an AI natural language processing engine to\nfit your needs – not the other way around. As a result, Augnito offers\nexcellent support for a wide variety of clinical vocabulary and workflows and\ncan halve your clinical reporting and admin time, increase revenue, prevent\nphysician burnout, eliminate transcription waiting delays, and enable you to\nfocus your energy on patient care – not documentation. Augnito is currently\ndeployed at 300+ hospitals and health systems and has a growing presence in 20+\ncountries, including the US, UK and Canada \n\nAbout\nthe role: \n\nAs\nan NLP Engineer at Augnito you will play a pivotal role in developing and\nenhancing our NLP-powered applications and services. You will work closely with\na cross-functional team of engineers, data scientists, and product managers to\nbuild innovative solutions that leverage natural language understanding to\ndeliver a seamless user experience. Your expertise in NLP will be essential in\ndriving our product development efforts forward. \n\nResponsibilities:\n\n· Apply skills and knowledge to solve NLP (Natural\nLanguage Processing) problems in areas such as text classification, entity\ntagging, information retrieval, question-answering, natural language\ngeneration, and summarization. \n\n· Be hands-on in identifying problems in data and\nimproving data quality using tools and data labelling techniques. \n\n· Raw data processing and transform large datasets to\nprepare them for model development. \n\n· Gather external data sets, create synthetic data,\nlabel datasets, as needed to train or fine-tune NLP models. \n\n· Research, design, and implement innovative\napproaches using state-of-the-art Transformer models, large language models\n(e.g., BERT, T5, GPT, LLama, Claude, Mistral, Gemini) and Generative AI\ntechniques to address complex\n\n· Lead and execute NLP projects to extract valuable\ninsights from medical/healthcare documents. \n\n· Evaluate and select appropriate NLP libraries,\nframeworks, and tools for projects. \n\n· Collaborate with product managers and engineers to\nunderstand user requirements and provide technical solutions. \n\n· Provide input into future data science strategy and\nproduct development. \n\n· Ensure compliance with data privacy and security\nregulations in projects. \n\n· Stay updated with state-of-the-art techniques in the\nNLP field and exchange knowledge with colleagues. \n\n· Coordinate with internal teams to translate business\nchallenges into data pipelines and model frameworks. \n\nQualifications:\n\n· Bachelor's or Master's degree in computer science,\nNatural Language Processing, Machine Learning, or a related field. P \n\n· In-depth knowledge of NLP, particularly keeping up\nwith new concepts and reading academic articles. \n\n· Experience working with various NLP toolkits\nincluding but not limited to NLTK, spaCy, Gensim, Stanford NLP, CoreNLP\nhighlighting a broad understanding of natural language processing. \n\n· Familiarity with at least one deep learning toolkit,\nsuch as PyTorch, TensorFlow, or MxNet, to apply advanced techniques in NLP. \n\n· Familiarity with internals of at least a few Machine\nLearning algorithms, transformer models and concepts. \n\n· Familiarity with training or fine-tuning experience\nwith Transformer-based Language Models like BERT, Roberta, T5, GPT, LLama,\nClaude, Mistral, Gemini etc\n\n· Knowledge of conversational Chatbot and dialogue\nengines. \n\n· Understanding of LLM (Large Language Model),\nLangchain framework is a plus. \n\n· Familiarity with Git workflows, including branching,\ncommitting, merging, and resolving conflicts. \n\n· Good to have the knowledge in healthcare domain,\nalthough not a strict requirement.",
