			"About NuveenNuveen\nis the investment management arm of TIAA. It is one of the largest global asset\nmanagers with specialist knowledge across a wide array of asset classes,\nincluding fixed income, equities and alternatives. Nuveen is driven not\nonly by the independent investment processes across the firm, but also the\ninsights, risk management, analytics and other tools and resources a truly\nworld-class platform provides. As a global asset manager, our mission is to\nwork in partnership with our clients to create outcome-focused solutions to\nhelp them secure their financial future. For more information about the\nfirm please visit our website at \nOverview of the Role: \nWe are a forward-thinking team committed to delivering transformative business\noutcomes leveraging both traditional AI/ML and next-gen technologies like\nGenerative AI. Join us to be part of a collaborative, innovative, and\nfast-paced environment where your ideas, contributions and skills will shape\nthe future of asset management. \nJob Description\n• Work on key AI products and AI projects, including Generative AI, Machine\nLearning and deep learning.\n• Collaborate with cross functional teams to design, build and deploy AI models\nthat directly impact business outcomes.\n• Interact and fine tune LLMs (Large Language Models) and SLMs (Small Language\nModels) to address diverse use cases including predictive analysis,\nconversational AI and recommendation systems.\n• Create, test and optimize prompt engineering strategies to enhance\nperformance of Generative AI models.\n• Apply strong machine learning concepts and principles to innovate across\nvarious line of businesses.\n• Deep dive into datasets to perform exploratory data analysis, extract\ninsights, train models, and develop end to end MDLC pipelines.\n• Stay updated with latest trends in AI and dynamically use new methodologies\nand tools to maintain competitive edge.\n• Participate in Hackathons, Kaggathons, brainstorming sessions to drive\ninnovation.\nTechnical Skills & Experience Required\n• Education: Grads/Post-Grads with a degree in Data Science , AI or related\nfield\n• AI/ML fundamentals: Solid understanding of machine learning concepts,\nstatistics, deep learning, NLP, algorithms and frameworks.\n• Gen AI Expertise: Experience or string interest in working on Gen AI\nincluding prompt engineering, LLM fine tuning and model evaluations\n• Programming Skills: Proficient in Python or R and familiarity with libraries\nlike PyTorch, SykitLearn, TensorFlow, HuggingFace etc. Knowledge of APIs and\nfront nd visualizations would be beneficial.\n•Problem-Solving: Creative thinkers with a skill to break down complex problems\ninto actionable solutions, and work in a dynamic environment with\nproactiveness\n•Collaboration: Team players who thrive in dynamic, collaborative, and learning\nfocused environment.\n•Passion for AI: A strong desire to stay ahead of the curve in AI advancements\n•Other Skills: Big data technologies such as Apache Hadoop and Apache Spark\n\nWhy join us?\n\n• Hands-on experience: Work among team of bright domain experts, technologists\nand data scientists on impactful projects that directly contribute to business\nsuccess. \n• Learning Opportunities: Access to training programs and resources at the\nenterprise level to enhance your expertise in cutting edge technologies.\n• Innovative Environment: Be part of an innovative, curious, creative and\ncollaborative team",
