			"Resume filtering | Technical test (01:00) | Group discussion (00:45) | Technical interview (01:00) | Personal interview (01:00)",
		details:
			"Role: Associate\nDevOps Engineer – NexusOne\n\n \n\nLocation: Pune\n\nCategory: Platform Engineering\n& DevOps\nReports To: DevOps Engineering\nManager\n\n \n\nRole Summary /\nPurpose\n\n \n\nAs an Associate DevOps Engineer at NexusOne, you’ll help design, automate,\nand optimize the infrastructure that powers our global data and analytics\nplatform. This role is ideal for recent graduates who are passionate about\ncloud infrastructure, CI/CD automation, and modern DevOps practices.\n\n \n\nYou’ll work\nalongside experienced engineers to support deployment pipelines, observability\ntools, and infrastructure-as-code environments — ensuring NexusOne delivers\nsecure, scalable, and reliable systems to customers worldwide.\n\n \n\nCore\nResponsibilities\n\n \n\n● \nAssist in building and maintaining\nCI/CD pipelines using tools like GitLab CI, Jenkins, or GitHub Actions.\n\n● \nSupport the provisioning and\nmanagement of cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP) using Terraform or similar IaC tools.\n\n● \nHelp automate environment setup,\napplication deployments, and monitoring processes.\n\n● \nContribute to containerized\napplication environments using Docker\nand Kubernetes.\n\n● \nParticipate in monitoring and\nincident response efforts by learning and using tools such as Prometheus, Grafana, and ELK Stack.\n\n● \nCollaborate with software, data,\nand platform teams to streamline development-to-production workflows.\n\n● \nDocument automation scripts,\ndeployment processes, and environment configurations.\n\n● \nLearn and apply DevOps best\npractices for security, scalability, and reliability.\n\nRequired Skills\n& Qualifications\n\n \n\n● \nEducation: Bachelor’s degree in Computer\nScience, Information Technology, Engineering, or a related technical field.\n\n● \nLanguages & Scripting: Proficiency in Python, Bash, or similar scripting languages.\n\n● \nVersion Control: Basic experience with Git and collaborative development\nworkflows.\n\n● \nFoundational Knowledge: Understanding of cloud\nplatforms, CI/CD concepts, and Linux-based systems.\n\n● \nProblem-Solving: Strong troubleshooting and\nanalytical skills.\n\n● \nCollaboration: Good communication and\neagerness to work in an Agile, team-oriented environment.\n\nNice-to-Have Skills\n\n \n\n● \nFamiliarity with Docker and Kubernetes concepts.\n\n● \nExposure to Terraform, Ansible, or CloudFormation for infrastructure\nautomation.\n\n● \nUnderstanding of networking,\nsystem security, or cloud IAM fundamentals.\n\n● \nExperience with log management and\nmonitoring tools (Grafana, Prometheus, Datadog, etc.).\n\n● \nInternship or academic project\nexperience in DevOps, cloud, or system automation.\n\nSuccess Criteria\n\n \n\n● \nDemonstrates growing proficiency\nin CI/CD and infrastructure automation.\n\n● \nContributes to stable, repeatable,\nand secure deployment processes.\n\n● \nShows initiative in learning new\nDevOps tools and cloud technologies.\n\n● \nWorks collaboratively with\ncross-functional teams to improve delivery efficiency.\n\n● \nProduces high-quality\ndocumentation and configuration transparency.",
		info: "At\nNexus Cognitive, we are at the forefront of technological innovation, driving\ntransformative solutions in the world of data and analytics. Our mission is to\nenable your business to harness the power of big data, transforming complex\ndata sets into actionable insights that disrupt industries and deliver a\ncompetitive advantage for our clients. We are a trusted advisor that handles\nthe heavy lifting of big data management and governance, so our clients can\nfocus on making informed, strategic decisions that drive growth and innovation.\nNexus Cognitive firmly grasps the transformative power of data and artificial\nintelligence. We have a spirited team of\nemployees across the U.S. dedicated to redefining the boundaries of technology\nand cognitive solutions.",
