		details:
			"We are\nlooking for highly talented and ambitious individuals to join our Graduate\nProgramme as Development Engineers. During a 12-month learning journey, you’ll\nlearn from leaders, get involved in key projects, and build the skills to\npropel your career forward, as part of our Technology and Operations team. About\nour Technology & Operations Team Our\nTechnology & Operations (T&O) team is the powerhouse for the Bank. We\naim to go further, faster, to ensure we're agile and ready for tomorrow, today.\nOur diverse network enables us to innovate and build banking solutions\nthat support communities to prosper. We're a place where talented people are\nencouraged to grow, learn, and thrive, to drive their own career\njourneys, to reach their full potential. When you work with us, you’re\nprotecting the reputation and legacy of a 170 year organisation\nand building on it. We’re driven by progress and continuously\nevolving to ensure we’re agile and ready for tomorrow, today. About the Graduate Programme – how you’ll learn and growFrom\nday one, you’ll be immersed in real-world projects that matter. Our 12-month\ngraduate programme is designed to accelerate your development and set you up\nfor long-term success. You’ll benefit from:· \nStructured\nlearning: Classroom training combined\nwith hands-on experience· \nGlobal\ncollaboration: Work with diverse teams and\nexperienced leaders· \nSkill\ndevelopment: Build technical expertise and\nprofessional capabilities\n\nYour\nprogramme starts with an 8-week Technical Bootcamp that will equip you with the\nnecessary skills and understanding of technology architecture, programming\nlanguages, and how banking solutions can be rapidly designed and\ndelivered. What\nyou’ll be doing \n\n• \nDesign\n& development of robust banking software product development\n\n• \nDelivery\nquality software which meets the business requirements \n\n• \nWork\nin a truly agile environment, as part of scrum teams that are striving to solve\ncustomer challenges\n\n• \nParticipate\nin full software development lifecycle – requirements, design, implementation\nto deployment\n\n• \nTake\nfull ownership and responsibility for product development and delivery \n\n• \nHandling\nproblems reported from the field and coming up with quick resolution,\nworkaround, recovery, and fixes.",
		info: "The\nCTC will be INR 17.2 LPA where INR 15.6 LPA is Fixed and INR 1.5 LPA (10% of\nFixed) is annual performance bonus variable.\n\n \n\nWe will also provide relocation allowance of INR 1\nLakh and relocation benefits (like 15 days hotel accommodation, etc) to\nnon-local joiners.Medical Insurance of INR 7L over and above the\nCTC",
		reqs: "Eligibility\n\n \n\nWe’re interested in people with diverse backgrounds. To\nbe eligible for this role, you must be graduating from a Bachelor of\nEngineering course in 2026. You’ll also: \n\n \n\n· \nHave\nsome experience with programming algorithms, data structures, OOP concepts and\nframeworks, and database fundamentals. \n\n· \nHave\nsome knowledge and hands-on on experience in programming languages like C, C++,\nJava, Python, C#, or Dot Net.\n\n· \nBe\nfamiliar with design patterns, Microservices, UI frameworks – Angular, React,\nAI MS Office, MI & visualisation tools like Canva.\n\n· \nHave\nsome knowledge of tools & frameworks like Selenium, JMETER, LoadRunner.\n\n· \nBe\nanalytical, a critical thinker & have strong problem-solving ability\n\n· \nHave\nstrong interpersonal and consultative skills.No active backlogs are allowed and minimum CGPA to apply is 7.",
