			"About the roleAt Revolut, Operations means problem-solving at scale. Our team tackles the company’s toughest challenges with speed, precision, and creativity. They design systems that unlock efficiency and power global growth.About the Rev-celerator Graduate programme 🎓Are you a recent graduate eager to shape the future of financial technology? Ready to make a meaningful impact and bring innovative ideas to life? Well, the Rev-celerator Graduate Operations Manager programme is designed just for you.First, kick off with a few weeks of bootcamp, where we’ll prepare you to jump into work at Revolut with workshops, lectures, and practical exercises to start developing your skills. After successful preparation, we’ll launch you into on-the-job training where you’ll be face-to-face with tough challenges, problem-solving, and tasks to own.We're looking for a Graduate Strategy & Operations Manager to help us solve the toughest problems in our global fintech. Someone to roll up their sleeves and dive into every area of our business to help millions of customers worldwide.What you'll be doingWorking to optimise product or services to enhance internal or external customer experienceResearching and proposing new features to ensure a seamless customer experiencePerforming deep analysis and translating the outcomes into meaningful next steps for operational implementationDeveloping strategic relationships and participating in negotiationsContributing to product development efforts that are vital to delivering the best possible experience to Revolut customersLearning from industry leaders and participating in weekly meetings to stay aligned with team prioritiesManaging project tasks, tracking progress, and communicating key outcomesSharing updates about your work with our diverse global teamsAttending regular performance reviews to receive feedback and guide your developmentWhat you'll needA 2:1 predicted or achieved grade (or above)A degree in a STEM subjectTo have graduated university in 2024, 2025, or 2026Hands-on coding experience with SQL, Python, and/or RA magic skill to break complex problems into smaller onesTo enjoy working with dataNatural curiosity and a will to make an impactAn interest in the financial industryPrevious working experience or an internship at a top-tier investment banking/PE, strategy consultancy, or fast-growing tech companyFull-time availability for the programme starting in September 2026",
		info: "Ready to trade the textbooks for real-world experience? Join us and turn your big ideas into bold innovations. Operations at Revolut is about speed, precision, and impact. Our team doesn’t just keep things running – we lead change. Our interns and graduates are empowered to drive transformation from day one.At Revolut, we aspire to lead technological disruption in the financial sector and we are aware that our success will be linked to the value of our human capital. We are looking for profiles from all over the world to join our team. We want to continue growing and welcoming more professionals who share our passion for a multicultural and diverse environment. Your international career starts here 🌎 Top-performing graduates can look forward to a wide range of flexible working arrangements and exciting opportunities to relocate to one of our international hubs.As you grow with us, you’ll find that our rewards structure is fundamentally linked to to impact. A strong, measurable performance directly results in greater compensation and faster progression. Exceptional performers can look forward to an additional performance bonus of >90% of your annual gross salary. Your bonus will include Company Equity components, which means when Revolut wins big, you win big too.",
		reqs: "You must not have accumulated more than 2 years of working experience to qualify for our graduate programme.",
