		details:
			"Job Summary:We are looking for a fresh highly organized and detail-oriented Operations Executive to join our team in Mumbai. The Operations Executive will be responsible for coordinating and managing the operational activities within the Non-Vessel Operating Common Carrier (NVOCC) industry. The ideal candidate should have a solid understanding of logistics and shipping processes, excellent problem-solving skills, and the ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment.Responsibilities:Coordinate and manage the end-to-end operational activities related to NVOCC shipments, including documentation, booking, cargo handling, and delivery.Liaise with various stakeholders, including slot operators, agents, freight forwarders, and customers, to ensure smooth and timely execution of shipments.Prepare and process shipping documentation, including bills of lading or Delivery order and other required documents.Communicate with customers to provide shipment updates, resolve inquiries, and address any operational issues that may arise.Collaborate with internal teams, such as sales, customer service, and finance, to ensure seamless coordination and customer satisfaction.Coordinate with customers and ensure timely pickup of containers and delivery.Monitor and track shipment statuses using the company's online systems and tools, and provide regular updates to customers and stakeholders.Handle and resolve operational issues, such as delays, damages, and claims, in a timely and effective manner.Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of shipments, documentation, and customer interactions.Stay informed about industry regulations, shipping trends, and best practices to ensure compliance and optimize operational processes.",
		info: "Annual bonus as per performace upto 70,000/- as per last year record (Every year it may increase)Health insurance policies for confirmed team members covering their family.Petrol allowance for confirmed team members if they are coming by their own car.Subsidized lunchStar of the month amounting to Rs.1,00,000/- (if nominated)5 days of working (As per your profile, you may have to work from home on weekends on rotational basis)Good increments more than industry standards.2. Company's Training Facilities:One week of classroom training.Three weeks of on floor training.3. Important Note:After the CEO round is completed, we will issue a letter of intent inviting you to attend the training.The first week of training will serve as a screening process. On the fifth day, we will conduct an assessment to evaluate your learning ability and behavior. If we find a lack of interest or behavior that doesn’t align with our company culture, we may ask you to leave during the first week of training.After completing the first week of training, you will be introduced to on-the-job training, where we will provide a structured program to support you as you transition into your role.Upon finishing one month of training, we will evaluate your performance, provide feedback, and issue an offer letter, which will include a six-month probation period.4. Interview Process: It takes 2 days to complete the interview process from Quickfire round to CEO round.",
