		details:
			"Job Title: AI EngineerLocation: Mumbai /Work from officeCompany Overview:We are a next-generation AI-driven organization focused on building intelligent products and scalable solutions using cutting-edge technologies. We are looking for an AI Engineer from IIT Bombay who is passionate about Generative AI, LLMs, and building AI solutions from scratch.Role Overview:As an AI Engineer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and deploying end-to-end AI systems leveraging Large Language Models (LLMs), RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation), and Transformer architectures. You will work on building APIs, integrating models into production using FastAPI, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to bring innovative AI concepts to life.Key Responsibilities:Build, fine-tune, and deploy LLM-based models and Generative AI applications.Design and implement RAG pipelines for knowledge-grounded responses.Develop AI projects from scratch – data collection, preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and deployment.Utilize Transformer architectures (BERT, GPT, T5, etc.) for NLP and GenAI use cases.Create robust and scalable APIs using FastAPI for AI model serving.Collaborate with software engineers and product teams to integrate AI modules into live environments.Maintain project documentation and showcase work via GitHub repositories.Stay updated with advancements in Generative AI, LLM optimization, and MLOps.Required Skills & Qualifications:B.Tech / M.Tech in Computer Science or related field from IIT Bombay.Strong understanding of LLM Models, Transformer architectures, and Generative AI frameworks.Hands-on experience with Python, PyTorch/TensorFlow, LangChain, and Hugging Face Transformers.Practical knowledge of RAG implementations, Vector Databases (FAISS, Pinecone, Chroma), and Prompt Engineering.Experience in developing and deploying applications via FastAPI.Ability to build AI projects end-to-end with well-structured, documented code (GitHub link required).Familiarity with cloud platforms (AWS / GCP / Azure) and MLOps workflows is a plus.What We Offer:Opportunity to work on real-world Generative AI and LLM-driven products.Mentorship from top AI professionals and industry leaders.Exposure to full-stack AI development — from idea to deployment.A dynamic, innovation-first work culture.Application Requirement:Interested candidates must share:Updated ResumeGitHub Profile / Project Links demonstrating AI/LLM workShort note on a recent AI project built from scratchJob Title: AI EngineerCompany: Rx ConsultantsLocation: Mumbai / Work from officeAbout Rx Consultants:At Rx Consultants, we’re driving the next wave of innovation by integrating Artificial Intelligence into the healthcare and consulting ecosystem. We specialize in developing intelligent, scalable, and impactful AI-driven solutions that enhance decision-making and operational efficiency.We’re looking for an AI Engineer from IIT Bombay who is passionate about LLMs, Generative AI, and building AI systems from scratch.Role Overview:As an AI Engineer, you will design, develop, and deploy end-to-end AI and Generative AI solutions using LLM models, RAG pipelines, and Transformer architectures. You’ll collaborate closely with our tech and product teams to build intelligent systems that redefine the way data and automation power business decisions.Key Responsibilities:Build, fine-tune, and deploy LLM-based and Generative AI applications.Design and implement RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) frameworks for knowledge-grounded AI systems.Lead AI projects from scratch – from data preprocessing and model training to evaluation and deployment.Work with Transformer architectures (BERT, GPT, T5, etc.) to develop advanced NLP solutions.Develop and deploy FastAPI-based APIs for AI model integration and scalability.Collaborate with cross-functional teams to align AI deliverables with project goals.Maintain project repositories and contribute actively on GitHub.Stay current with advancements in LLM optimization, RAG pipelines, and MLOps best practices.Required Skills & Qualifications:B.Tech / M.Tech in Computer Science or related field from IIT Bombay.Strong foundation in LLM Models, Transformer architectures, and Generative AI frameworks.Proficiency in Python, PyTorch/TensorFlow, LangChain, and Hugging Face Transformers.Experience in building RAG pipelines and using Vector Databases (FAISS, Pinecone, Chroma, etc.).Skilled in developing scalable APIs using FastAPI.Proven ability to execute AI projects end-to-end (GitHub link required).Familiarity with cloud platforms (AWS/GCP/Azure) and MLOps is a plus.Why Join Us:Work on real-world Generative AI and LLM-based projects with direct impact.Opportunity to build AI solutions from scratch in a fast-growing innovation environment.Collaborative culture with mentorship from AI and domain experts.Exposure to AI in healthcare and enterprise automation use cases.",
