		details:
			"A. Position Details\n \n \n \n \n Position Title:\n \n \n Management Trainee\n \n \n \n \n Grade:\n \n \n Management Trainee \n \n \n \n \n Department:\n \n \n Marketing, Digital & Customer Experience\n \n \n \n \n Education Background\n \n \n B.Tech in Computer Science & Engineering or Information\n Technology\n \n \n\n \n\n \n \n B. About ICICI\n Prudential AMC & the AI & Analytics Team\n \n \n \n \n \n ICICI Prudential Asset Management stands as one of India's preeminent asset\n managers, entrusted with the financial goals of millions. We are not just\n participants in the market; we are dedicated to shaping its future.\n Our AI & Analytics team\n is the engine of innovation driving this mission. We are not a back-office\n support function; we are a strategic, front-line unit that partners with\n every part of the firm. Our mission is to build intelligent systems, optimize\n investment strategies, and redefine operational excellence through data.\n \n \n \n \n C. The Opportunity:\n Build the Future of Asset Management\n \n \n \n \n \n This is not your typical graduate role. This is a high-impact opportunity at\n the absolute nexus of finance and artificial intelligence. We are seeking a\n brilliant, hybrid thinker who refuses to be soiled into just tech or just\n finance, but is driven to master both.\n As a Management Trainee, you will be the critical bridge\n translating complex market dynamics into tangible, data-driven solutions. You\n will be coding, analyzing, and building, but you will also be a strategic\n partner, solving the core challenges that shape our investment decisions.\n \n \n\n \n\n \n \n D. What You Will\n Build & Own (Key Responsibilities)\n \n \n \n \n \n Translate complex market scenarios and investment theses into high-performance, predictive AI\n models using Python and advanced data analysis.\n Design, build, and deploy intelligent workflows using our modern stack (Python, SQL,\n Azure, and n8n) to automate processes and enhance decision-making\n across the firm.\n Pioneer the development and implementation of agentic AI systems to create\n entirely new, autonomous capabilities for our investment and operations\n teams.\n Partner directly with portfolio\n managers, business leaders, and market analysts to\n understand their most pressing, data-driven challenges and deliver\n robust, scalable solutions.\n \n \n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n \n E. The Ideal Candidate (Qualifications)\n \n \n \n \n Must-Have Technical Skills:\n \n Deep proficiency in Python\n and SQL for complex data analysis and application development.\n Hands-on experience with cloud\n platforms, specifically Azure.\n A strong, practical foundation in coding\n principles and data analysis.\n \n Must-Have Functional Skills:\n \n A solid understanding and high\n curiosity for the investment landscape and financial markets.\n Exceptional business acumen\n and first-principles problem-solving skills.\n \n Your Profile: You are a 'techno-functional'\n builder by nature. You don't just write code; you understand the business\n problem it solves. You are not intimidated by complex financial concepts; you\n are driven to model them. You are relentlessly curious, thrive on seeing your\n models create real-world value, and are ready to be on the cutting edge of AI\n development.\n \n \n \n \n \n F. Why Join Us?\n \n \n \n \n \n A competitive, all-inclusive\n compensation package of INR 18 lakhs per annum (structured as INR\n 16.5 lakhs fixed + an INR 1.5 lakh confirmation bonus upon successful\n completion of one year).\n Unmatched mentorship from senior leaders across both technology and finance, giving\n you a holistic view of the business.\n A true 'tip-of-the-spear' role, working on problems that define the future of India's\n InvestTech landscape.\n A structured, fast-track\n career path\n designed for high-impact performers to grow into future leaders.",
		info: "This is not your typical graduate role. This is a high-impact\n opportunity at the absolute nexus of finance and artificial intelligence. We\n are seeking a brilliant, hybrid thinker who refuses to be soiled into just\n tech or just finance but is driven to master both. The role demands 70% coding. \n \n \n\nAs a Management Trainee, you will be the critical bridge translating\ncomplex market dynamics into tangible, data-driven solutions. You will be\ncoding, analyzing, and building, but you will also be a strategic partner,\nsolving the core challenges that shape our investment decisions.Interest and knowledge in Agentic AI are a must. The company offers a robust 2 yr. management trainee journey with role-based learning interventions.",
