		details:
			"About UnifyApps:UnifyApps is an Agentic AI Platform for the Enterprise, headquartered in Gurugram, India. Our mission is to empower organizations to become AI-native enterprises—enabling them to securely and confidently operationalize AI at scale.Our horizontal platform unifies systems of record, knowledge, and activity, allowing enterprises to find data, reason with AI models, and act within business workflows. By bringing together low-code application development, workflow automation (iPaaS), data transformation (ETL/Reverse ETL), and GenAI/LLM-driven automation into a single platform, UnifyApps transforms stalled AI initiatives into production-grade, enterprise-ready solutions.Position Summary: At UnifyApps, our Platform Engineers are the backbone of our technical operations. In this role, you will focus on building the core infrastructure related to workflow orchestration, streaming, monitoring, and alerting. Also you will focus on building and maintaining core infrastructure for Large Language Model (LLM) applications. If you are passionate about creating scalable, efficient, and reliable backend systems, this is the role for you.Key Responsibilities:End-to-End Product Development: Constructs foundational infrastructure and pioneers new product capabilities from the ground up. At UnifyApps, we prioritize the creation of scalable and streamlined solutions over merely adding features. Every solution undergoes a comprehensive process, encompassing ideation, research, brainstorming, deployment, and culminating in both functional and load testing.Collaboration: Engage with fellow engineers and the Product Management team to discern requirements, strategize features, and architect scalable, technically sound solutions.Quality Assurance: Partner with the QA team to uphold product consistency and address potential issues.Lifecycle Management: Support the entire application lifecycle, from concept and design to testing, release, and ongoing support.Performance Optimization: Proactively troubleshoot and refine applications to enhance performance.Quality Control: Ensure both new and legacy applications adhere to our quality standards.System Oversight: Continuously monitor system health and performance metrics to preemptively identify potential issues.Alert Configuration: Set up, maintain, and fine-tune alerting rules to ensure timely notifications for abnormal system behavior or performance degradationIncident Response: Act promptly to alerts, ensuring that issues are addressed efficiently to minimize system downtime and maintain service quality.LLM Pipeline Infrastructure: Assist in designing and implementing infrastructure to support Large Language Model workflows, including prompt management systems, embedding generation pipelines, and model versioning systems.Documentation & Review: Maintain documentation of monitoring processes, alert thresholds, and incident response procedures. Periodically review and update these to adapt to system changes.Tool Integration: Ensure that monitoring and alerting tools integrate seamlessly with other tools in the system, such as logging or incident management tools.Interview Engagement: Participate in interviewing prospective team members, ensuring that candidates align with our technical requirements and company culture.Tech Trend Awareness: Stay updated with emerging technology trends and suggest innovative mobile products, applications, and protocols.Open-Source Engagement: Engage with the open-source community, advocating for and assisting in the implementation of crucial software enhancements.Team Dynamics: Be an active voice in design discussions, code reviews, and project-related team meetups.Skills & Qualifications:Experience: Familiarity with Java, with hands-on experience.Basic understanding of Large Language Models and popular frameworksCode Quality: Ability to maintain code and craft automated tests, ensuring top-tier product quality.Coding Best Practices: Proficiency in writing modular, reusable, well-documented, and thoroughly tested code.Backend Development & Technologies: Displays a strong inclination towards backend development and possesses a solid grasp of Workflow Automation, Apache Flink, Kubernetes, Quarkus, and MongoDB. Additionally, has knowledge of KV Stores, Distributed & In-Memory Caches, the complete web development lifecycle, and is familiar with either GraphQL or REST APIs.Tool Proficiency: Familiarity with popular monitoring and alerting tools like Prometheus, Grafana.Cloud Acumen: Understanding of cloud platform monitoring solutions, e.g., AWS CloudWatch, Azure Monitor, or Google Cloud Monitoring.Replication Strategies: Understand the different strategies for application replication and their trade-offs, especially within the context of Kubernetes (e.g., ReplicaSets, DaemonSets).Distributed Systems Acumen: Strong foundation in distributed system concepts such as consensus algorithms, distributed transactions, and CAP theorem.Availability Techniques: Proficiency in techniques to achieve high availability, including load balancing, health checks, and failover strategies.Analytical Skills: Ability to analyze monitoring data to discern patterns and insights.Problem Solving: Aptitude for diagnosing and rectifying bugs and performance issues in existing applications.Adaptable Learning: Eagerness to explore diverse realms and frameworks within backend development.Programming Paradigms: Knowledge of either functional or object-oriented programming.Third-party Integration: Expertise in working with third-party dependencies and debugging external code.Notification Management: Experience in managing and configuring notification channels like email, SMS, or platforms like Slack and Microsoft Teams for alerting.Tech Stack:JavaGraphQLSpring/QuarkusGRPCKafkaApache FlinkMongoDBKubernetesRedisGradlePrometheusGrafana",
