		details:
			"Engineering Trainee | Build the Future of Insurance Tech\n\nJoin us in redefining the insurance\nindustry with cutting-edge technology! We're looking for Engineering\nTrainees who thrive on building scalable systems from the ground up,\nenjoys working across the stack, and wants to be part of an incredible\n0 to 100 journey.\n\nRole: Engineering\nTrainee\n\nLocation: Mumbai\n\n—------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\n● Design and develop\nworld-class insurance tech solutions\nfrom the ground up\n\n● Work across the\nstack, from frontend (React/Next.js)\nto backend (Node.js / Python,\nTypeScript, APIs, databases)\n\n● Own features\nend-to-end – from API design to deployment, ensuring performance and\nscalability\n\n● Play a key role in\nshaping technical decisions, architecture, and best practices\n\n● \nIterate quickly based on user feedback, balancing\nspeed and scalability\n\nWhat We’re Looking For\n\nü Proficiency in React (or similar frontend frameworks),\nNode.js / Python, and TypeScript\n\nü Experience working with and building backend systems\nthat have been used in the real world\n\nü Ability to navigate different stages of product\ndevelopment – from scrappy MVPs to scalable architectures\n\nü Passion for\nbuilding customer-driven products\nand solving real-world problems\n\nThis is a\nrare opportunity to shape a product from the ground up, work with a stellar\nteam, and transform the insurance space with technology. If that excites you,\nwe’d love to chat! 🚀\n\n—------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nABOUT THE COMPANY\n\nKiwi\nGeneral Insurance\n\nWe want to revolutionize the insurance\nindustry with our focus on Customer and Technology. At Kiwi, we are passionate\nabout our customers and want to deliver customized products, simple processes\nand the best experience to them. We will leverage technology to enable the move\nfrom an “asset based” underwriting approach to a “customer based” underwriting\napproach to insurance.\n\n \n\nThe\nTeam behind Kiwi\n\nWestbridge Capital - One of the largest and most experienced investors of India,\nWestbridge have been investing in passionate entrepreneurs building stable and\nsustainable businesses in India, since 2000. With a current fund size over USD\n7.5bn, Westbridge firmly believes in and backs tech-enabled and tech-led Indian\nbusinesses for future growth.\n\n \n\nNeelesh Garg\n- A respected leader of India’s General Insurance industry, with more than 20\nyears in various leadership roles at ICICI Lombard and Tata AIG. One of the\nfounding team members, he went on to lead the Retail and International business\nat ICICI Lombard before joining Tata AIG as the MD & CEO. After leading\nTata AIG for nearly a decade, Neelesh has started Kiwi General Insurance with\nWestbridge Capital.\n\nSaurav Jaiswal - More than 20 years in the Insurance industry, leading various\nbusiness lines at companies like ICICI Lombard, Bharti AXA and Tata AIG, Saurav\nwas the COO at Tata AIG in his most recent role before joining the Kiwi General\nInsurance team as the MD & CEO designate.",
