		info: 'About the allowance1. Home AllowanceEmployees can reside in company-contracted rental properties under this system.・You can live in a property with a maximum rent of 70,000 yen, with a personal contribution of 9,000 yen.・The personal contribution is deducted from your salary.・This does not mean that an allowance of 61,000 yen is provided.・The 61,000 yen represents the company\'s contribution for a property with a maximum rent of 70,000 yen.・If you live in a property with a rent of 60,000 yen, the company\'s contribution will be 51,000 yen.・If the rent exceeds the limit, the excess amount plus the 9,000 yen will be your responsibility.・Therefore, the maximum amount the company will contribute is 61,000 yen.※This will vary depending on your actual rent. Cost to Company.2. Commutation AllowanceActual expenses (maximum JPY 51,500/month) will be reimbursed. 　Payment is made every six months.※This will vary depending on your actual amount of the company.3. Sign up BonusThe sign-up bonus will be paid as"Allowance for entering dormitory"&"Moving Allowance" in Japanese yen at the time of the initial salary payment. 4. Reserve fundEquivalent of 150,000 Japanese yen will be provided in the local currency as relocation reserve fund before relocation. "Reserve fund" is also referred to as "Preparation Allowance" within the company.5. Relocation SupportThe company covers the actual relocation expenses.If you can bring all your luggage on the plane, the company will cover these extra charges as Relocation Support.If the amount of luggage exceeds what can be brought on the plane, you can use sea shipment.The company will cover the sea shipment costs as Relocation Support.Please consult with us in advance if youuse sea shipment.Note: The company cannot cover both the extra baggage fees for the flight and the sea shipment costs.If you use sea shipment, please ensure no extra baggage fees occur for the flight (any excess fees will be your responsibility).6. Flight supportThe company covers the actual amount of flight expenses.7. Temporary Home Return SupportYou can take leave for home return twice a year.For each home return, you will be granted 5 days of special leave, in addition to your regular paid leave.The company covers the actual amount of round flight expenses twice a year.Temporary return support is available twice a year, but for employees joining in the second half of the year (October or later), it is only available once for the initial year.*For employees joining in October 2026, it can be used once between 2026/10 and 2026/3, twice between 2027/4 and 2028/3, and twice each year thereafter.Other Benefits・Qualification Support Program: We fully cover the examination fees and transportation expenses for obtaining qualifications specified in our internal regulations.・Learning Assistance Program: We provide licenses for services like Schoo to those interested.・Employee Stock Ownership Association / Defined Contribution Pension / Workplace Accumulated NISA (Nippon Individual Savings Account) / Savings Deposit Plan / Mutual Aid Association, etc.・Parental Leave Policy: Available until the child reaches 1 year old (can be extended up to 2 years).・Reduced Working Hours for Childcare: Available until the child completes 6th grade of elementary school.・Health Checkup Subsidy: We provide subsidies of up to ¥35,000 per session.・Influenza Vaccination Subsidy: We cover the costs for employees and their dependents.Expected joining date October 1st, 2026( It may be subject to change depending on visa status.)',
