			"We are seeking highly motivated engineers to join our R&D team in the field of predictive modeling for advanced semiconductor packaging. Currently, Resonac does not have an R&D base in India, but we are planning to establish a new predictive modeling center in India in the near future. Selected candidates will play a key role in building this new capability.\nBefore the India center becomes operational, successful candidates will undergo technical training and initial project work in Japan, working closely with our global R&D experts.\nResponsibilities:\n\nConduct multiphysics simulations (thermal, mechanical, warpage, reliability, etc.) for advanced semiconductor packaging structures such as 2.5D/3D integration, fan-out, and hybrid bonding.\n\nDevelop and validate predictive models for materials and processes to support design optimization and reliability improvements.\n\nCollaborate with global R&D teams to provide simulation-based insights for next-generation packaging solutions.\n\nLearning Opportunities:\n\nIntensive training in Japan on advanced modeling, simulation tools (e.g., ANSYS, COMSOL), and semiconductor packaging technologies.\n\nExposure to cutting-edge research projects in collaboration with leading global semiconductor companies.\n\nOpportunity to contribute to the creation of a new R&D base in India from the ground up.",
