		details:
			"Role Title: Management Trainee – UX DesignerDepartment: Digital PlatformsCompany: Bajaj Finance Limited Job Purpose:(A brief of the type of candidate we need to take on this role)To ideate & create suitable interactions & designs for various requirements for the assigned products. Work with internal domain experts like CX Analysts, UX Writers & UX POs to create creative and user-friendly visual solutions. Give feedback to designs coming in from the satellite design teams sitting with the COE teams. Work with the testing team to try out new designs and create new industry benchmarks using data-based designs.PRINCIPAL ACCOUNTABILITIES(Accountabilities associated with the job)1. Designing visually compelling and impactful creatives while adhering to our established design language as the foundational framework.2. Making sure your creations look good on all screen sizes with an understanding of responsive scaling and grid structures3. To be able to make stunning designs, you need an awareness of Colors, Typography, Layout & composition, spacing, materials & textures and a great aesthetic sense4. Adding micro interactions to your concepts can help launch them over the line5. Knowing the limitations that our tech team works with, will help your designs go all the way much faster.6. There’s a lot of great stuff happening out there everyday! Keeping up to date with it will help you stay on the top of your game. Being active and upto trends7. To be a project/track owner, you need to be decisive and good at absorbing critical feedback.8. You will need help to achieve your targets, and for that you need to be able to scout, rear, manage and guide vendor teams.9. You will help your team meet their potential by planning their Goals and KRAs to keep everyone on their sharp and ever ready.10. Evolving, upgrading and maintaining a design system is a very important part of both a Design ecosystem, and your responsibilities11. Understanding the business landscape, goals and the design requirements associated with it12. Understanding the customer behavior, needs and challenges faced by them13. Benchmarking online journeys with competitors and define best user experience for our product14. Mapping business requirements to design solutions15. Documenting requirements received via user stories or stakeholder meetings16. Planning and prioritizing for multiple ongoing requirements17. Managing stakeholders and their expectations from time to timeDECISIONS(Key decisions taken by job holder at his/her end)1. Decisions regarding planning of individual bandwidth and task prioritization2. Decisions on design solutioning for requirements3. Decisions regarding user experience journey4. Decisions on visual and usability options for requirementADDITIONAL SKILLSETS:1. “Function before form” they say, and that’s why it’s important for youto be able to understand the requirement that business comes up with and thesolution proposed by our UX experts2. Knowing how screens, components and other digital assets interact, transition and play out in front of the user is a skill that helps make your visuals complete3. “User centric design” is popular terminology these days, but you need to be able to run certain usability tests for your designs to be truly user centric4. Well versed with Figma, and utility plugins5. How best to use AI in your design thinking processMAJOR CHALLENGES(Challenges faced on an on-going basis in carrying out the job)1. Cross functional teams not responding on time thus impacting project delivery deadline2. Frequent changes in requirements, leading to rework3. Ad-hoc requirements from different stakeholders impacting planned tasksINTERACTIONS:(Key working relationships a job holder needs to have INSIDE and OUTSIDE the company to accomplish the job)Internal Clients:1. Other member of the design & DCX teams- CX Analysts- UX Writers- UX Product Owners- DCX Head- IED Head2. Vendor design resources3. Content team member4. Developers5. Product/Project Managers6. Function-Head (Marketing)7. COE/Business heads8. COE/Business SPOCsExternal Clients:1. Interact with vendors for resources, tools Etc.2. Other Finserv group companiesDIMENSIONS(Significant volume dimensions associated with the job)Total Team Size: 8-10Number of Direct Reports:Number of Indirect Reports:Number of Outsourced employees: 2-3Number of locations:1Number of products:2-3SKILLS:Educational Qualifications –(Minimum acceptable proficiency for this job which best indicates the education and/or experience requirements of this job and not the incumbent)B.Des/M.Des from a recognized design school or equivalent practical experience in visual/digital designing and frontend developmentExperience (Good to have) not mandatory.2-3 years of experience working as a Visual/Interaction Designer.The main focus of the experience should have been on Visuals, Interactions, Aesthetics & Usability. Experience collaborating with multidisciplinary UX/Product teams (motion, interaction, UX research,etc.) on technical implementationExperience implementing visual design systems across platforms in a software development environmentPreference given to candidates who have worked at tech firms and in large corporate format environments",
