		details:
			"TerraTern is the fastest-growing Global Talent Mobility Solution, dedicated to guiding clients through seamless relocation journeys. We offer personalized visa assistance, job search support, and comprehensive resources to empower individuals pursuing opportunities abroad. Our commitment to client satisfaction and transparency ensures a smooth, reliable experience at every step of the immigration process. Role Overview: We are seeking a dynamic and detail-oriented Associate Product Manager to join our growing team. In this role, you will work closely with cross-functional teams—including design, engineering, marketing, and operations—to build user-centric solutions that enhance our global mobility platform. You’ll be a key player in defining product features, gathering user feedback, and helping shape the future of our digital services. Key Responsibilities:Support the product lifecycle from ideation to launch, ensuring timely and high-quality deliverables.Collaborate with stakeholders to gather and define business and user requirements.Conduct market research and competitor analysis to identify trends and opportunities.Work with engineering and design teams to turn requirements into wireframes, user stories, and product specs.Analyze product performance using data-driven insights and suggest improvements.Prioritize features and maintain product backlog with a clear rationale for business impact.Ensure seamless communication across teams to meet product development goals. KPI (Key Performance Indicators):Timely delivery of product milestones.Customer satisfaction and engagement metrics.Product adoption and usage rates.Reduction in user complaints and support tickets.Quality and clarity of product documentation and user stories. Eligibility:0–2 years of experience in Product Management or a related role (internships count!).Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.Excellent communication and organizational abilities.Familiarity with Agile methodologies and product management tools (e.g., Jira, Trello, Figma).Passion for technology and global mobility solutions is a strong plus. Why Join TerraTern: Impactful Work: Assist individuals in achieving their global mobility goals by guiding them through the entire process.Professional Growth: Learn from our industry experts and access continuous training about the latest immigration trends and product best practices.Entrepreneurial Culture: You have authority and ownership in your role. Share ideas, try new solutions and more.Work-Life Balance: Hybrid work arrangements that take care of your well-being.Collaborative Environment: Be part of an enthusiastic team eager for collaboration and excellence.Your Move So, want to be part of this exciting journey? Apply now!",
