		process:
			"Resume and portfolio filtering | Take home assignment (120:00) | Culture and taste interview (00:45) | Personal interview (00:30)",
		details:
			"About Chronicle: Cursor for Slides\nChronicle is the modern format of presentations, an AI-native platform that blends the craft of world-class designers and storytellers to help teams communicate with clarity and impact. Founded by IIT Bombay alumni Mayuresh and Tejas, the company’s roots lie in a deep understanding of storytelling and visual communication. During his time at IIT Bombay, Mayuresh packed lecture halls teaching students how to create compelling decks and was a core contributor to Case Interviews Cracked, the flagship consulting case book that remains a go-to resource for interview prep. This passion eventually evolved into building Chronicle. With prior experience in consulting and growth, the founders bring a mix of analytical and creative thinking to everything they build.A fully remote team backed by Accel and angel investors from Google, Stripe, Slack, and Facebook ($7.5M seed), the company launched to a waitlist of 100,000+ users, onboarded 6,000+ teams, and was named #1 Product of the Month on Product Hunt. Today, hundreds of decks are shared daily by founders, agencies, and global teams who call it the “Cursor for Slides.” Experience it for yourself → Try ChronicleLearn more about why we created Chronicle → Our story\n\nYou can also view a sample deck here on desktop: Intro to ChronicleAbout the roleBeing an Associate Product Designer at Chronicle is about shaping the future of how people tell stories and share ideas.You’ll work with a small team obsessed with design and storytelling. You’ll learn to think deeply about product and apply the principles of human-computer interaction, systems thinking, and information visualisation. You’ll explore how interaction design, visual communication, motion, and information architecture come together to create experiences that feel seamless and expressive.This is a full-time opportunity for recent graduates who want to work at the intersection of design, storytelling, and technology.Core responsibilities of this role →\nWork on designing new features of our core product\nContribute to the end-to-end design of new widgets and product features\nOwn the user experience across flows, components, and interactions - balancing beautiful visuals, usability, craft, and performance\nCollaborate closely with engineering to bring ideas to life with precision, usability, and craft\nHelp evolve Chronicle’s visual and interaction language, shaping how components, motion, and systems scale across the product\nParticipate in design critiques, share explorations, and help shape Chronicle’s design culture\n\nAs one of our first early-career design hires, you’ll work on real product challenges and help define the foundation of a new design system that thousands of storytellers will use daily.This is a remote, full-time role. Our team is spread across the US, India, and Australia.Must haves\nExperience in using Figma to design workflows, systems, components and prototype for rapid iteration\nA portfolio that demonstrates information design and product design\nAbility to distill complex data or narratives into elegant, instantly understandable visual systems\nObsess over visual hierarchy, proportion, and the relationship between content and context\nCan think deeply about how information can be visualised using - motion, interaction, and visuals\nLove working at the intersection of design and storytelling\nStrong visual and interaction design skills, with a proven ability to sweat the details that elevate product experiences\nFirst-principles problem solver with a bias for simplicity and clarity\nGreat to have\n\nExposure to motion design, micro-interactions, or data visualisation\nUnderstanding of front-end basics (HTML, CSS, Tailwind)\nExperience with AI-tools and creative technologies\nPrior internship or project experience building interactive prototypes or digital tools\nContributions to creative or design communities\nWhy join us\nEverything starts with a story. We are reimagining how the world tells their’s - and we want you to shape that future with us. We are passionate to help anyone deliver presentations that are not just bearable, but enjoyable.\n\nWork on a category-defining product in a $100B+ marketWe are a design led company with an appreciation of great product taste. Think of it as joining the next Notion, Figma or Linear. We offer an opportunity to build the next big productivity tool with some of the smartest people in the spaceWe are remote from day one and support you to work from wherever you want by covering your home office expenses (₹1,00,000), hooking you up with the latest technologyWe enable ownership. From day 1 of your time at Chronicle you will have the opportunity to own, lead and contribute to the company in more ways than just your core roleLead medium to large features end to end → you will be given end to end responsibility to lead medium to large features along with product (founder led) and design teamBringing craft into the execution → you will have plenty of opportunity to add your personality into how you bring a feature to life - especially in pouring love into micro-interactions and detailsLearn new skills → whether you want to pick up a new tool or skillset or want to learn being a leader - we will invest in you\nWe work flexibly and do not believe in driving work through forced accountability. We try to hire only the best and give them the flexibility and space to do their life’s best work at ChronicleWe offer competitive salaries, significant ESOPs and have open and transparent conversations about your compensation",
