		details:
			"About ChronicleChronicle is the modern format of presentations, an AI-native platform that blends the craft of world-class designers and storytellers to help teams communicate with clarity and impact. Founded by IIT Bombay alumni Mayuresh and Tejas, the company’s roots lie in a deep understanding of storytelling and visual communication. During his time at IIT Bombay, Mayuresh packed lecture halls teaching students how to create compelling decks and was a core contributor to Case Interviews Cracked, the flagship consulting case book that remains a go-to resource for interview prep. This passion eventually evolved into building Chronicle. With prior experience in consulting and growth, the founders bring a mix of analytical and creative thinking to everything they build.A fully remote team backed by Accel and angel investors from Google, Stripe, Slack, and Facebook ($7.5M seed), the company launched to a waitlist of 100,000+ users, onboarded 6,000+ teams, and was named #1 Product of the Month on Product Hunt. Today, hundreds of decks are shared daily by founders, agencies, and global teams who call it the “Cursor for Slides.” Find out more about the company here: Intro to Chronicle and experience it for yourself: Try ChronicleAbout the RoleShip features with a mentor: Pair with a senior engineer to deliver product features from spec to production. Own well scoped components or flows, write high quality code, and see work through QA and rolloutTranslate design into resilient UI: Implement responsive layouts, typography, motion, and micro-interactions from Figma with pixel-level careHarden quality and performance: Use DevTools to profile and debug. Add thoughtful tests for critical pathsCollaborate tightly with design and product: Deep dive on design problems, consider broader impacts define and implement solutions that align with architectural standardsClose the loop with users: Triage UI bugs, fix polish issues, and learn to connect engineering decisions to user outcomes\nRequirements\n\nEvidence of craft: A portfolio, repo, or open-source work that shows taste and finish. This can be internships, freelance projects, personal apps, or open-source contributions related to frontend toolsStrong HTML and CSS: Fluency with layout, spacing, typography, responsive design, and component driven stylingPractical JavaScript or TypeScript: Comfort with modern JS and at least one component model such as React. You can break a problem into small composable piecesFirst principles problem-solving: Ability to understand problems deeply, come up with elegant, simple solutions and take end-to-end ownership to bring these to life. Comfortable picking up new stacks and choosing the right tool for the jobDesign sense: Literacy in visual or motion designWhy join usEverything starts with a story. We are reimagining how the world tells their’s - and we want you to shape that future with us. We are passionate to help anyone deliver presentations that are not just bearable, but enjoyable.Work on a category-defining product in a $100B+ marketWe are a design led company with an appreciation of great product taste. Think of it as joining the next Notion, Figma or Linear. We offer an opportunity to build the next big productivity tool with some of the smartest people in the spaceWe are remote from day one and support you to work from wherever you want by covering your home office expenses (₹1,00,000), hooking you up with the latest technologyWe enable ownership. From day 1 of your time at Chronicle you will have the opportunity to own, lead and contribute to the company in more ways than just your core roleLead medium to large features end to end → you will be given end to end responsibility to lead medium to large features along with product (founder led) and design team.Bringing craft into the execution → you will have plenty of opportunity to add your personality into how you bring a feature to life - especially in pouring love into micro-interactions and details.Learn new skills → whether you want to pick up a new tool or skillset or want to learn being a leader - we will invest in youWe work flexibly and do not believe in driving work through forced accountability. We try to hire only the best and give them the flexibility and space to do their life’s best work at ChronicleWe offer competitive salaries, significant ESOPs and have open and transparent conversations about your compensation",
