		details:
			"At Aarvee Engineering Consultants, we are moving beyond traditional engineering. We are building the next generation of Digital Twins — dynamic, living replicas of our complex systems. Among our digital engineering undertakings we are creating pioneering software and deploying AI/ML tools to make the design and operations of rail, roads and urban systems intelligent, sustainable and safer. We are looking for four distinct types of innovators to help us build a platform that doesn't just visualize the problem, but understands it.",
		info: 'Information for Students\nAt Aarvee, we believe young engineers are the drivers of tomorrow’s infrastructure. As you explore career opportunities with us, here are a few key points to help you prepare and understand what to expect:\nPerks & Opportunities Beyond Compensation\n\nWork on global infrastructure projects across 20+ countries.\n\nEarly responsibility — young engineers often lead project components from day one.\n\nExposure to multidisciplinary teams across Railways, Highways, Water, Urban Planning, Energy, Geospatial, Digital Engineering, and more.\n\nIn-house digital tools including LiDAR, BIM, GIS, and 3D modelling, giving you hands-on experience with modern engineering technologies.\n\nChance to collaborate with international funding agencies like ADB, World Bank, AIIB, KfW.\n\nCompany Culture\n\nEntrepreneurial, collaborative, and merit-driven — "There is no I in Aarvee, only V."\n\nA culture built on teamwork, innovation, and technical excellence.\n\nSupportive environment where curiosity is encouraged and effort is rewarded.\n\nOpen, professional workspace with opportunities for cross-functional learning.\n\nTraining & Development\n\nStructured induction program to familiarize you with tools, teams, and project workflows.\n\nRole-specific technical training delivered by senior experts.\n\nContinuous learning through project rotations, mentoring, digital engineering labs, and internal knowledge-sharing sessions.\n\nCareer growth pathways that help you transition from trainee to project lead with clear milestones.\n\nGuidance for Screening & Selection\n\nBrush up on core engineering concepts (branch-specific): structural analysis, survey basics, transportation, hydraulics, geotechnical fundamentals, etc.\n\nExpect assessments on analytical ability, problem-solving, and basic engineering aptitude.\n\nFor interviews, focus on clarity of thought, fundamentals, willingness to learn, and real-world application of concepts.\n\nHighlight internships, project work, design tools, software exposure, or any hands-on experience.',
