		details:
			"About the Role\nWe are looking for enthusiastic and driven Individuals to join our Innovation Hub—a cross-functional team that explores, experiments, and implements the latest technologies across Construction, Materials, MEP, Structures, and Sustainability.\nThis role is ideal for those who are curious, hands-on, and excited about shaping the future of construction. As an Innovation Hub team member, you will work closely with senior engineers, support innovation projects, and gain a holistic understanding of modern construction technologies and practices.Key Responsibilities\n\nExplore emerging construction technologies such as modular construction, precast systems, digital twins, IoT-enabled solutions, drones, and automation tools.\n\nSupport pilot projects and proof-of-concept initiatives for new materials, building systems, and sustainable innovations.\n\nConduct research studies, benchmarking, and market scans to identify opportunities for improvement and adoption.Assist Civil, Structural, MEP, and Materials teams with technical reports, data analysis, and feasibility assessments.\n\nParticipate in design coordination, drawing reviews, and clash detection using digital engineering tools.Evaluate materials, products, and systems from a sustainability and environmental perspectives.Assist in testing, validating, and documenting performance of new construction materials.\n\nCoordinate with labs, vendors, and internal teams for material trials and quality assessments.\n\nCompile insights, findings, and recommendations for review by leadership.Visit project sites to observe real-time construction processes and challenges.\n\nCollect technical data, support implementation of pilot technologies, and provide on-ground assistance.\n\nGain practical exposure to field engineering, quality processes, and site operations.\n\nEducational Background\n\nB.E./B.Tech in Civil Engineering, Construction Technology, Mechanical (for MEP), Structural Engineering, Environmental/Sustainability Engineering, Materials Science, or related fields.\n\nSkills & Qualities\n\nStrong foundational understanding of Civil, MEP, and Structural engineering concepts.\n\nGenuine curiosity for new materials, technologies, and sustainable construction practices.\n\nAnalytical mindset with strong problem-solving abilities.\n\nComfort working with cross-functional and multidisciplinary teams.\n\nClear communication and good documentation skills.\n\nEagerness to learn, collaborate, experiment, and contribute to innovation initiatives.",
