		details:
			"Please find\nbelow is the Jd for Technical Support Executive .\n\nProduction\nSupport Engineer Roles and Responsibilities\n\nManaging\nincidents:\nWhen software products fail to function as expected, production support\nengineers identify, diagnose, and escalate it to L3. \n\nPreparing\nand documenting reports: These engineers prepare and maintain up-to-date\ndocumentation of systems and procedures, and other relevant information. \n\nTroubleshooting\nissues:\nProduction support engineers analyse various metrics and logs to understand the\nreason for system failure or non-performance.\n\nCollaborating\nwith other departments: Production support engineers collaborate with various\ncross-functional teams and work with developers, system administrators and\nsoftware engineers to solve production issues. Providing update senior leaders\nabout the system status and share timely resolution progress.\n\nEnhancing\nsystem performance:\nProduction support engineers identify potential improvement areas in the\nproduction system. Based on their skills, they implement suggestions.\n\nTraining\nnew employees:\nThese engineers guide new employees on using production support software\npackages.\n\nOther\nRoles and Responsibilities:\n\nMonitoring\napplications and infrastructure alerts and reacting quickly.\n\nRecommending\nand implementing solutions to mitigate repeat product issues.\n\nTaking\nownership and responding to open support tickets\n\nClosing\nopen support tickets by adhering to the production support service level\nagreements\n\nIdentifying\nand implementing automation opportunities to ensure success.\n\nPrimary\nResponsibilities: \n\n3+ years of\nstrong production support (L2 support) experience.\n\nWorking\nKnowledge in Linux, and Database (SQL, MySQL etc.) is must.\n\nTake\nownership of user problems and be proactive when dealing with user issues.\n\nMonitor all\nalerts and report any issue that may significantly impact the business.\n\nMonitoring,\nanalysing, troubleshooting problems to enhance application availability and\nperformance in production.\n\nFollow\nestablished set of processes while handling issues and for proper escalation of\nunresolved issues to appropriate internal/external teams.\n\nMaintain\nlogs of all issues and ensure resolutions according to quality assurance tests\nfor all production processes.\n\nEnsure\non-time delivery of all assigned tasks – incidents, problem tickets, etc.\n\nAdhere to\nthe defined support delivery process/guidelines like Problem.\n\nIdentify\nand learn more about the software and hardware used/ supported by the\norganization.\n\nExperience\nin Finance domain preferred.\n\nRelease Management, deployment management preferred.\n\nWork independently, to be able to\ncommunicate effectively with users, and development and support teams during\ndowntimes and when",
