		details:
			"Software Developer\nCompany: PhotonX Technologies Pvt. Ltd.\nLocation: Hyderabad (On-site)\nAbout PhotonX\nPhotonX Technologies is a Hyderabad-based technology company specialising in innovative software development and digital transformation. We build high-performance digital platforms for clients across industries, combining solid engineering with thoughtful design.\nRole Overview\nAs a Software Developer (Fresher), you’ll learn, build, and ship production-quality software under the guidance of senior engineers. You’ll work across the stack (based on project needs) and contribute to real-world products from day one.\nEligibility\n\nFinal-year or recently graduated students in CSE/IT or related engineering disciplines\n\nMinimum 75% or 7.5 CGPA\n\nStrong grasp of DSA, OOP, and core CS fundamentals\n\nDemonstrated problem-solving skills (projects, competitions, internships, or GitHub work)\n\nPassion for technology and eagerness to learn\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nDevelop clean, maintainable code for web and backend services\n\nCollaborate with mentors to design, implement, test, and deploy features\n\nWrite unit tests and participate in code reviews\n\nWork with APIs, databases, and cloud services as per project requirements\n\nDocument work and follow Agile practices (standups, sprints, retros)\n\nTech You May Work With (project-dependent)\n\nBackend: Node.js / Python (FastAPI/Django) / Java (Spring)\n\nFrontend: React / Next.js, HTML/CSS/JS\n\nDatabases: PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, Redis\n\nDevOps/Cloud: Git/GitHub, Docker, CI/CD, AWS/GCP basics\n(Exposure to any of the above is a plus; training provided.)\n\nMust-Have Skills\n\nSolid programming fundamentals (DSA, OOP, DBMS, OS, Networks)\n\nAbility to learn new technologies quickly\n\nClear communication and a collaborative mindset\n\nAttention to detail and ownership of tasks\n\nGood-to-Have (Optional)\n\nInternship experience or notable academic/side projects\n\nBasic knowledge of REST APIs, Git workflows, and unit testing\n\nParticipation in hackathons/coding contests; open-source contributions\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nStructured training & mentorship program\n\nExposure to cutting-edge tech and live projects\n\nCollaborative, high-growth environment\n\nCompetitive compensation and a clear growth path\n\nSelection Process\n\nOnline Assessment: Aptitude + DSA (MCQ/coding)\n\nTechnical Interview(s): Problem-solving, core CS, and project deep-dive\n\nCulture/Managerial Round: Communication, teamwork, and ownership\n(Campus TPOs will receive detailed schedules and formats.)\n\nApplication Instructions (Campus)\n\nEligible students to submit: Resume + Transcript + Project Links (GitHub/Portfolio) via the TPO or the provided form\n\nShortlisted candidates will receive assessment invites via email\n\nStart Date\n\nImmediate to 60 days from offer (flexible for final-semester exams)\n\nEqual Opportunity\nPhotonX Technologies is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.",
