		details:
			"About the company:Harness.io is a modern DevOps and software delivery platform that helps teams automate the entire CI/CD process — from code build and testing to deployment, verification, and cost optimization.\nFounded in 2017 by Jyoti Bansal (of AppDynamics fame), it uses AI and automation to make deployments safer, faster, and more efficient. Its main modules include:\n\nContinuous Integration (CI) – automated builds and tests\n\nContinuous Delivery (CD) – deployment pipelines with rollback options\n\nContinuous Verification – monitors releases for issues\n\nFeature Flags & Cloud Cost Management\n\nHarness competes with tools like Jenkins, GitLab, and Argo, standing out for its simplicity and AI-driven automation.About the Role:\nWe are looking for passionate and motivated fresh graduates to join our engineering team. As a Software Engineer, you’ll work closely with senior developers to design, develop, test, and maintain scalable software solutions. This is a great opportunity to learn, grow, and contribute to real-world projects in a collaborative environment.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nDesign, code, test, and debug software applications.\n\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams (Product, QA, DevOps) to deliver high-quality solutions.\n\nParticipate in code reviews and learn best engineering practices.\n\nWrite clean, efficient, and maintainable code.\n\nContribute to documentation and continuous improvement initiatives.\n\nRequirements:\n\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.\n\nGood understanding of data structures, algorithms, and object-oriented programming.\n\nKnowledge of at least one programming language such as Java, Python, JavaScript, C++, or Go.\n\nFamiliarity with version control (Git) and basic software development lifecycle concepts.\n\nStrong problem-solving and analytical skills.\n\nEagerness to learn new technologies and frameworks.\n\nNice to Have:\n\nExposure to web development, cloud platforms, or databases.\n\nInternship or project experience in software development.\n\nWhat We Offer:\n\nMentorship from experienced engineers.\n\nExposure to modern tech stacks and agile processes.\n\nOpportunity to work on impactful, real-world products.\n\nA supportive and inclusive learning environment.Location - Bangalore (2 days Work from office , 3 days hybrid)",
