		details:
			"About 12 Flags12 Flags is a global investment firm founded by Rakesh Kapoor, former Global CEO of Reckitt - the $50 billion consumer goods giant behind brands like Dettol, Harpic, and Durex. We invest in early growth start-ups (Series A/B) in India with a focus on consumer-tech, D2C brands, retail, and healthcare sectors. We have presence in London, Dubai, Bangalore, and Delhi NCR.The RoleWe are looking for an Investment Analyst to join our team. This is a unique opportunity to work in a small, high-velocity environment where you will have direct exposure to the investment life cycle and play a central role working directly with the partners.What You Will DoSourcing & NetworkingIdentify, meet and build long-term relationships with the most promising founders building consumer-facing businesses across consumer brands, retail, healthtech and consumer internet.Develop a personal network with angels, VCs, and ecosystem operators to deepen market access.Thesis DevelopmentBuild structured, conviction-led theses on categories shaping the future of consumption in IndiaBenchmark Indian opportunities against global consumer innovations and derive actionable insightsIdentify emerging trends and track early signals, whitespace opportunities, and competitive dynamicDue DiligenceDive deep into startups’ metrics, unit economics, and retention modelsRun structured company assessments, customer and ecosystem references, and competitor analysesForm a differentiated point of view business quality and scalability, and translate the same into underwriting business modelPortfolio SupportWork closely with portfolio founders on key strategic and growth initiativesTrack performance and assist with board-level materials and portfolio strategyAdditional Information:At 12 Flags, the Investment Analyst program is designed as a high-intensity, high-reward launchpad for young professionals who want to shape the future of India’s consumer and technology ecosystem — as founders, investors, or operators. With a lean team structure, analysts get direct exposure to the entire investing lifecycle — from spotting emerging categories and building theses benchmarked against global analogues, to engaging with hundreds of founders and driving deep evaluations where your independent view truly matters. The program combines the right balance of breadth (access to diverse business models and innovation) with depth (developing conviction through data, references, and competitive insights), ensuring a steep learning curve and accelerated growth.The culture at 12 Flags is best described as a “outperformance through ownership” — where every Analyst works closely with the partners, owns workstreams early, and learns to balance founder empathy with sharp business judgment. We don’t measure success by the volume, but by the conviction of insights you build and outcomes you generated. Intellectual honesty, curiosity about consumer behavior, and the courage to form and evolve your own views are the traits we value most. For the right candidate, this is a rare opportunity to work in a small, high-trust team, contribute meaningfully from day one, and grow into a future leader in the private investing ecosystem.",
