		details:
			"About Us\nSlikk is a fast-growing e-commerce company committed to delivering products in 60 minutes. With a rapidly evolving catalog, seasonal collections, and dynamic inventory, we blend technology, data, and creativity to redefine how fashion and lifestyle products reach customers. We’re looking for a Data Analyst to join our team and play a crucial role in driving data-backed decision-making across business, product, and operations.\n\nRole Overview\nAs a Data Analyst at Slikk, you will be responsible for collecting, analyzing, and interpreting large datasets to uncover actionable insights. You will help optimize merchandising, inventory, customer acquisition, and operational efficiency through data-driven recommendations. This role is ideal for someone who thrives in fast-paced, high-growth environments and is passionate about using data to solve real-world business problems.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nWork closely with business, product, and operations teams to define metrics, measure performance, and identify growth opportunities.\n\nAnalyze user behavior, sales trends, and inventory movement to drive actionable insights for marketing and category teams.\n\nBuild and maintain dashboards and automated reports to support decision-making across functions.\n\nConduct deep-dives into key performance areas (e.g., conversion, retention, delivery performance) to identify root causes and improvement levers.\n\nSupport demand forecasting, pricing, and assortment planning using statistical and machine learning models.\n\nTranslate complex data into simple, visual, and compelling stories through dashboards, presentations, and reports.\n\nEnsure data integrity by validating sources, cleaning datasets, and maintaining analytical consistency across systems.\n\nCollaborate with engineering teams to define data requirements, pipelines, and analytics tracking for new product features.\n\nContinuously evaluate and improve data quality, accessibility, and reporting processes.\n\nRequired Skills and Qualifications\n\nBachelor’s or Master’s degree in a quantitative field (Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Economics, Engineering, or related discipline).\n\nStrong proficiency in SQL and data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI.\n\nProficiency in Python for data manipulation, analysis, and automation.\n\nGood understanding of statistical analysis, experimentation (A/B testing), and hypothesis-driven research.\n\nExperience working with large datasets and cloud-based data warehouses (e.g., BigQuery, Redshift, Snowflake).\n\nExcellent problem-solving skills and a keen eye for patterns, trends, and anomalies in data.\n\nAbility to communicate insights effectively to technical and non-technical stakeholders.\n\nA self-starter mindset, comfortable working with ambiguity and delivering high-quality work under tight timelines.\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nCompetitive salary and benefits.\n\nA high-impact role in shaping how data informs decisions at Slikk.\n\nOpportunity to work cross-functionally with product, marketing, and operations teams.\n\nA collaborative and fast-paced environment with room for rapid professional growth.\n\nBe part of a passionate, data-driven team building one of India’s fastest commerce experiences.",
		info: "Slikk is the fastest growing lifestyle app in India providing trendiest fashion, beauty & accessories in under 60 mins. We're a Series A company on a high growth trajectory. We are a small bunch of team focused on improving lifestyle experience in India. We need people who are motivated by our mission and want to work for a start-up in building systems from scratch to scale. You get opportunity to work with the best talent from the industry and learn by building fast and correct.",
