		process:
			"Resume filtering | Pre-placement Talk (00:45) | Screening Test - Offline (01:30) | Personal Interview – Offline (HR & Technical) (01:00) | Personal Interview – Online via MS Teams (HR & Technical) (00:30)",
		details:
			"ABOUT\nRELSAFE PRA CONSULTING (PART OF ASSYSTEM GROUP)The recognition \nof nuclear power as \na reliable, low-carbon \nenergy source to\nmitigate the impacts of climate change has led to renewed global interest in\nnew nuclear power plant constructions (both, large\nNPPs & SMRs) and upgrades to existing ones. RELSAFE PRA Consulting\n(referred to as RELSAFE) is a specialized\nconsulting company providing technical advisory services in the niche\narea of nuclear safety assessment, for \nutilities/power plants, regulatory authorities \n& EPCs globally. RELSAFE has been a reliable and long-term strategic partner to various stakeholders in Europe,\nespecially in Switzerland, France & Belgium, South Africa \nand the United \nArab Emirates. RELSAFE also \nprovides advisory and training support to clients in Sweden,\nJapan, Korea, Argentina & Spain and to the International Atomic Energy\nAgency (IAEA). RELSAFE is \npart of the \nAssystem Croup, a \nmulti-national company headquartered in\nFrance, having more than 7500 employees spread across 12 countries. Assystem is \nplaying a leading \nrole in the fight \nagainst climate\nchange, helping governments and clients meet their energy transition\naspirations with engineering, project\nmanagement and digital services. Assystem has been ranked as one of the top 3\nindependent nuclear engineering companies in\nthe world. \n\nBesides \nnuclear, RELSAFE also aims \nto progressively expand services to other industries\nsuch as space, green hydrogen, data centres, etc.\nReliability/Availability Analysis and Quantitative Risk Assessment also form\npart of our service profile. JOB\nOVERVIEW\n\nRELSAFE is currently\nlooking for dynamic and enthusiastic engineers for the position of “Safety\nConsultant.” We seek candidates with strong engineering, analytical, and\nlogical reasoning skills and aptitude.\n\nAs a Safety Consultant, the\nengineer will undergo an initial training phase in nuclear safety concepts and\nsubsequently engage in diverse safety assessment projects. They will assist in\nthe timely execution and delivery of projects in accordance with established QA\nprocedures. This position also provides opportunities to interact with senior\nexperts in the industry. INCENTIVES\nOF WORKING WITH USJOB\nRESPONSIBILITIESPerform assigned technical tasks per\nrequirements from team/project managers and clients, ensuring quality, schedule\nadherence, and client satisfaction.Understand and analyse inputs received from\nclients; identify and record observations, and provide solutions and\nsuggestions to address any gaps.Support detailed modelling, simulations, and\nanalytical work.Assist in preparing detailed technical\nreports and presentations.Support preparation, enhancement, and\nmanagement of organisational templates, marketing materials, and in-house tools\nto automate project/business tasks.Ensure strict adherence to company policies.\n\nSKILLS/QUALIFICATIONSWe invite applications from\ncandidates who meet the requirements outlined below:A graduate degree in core engineering\ndisciplines (Mechanical / Electrical / Electronics) from reputed institutions\n(IITs, NITs and other top-rated deemed institutions);Academic scores of above 80% in SSC / HSC\nand CGPA equivalent to First Class or above in Bachelor's degree with no\nhistory of arrears;Should possess good technical knowledge on\ncore engineering subjects in respective disciplines;Proficiency in MS Office tools such as\nExcel, Word, Access, PowerPoint, etc.;Proven interest towards programming\nlanguages such as Visual Basic/SQL/Python, etc. is an added advantage;Excellent analytical, interpersonal,\ncommunication and presentation skills (written and verbal);Excellent proficiency in English;Good attention to detail and positive,\nproactive and enthusiastic approach towards work with flexibility;Ability to work effectively and\nprofessionally across different cultural environments;Ability to work in multi-disciplinary\nprojects;Flexibility to travel according to\ncompany’s/client’s requirements;Willingness to take initiative and\ncontinuously learn;Ability to speak/write languages like\nFrench/German is an added advantage.",
		info: "At\nRELSAFE PRA Consulting (part of Assystem Group), we offer a collaborative and\nlearning-oriented environment where young engineers can build expertise in\nnuclear safety and reliability assessment. New recruits undergo structured\ntraining in core engineering analysis, nuclear safety concepts, and technical\ndocumentation practices. The work involves analytical studies, including\nprobabilistic and deterministic safety assessments, system reliability\nevaluations, and preparation of technical safety reports for major utilities\nand nuclear plants in Switzerland, France, Belgium, and other countries.A\ncareer at RELSAFE offers opportunities to contribute to prestigious\ninternational projects. We value customer focus, flexibility, and commitment to\nachieve both personal and organizational goals. Assignments may involve travel\nor short-term deputations to client or group company offices. Growth is driven\nby skills, capability, and willingness to go the extra mile.The\ninitial probation period is six months, following which confirmation is based\non performance. Considering the investment made in training and to ensure\nproject continuity, a two-year service agreement applies. In case an employee\nresigns before completing this period, an amount equivalent to six months’\ngross salary is payable to the company.In\naddition to CTC, employees are covered under Group Mediclaim Health Insurance\n(INR 300,000 /year) for self, spouse, and up to two children.For\ndata security and productivity reasons, the use of personal electronic devices\nis not permitted during business hours, except in case of emergencies. These\ndevices can be safely stored in individual lockers provided for employees. Each\nemployee is provided with a desk phone that may be used for both business and\npersonal communication. Incoming calls to personal devices can also be\nconveniently forwarded to the desk phones.For\nthe screening process, candidates are advised to revise engineering\nfundamentals, aptitude, logical reasoning, and writing skills. The offline\nScreening Test includes objective and descriptive questions covering these\nareas along with comprehension and short essay writing. A cut-off score may be applied during the screening process based on overall performance and the number of candidates appearing for the test.A\ncompany presentation will be delivered if a slot is allotted for the\npre-placement talk. In case no slot is available, or regardless, students are encouraged to visit our websites for more information about our work and global presence:RELSAFE\n PRA Consulting: \n Assystem\n Group: \n\nStudents\nare advised to review these websites regardless, to gain a better understanding\nof us, our work, and global presence.",
		reqs: "Academic\nCriteria:\n\n Class X and XII: Minimum score\n of 80% or equivalent\n UG: CGPA equivalent to or\n higher than First Class\n No history of arrears\n\nMedical\nCriteria:\nCandidates should be medically fit to perform desk-based, IT-enabled analytical\nand documentation tasks, with adequate vision, hearing, and color perception to\ninterpret color-coded information. The location offering this position provides\nstandard physical access and is not specially adapted for individuals with\nsignificant mobility impairments.\nThe selected candidate will be required to undergo a pre-employment medical\ncheck-up to confirm fitness for the role.",
		url: "https://campus.placements.iitb.ac.in/applicant/job/11930",
