		process:
			"Resume filtering | Technical test (00:30) | Group discussion (01:00) | Technical interview (01:00) | Personal interview (00:30)",
		details:
			"We are looking for a React Native Developer interested in building performant mobile apps on both the iOS and Android platforms. You will be responsible for architecting and building these applications, as well as coordinating with the teams responsible for other layers of the product infrastructure.Building a product is a highly collaborative effort, and as such, a strong team player with a commitment to perfection and high-quality code is required.ResponsibilitiesBuild pixel-perfect, buttery smooth UIs across both mobile platforms.Leverage native APIs for deep integrations with both iOS and Android.Diagnose and fix bugs and performance bottlenecks to deliver a native-like experience.Collaborate with the open-source community to encourage and help implement mission-critical software fixes (React Native moves fast and often breaks things).Maintain code quality and write automated tests to ensure product reliability.Transition existing React web apps to React Native.Core Skills (Must-Have)Strong proficiency in React Native and TypeScript (modern React with Hooks/Context, Hermes, Flipper).Navigation & State Management: React Navigation, Redux Toolkit, React Query (server state).Data & Offline Handling: REST/GraphQL integration, pagination, caching, offline persistence (AsyncStorage).Platform & Native: Xcode, Android Studio, CocoaPods, Gradle; ability to create and maintain native modules, JSI, and bridges.Familiarity with device APIs (camera, location, background tasks).Build & Release Management: CI/CD (GitHub Actions/Jenkins), Fastlane, App Store Connect, Play Console.Quality & Observability: Testing (Jest, React Native Testing Library), crash & analytics tools (Crashlytics), performance profiling.Security Practices: Secure storage (Keychain/Keystore), network hardening (TLS/certificate pinning).Preferred (Good-to-Have)Experience with Firebase, App Center, or mobile DevOps workflows.Exposure to React Native New Architecture (Tanstack, Fabric, TurboModules).Strong debugging skills and familiarity with mobile performance optimization tools.Prior experience working in Agile or Scrum environments.Technical SkillsFirm grasp of the JavaScript language and its nuances, including ES6+ syntax.Knowledge of functional or object-oriented programming principles.Ability to write clean, well-documented JavaScript code.Skilled at working with third-party dependencies and resolving dependency conflicts.Familiarity with native build tools such as Xcode and Gradle.Understanding of REST APIs, the document request model, and offline storage.Experience with automated testing suites.",
		info: "Why Join Qoneqt? Build the Backbone of Authentic Social in a Web3 World\nAt Qoneqt, we're redefining social media as a verified haven for real humans—no bots, no algorithmic overlords, just pure, unfiltered connections. Founded in 2021 and powering 20K+ users on iOS and Android, our Web3-infused app is the anti-everything: decentralized, transparent, and built for communities that actually vibe. As a full-time React Native Developer, you'll architect the mobile magic that brings our vision to life—crafting seamless cross-platform experiences with Expo, TypeScript, and blockchain integrations that verify souls, not just selfies. If you're a code wizard who's tired of cookie-cutter apps and ready to ship features that decentralize the feed, this is your arena. Thane-based (with remote flex), join our 10-strong squad of rebels and turn \"stay human\" into scalable reality. Let's code the revolution. 🔥\nOur Culture: Unscripted Innovation, Zero BS\nQoneqt's vibe is a high-octane blend of Mumbai hustle and global hacker ethos. Authenticity isn't a buzzword; it's our API—expect flat hierarchies where your pull request on user verification could hit prod by EOD, celebrated with team memes and street-food feasts. We thrive on chaos that creates: Hackathons over holidays, Gen Z energy in every commit, and a \"no-ego\" pact that keeps egos in check and ideas flowing. Work here, and you'll evolve from dev to co-creator in a culture that's as real as our verified feeds.Perks That Fuel Your Codefire (Beyond the Competitive Package)We're not just offering a paycheck—we're handing you the keys to a career accelerator. Starting with market-beating comp (think ₹8 LPA), plus:\n\nHybrid Hustle: Thane HQ for those electric collab days, or remote from your setup—your call, as long as the code sings.\nWeb3 Wealth Builder: beta access to Qoneqt's decentralized features. Code the future? Stake your claim.\nRecharge Rituals: Unlimited coffee/snack credits (because debugging on an empty stomach is criminal), team lunch and \"fun Fridays\" to prevent burnout in this always-on world.",
