		details:
			"Position: Automation EngineerLocation: On-siteEmployment Type: Full-timeJob Overview:We’re looking for an Automation Engineer with strong software knowledge in industrial automation systems such as PLC, SCADA, and HMI. The candidate will be responsible for designing, programming, and maintaining automation control systems to enhance process efficiency and ensure smooth operations across our automation projects.Responsibilities:• Design, develop, and implement automation systems using PLC, SCADA, and HMI platforms• Program and configure controllers (e.g., Siemens, Allen-Bradley, Mitsubishi, Schneider, etc.)• Develop and test control logic, interlocks, and safety systems• Integrate field instruments and devices with automation systems• Prepare and review technical documentation, wiring diagrams, and software backups• Perform troubleshooting, debugging, and optimization of control systems• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to deliver reliable automation solutions• Stay updated with the latest industrial automation technologies and software toolsRequirements: • Proficiency in PLC programming languages (Ladder Logic, Function Block, Structured Text, etc.)• Hands-on experience with SCADA/HMI software such as Wonderware, WinCC, iFIX, or Citect• Strong understanding of industrial communication protocols (Modbus, Profibus, Ethernet/IP, OPC, etc.)• Knowledge of automation system design, testing, and commissioning• Good analytical, problem-solving, and documentation skills",
