			"Position: Robotics EngineerLocation: On-siteEmployment Type: Full-timeJob Overview:We’re looking for a Robotics Engineer with strong software expertise to design, simulate, and implement intelligent robotic systems. The role involves working on robot perception, motion control, and automation software using advanced tools like ROS, Gazebo, and CAD platforms. You’ll collaborate with multidisciplinary teams to develop smart robotic solutions for real-world applications.Responsibilities:• Design and develop software for robotic systems using ROS (Robot Operating System)• Simulate and test robotic behaviors in virtual environments using Gazebo or similar tools- Create and modify 3D models and mechanical components using CAD/KiCAD software• Develop algorithms for path planning, motion control, and sensor integration• Collaborate with AI/ML and automation teams for intelligent robotic functionalities- Calibrate and optimize robotic systems for performance and accuracy• Document design specifications, software architecture, and testing reports• Stay updated with the latest trends in robotics software and simulation technologiesRequirements:• Proficiency in ROS, Gazebo, and Python/C++ for robotics programming• Experience with CAD/KiCAD or SolidWorks for robotic design and modeling• Understanding of robot kinematics, dynamics, and control systems• Familiarity with sensors, computer vision, and embedded software integration• Strong problem-solving, simulation, and analytical skills",
