		details:
			"Experience: 0–1 year (new grads welcome) \n\nWork Type: Hybrid\n\n \n\nWhat you’ll do \n\n• Ship GenAI features end-to-end: problem framing → data\npipelines → model \n\ntraining/fine-tuning → evaluation → scalable APIs/UI. \n\n• RAG & agents: retrieval pipelines, tool-using agents,\nmulti-step workflows \n\n(LangGraph or equivalent). \n\n• LLM optimization: PEFT/LoRA, distillation, prompt/grammar\nconstraints; latency \n\n& cost tuning; safety/guardrails. \n\n• MLOps: reproducible training, versioned\ndatasets/artifacts, CI/CD for models, \n\ncanary/shadow rollouts, eval dashboards. \n\n• Foundation work: experiments toward domain LMs\n(tokenization, \n\npretraining/continual learning). \n\n• Quality & safety: groundedness, bias/privacy checks;\nred-team playbooks. \n\n• Product collaboration: translate HR/Finance workflows into\nagents, APIs, and \n\nsimple UIs. \n\n• Research & writing: ablations, lab notebooks, internal\ntech notes, public \n\nblogs/papers. \n\n \n\nMinimum qualifications \n\n• Strong coding: Python (numpy/pandas + PyTorch/JAX/TF),\nGit, tests; ability to read \n\npapers/repos. \n\n• ML fundamentals: data prep, classical ML, metrics,\nregularization, vectorization, \n\nprofiling. \n\n• LLM basics: tokenization/embeddings, prompts, RAG\nconcepts, fine-tuning (any \n\nframework), evaluation. \n\n• Systems thinking: clean data/model flows; Linux,\ncontainers, basic cloud CLI. \n\n• Bias for action: small PRs, clear experiments, shipping\nmindset. \n\n \n\nBonus (nice-to-have) \n\n• Agent frameworks: LangGraph / LangChain / assistants /\ncustom state machines. \n\n• Back-end: FastAPI/Flask; Node.js/TypeScript\n(Express/Nest); \n\nREST/gRPC/WebSockets. \n\n• Data & retrieval: PostgreSQL, Redis,\nElastic/OpenSearch; FAISS/Milvus/Weaviate; \n\npgvector. \n\n• Pipelines & MLOps: MLflow/W&B/Comet; DVC/LakeFS; \n\nAirflow/Prefect/Databricks Workflows; Ray. \n\n• Infra & serving: Docker, K8s, GPUs, CUDA;\nvLLM/Triton/TensorRT; Hugging \n\nFace stack. \n\n• Optimization: quantization (8/4/3-bit), KV-cache,\nspeculative decoding, flash-attn. \n\n• Front-end & viz: React/Tailwind (light),\nPlotly/Altair/Matplotlib; simple eval \n\ndashboards. \n\n• Security & compliance: PII handling, RBAC/ABAC, audit\nlogs (HR/Fin). \n\n• Public artifacts: GitHub projects, blogs, preprints, or\ninternships. \n\n \n\nSkills required (Data Platform, Model Training & Ops)\n\nNote: Not all skills are mandatory—we hire for\nfundamentals, first-principles reasoning, and learning velocity. \n\nData Platform (ingest → transform → serve) \n\nKafka/Kinesis, webhooks, CDC (Debezium), Airbyte/Fivetran;\nS3/ADLS/GCS with \n\nDelta/Parquet/Iceberg; Spark/PySpark, DuckDB, dbt,\nAirflow/Prefect; Feature Store \n\n(Feast/Hopsworks/Databricks FS); Postgres/pgvector,\nElastic/OpenSearch, \n\nFAISS/Milvus/Weaviate; Great Expectations/Deequ;\nFastAPI/Node, REST/gRPC; auth \n\n(JWT/OAuth2), RBAC/ABAC. \n\nModel Training & Evaluation \n\nscikit-learn/XGBoost; PyTorch/JAX; efficient dataloaders;\nAMP; embeddings (BGE/E5), \n\nchunking/windowing, rerankers; LoRA/QLoRA/PEFT, SFT +\nDPO/ORPO; distillation; \n\ncontinual learning; quantization, KV-cache, speculative\ndecoding, vLLM/Triton; \n\nMLflow/W&B/Comet; EM/F1/ROUGE/BLEU, nDCG@k; human evals;\n\nsafety/groundedness; segment KPIs. \n\nMLOps & Productionization \n\nDocker; env pinning; data/model versioning\n(LakeFS/DVC/MLflow Models); GitHub \n\nActions/GitLab CI; data tests + model gates; canary/shadow;\nrollback; FastAPI/Node \n\nservices; async/streaming; vLLM/Triton/TorchServe;\nautoscaling; \n\nPrometheus/Grafana/OpenTelemetry; drift (PSI/KS),\nlatency/throughput, cost/request; Linux, \n\nGPUs, CUDA/cuDNN, K8s/Helm, Terraform. \n\nSecurity, Governance & Domain \n\nPII masking/tokenization; KMS/TLS; IAM, Vault, audit logs,\nretention; prompt filters, red\n\nteaming; OCR (PaddleOCR/Tesseract), layout parsing\n(LayoutLM/Donut/DocTR), table/field \n\nextraction; schema mapping, entity resolution, business-rule\nvalidation; HR/Finance basics \n\n(payroll/benefits, policy Q&A, invoice/GL). \n\n \n\nWhat success looks like (first 90 days)• 30 days: ship a small RAG microservice with evals; land\none measurable latency/cost \n\nwin. \n\n• 60 days: fine-tune a task LLM (PEFT) with clear offline +\nhuman-eval lift; \n\nproductionize with canary. \n\n• 90 days: own a feature (agentic workflow or policy\nchecker) end-to-end with \n\ndashboards, alerts, and an internal tech note.",
