		details:
			"Trainee EngineerKey Responsibility Areas (KRA) Document Position: Trainee EngineerReporting To: Projects Team LeadCompany: Hindustan Waste Treatment Pvt. Ltd. (Subsidiary of SFC Environmental Technologies Ltd.) ABOUT HINDUSTAN WASTE TREATMENT PVT LTD Hindustan Waste Treatment Pvt. Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of SFC Environmental Technologies Ltd., specializes in Municipal Solid Waste (MSW) Treatment Projects. With successful large-scale waste management initiatives in Goa and upcoming projects across India, HWT is setting new benchmarks in sustainable waste infrastructure. Our parent company, SFC Environmental Technologies, is at the forefront of environmental innovation with solutions like C-Tech wastewater treatment and OREX solid waste segregation. Together, we are building a cleaner and more sustainable tomorrow VISION“Be the trusted leader in environmental technologies, continuously innovating to create value, inspiring sustainable change for a better tomorrow.”MISSION“Harnessing technology and human insights to develop and deliver simple, flexible, and cost-effective environmental solutions.” Role OverviewThe Trainee Engineer will be responsible for conceptualizing, designing, and supporting the implementation of process schemes for Integrated Municipal Solid Waste to CBG plants. The role involves close coordination with cross-functional teams to ensure technical feasibility, regulatory compliance, and project efficiency. From pre-bid evaluation to operational support, the Process Engineer plays a vital role in translating project concepts into technically viable and sustainable engineering solutions. The key responsibilities of this role include, Key Result Areas (KRAs)1. Tender & Proposal Engineering:· Study tenders, prepare pre-bid and post-bid clarifications, and develop tailored process schemes compliant with environmental regulations. 2. Process Design Development:· Create detailed engineering documents such as PFDs, P&IDs, mass and energy balances, and layouts specific to each project requirement. 3. Cross-functional Coordination:· Collaborate with mechanical, electrical, civil, and project teams to ensure integrated and optimized process designs. 4. Vendor & Technical Evaluation:· Coordinate with suppliers for technical specifications and commercial quotations for equipment and services.5. Cost & Feasibility Analysis:· Prepare cost evaluations and financial models to support proposal budgeting and decision-making.6. Project Viability Studies:· Conduct site-specific technical and economic feasibility studies considering feedstock, environmental conditions, and regulatory norms. 7. Stakeholder Management:· Liaise with clients, consultants, and regulatory authorities to provide technical clarifications and ensure compliance. 8. Learning & Development:· Gain proficiency in AutoCAD, MS Excel, and project management tools; build strong commercial and technical knowledge. 9. Presentation & Documentation:· Present complex technical details in a simplified, structured manner for varied audiences to facilitate approvals and decision-making. 10. Execution Support:· Provide hands-on process support during the execution phase, including construction, commissioning, troubleshooting, and handover. Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)1. Design Accuracy & Timeliness· Ensuring timely submission of design deliverables with minimal need for revisions.2. Proposal Conversion EfficiencyEffectiveness in converting technical proposals into awarded projects.3. Compliance· Adherence to all environmental and statutory requirements without audit issues.4. Efficiency· Reduction in estimation turnaround time.· Providing effective support during execution to ensure smooth plant startup and minimal on-site issues.5. Coordination & DocumentationClear and complete communication with internal teams.Academic Qualifications· M. Tech – Environmental Engineering and/or Related Fields. Skills & Competencies Required · 0–3 years of experience in solid waste or biogas project design· Strong knowledge of anaerobic digestion, gas generation, and resource recovery systems· Proficiency in process simulation tools and MS Office· Ability to interpret and create technical drawings (PFDs, P&IDs)· Effective coordination and communication with cross-functional teams· Strong analytical and documentation skills Reporting Structure & Collaboration• Reports To: Projects Team Lead• Collaborates With: o All internal departments (MSW, Supply Chain Management, Process Engineering, Electrical & Commission etc.)o HR & Internal Communication Teamso Team Leaders across Business Unitso Finance & Accounts Team The Trainee Engineer at Hindustan Waste Treatment Pvt. Ltd. plays a critical role in designing and optimizing technical solutions for integrated solid waste to biogas facilities. This role is responsible for developing process flow diagrams, performing mass-energy balances, preparing technical proposals, and ensuring regulatory compliance. With a strong foundation in environmental engineering principles and interdepartmental coordination, the Process Engineer transforms complex project requirements into efficient, feasible, and sustainable process designs. Through technical innovation and execution support, this role directly contributes to SFC’s mission of delivering impactful and future-ready environmental solutions.",
