		details:
			"Trainee Design Engineer Key Responsibility Areas (KRA) Document Position: Trainee Design EngineerReporting To: Head EngineeringCompany: Hindustan Waste Treatment Pvt. Ltd. (Subsidiary of SFC Environmental Technologies Ltd.) ABOUT HINDUSTAN WASTE TREATMENT PVT LTD Hindustan Waste Treatment Pvt. Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of SFC Environmental Technologies Ltd., specializes in Municipal Solid Waste (MSW) Treatment Projects. With successful large-scale waste management initiatives in Goa and upcoming projects across India, HWT is setting new benchmarks in sustainable waste infrastructure. Our parent company, SFC Environmental Technologies, is at the forefront of environmental innovation with solutions like C-Tech wastewater treatment and OREX solid waste segregation. Together, we are building a cleaner and more sustainable tomorrow VISION“Be the trusted leader in environmental technologies, continuously innovating to create value, inspiring sustainable change for a better tomorrow.”MISSION“Harnessing technology and human insights to develop and deliver simple, flexible, and cost-effective environmental solutions.” Role OverviewTrainee Design Engineer will be responsible for preparing basic and detailed engineering designs for civil units—including buildings, tanks, and PEB structures—associated with Municipal Solid Waste projects, as well as water and wastewater treatment systems. The role requires strong technical expertise in civil and structural engineering, along with a sound understanding of relevant IS and international codes. The engineer will ensure that all designs adhere to project specifications and applicable design standards. Key Result Areas (KRAs) 1. Structural Design & Analysis: Design and analyze RCC buildings, Pre-Engineered Building (PEB) structures, water-retaining structures (tanks, sumps, pumping stations), roads, stormwater drains, pipe racks/sleepers, etc., with emphasis on economical design, value engineering, and compliance with IS and international codes/standards. Apply geotechnical principles for foundation design, including selection of foundations and pile design 2. Drawings & Documentation: Prepare GA drawings, civil guideline drawings, BOQs, specifications, calculation reports, and structural design documents as per IS/international standards. Conduct proof-checking of RCC and steel designs/drawings to ensure accuracy and compliance. 3. Software Proficiency: Use STAAD.Pro, ETABS, Revit, and AutoCAD for structural modelling, analysis, and design. 4. Coordination & Collaboration: Coordinate with Process, Mechanical, Electrical, Instrumentation, and Environmental teams and perform interdisciplinary checks. Engage with external design agencies and vendors to obtain and integrate design inputs.5. Review & Approvals:Review design submissions from contractors/sub-consultants for adequacy and compliance. Coordinate and secure design and drawing approvals from clients/consultants. 6. Procurement & Documentation Control:Prepare RFQs for civil-related items and review vendor designs/drawings. Maintain the Master Document List (MDL) and track civil design progress.7. Site & Professional Support:Support the site team to ensure construction aligns with design specifications. Demonstrate willingness to learn new concepts/software and maintain effective communication within the project team.Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)1. Structural Design:Accurate and timely preparation of designs, drawings, and Civil GADs. On-time delivery of design outputs and securing timely approvals. 2. Technical Documentation:Complete and accurate preparation of MDLs, BOQs/BOMs, specifications, and drawings. High client acceptance with reduced documentation cycle time. 3. Standards Compliance:100% adherence to Contract requirements, IS codes, and relevant international standards. Minimal non-conformities and strong audit performance. 4. Vendor / Client Support:· Effective interaction for design approvals, clarifications, and input coordination. · High client satisfaction and timely receipt of vendor inputs. 5. Value Engineering & OptimizationContribution to time/cost savings through design optimization and standardisation. Consistent capture and implementation of key learnings. Academic QualificationsB.E / B.Tech in Civil Engineering with relevant experience & M.E / M.Tech in Structural Engineering. Skills & Competencies RequiredStrong foundation in civil engineering principles, structural design, and estimation.Proficiency in MS Excel and AutoCAD; familiarity with MS Project desirable.Analytical skills with high numerical accuracy.Awareness of IS codes and CPWD schedulesStrong communication and teamwork abilities.Strong communication and documentation skills Reporting Structure & Collaboration• Reports To: Head Engineering• Collaborates With: o All internal departments (MSW, Supply Chain Management, Process Engineering, Electrical & Commission etc.)o HR & Internal Communication Teamso Team Leaders across Business Unitso Finance & Accounts Team The Trainee Design Engineer at Hindustan Waste Treatment Pvt. Ltd. will play a crucial role in supporting the planning and execution of MSW projects. By assisting in structural and civil design, preparing drawings, and ensuring compliance with design standards, the candidate will contribute to the development of sustainable infrastructure that enhances city services and community well-being.",
