		details:
			"JOB DESCRIPTION – Graduate\nEngineer Trainee – Instrumentation & Electrical\n\nJob Title: Graduate Engineer Trainee\n(Chemical Engineering)\n\nCompany: Intech Organics\nLimited\nLocation: Gurugram/Plant Sites (PAN INDIA)\nDepartment: Production / Process / Projects\nBatch: 2026 (IITs)\nPositions Available: 2\n\nAbout Intech Organics Limited\n\nIntech Organics Limited is a leading chemical\nmanufacturing organization engaged in the production of bromine and\nbromine-based compounds, inorganic chemicals, and specialty chemicals. With a\nstrong emphasis on innovation, safety, and sustainability, we continue to\nexpand our manufacturing capabilities and global presence.\n\nOur Graduate Engineer Trainee (GET) program aims to\nnurture young engineering talent into skilled professionals ready to lead the\nfuture of chemical manufacturing.\n\nRole Objective\n\nAs a Graduate Engineer Trainee (Chemical Engineering),\nyou will be part of our operations and process teams, gaining hands-on\nexperience in plant processes, production control, and process optimization.\nThe role focuses on developing your technical expertise in chemical plant\noperations, process safety, and continuous improvement.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n Assist\n in monitoring and controlling daily plant operations and process\n parameters.\n Work\n on optimizing chemical processes to enhance productivity and quality.\n Support\n troubleshooting of process deviations and participate in root cause\n analysis.\n Collaborate\n with R&D and process engineering teams for process improvement\n projects.\n Ensure\n adherence to safety, health, and environmental standards.\n Prepare\n technical reports, process documentation, and operating procedures.\n Participate\n in projects related to capacity expansion, energy efficiency, and\n sustainability.\n\nQualifications\n\n B.Tech\n / B.E. in Chemical Engineering.\n Graduating\n Batch: 2026 (from IITs)\n\nDesired Skills & Attributes\n\n Strong\n knowledge of chemical process fundamentals and thermodynamics.\n Analytical,\n data-driven, and detail-oriented approach.\n Good\n communication and teamwork skills.\n Willingness\n to work in a plant environment and learn continuously.\n Commitment\n to safety, quality, and environmental compliance.\n\nCompensation & Benefits\n\n Compensation\n will be as per industry standards and based on qualifications and\n performance.\n Additional\n benefits include accommodation assistance and medical coverage as per\n company policy.\n\nCareer Path\n\nAfter successful completion of the training period, the\ncandidate will be absorbed as an Assistant Engineer – Chemical / Process,\ndepending on performance and business requirements.\n\nSelection Process\n\n Pre-Placement\n Talk (PPT)\n Aptitude\n / Technical Test\n Technical\n Interview\n HR\n Interview",
		info: "Medical InsuranceTraining Facilities will be provided.You should be technically sound.",
