			"Resume filtering | Technical test (2 Hours) | Technical interview (1 Hour) | Personal interview (1 Hour)",
		details:
			"Talent search for Kimbal\n\n \n\nAvailable Job role: Hardware\nDesign Engineer\n\nJob location:\nDelhi NCR\n\n \n\nKimbal is at the forefront of building a\nsmarter and cleaner energy future. We enable utilities to modernize and scale\nthrough cutting-edge smart metering, RF-based connectivity, cloud-native\nplatforms, and advanced energy management solutions. As the energy landscape\nevolves rapidly, we empower our partners to future-proof their networks with\nunmatched reliability, agility, and intelligence.\n\nIn a fast-paced and innovation-driven\nenvironment, we design and deliver solutions that address urgent industry needs\nwhile shaping long-term transformation. Our vision is to create resilient,\naffordable, and adaptable power grids that thrive in complex energy\necosystems—driving meaningful progress toward carbon neutrality and sustainable\ngrowth. \n\nKimbal Private Limited (formerly Crystal) is\nthe fastest-rising Indian energy-tech enterprise, building tools to modernize\nthe distribution grid since 2011. \n\n \n\nCultural\nelements we are looking for:\n\n Agility advocate\n Tech driven curiosity &\n mind bend\n Scaling unlearning to\n learning & reverse in a swift pace.\n Problem - solver attitude\n High on individual ownership\n & accountability\n Team player and champion\n collaborator.\n\n \n\nCheck\nout the details of the role in the next page and apply now!\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nHardware Design Engineer \n\n \n\nRole\nDescription \n\nAs a Hardware Design\nEngineer at Kimbal, you will design and develop high-performance, reliable, and\nfield-ready electronic hardware for smart metering, grid monitoring, and\ndistributed energy management devices.\n\nYou will work across the\ncomplete hardware lifecycle — from schematic design and component selection to\nPCB layout, prototyping, validation, and certification. Your work will directly\nimpact how India’s utilities monitor power quality, protect assets, and\noptimize energy efficiency. \n\n \n\nKey\nResponsibilities \n\n· \nDesign analog\nand mixed-signal circuits for metering, sensing, and communication applications\n(RF, PLC, Ethernet, etc.)\n\n· \nDevelop PCB\nlayouts for low-power and EMI/EMC-compliant designs using Altium or similar EDA\ntools.\n\n· \nCollaborate\nwith firmware and mechanical teams for seamless system integration.\n\n· \nConduct\nprototype validation, testing, and performance characterization.\n\n· \nEnsure\ncompliance with metering and grid standards (IS16444, IS15959, IEC61000, etc.)\n\n· \nWork on power\nsupply design (AC/DC converters, surge protection, isolation).\n\n· \nPrepare and\nmaintain hardware design documentation — BOM, test plans, and schematics.\n\n· \nSupport field\ntrials and gather feedback from live utility deployments.\n\n \n\nCurrent\nChallenges \n\n· \nDesigning\ncost-efficient yet highly reliable hardware for harsh Indian grid environments\n(voltage surges, humidity, dust).\n\n· \nAchieving\nlow-power, compact PCB architectures without compromising RF performance.\n\n· \nManaging\ncomponent obsolescence and supply chain variability.\n\n· \nEnsuring\nrapid prototyping and validation cycles for new product lines (PQ monitors, LV\nnetwork sensors, DTR protection).\n\n· \nIntegrating\nmulti-protocol communication (RF, NB-IoT, BLE, etc.) into a single board\ndesign.\n\n \n\n \n\nJob Requirements \n\n \n\nQualifications\n\n \n\n· \nB.Tech / Dual\nDegree / M.Tech in Electrical, Electronics, or Instrumentation Engineering (IIT\nor equivalent tier 1 institutes).\n\n· \nFresh\ngraduates or with relevant internships/projects.\n\n· \nKnowledge of\ncircuit design & simulation (LTspice, Multisim, or equivalent)\n\n· \nFamiliarity\nwith PCB design tools (Altium Designer, KiCAD, or Cadence)\n\n· \nUnderstanding\nof analog front-end, ADCs, sensors, isolation circuits\n\n· \nFamiliarity\nwith EMI/EMC testing and debugging\n\n· \nStrong\nanalytical thinking, design curiosity, and cross-functional collaboration\nability.\n\n· \nExcellent\ncommunication, storytelling, and presentation skills — ability to simplify\ntechnical concepts.\n\n \n\nWhy Kimbal?\n\n \n\nAt Kimbal, the circuits you design won’t just blink LEDs on a bench —\nthey’ll live on electricity poles, transformers, and metering boxes across\nIndia’s towns and cities.\n\n \n\nYou’ll see your hardware stand up to heat, dust, surges, and rain — and\nstill deliver data that keeps the grid alive.\n\n \n\nHere, you’ll:\n\n \n\n· \nDesign\nproducts that operate in the real world, not just lab simulations.\n\n· \nLearn how to\ntake a board from concept → prototype → mass production.\n\n· \nCollaborate\nwith firmware and field engineers, understanding how hardware performs outside\nthe comfort of a test bench.\n\n· \nWork with\nIndia’s newest and smartest energy technologies — from power-quality analyzers\nto RF-based communication systems.\n\n· \nGrow into a\nfull-stack hardware engineer, capable of building products that truly power the\ncountry.\n\n· \nAt Kimbal,\nevery circuit you draw brings the grid one step closer to being intelligent. ⚙️",
