		details:
			"Talent search for Kimbal\n\n \n\nAvailable Job role: IoT\nFirmware/Embedded Engineer\n\nJob location:\nDelhi NCR\n\n \n\nKimbal is at the forefront of building a\nsmarter and cleaner energy future. We enable utilities to modernize and scale\nthrough cutting-edge smart metering, RF-based connectivity, cloud-native\nplatforms, and advanced energy management solutions. As the energy landscape\nevolves rapidly, we empower our partners to future-proof their networks with\nunmatched reliability, agility, and intelligence.\n\nIn a fast-paced and innovation-driven\nenvironment, we design and deliver solutions that address urgent industry needs\nwhile shaping long-term transformation. Our vision is to create resilient,\naffordable, and adaptable power grids that thrive in complex energy\necosystems—driving meaningful progress toward carbon neutrality and sustainable\ngrowth. \n\nKimbal Private Limited (formerly Crystal) is\nthe fastest-rising Indian energy-tech enterprise, building tools to modernize\nthe distribution grid since 2011. \n\n \n\nCultural\nelements we are looking for:\n\n Agility advocate\n Tech driven curiosity &\n mind bend\n Scaling unlearning to\n learning & reverse in a swift pace.\n Problem - solver attitude\n High on individual ownership\n & accountability\n Team player and champion\n collaborator.\n\n \n\nCheck\nout the details of the role in the next page and apply now!\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nIoT Firmware/Embedded Engineer \n\n \n\nRole\nDescription \n\nAs an IoT Firmware /\nEmbedded Engineer at Kimbal, you will design and develop firmware that powers\nour smart meters, grid sensors, and home energy management devices.\n\nYour code will live on\nedge devices deployed across India’s utility networks — enabling real-time data\ncapture, wireless communication, and intelligent control.\n\nYou’ll work closely with\nhardware, RF, and cloud teams to make Kimbal’s connected energy ecosystem\nreliable, scalable, and intelligent.\n\n \n\nKey\nResponsibilities \n\n· \nDesign and\ndevelop embedded firmware for smart metering, smart grids, LV monitoring, HEMS\nand other devices.\n\n· \nImplement and\noptimize communication stacks (RF, BLE, Wi-Fi, NB-IoT, Modbus, DLMS, MQTT).\n\n· \nWrite\nlow-level drivers for sensors, ADCs, and communication peripherals (SPI, UART,\nI2C).\n\n· \nOptimize\npower consumption and memory footprint for long-life field deployments.\n\n· \nIntegrate and\ntest firmware with hardware prototypes and IoT gateways.\n\n· \nSupport\nOver-the-Air (OTA) firmware update functionality.\n\n· \nCollaborate\nwith the cloud and data teams to define device–server communication protocols.\n\n· \nConduct field\ntesting and diagnostics for real-world reliability validation.\n\n \n\nCurrent\nChallenges \n\n· \nBuilding\nultra-low-power embedded firmware for devices running in tough field\nconditions.\n\n· \nHandling\nintermittent connectivity and ensuring robust data buffering and recovery.\n\n· \nManaging\nmulti-protocol communication in compact hardware with limited resources.\n\n· \nAchieving\nsecure OTA updates and encryption within constrained devices.\n\n· \nIntegrating\nfirmware seamlessly across new hardware platforms and metering variants.\n\n \n\nJob Requirements \n\n \n\nQualifications\n\n \n\n· \nB.Tech / Dual\nDegree / M.Tech in Electrical, Electronics, Computer Science or Instrumentation\nEngineering (IITs or equivalent tier 1 institutes).\n\n· \nFresh\ngraduates or with relevant internships/projects.\n\n· \nKnowledge of C/C++\nprogramming for embedded systems (ARM, STM32, ESP, etc.)\n\n· \nFamiliarity\nwith RTOS / bare-metal programming\n\n· \nKnowledge of\ncommunication protocols: UART, I2C, SPI, TCP/IP, MQTT\n\n· \nKnowledge of\ndebugging tools: JTAG, Logic Analyzer, Oscilloscope\n\n· \nFamiliarity\nwith OTA, device provisioning, and IoT security\n\n· \nExposure to\nsmart metering, sensor networks, or IoT products (not mandatory)\n\n· \nCuriosity to\nexperiment, strong debugging discipline, and ability to collaborate with\ncross-functional hardware & cloud teams.\n\n \n\n \n\nWhy Kimbal?\n\n \n\nAt Kimbal, your firmware will literally travel across India — running\nquietly inside smart meters, gateways, and grid sensors that light up cities.\n\n \n\nYou’ll see how a few lines of code written in your IDE can turn a\npassive device into an intelligent node that talks, learns, and responds in\nreal time.\n\n \n\nHere, you’ll:\n\n \n\n· \nBuild real\nIoT products — not experiments — that impact how utilities and consumers use\nenergy.\n\n· \nGet to work\nacross the stack — from sensors to cloud integration.\n\n· \nTackle\nexciting challenges like ultra-low-power design, RF communication, and edge\nanalytics.\n\n· \nTest your\ncode in real-world conditions — you’ll learn to debug not just firmware, but\nthe ecosystem around it.\n\n· \nBe mentored\nby industry experts who have built India’s first generation of smart metering\nproducts.\n\n· \nAt Kimbal,\nyour code won’t just run — it will speak to the grid. ⚡",
