			"Resume filtering | Technical test (2 Hour) | Technical interview (1 Hour) | Personal interview (1 Hour)",
		details:
			"Talent search for Kimbal\n\n \n\nAvailable Job role: Data\nScientist \n\nJob location:\nDelhi NCR\n\n \n\nKimbal is at the forefront of building a\nsmarter and cleaner energy future. We enable utilities to modernize and scale\nthrough cutting-edge smart metering, RF-based connectivity, cloud-native\nplatforms, and advanced energy management solutions. As the energy landscape\nevolves rapidly, we empower our partners to future-proof their networks with\nunmatched reliability, agility, and intelligence.\n\nIn a fast-paced and innovation-driven\nenvironment, we design and deliver solutions that address urgent industry needs\nwhile shaping long-term transformation. Our vision is to create resilient,\naffordable, and adaptable power grids that thrive in complex energy\necosystems—driving meaningful progress toward carbon neutrality and sustainable\ngrowth. \n\nKimbal Private Limited (formerly Crystal) is\nthe fastest-rising Indian energy-tech enterprise, building tools to modernize\nthe distribution grid since 2011. \n\n \n\nCultural\nelements we are looking for:\n\n Agility advocate\n Tech driven curiosity &\n mind bend\n Scaling unlearning to\n learning & reverse in a swift pace.\n Problem - solver attitude\n High on individual ownership\n & accountability\n Team player and champion\n collaborator.\n\n \n\nCheck\nout the details of the role in the next page and apply now!\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nData Scientist \n\n \n\nRole\nDescription \n\nAs a Data Scientist at\nKimbal, you will turn massive streams of smart meter and IoT data into\nactionable intelligence for utilities, large power consumers, and prosumers.\n\nYour models will power\nKimbal’s analytics platform — predicting energy demand, detecting grid\nanomalies, improving asset efficiency, and enabling energy trading decisions.\n\nYou’ll work at the\nintersection of data science, energy systems, and AI, helping build a smarter,\ncleaner grid for India. \n\n \n\nKey\nResponsibilities \n\n· \nDevelop and\ndeploy machine learning models for energy analytics — demand forecasting,\nanomaly detection, PQ analysis, and load disaggregation (NILM).\n\n· \nDesign and\nmaintain data pipelines from IoT devices to cloud analytics platforms.\n\n· \nAnalyse smart\nmeter, transformer, and PQ sensor data to derive performance insights and\noptimization opportunities.\n\n· \nCollaborate\nwith firmware, cloud, and product teams to integrate models into live systems.\n\n· \nBuild data\nvisualization dashboards for utilities and consumers (load curves, DR\npotential, PQ metrics).\n\n· \nWork on\nalgorithms for Time-of-Day tariffs, Demand Response, and Distributed Energy\nResource (DER) optimization.\n\n· \nValidate\nmodels with real field data and continuously improve prediction accuracy.\n\n \n\n \n\nCurrent\nChallenges \n\n· \nHandling\nhigh-frequency, large-scale streaming data from heterogeneous IoT sources.\n\n· \nEnsuring data\nquality and consistency from field devices operating under unstable grid\nconditions.\n\n· \nDeveloping\nlightweight ML models that can run efficiently on edge or constrained\nenvironments.\n\n· \nIntegrating\nenergy domain knowledge with data-driven modelling for actionable insights.\n\n· \nBuilding\nmodels that drive monetizable outcomes — tariff optimization, DR savings,\ncarbon credits.\n\n \n\nJob Requirements \n\n \n\nQualifications\n\n \n\n· \nB.Tech / Dual\nDegree / M.Tech in Computer Science Engineering, Data Science, Artificial\nIntelligence, Machine Learning or Applied Mathematics.\n\n· \nFresh\ngraduates or with relevant internships/projects.\n\n· \nProficiency\nin Python, Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, TensorFlow/PyTorch\n\n· \nStrong\nunderstanding of statistics, regression, time-series forecasting\n\n· \nKnowledge of SQL/NoSQL\ndatabases and data pipeline tools\n\n· \nFamiliarity\nwith APIs, cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure)\n\n· \nAnalytical\ncuriosity, problem formulation ability, storytelling with data, and willingness\nto work in fast-changing product environments.\n\n \n\n \n\nWhy Kimbal?\n\n \n\nAt Kimbal, your models won’t just predict numbers on a dashboard —\nthey’ll help utilities save power, reduce losses, and make India’s grid more\nefficient.\n\nYou’ll work with data that comes straight from smart meters, EV\nchargers, transformers, and solar rooftops — not from pre-cleaned CSVs.\n\n \n\nHere, you’ll:\n\n \n\n· \nSolve real\nenergy problems through data — from forecasting demand to detecting theft or\ntransformer failures.\n\n· \nWork on\ndatasets measured in billions of readings, streamed directly from live field\ndevices.\n\n· \nCollaborate\nwith engineers who build the hardware and firmware generating the data — giving\nyou context beyond the code.\n\n· \nExperiment\nwith AI, ML, and time-series models that directly influence how utilities plan\nand operate.\n\n· \nLearn to\ntranslate insights into actionable business impact — not just academic metrics.\n\n· \nAt Kimbal,\nyour algorithms won’t just predict — they’ll power better energy decisions.",
