		details:
			"Talent search for Kimbal\n\n \n\nAvailable Job role: Software\nEngineer \n\nJob location:\nDelhi NCR\n\n \n\nKimbal is at the forefront of building a\nsmarter and cleaner energy future. We enable utilities to modernize and scale\nthrough cutting-edge smart metering, RF-based connectivity, cloud-native\nplatforms, and advanced energy management solutions. As the energy landscape\nevolves rapidly, we empower our partners to future-proof their networks with\nunmatched reliability, agility, and intelligence.\n\nIn a fast-paced and innovation-driven\nenvironment, we design and deliver solutions that address urgent industry needs\nwhile shaping long-term transformation. Our vision is to create resilient,\naffordable, and adaptable power grids that thrive in complex energy\necosystems—driving meaningful progress toward carbon neutrality and sustainable\ngrowth. \n\nKimbal Private Limited (formerly Crystal) is\nthe fastest-rising Indian energy-tech enterprise, building tools to modernize\nthe distribution grid since 2011. \n\n \n\nCultural\nelements we are looking for:\n\n Agility advocate\n Tech driven curiosity &\n mind bend\n Scaling unlearning to\n learning & reverse in a swift pace.\n Problem - solver attitude\n High on individual ownership\n & accountability\n Team player and champion\n collaborator.\n\n \n\nCheck\nout the details of the role in the next page and apply now!\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nSoftware Engineer \n\n \n\nRole\nDescription \n\nAs a Software Engineer at\nKimbal, you will build and scale the digital infrastructure that connects\nmillions of smart meters and energy devices to our cloud platform.\n\nYou’ll design APIs,\nservices, and data pipelines that power real-time analytics, visualization, and\ndecision-making for utilities, large power consumers, and prosumers.\n\nThis role offers a unique\nopportunity to work at the intersection of IoT, cloud computing, and clean\nenergy, transforming how India measures, manages, and trades electricity. \n\n \n\nKey\nResponsibilities \n\n· \nDesign and\ndevelop scalable backend services and APIs for smart metering and energy\nmanagement platforms.\n\n· \nCollaborate\nwith firmware, data, and product teams to enable seamless device–cloud\nintegration.\n\n· \nBuild and\nmaintain real-time data pipelines for ingestion, processing, and storage of\nmetering data.\n\n· \nDevelop\nmicroservices and containerized applications (Docker, Kubernetes).\n\n· \nImplement\nauthentication, access control, and data security mechanisms for multi-tenant\nsystems.\n\n· \nCollaborate\nwith front-end developers to deliver interactive dashboards and user\napplications.\n\n· \nWrite clean,\nefficient, and well-documented code, following CI/CD and DevOps best practices.\n\n· \nParticipate\nin system architecture reviews and contribute to technical roadmap planning.\n\n \n\n \n\nCurrent\nChallenges \n\n· \nHandling\nmassive real-time data from distributed IoT devices with minimal latency.\n\n· \nBuilding\nfault-tolerant, cloud-native systems that scale dynamically.\n\n· \nIntegrating\nheterogeneous device protocols into unified APIs.\n\n· \nBalancing\ndata security, reliability, and performance in energy-critical applications.\n\n· \nAccelerating\nfeature deployment cycles while maintaining system stability.\n\n \n\n \n\nJob Requirements \n\n \n\nQualifications\n\n \n\n· \nB.Tech / Dual\nDegree / M.Tech in Computer Science or related field.\n\n· \nFreshers with\nrelevant internships/projects.\n\n· \nGood at\nprogramming — proficient in Python, Java, or Node.js. etc. \n\n· \nStrong knowledge\nin algorithm and data structures.\n\n· \nUnderstand\nhow software talks to databases (SQL & NoSQL) and APIs.\n\n· \nCurious about\ncloud computing and IoT — how connected devices send and use data.\n\n· \nEnjoy solving\nreal-world problems through code.\n\n \n\nDesired Attributes\n\n \n\n· \nReady to\nlearn, experiment, and build things that go live in the field.\n\n· \nAnalytical\ncuriosity, problem formulation ability, storytelling with data, and willingness\nto work in fast-changing product environments.\n\n· \nHigh-ownership\nmindset, system-level thinking, and comfort with agile, cross-functional\ncollaboration. \n\n· \nPrior exposure\nto energy or IoT platforms, distributed systems, or SaaS application\ndevelopment is a plus (not mandatory).\n\n \n\n \n\nWhy Kimbal? \n\n \n\nAt Kimbal, you won’t be writing code that just stays in a folder —\nyou’ll see it come alive across India’s power grids, data centres, and homes.\n\n \n\nYou’ll be part of a small, passionate team that’s building the digital\nnervous system of India’s energy network — from smart meters on poles to\ndashboards in control rooms.\n\n \n\nHere, you’ll:\n\n \n\n· \nWork on real\nIoT and energy-tech challenges that few companies in India are solving.\n\n· \nSee your work\nimpact millions of people — every optimization you code helps reduce power\nlosses and makes energy cleaner. \n\n· \nLearn\ndirectly from hardware, data, and embedded experts, not just other software\nengineers.\n\n· \nGrow fast —\nwe believe in giving ownership early, not waiting for years.\n\n· \nAnd most\nimportantly, you’ll help build the future of how India measures, manages, and\ntrades electricity.\n\n· \nAt Kimbal,\nyour code won’t just run — it will power the grid. ⚡",
