		details:
			"About BSE Ltd.: Be part of a 150-year-old legacy organization leading a bold turnaround in the Indian Capital Market—\n where innovation, emerging technologies, and ambitious minds converge to create real impact. If that \nexcites you, you’re in the right place. \n \nAt BSE, technology isn’t just an enabler—it’s the backbone of India’s financial markets. From \nprocessing over 700 crore transactions daily to deploying Artificial intelligence for managing operations \nefficiently, we’re redefining what a 150-year-old institution can achieve. If you’re excited by high\nimpact innovation at scale, this is where your journey begins. \n \nBSE Technologies is among the few companies in its space, following stringent quality and information \nsecurity standards. Job Description Job Summary: We are seeking motivated and talented Engineering graduates from Indian Institute of Technology to \njoin our technology vertical. This role is ideal for fresh graduates with a strong foundation in Computer \nEngineering, Electronics, or Telecommunications, who are passionate about bridging technology and \nbusiness needs. You will work on diverse projects involving trading system architecture, real time \nsurveillance systems, cybersecurity Security Operations Center (SOC) and other application \ndevelopments, gaining hands-on experience in a collaborative environment. You will be joining our \nGraduate Trainee program.When you join us, you will have: • Learning & Development: The journey will begin with placement of a short duration in key \ndepartments within the technological vertical to get a holistic view about the technology \noperations and technology development, before you commence in the role assigned to you. • Fintech Experience: Stock Exchange has been one of the first proponents of India’s Fintech \nStory. You’ll experience the power of large-scale, low-latency trading systems and robust \ndownstream applications built to handle massive transaction volumes. An opportunity to work \nat the intersection of financial infrastructure and cutting-edge technology• Your voice matters: We believe in the power of fresh ideas and practical solutions – especially \nthose that embrace emerging technologies. Here, diverse perspectives aren’t just welcomed; \nthey’re essential to driving innovation and delivering meaningful impact. • World-class benefits: On top of a competitive salary, we provide a comprehensive benefits \npackage to enable holistic well-being. Preferred Qualifications • Bachelor’s degree in computer science, engineering and other allied fields • Fundamental knowledge of network engineering concepts, including TCP/IP, routing protocols, \nand network security basics. • Solid understanding of data structures, algorithms, and operating systems. • Familiarity with system architecture principles, including microservices, cloud computing \n(AWS/Azure basics), and database management (SQL/NoSQL). • Basic understanding of capital markets particularly equity and equity derivatives will be an \nadded advantage • Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills. • Demonstrated curiosity, ownership, and a willingness to work in a collaborative environment.",
