			"About BSE Ltd.: Be part of a 150-year-old legacy organization leading a bold turnaround in the Indian Capital Market—\n where innovation, emerging technologies, and ambitious minds converge to create real impact. If that \nexcites you, you’re in the right place. \n \nBSE, India’s oldest stock exchange, plays a dual role – that of being the first line of regulator for capital \nmarkets under Securities Exchange Board of India (SEBI) framework, while also operating as a \ncorporate entity accountable to a diverse set of stakeholders. Exchange is scripting a bold turnaround \nstory by expanding market access, driving financial inclusion, and redefining its role in the capital \necosystem. This blend of purpose and performance is what makes BSE’s journey unique and at the \nsame time forward-looking. Job Description Job Summary: \nWe are seeking highly motivated and intellectually curious graduates from premier institutions to join \nBSE in its transformative journey. As India’s oldest stock exchange, BSE plays a unique dual role — \nacting as the first line of regulation under the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) framework, \nwhile also operating as a dynamic corporate entity accountable to a diverse set of stakeholders. This \nopportunity is ideal for individuals passionate about shaping the future of capital markets through \nroles in business development, regulatory compliance, and operations. You will be part of a bold \nturnaround story focused on expanding market access, driving financial inclusion, and redefining the \nexchange’s role in the financial ecosystem. When you join us, you will have: • Learning & Development: The journey will begin with placement of a short duration in key \ndepartments within the technological vertical to get a holistic view about the technology \noperations and technology development, before you commence in the role assigned to you. • Fintech Experience: Stock Exchange has been one of the first proponents of India’s Fintech \nStory. You’ll experience the power of large-scale, low-latency trading systems and robust \ndownstream applications built to handle massive transaction volumes. An opportunity to work \nat the intersection of financial infrastructure and cutting-edge technology • Your voice matters: We believe in the power of fresh ideas and practical solutions – especially \nthose that embrace emerging technologies. Here, diverse perspectives aren’t just welcomed; \nthey’re essential to driving innovation and delivering meaningful impact. • Investor driven, B2B Model – Exchange offers platform for financial products offered by Issuers \nand distributed through Intermediaries to investors. As a first line of regulator, Exchange \noverseas regulatory compliance of Issuers as well as Intermediaries. • World-class benefits: On top of a competitive salary, we provide a comprehensive benefits \npackage to enable holistic well-being. Preferred Qualifications • Master’s degree in finance, financial services, dual degree with finance or operations is one of \nthe specializations. • Well versed in using Microsoft office. Familiarity with using other databases, agentic AI will be a \nplus. • Basic understanding of capital markets particularly equity and equity derivatives will be an \nadded advantage \n• Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills. \n• Demonstrated curiosity, ownership, and a willingness to work in a collaborative environment.",
