		details:
			"Product DesignerAbout PlivoPlivo is a leading technology company transforming customer engagement for some of the world’s largest B2C brands, including Uber, WhatsApp, and Zomato. Our AI agents platform automates the entire customer lifecycle - from acquiring, engaging, and supporting customers - through cutting-edge multimodal AI, including LLMs, text-to-speech, and speech detection. With a 150+ member team based out of India & US. We are building high-impact global products that handle over 1 billion API requests per month. If you are excited about solving hard, real-world AI challenges at scale, this is where you belong. 🚀The OpportunityWe're looking for a brilliant and ambitious Product Designer to join the team building our most strategic product: the AI Agents Platform.You'll tackle real product challenges, and your work will ship to real customers. You won't just be a \"spec-taker\"; you'll be a key partner in helping us define what we build and how we empower our users to create powerful AI agents with ease.What You'll DoContribute to the Full Design Process: Work closely with Senior Designers and Engineers to take features from early concepts, user flows, and wireframes to high-fidelity, polished UI designs in Figma.Be a Product Partner: You'll participate in design sprints, user research sessions, and strategic discussions, learning how to define and solve the right problems for our users.Design, Ship, and Iterate: See your designs come to life. You'll prepare assets for engineering and, after launch, help analyze customer feedback and data to find opportunities for improvement.Present Your Work: Learn to clearly articulate your design decisions. You'll participate in design critiques and present your work, receiving direct mentorship and feedback from senior leaders.Build the System: Contribute to and help maintain our design system, learning what it takes to ensure a consistent and high-quality experience at scale.What We're Looking ForA Compelling Portfolio: You have a portfolio that showcases your design process, problem-solving skills, and excellent UI/UX craft. Please include a link to it in your application.A Passion for Craft: You have a keen eye for detail, typography, and layout. You're passionate about creating high-quality, polished interfaces and are eager to refine your skills.A \"Product Thinker\" Mindset: You're curious about why things are built, not just what they look like. You're eager to understand the user's problem and can think in terms of user journeys and systems.Fluency in Design Tools: You are proficient with modern design and prototyping tools (we live and breathe Figma) and are actively curious about incorporating AI into your workflow to work more efficiently.A Love for Complexity: You aren't afraid of a challenge. You're excited by the idea of designing complex, technical products and making them simple and intuitive.Eager to Learn & Communicate: You're an excellent communicator, and a proactive team player. Why Plivo?Real Impact: You will be a core part of a high-impact team building Plivo's most strategic new product. This isn't a theoretical exercise; your work will ship and be used by customers.Cutting-Edge Problem Space: You'll be designing at the frontier of AI and customer communications—one of the most exciting and rapidly-evolving fields in tech today.Mentorship & Growth: You'll be mentored by senior designers and leaders who are invested in your growth. You won't just learn how to design, but how to think, build, and ship products at scale.Real Ownership: We give our interns projects with real scope and impact. You'll have the opportunity to truly own a piece of the product experience.",
