			"Company Description: We are an IIT Delhi-incubated deep-tech EV startup. Vecmocon is making the EV ecosystem smart, \nconnected and reliable by using its state-of-the-art solutions and data-centric approach, to drive the \nelectric mobility revolution in India. \nWe are a young company with futuristic vision and stellar aspirations. We are a passionate team with \ncapable and empathetic leadership, a great working environment and collaborative team culture. Job Overview As an Electronics Hardware Engineer, you will play a crucial role in designing, developing, and \ntesting products which will be deployed in Electric vehicles. Your responsibilities will span from \ninitial conceptualisation to field deployment. You’ll collaborate with cross-functional teams, \nanalyze hardware issues, and contribute to continuous improvement efforts. Key Responsibilities ● Create hardware architecture diagram based on the requirements ● Select components to meet technical and commercial requirements ● Ideate circuits and simulate them using software tools for validation ● Create and prototype electronic circuits and systems ● Guide PCB designers to create optimized layout considering technical and commercial \naspects ● Troubleshoot and diagnose issues during testing phases ● Investigate hardware failures and identify their root causes, and create reports ● Create and maintain engineering documentation, including design specifications, test \nplans, and reports ● Work closely with software engineers, firmware developers, and other team members to \nintegrate hardware with software systems ● Participate in product improvement exercises such as cost optimization, failure reduction \netc.Key skills ● Good fundamentals of electrical and electronics engineering ● Hands-on experience with circuit simulation tools (e.g., LTspice, MATLAB/Simulink) ● Familiarity with testing equipment like DSO, multimeters, FRA etc ● Knowledge of PCB layout guidelines for EMI-EMC and ease of manufacturing ● Hands-on or theoretical understanding of electrical and mechanical designs of \ntransformers ● Good communication and teamwork abilities. Qualifications \nBachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering, Electronics, or a related field",
