		details:
			"About Us:SuperAGI is pioneering the future of Artificial General Intelligence with groundbreaking research and innovative AI products. Our mission is to transform the future of applications through intelligent, autonomous solutions that drive unparalleled efficiency and growth. We are building a world where AI and human intelligence collaborate seamlessly to achieve extraordinary outcomes. If you are passionate about AI and eager to be part of a team that is shaping the future, SuperAGI is the place for you.Job Summary:We are seeking a creative and detail-oriented Product Designer to join our dynamic design team. As a Product Designer, you will play a key role in designing innovative and user-centered products that create seamless experiences across digital platforms. You will work closely with cross-functional teams, including product managers, engineers, and other designers, to translate business requirements and user needs into intuitive designs that delight our customers.Key Responsibilities:Product Design: Lead the end-to-end design process for digital products, from initial concept to final implementation, ensuring a consistent and intuitive user experience across multiple platforms (web, mobile, etc.).Wireframing & Prototyping: Create wireframes, mockups, and high-fidelity prototypes that effectively communicate design concepts and interactions.UI/UX Design: Focus on creating clean, modern, and aesthetically pleasing user interfaces while ensuring usability, accessibility, and performance. Advocate for the user experience throughout the product development lifecycle.Collaboration: Work closely with product managers, engineers, and other stakeholders to iterate on designs based on feedback and technical constraints. Be an advocate for user-centered design within the team.Design Systems: Contribute to and maintain design systems, ensuring consistency and scalability across all products. Help define and enforce design standards and best practices.Brand Alignment: Ensure that the design solutions align with the company’s brand identity and visual language while enhancing the product’s usability and functionality.Problem Solving: Identify and solve complex design challenges through creative, innovative solutions that balance user needs, business goals, and technical feasibility.Required Skills & Qualifications:Experience: Experience in product design, UI/UX design, or a similar role. A portfolio showcasing a range of design work, including case studies and design processes.Proficiency with Design Tools: Strong proficiency with design and prototyping tools such as Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD, InVision, etc. Experience with design systems and version control is a plus.User-Centered Mindset: Strong understanding of user-centered design principles and methodologies. Experience with user research, wireframing, prototyping, and user testing.UI/UX Expertise: Solid knowledge of UI design patterns, user flows, and interactive design. Experience designing for mobile-first and responsive web experiences.Problem Solving & Analytical Thinking: Ability to think critically and solve complex design problems while balancing user needs, business goals, and technical constraints.Collaboration & Communication: Excellent interpersonal and communication skills. Ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams and present design concepts and rationale clearly.Attention to Detail: A keen eye for detail, typography, color, and consistency across design assets and prototypes.Preferred Qualifications:Experience in a Fast-Paced Environment:Comfort working in an agile, fast-paced development cycle where priorities may shift rapidly.Experience with HTML/CSS/JavaScript:Familiarity with front-end development and understanding of basic coding principles to collaborate better with developers.",
