			"Data Scientist (Research)Location: Hybrid –Mumbai, IndiaCompany: Commotion – Building AI Workers for the Future of CXAbout UsWe are a fast-growing startup reimagining the future of customer experience through AI Workers — persistent, multimodal agents that live across every channel, continuously listen to asynchronous events, and engage in real-time conversations.Our mission is to push the boundaries of autonomous, self-learning AI, combining the latest in speech modeling, agentic reinforcement, and memory architectures. We are building a world where AI Workers can listen, think, and speak naturally — just like humans.Role OverviewWe’re looking for a Data Scientist (Research Track) who is passionate about speech AI, multimodal learning, and large language models.This is a research-focused role, ideal for someone excited to learn, experiment, and contribute to next-generation conversational AI systems. You’ll work closely with senior researchers and engineers to explore new ideas, prototype models, and support experiments in speech-to-speech AI, real-time conversation modeling, and agentic learning.Key ResponsibilitiesResearch and develop direct speech-to-speech modeling pipelines leveraging LLM backbones (e.g., Qwen) and audio encoders/decoders (e.g., Whisper).Model and evaluate turn-taking, latency handling, and voice activity detection (VAD) mechanisms for real-time conversational AI.Explore Agentic Reinforcement Training (ART) and self-learning loops for continual improvement of speech models.Design and experiment with memory-augmented multimodal architectures that allow persistent recall and contextual understanding across interactions.Develop novel approaches for expressive speech generation, emotion conditioning, and speaker identity preservation.Collaborate with the Research Director to define and drive long-term AI research roadmaps around autonomy, speech cognition, and agentic intelligence.Conduct internal benchmarks and contribute to SOTA research in multimodal learning, audio-language alignment, and agent reasoning.Work closely with MLEs for model training and evaluation, while focusing entirely on research design, datasets, and experimentation.Requirements.Education: Bachelor’s or Master’s in Computer Science, AI/ML, Electrical Engineering, or related fields.Programming: Strong Python skills; comfortable with NumPy, PyTorch/TensorFlowCore Skills:Deep understanding of LLM architectures, transformers, and multimodal embeddings.Interest in speech processing (ASR, TTS, audio encoders) or LLM-based systems.Strong background in dataset curation, experimental design, and model evaluation.Bonus (Nice-To-Have, Not Mandatory):Exposure to audio processing libraries.Familiarity with any of the following: VAD, ASR, TTS, reinforcement learning.Soft Skills:Strong curiosity and eagerness to learn frontier AI research.Ability to analyze, experiment, and iterate with guidance.What We OfferOpportunity to work on frontier research in speech, multimodal, and agentic AI.Access to dedicated compute infrastructure and collaboration with experienced ML researchers.Environment that encourages paper publication, experimentation, and rapid innovation.High-growth trajectory in one of the fastest-evolving AI domains globally.",
