		details:
			"Machine Learning EngineerLocation: Hybrid –Mumbai, India Company: Commotion – Building AI Workers for the Future of CXAbout UsWe are a fast-growing startup reimagining the future of customer experience through AI Workers — persistent, multimodal agents that live across every channel, continuously listen to asynchronous events, and engage in real-time conversations.Our mission is to push the boundaries of autonomous, self-learning AI, combining the latest in speech modeling, agentic reinforcement, and memory architectures. We are building a world where AI Workers can listen, think, and speak naturally — just like humans.Role OverviewAs a Machine Learning Engineer (Entry Level), you will help build and scale the ML backbone of our AI Worker platform. You will work on the full ML cycle — from data ingestion and preprocessing to training, deployment, and continual reinforcement learning. This role blends deep research with production-grade engineering, giving you the chance to work on systems that must deliver near real-time responses across multiple modalities (voice, chat, and beyond).Key ResponsibilitiesDevelop ML models that power AI Workers capable of handling both event-driven async interactions and real-time conversations.Own the end-to-end ML lifecycle: data pipelines, training, evaluation, deployment, and monitoring.Design and implement reinforcement learning algorithms (online and offline) for continuous self-improvement of AI Workers.Collaborate with engineering teams to integrate ML systems into distributed, cloud-native infrastructures (AWS, GCP, Azure).Work with Kubernetes, Docker, and networking/OS fundamentals to ensure low-latency, scalable deployments.Translate research insights into practical, production-ready ML features.Build and optimize models for real-time voice interactions, including ASR, TTS, Speech to Speech, diarization, and VAD.Implement streaming inference pipelines for low-latency voice agent deployment. Integrate multimodal processing (voice + text) to create fluid, human-like conversational agents.Enhance voice agents through RL, continual learning, and user behavior feedback loops.Requirements.Programming & CS Fundamentals:Strong programming skills in Python (bonus if also comfortable with C++/Java).Solid grasp of data structures, algorithms, operating systems, and networking fundamentals.Background in competitive programming / coding contests (Codeforces, LeetCode, ICPC, etc.) is highly valued — we want fast, efficient coders who can think under constraints.Familiarity with agentic coding tools (e.g., Cursor, Claude Code, GitHub Copilot) and ability to leverage them productively is a plus.Strong debugging skills and ability to optimize for performance and latency.Machine Learning Foundations:Strong understanding of core ML concepts (supervised, unsupervised, reinforcement learning). Exposure to Large Language Models (LLMs) and their training/finetuning.Awareness of multimodal ML (text, voice, image, video) and related architectures.Basics of speech processing (ASR/TTS), computer vision, and representation learning.Curiosity to explore cutting-edge research in agentic AI, continual learning, and real-time inference.Frameworks & Tools:Experience or familiarity with PyTorch, TensorFlow, Scikit-learn.Exposure to modern LLM and agent ecosystems: vLLM, HuggingFace, Agno, Langflow, CrewAI, LoRA finetuning.Comfort with Git, CI/CD, and collaborative development practices.Systems Knowledge:Understanding of ML model training pipelines: data ingestion, preprocessing, distributed training, evaluation, and deployment.Familiarity with scaling ML systems in production (latency optimization, load balancing, monitoring).Comfort with cloud-native environments (AWS, GCP, Azure) and containerization/orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes).What We OfferOpportunity to work on next-gen AI Workers, beyond traditional chatbots and conversational systems.High-growth, high-learning environment — strong mentorship, cutting-edge research, and real-world engineering.Industry-best compensation with no upper cap on career growth.Chance to shape how AI Workers redefine customer experience across industries.",
