		details:
			"MANAGER\nPOSTS – ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA & SELECTION PROCESS\n\nELIGIBILITY\nCRITERIA:\n\n \n \n Post Name\n \n \n Ex. Grade\n \n \n Scale of Pay (Rs.)\n \n \n Upper Age Limit as on cut-off date (yrs)\n \n \n \n \n Manager (Metallurgy)\n \n \n Gr-IV\n \n \n 60,000-3%-1,80,000\n \n \n OBC – 43\n SC / ST - 45\n \n \n\n \n\n§ \nThe above-mentioned vacancies will be filled\nby visiting multiple institutes/campuses including yours. The result will be\nprepared & declared based on the overall final merit list of candidates, after\nconducting campus recruitment drive in all the intended campuses and considering\nroster/reservation points.\n\n \n\n§ The eligible streams are only Metallurgy /\nMaterial Science.\n\n \n\n§ The mandated qualification for this post is\nPhD (Doctor of Philosophy). The cut-off date for completion of the course i.e.\nPhD is 31 Jul 2026, failing which the candidature of the candidate shall\nnot be considered and will be summarily rejected.\n\n \n\n§ Cut-Off\nDate for upper age limit is 01 Dec 2025. Age relaxation in accordance with the\nGovernment of India orders issued from time to time are applicable and extended.\nCandidates seeking reservation as OBC are required to mandatorily provide the OBC\nNCL certificate regarding his/her “OBC Non-Creamy Layer (NCL) Status” issued by\nthe competent authority at the time of document verification. In case of\nunavailability of recent certificate, the candidates may submit old OBC\nNon-Creamy Layer (NCL) Certificate at the time of document verification,\nhowever, such candidates, if provisionally selected, will have to mandatorily\nproduce original OBC Non-Creamy Layer certificate before joining and it should\nbe issued on or after 01 Jun 2025.\n\n§ Only Indian nationals can\napply.\n\n \n\n \n\nSELECTION PROCESS:\n\n \n\n§ Direct Interviews will be\nconducted for the eligible candidates.\n\n \n\n§ Document verification will be\ndone for all eligible candidates prior to conducting interviews. Only those\ncandidates who clear the document verification process will be further allowed\nto appear for interviews. All the candidates who fulfil the eligibility criteria\n& clear the document verification process will be allowed to appear for\ninterview.\n\n \n\n§ \nPercentage\nof marks / CGPA of the highest available qualification will be considered and\nthe candidates should have secured a minimum of 60% marks or equivalent CGPA in\nthe available qualifying degree (minimum 50% marks or equivalent CGPA for SC/ST\ncandidates, as posts are reserved for them), in the aggregate up to and\nincluding previous semester for which results are declared, as per\napplicability.\n\n \n\n§ Even if a candidate is\nprovisionally selected in campus recruitment on the basis of qualifying marks\navailable at the time of campus selection process, he/she should obtain minimum\n60% marks or equivalent CGPA in aggregate at the time of completion of the course\n(minimum 50% marks or equivalent CGPA in aggregate at the time of completion of\nthe course for SC/ST candidates, as posts\nare reserved for them). The\ncandidature of candidates not meeting\nthis criterion will be summarily rejected.\n\n \n\n§ \nEven\nif a candidate is selected in campus recruitment, he/she should complete PhD\nwithin the prescribed date. If\nthe provisionally selected candidate is unable to complete PhD within the\nprescribed date, the candidature of such candidate will be summarily rejected.\n\n \n\n§ After the results are declared,\nprovisional offer letters will be issued to the selected candidate(s).\n\n \n\n§ Pre-employment medical\nexamination will be conducted for the provisionally selected candidate(s).\n\n \n\n§ Final offer letter will be\nissued subject to the provisionally selected candidates clearing the pre-\nemployment medical examination conducted by MIDHANI and receipt of Identity cum\nCharacter Certificate(s).\n\n \n\n§ Joining of selected candidate\nwill be carried out, after he / she passes out from the college and receives\nthe provisional or final degree of the qualifying course from the college\nwithin the prescribed period/MIDHANI’s requirement.\n\n \n\n§ \nDecision\nof MIDHANI Management regarding selection will be final. Further, MIDHANI\nManagement reserves the right to fill up or otherwise, any or all the aforesaid\nposts and also to fill up future vacancies, if any, from the valid panel of\nselected candidates as per the rules of the company.\n\n \n\nCTC TO BE OFFERED:\n\n \n\n§ \nApproximately Rs. 18.5 Lakhs per Annum\n\n \n\n \n\nBOND:\n\n \n\n§ The candidates selected for the post of Manager\n(Metallurgy) are required to execute a service bond for a period of 3 years from\nthe date of joining.\n\n \n\n§ Bond Violation Recovery will be done as under:\n\n \n\n \n \n (i)\n \n \n If he/she leaves the service before the\n expiry of one full year\n \n \n The actual expenses incurred (including the\n amount paid during the probation period) subject to a maximum of Rs. 2.00 lakhs.\n \n \n \n \n (ii)\n \n \n If he/she leaves the service after one Year\n but before completing three Years\n \n \n Then\n proportionately less incurred (including the amount paid during probation\n period) for every year of service completed subject to a maximum of Rs. 3.00\n lakhs.\n \n \n \n \n EXPLANATION:\n Portion of less than 12 months service put in shall be ignored for this\n purpose.",
