			"MANAGEMENT\nTRAINEE (MT) POSTS – ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA & SELECTION PROCESS\n\nELIGIBILITY\nCRITERIA:\n\n \n \n Post Name\n \n \n Ex. Grade\n \n \n Scale of Pay (Rs.)\n \n \n Upper Age Limit as on cut-off date (yrs)\n \n \n \n \n Management Trainee (Metallurgy)\n \n \n Gr-II\n \n \n 40,000-3%-1,40,000\n \n \n UR / EWS – 30\n OBC – 33\n SC - 35\n \n \n\n \n\n§ \nThe above-mentioned vacancies will be filled\nby visiting multiple institutes/campuses including yours. The result will be\nprepared & declared based on the overall final merit list of candidates, after\nconducting campus recruitment drive in all the intended campuses and considering\nroster/reservation points.\n\n \n\n§ The eligible streams are only Metallurgy /\nMaterial Science.\n\n \n\n§ The mandated qualification for the post of MT\nwill only be BE/ B.Tech. Interested candidates pursuing higher qualifications\nviz. ME/ M.Tech, Dual Degree B.Tech + M.Tech, MS (By Research), even PhD etc.\nmeeting all other mandatory eligibility criteria will be allowed to appear for\nthe selection process for MT posts, provided that their course completion\nperiod aligns with MIDHANI's requirements.\n\n \n\n§ Candidates in final year will only be\neligible for appearing in campus recruitment process and they should complete\nthe qualifying degree within the prescribed period of the course as defined by\nthe institute. For candidates pursuing MS (By Research) or PhD, the cut-off\ndate for completion of the course is 31 Jul 2026, failing which their\ncandidature shall not be considered and will be summarily rejected.\n\n \n\n§ Cut-Off\nDate for upper age limit is 01 Dec 2025. Age relaxation in accordance with the\nGovernment of India orders issued from time to time are applicable and extended.\nCandidates seeking reservation as EWS/ OBC are required to mandatorily provide\nthe EWS/ OBC NCL certificate regarding his/her “EWS/ OBC Non-Creamy Layer (NCL)\nStatus” issued by the competent authority at the time of document verification.\nIn case of unavailability of recent certificate, the candidates may submit old\nEWS/ OBC Non-Creamy Layer (NCL) Certificate at the time of document\nverification, however, such candidates, if provisionally selected, will have to\nmandatorily produce original EWS/ OBC Non-Creamy Layer certificate before joining\nand it should be issued on or after 01 Jun 2025.\n\n§ Only Indian nationals can\napply.\n\n \n\nSELECTION PROCESS:\n\n \n\n§ Direct Interviews will be\nconducted for the eligible candidates.\n\n \n\n§ Document verification will be\ndone for all eligible candidates prior to conducting interviews. Only those\ncandidates who clear the document verification process will be further allowed\nto appear for interviews. All the candidates who fulfil the eligibility\ncriteria & clear the document verification process will be allowed to\nappear for interview.\n\n \n\n§ Percentage of marks / CGPA of\nthe highest available qualification will be considered and the candidates\nshould have secured a minimum of 60% marks or equivalent CGPA in the available\nqualifying degree (minimum 50% marks or equivalent CGPA for SC candidates, as posts\nare reserved for them) in the aggregate up to and including previous semester\nfor which results are declared.\n\n \n\n§ Even if a candidate is\nprovisionally selected in campus recruitment on the basis of qualifying marks\nof the available semesters, he/she should obtain minimum 60% marks or\nequivalent CGPA in aggregate at the time of completion of the said Degree\nincluding all the semesters (minimum 50% marks or equivalent CGPA in aggregate\nat the time of completion of the said Degree including all the semesters for SC\ncandidates, as posts are reserved for them). The candidature of candidates not meeting this criterion will be\nsummarily rejected.\n\n \n\n§ \nEven\nif a candidate is selected in campus recruitment, he/she should complete the\nqualifying Degree / higher courses within the prescribed period of the course/ MIDHANI’s\nrequirement. If the provisionally selected candidate is unable to complete the\nqualifying Degree / higher courses within the prescribed period of the\ncourse/MIDHANI’s requirement, the candidature of such candidate will be\nsummarily rejected.\n\n \n\n§ After the results are\ndeclared, provisional offer letters will be issued to the selected candidate(s).\n\n \n\n§ Pre-employment medical\nexamination will be conducted for the provisionally selected candidate(s).\n\n \n\n§ Final offer letter will be\nissued subject to the provisionally selected candidates clearing the pre-\nemployment medical examination conducted by MIDHANI and receipt of Identity cum\nCharacter Certificate(s).\n\n \n\n§ Joining of selected candidate\nwill be carried out, after he / she passes out from the college and receives\nthe provisional or final degree of the qualifying / higher course from the\ncollege within the prescribed period/MIDHANI’s requirement & obtains the\nqualifying percentage of marks, as per applicability.\n\n \n\n§ \nDecision\nof MIDHANI Management regarding selection will be final. Further, MIDHANI\nManagement reserves the right to fill up or otherwise, any or all the aforesaid\nposts and also to fill up future vacancies, if any, from the valid panel of\nselected candidates as per the rules of the company.\n\n \n\nCTC TO BE OFFERED:\n\n \n\n§ \nApproximately Rs. 11.8 Lakhs per Annum\n\n \n\n§ After\nsatisfactory completion of one year training period, the incumbent will be absorbed\nas Assistant Manager.\n\n \n\nBOND:\n\n \n\n§ The candidates selected for the post of\nManagement Trainee will be on training for a period of one year and are\nrequired to execute a service bond for a period of 5 years effective from the\ndate of absorption into regular post. \n\n \n\n§ Bond Violation Recovery will be done as under:\n\n \n\n \n \n (i)\n \n \n In case the Trainee abandons the training\n before the completion of the period of training\n \n \n The actual cost of training incurred for the\n period of training undergone subject to a maximum of Rs.3.00 lakhs.\n \n \n \n \n (ii)\n \n \n If he/she leaves the service before the\n expiry of one full year\n \n \n The actual training expenses incurred\n (including the amount paid during the training period) subject to a maximum\n of Rs. 3.00 lakhs.\n And\n If he/she\n leaves the service after one Year but before completing five Years, then\n proportionately less by 1/5th of the training expenses incurred\n (including the amount paid during training period) for every year of service\n completed subject to a maximum of Rs. 4.8 lakhs.\n \n \n \n \n EXPLANATION:\n Portion of less than 12 months service put in shall be ignored for this\n purpose.",
