		details:
			"We are looking for front-end and back-end fully remote entry-level software engineer roles, ideally with knowledge of React (front-end) and/or C# (back-end). At ENTNT, our technology stack is built around a Microsoft-based ecosystem. Our core setup includes SQL Server for data management, C# and .NET for backend and API development, and React and Angular for frontend applications. For mobile, we use React Native, which allows us to deliver cross-platform apps with a single codebase.We also make extensive use of Azure DevOps for version control, automated builds, continuous integration and deployment, and project tracking. In the area of Artificial Intelligence, we work with technologies such as machine learning frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch), NLP models, and Azure AI services for tasks like text analysis, document processing, predictive analytics, and intelligent automation.",
		info: "The advertised $750 per month is take-home salary, not CTC.\n👉 This is an important distinction: unlike most Indian job postings that inflate with “CTC” figures, here we are quoting your real take-home.\nIf expressed in standard CTC terms, $750 take-home corresponds to ₹10–11 lakhs per year.\nOn top of this:\n  •  Remote-work savings: No need for a PG/hostel or metro city rent, which is typically ₹25–30k per month. Over a year, this is a ₹3 lakh value in savings.\n  •  Company retreats: We organize two retreats per year, each lasting 2 weeks, hosted in 4–5 star hotels. The value of this is another ₹1–2 lakhs annually in benefits.\n⸻\n🎯 Total Value of Package\n  •  Base take-home salary = $750/month (~₹10–11 lakhs CTC equivalent)\n  •  Remote-work savings = ~₹3 lakhs (3000 USD approx)\n  •  Paid luxury retreats = ₹1–2 lakhs (1500 USD approx)\n👉 That brings the true value of this offer to ₹14–16(13500 USD approx) lakhs per year, making it absolutely IIT-level compensation.",
