		details:
			"Role Overview:As a UAV Engineer at Nurture Aerospace, you will play a key role in the design, integration, \ntesting, and optimization of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) for a range of applications including \nsurveillance, mapping, industrial inspection, and defense. \nYou will collaborate with multidisciplinary teams in aerodynamics, electronics, propulsion, control \nsystems, and software to develop reliable, efficient, and high-performance UAV systems. This \nposition is ideal for individuals who are passionate about aerospace technology, drone innovation, \nand hands-on system engineering. Key Responsibilities: Design and integrate UAV subsystems including propulsion, avionics, and payloads. Conduct flight tests and analyze performance data. Troubleshoot and optimize UAV flight systems. Ensure compliance with safety and regulatory standards. Required Skills: Strong knowledge of aerodynamics, control systems, and propulsion. Experience with CAD tools and simulation software. Hands-on experience with UAV assembly and testing. Proficiency in Python/C++/MATLAB preferred.Eligibility: B.E./B.Tech in Aerospace, Mechanical, or Electronics Engineering. 0–2 years of relevant experience (fresh graduates welcome).",
