		details:
			"Role Overview\n\nWe are looking for a highly skilled UAV Design Engineer\nto lead the concept, design, structural development, and performance\noptimization of unmanned aerial vehicles. The ideal candidate will have strong\nexpertise in aerodynamics, airframe design, propulsion integration, CAD\nmodeling, and UAV system engineering. You will work closely with\nmultidisciplinary teams to create innovative, reliable, and high-performance\nUAV platforms.\n\n \n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n1. UAV Concept & Design Development\n\n Develop\n conceptual and detailed designs for fixed-wing, multirotor, VTOL, or\n hybrid UAVs.\n Perform\n aerodynamic analysis, sizing, weight estimation, and layout configuration.\n Build\n 3D CAD models and engineering drawings for prototypes and production-ready\n aircraft.\n\n2. Structural & Mechanical Engineering\n\n Design\n airframes using composites, lightweight metals, and additive manufacturing\n methods.\n Conduct\n structural analysis (FEM) to validate strength, stiffness, and durability.\n Optimize\n UAV structure for weight, manufacturability, and performance.\n\n3. Propulsion & Subsystem Integration\n\n Select\n and integrate propulsion systems: motors, ESCs, propellers, batteries,\n fuel systems, etc.\n Work\n with avionics teams to integrate sensors, flight controllers, antennas,\n and power systems.\n Ensure\n proper thermal management, vibration reduction, and component placement.\n\n4. Simulation, Testing & Validation\n\n Perform\n aerodynamic simulations (CFD), stability analysis, and performance\n prediction.\n Support\n prototype fabrication and participate in ground/flight tests.\n Analyze\n test data to refine design parameters and improve system performance.\n\n5. Documentation & Collaboration\n\n Create\n design documentation, BOMs, technical reports, and test records.\n Work\n closely with R&D, manufacturing, avionics, and software teams.\n Support\n pilot builds, production processes, and design reviews.\n\n \n\nRequired Qualifications\n\n Bachelor’s/master’s degree in aerospace engineering, Mechanical Engineering, or related field.\n Proficiency\n in 3D CAD tools (SolidWorks, CATIA, Fusion 360, NX, etc.).\n Strong\n understanding of aerodynamics, flight mechanics, and structural design.\n Experience\n with CFD tools (ANSYS Fluent, XFoil/XFLR5, Open FOAM, etc.).\n Knowledge\n of structural analysis using FEA tools (ANSYS, Abaqus, Hyper Mesh, etc.).\n Familiarity\n with UAV systems: propulsion, avionics, power systems, materials.\n Knowledge\n of PX4/ArduPilot ecosystem is a plus.\n\n \n\nPreferred Experience\n\n Hands-on\n experience with prototype building, composites, and manufacturing\n processes.\n Understanding\n of regulatory requirements for UAV design and testing.\n Experience\n with MATLAB/Simulink for modeling and analysis.\n Knowledge\n of rapid prototyping, 3D printing, and composite layup methods.\n Familiarity\n with flight testing procedures and data analysis tools (Mission Planner,\n QGroundControl, etc.).\n\n \n\nSoft Skills\n\n Strong\n analytical and problem-solving abilities.\n Excellent\n communication and technical writing skills.\n Ability\n to work independently and in cross-functional teams.\n Detail-oriented,\n innovative, and proactive mindset.",
		info: "",
		reqs: "",
		url: "https://campus.placements.iitb.ac.in/applicant/job/12443",
