			"Resume filtering | Introductory round  (30 Mins ) | Technical round  (30 mins ) | Practical Assessment/ Technical assignment  (24 hrs ) | Management round  (1 hr )",
		details:
			"Role Overview\n\nWe are seeking a passionate and highly skilled Research\n& Development Engineer to join our core engineering team. In this role,\nyou will design, prototype, test, and optimize new drone technologies and\nsubsystems—including aerodynamics, propulsion, electronics, sensors, autonomy,\nand payload integrations. You will collaborate across multidisciplinary teams\nto transform conceptual ideas into production-ready solutions.\n\n \n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nResearch & Innovation\n\n Conduct\n research on cutting-edge drone technologies, autonomous flight systems,\n and emerging aerospace trends.\n Explore\n advanced materials, propulsion systems, power systems, sensors, and\n communication technologies.\n Identify\n opportunities for performance enhancement, cost reduction, and improved\n reliability.\n\nDesign & Development\n\n Design\n and model drone components and assemblies using CAD and simulation tools.\n Develop\n prototypes (mechanical, electrical, and software subsystems) and validate\n performance through iterative testing.\n Work\n on flight control algorithms, embedded systems, and payload integration\n (EO/IR cameras, LiDAR, GPS, etc.).\n\nTesting & Validation\n\n Plan\n and execute lab tests, ground tests, and flight tests to evaluate system\n performance.\n Analyze\n test data to refine designs and troubleshoot performance issues.\n Prepare\n detailed documentation, test reports, and design specifications.\n\nCross-Functional Collaboration\n\n Work\n closely with aerodynamics, electronics, software, and manufacturing teams\n to ensure seamless integration.\n Support\n product certification, regulatory compliance, and quality assurance\n processes.\n Assist\n in transitioning prototypes to scalable production.\n\n \n\nRequired Qualifications\n\n Bachelor’s\n or master’s degree in aerospace engineering, Mechanical Engineering,\n Robotics, Electrical Engineering, or related field.\n Strong\n knowledge of aerodynamics, flight mechanics, propulsion systems, and\n structural design.\n Hands-on\n experience with UAV components, sensors, telemetry systems, and flight\n controllers (e.g., PX4, ArduPilot).\n Proficiency\n in CAD tools (SolidWorks, CATIA, Fusion 360) and simulation tools\n (MATLAB/Simulink, Ansys, CFD).\n Experience\n with embedded systems, microcontrollers, PCB design, or firmware\n development is a plus.\n Strong\n analytical, problem-solving, and experimental design skills.\n\n \n\nPreferred Skills (Good to Have)\n\n Experience\n with autonomous navigation, SLAM, or AI-based flight algorithms.\n Knowledge\n of battery systems, hybrid propulsion, and energy management.\n Understanding\n of DO-160, MIL-STD, or other aerospace standards.\n Experience\n with composite materials and lightweight structural engineering.\n Familiarity\n with ROS, Python, or C++ for robotics and flight autonomy.\n\nPersonal Attributes\n\n Innovative\n mindset with a passion for pushing the boundaries of aerial robotics.\n Strong\n communication and documentation skills.\n Ability\n to thrive in a fast-paced, research-driven environment.\n Team\n player with strong ownership and accountability.",
		info: "",
