		details:
			"GO DIGITAL TECHNOLOGY CONSULTING LLPRole: Data Consultant (Campus Hire – Full Time)Location: Mumbai / PuneAbout the RoleWe are looking for smart, analytical, and technically strong problem-solvers who are passionate about data, technology, and real-world business challenges. As a Data Consultant, you will work at the intersection of data engineering, analytics, cloud technologies, and consulting.You will help design and evaluate data solutions, support digital transformation initiatives, and collaborate with cross-functional teams to solve high-impact problems for global enterprises.This role is ideal for students who enjoy:Solving complex data problemsBuilding and understanding systemsWorking with modern technologiesCommunicating ideas clearlyWorking in a fast-paced consulting environmentKey Responsibilities1. Technical Consulting & Data StrategyAnalyze data ecosystems including pipelines, architectures, and integration layers.Contribute to data strategies for ingestion, governance, modeling, and quality.Recommend scalable data architectures aligned to client needs (cloud, big data, modern data stacks).2. Data Architecture & EvaluationReview existing systems, data sources, and flows to identify gaps or improvement areas.Translate business requirements into technical specifications, data models, and workflows.Evaluate tools and platforms that support modernization or migration initiatives.3. Solution & Product DesignWork with data engineers, architects, and product teams to design robust data solutions.Contribute to architecture diagrams, data flow designs, integration patterns, and prototypes.Apply user-centric thinking to create intuitive dashboards, analytics, or data products.4. Technical Pre-Sales & Internal EnablementPrepare technical solution decks, architecture proposals, and capability presentations.Support RFP/RFI responses with solution design and effort estimation.Collaborate with internal sales and engineering teams to build demos, POVs, and reusable assets.5. Stakeholder Collaboration & Project EnablementParticipate in requirement workshops, technical discussions, and architecture reviews.Act as a bridge between business users, engineering teams, and leadership.Drive clarity in scope, deliverables, risks, and dependencies.6. Documentation & Technical CommunicationCreate technical documents such as solution designs, assessment reports, evaluation matrices, and POV summaries.Present complex technical concepts in a structured and simplified manner to stakeholders.Technical Skills (Preferred)You don’t need to know all of these — but familiarity with some is expected, and you will learn the rest on the job.Strong understanding of programming fundamentals (Python preferred).Good grasp of SQL and working with data.Knowledge of cloud basics (AWS / Azure / GCP) and modern data stack concepts.Understanding of data modelling (dimensional/relational) and data quality concepts.Awareness of visualization tools (Power BI, Tableau) and prototyping tools (Figma, Miro).Interest in modern architecture patterns such as microservices, event-driven systems, and lakehouse designs.What You Will Work on After JoiningAs a Data Consultant, you will get hands-on experience with:Designing and reviewing real-world data pipelines and workflows.Working on cloud-based data platforms and engineering solutions.Evaluating tools, technologies, and frameworks used by modern enterprises.Participating in client workshops and understanding business needs.Building prototypes, demos, dashboards, and data product concepts.Writing technical documents, solution proposals, and architecture designs.Collaborating with teams across engineering, consulting, and digital strategy.You will gradually take on more ownership as you grow.Why Join Go Digital?Opportunity to work on enterprise-grade digital and data transformation programs.Exposure to cutting-edge cloud, analytics, and engineering technologies.Work closely with senior consultants, architects, and leadership teams.Fast learning environment with continuous innovation and collaboration.Ability to influence and contribute to real client solutions early in your career.",
