		details:
			"JOB OVERVIEW :\n India's Largest Polymer Distribution Company\n This role spans customer research, product definition, and hands-on\n engineering to build and enhance digital products and platforms. You will\n work with product managers, designers, and senior engineers to convert\n business goals into scalable, high-quality software. It’s ideal for someone who\n enjoys understanding users and writing code, and wants to grow into a well\nrounded product + technology professional. CREATE \nCollaborate with Product, Design, Engineering, and Business teams to\n align features with customer needs and business goals\n .Gather and incorporate feedback from users, internal stakeholders, and\n production incidents to improve usability and product quality.\n Support documentation of features, decisions, workflow diagrams, and\n user stories for clarity and long-term maintainability.\n Work with senior product and engineering leaders to refine requirements,\n manage dependencies, and ensure seamless delivery.\n Participate in UX and customer experience discussions to improve product\n flows and usability. NURTURE \nConduct customer and market research (quantitative & qualitative) to\n understand user pain points, user journeys, and market opportunities.\n Translate business problems and user needs into structured user stories,\n technical specifications, and acceptance criteria\n .Participate in brainstorming sessions, ideation, and initial solution design.\n Contribute to backlog grooming, sprint planning, and product roadmap\n discussions with data-driven inputs.\n Monitor KPIs and feature performance using analytics tools, and\n recommend improvements or next iterations.MANAGE \nOwn small features or modules end-to-end — design, development,\n testing, and deployment — under senior mentorship.\n Write clean, efficient, well-documented code and assist in code reviews.\n Conduct unit, integration, and functional testing to ensure reliability,\n performance, and release readiness.\n Troubleshoot bugs, performance issues, and production incidents; assist\n with debugging and optimization tasks. WE ARE LOOKING FOR SOMEONE WITH:\n India's Largest Polymer Distribution Company\n Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related\n field (or graduating soon).Good fundamentals in data structures,\n algorithms, and core software engineering concepts.\n Proficiency in one modern programming language (Python, Java,\n JavaScript, Go, etc.).Familiarity with Agile/Scrum and Git-based version\n control.\n Basic understanding of databases (SQL/NoSQL) and cloud platforms\n (AWS/Azure/GCP).Strong communication skills and the ability to explain\n technical ideas clearly.\n Self-driven attitude and ability to work in a fast-paced environment.\n Passion for product + technology and interest in solving real-world\n business problems. WHY JOIN OUR TEAM?\n Mentorship: Learn directly from senior engineers and product leaders.\n Impact: Work on features that directly impact customers and business\n outcomes.\n Versatility: Gain hands-on experience across the full product + engineering\n lifecycle.\n Culture: Work in a collaborative, ownership-driven, learning-focused\n environment. PREFERRED SKILLS (GOOD TO HAVE) \nInternship experience in software development or product management.\n Projects demonstrating UX awareness or human-centered design.\n Exposure to microservices, APIs, or distributed systems.\n Experience with analytics/BI dashboards",
