		details:
			"Makr Microsystems is a venture backed\nstartup developing disruptive sub-surface and 3D metrology tools for the\nsemiconductor industry. Founded in 2024 by a group of nanotechnology and\nsoftware experts, we have core innovations in “Acoustic Atomic Force\nMicroscopy” and “Optical Tomography”. These tools will be used in both R&D\nand production of advanced semiconductor chips fabrication and packaging.\nAdvanced semiconductor fabrication involves 3D integration of complex circuits\nat the micro and nanoscale, which present unique challenges for metrology. We\nare continuously enhancing the capabilities of our instrument in\nsync with the industry requirements and building applications in collaboration\nwith global industry leaders.\n\nWe are a focused, dynamic, interdisciplinary\nteam combining nanotechnology, semiconductors, physics, data analytics,\nrobotics, controls and AI to solve cutting edge problems in the semiconductor\nfield. We love to challenge and continuously evolve ourselves. We provide a fun\nenvironment to learn and apply our knowledge to build novel solutions.\n\nRoles & Responsibilities: Development of\nmechanical, precision positioning and robotics modules of an Advanced AFM\ninstrument. Wafer metrology puts significant constraints on the positioning\nstages with respect to movement range, speed, resolution and stability. The\ncandidate will work with a core team to develop and enhance the micro and\nnanometer multi DOF positioning stages. She or he should have –\n\n- \nCreative\nproblem-solving ability involving robotics, positioners and mechanical design- \nInterest\nand familiarity with robotics, precision machines- \nProject\nexperience in mechatronics - \nGood\nexposure to programming, control systems and FEA (Finite Element Analysis)\n\nThe candidate will be involved in building out\nthe specs, iterating designs, and implementing the solutions within the broader\nproduct. There will be opportunities to interact with global semiconductor\nclients and get exposed to state-of-the-art in the field. We look for motivated\ncandidates, with a degree of independence who enjoy working within a diverse team.\nThe opportunity can be financially rewarding through competitive compensation\nand ESOPs. Excellent career growth opportunities as we build out a global deep\nscience company.",
