		details:
			"PristineAI\n– AI Solution Engineer (0–1 Years)\n\nAbout\nPristineAI\n\nOur\nflagship platform Kai unifies legacy applications, databases,\nspreadsheets, processes, and documents into a natural-language, agentic\nAI–driven intelligence layer.\n\nWith\nKai, users don’t just automate — they converse, reason, and execute through\nintelligent AI agents.\n\nWith\nour platform Kai, users can:\n\n· \nAsk their\nenterprise complex questions in natural language\n\n· \nBuild workflows\nusing agentic AI and prompt-driven orchestration\n\n· \nAutomate in\nminutes what once took months\n\nAt PristineAI, you won’t “work on\nfeatures.”\nYou will engineer the foundation of how enterprises think, reason, and act\nusing AgenticAI.\n\nWho\nWe’re Looking For\n\nWe\nare looking for relentlessly curious engineers who enjoy solving hard\nproblems, thinking from first principles, and building intelligent systems that\ndon’t exist yet.\n\nThis\nrole blends core software engineering + applied AI + agentic workflows\nwho want to work end-to-end: design → build → ship → impact.\n\nWe’re\nseeking AI Solution Engineers who combine strong engineering\nfundamentals with emerging AI capabilities — people who are analytical,\ncurious, and excited to work with Agentic AI systems in real-world\nenterprise environments.\n\n \n\nWhat\nyou’ll do\n\n· \nBuild agentic\nAI–powered enterprise systems that connect and simplify complex workflows.\n\n· \nWork hands-on\nwith LLMs, Agentic AI frameworks, Knowledge Graphs, Generative AI, and ML\npipelines.\n\n· \nApply prompt\nengineering techniques to guide reasoning, tool use, and task execution by\nAI agents.\n\n· \nImplement Retrieval-Augmented\nGeneration (RAG) using vector databases to ground AI responses in\nenterprise data.\n\n· \nTranslate real\nbusiness problems into scalable, production-grade AI solutions.\n\n· \nDesign and\nintegrate systems across .NET, React, Node.js, Python, and cloud\nenvironments.\n\n· \nCollaborate with\nteams spanning enterprise architecture, applied AI, and product engineering.\n\n \n\n \n\nWhat\nwe’re looking for\n\nWe\nevaluate candidates on skill + thinking + learning agility.\n\nRequired\n Skills\n\n Strong\n foundation in:\n CS\n fundamentals (DSA, OS, DBMS, Algorithms, System Design)\n Python and\n SQL fundamentals\n Basic\n understanding of Machine Learning & Deep Learning concepts\n Generative\n AI & LLM fundamentals\n (ChatGPT-family models, open-source LLMs)\n Prompt\n engineering basics\n (prompt structuring, role prompting, reasoning prompts)\n RAG\n fundamentals and\n awareness of vector databases (FAISS, Pinecone, Chroma)\n Conceptual\n understanding of agentic AI workflows (multi-step reasoning, tool\n calling, orchestration)\n Familiarity\n with LangChain, LlamaIndex, OpenAI / Hugging Face APIs (academic or\n project-level exposure is sufficient)\n Understanding\n of end-to-end AI pipelines (data → inference → evaluation →\n iteration)\n Cloud\n fundamentals (AWS / Azure / GCP)\n Version\n control using Git / GitHub\n Exposure to unit\n testing and integration testing\n\n \n\nEligibility:\n\nBachelor’s\nor Master’s degree in Computer\nScience, Statistics, Mathematics, Data Science.\n\nWho\nwill thrive here\n\nWe\nvalue mindset more than buzzwords.\n\n Owners, not\n operators — you\n see things through end-to-end.\n Fast\n learners — you\n pick up frameworks, tools, concepts quickly.\n Curiosity-driven\n thinkers — you\n enjoy breaking down problems.\n Adaptable\n builders —\n comfortable with rapid prototyping and iteration.\n Team players — collaborative, humble, and open\n to feedback.\n\n \n\nWhy\njoin PristineAI\n\n Build at the\n intersection of enterprise systems, Agentic AI, and Generative AI\n engineering.\n Work\n hands-on with LLMs, Agentic AI workflows, prompt engineering, RAG\n pipelines, and vector databases to solve real enterprise problems.\n 2 weeks of\n annual learning leave\n Competitive\n salary + equity\n High-trust,\n inclusive, curiosity-driven culture\n Opportunity\n to shape a platform used by Fortune-scale enterprises\n\nIf\nyou’re excited to build intelligent systems that think, plan, and act — not\njust generate text — we’d love to meet you.",
		info: "",
		reqs: "Minimum\nRequirements\n\nEducation\n& Academic Performance\n\n· \nBachelor’s or\nMaster’s degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Data Science.\n\n· \nMinimum 60%\naggregate throughout academics (10th, 12th, Graduation).\n\n· \nNo active\nbacklogs.\n\n \n\nCommunication\n& Problem-Solving\n\n· \nGood to excellent\ncommunication skills (minimum 7/10 self-rating or equivalent).\n\n· \nAbility to\narticulate thoughts clearly and work in cross-functional teams.\n\n· \nDemonstrated\nproblem-solving mindset through projects, competitions, GitHub work, or\ninternships.\n\n \n\nBehavioral\nCompetencies\n\n· \nHigh willingness\nto learn, adapt, and grow in a fast-paced product environment.\n\n· \nResilience and\nemotional steadiness — ability to stay composed, manage pressure, and remain\nproductive during demanding workloads.\n\n· \nStrong work\ndiscipline, reliability, and consistent follow-through.\n\n· \nOpenness to\nfeedback and collaborative working style.\n\n \n\nLocation\n& Work Mode\n\n· \nRole is 100% Work\nFrom Office — 5 days a week.(Monday to Friday)\n\n· \nOffice location:\nMumbai (No remote or hybrid option).\n\n· \nNo accommodation\nor relocation support provided — preference for candidates already based in\nMumbai or with family accommodation in the city.\n\n \n\nOther\nRequirements\n\n· \nReady to join in\nJuly 2026.\n\n· \nWillingness to\nundergo training and assessment during the onboarding period.\n\n· \nMust be legally\neligible to work in India.",
