			"PristineAI –\nSoftware Engineer / Solution Engineer (0–1 Years)\n\n \n\nAbout PristineAI\n\nOur flagship platform Kai unifies\nlegacy applications, databases, spreadsheets, processes, and documents into\na natural-language intelligence layer.\nWith Kai, users don’t just automate — they converse, create, and\nexecute.\n\nWith our platform Kai,\nusers can:\n\nAsk their enterprise a question\nBuild workflows using natural language\nAutomate in minutes what once took months\n\nAt PristineAI, you won’t “work on features.”\n\nYou will engineer the\nfoundation of how enterprises think and operate in the age of AI.\n\nIf you're someone who wants to build\nwhat has never been built before — this is your place.\n\nWe are looking for relentlessly\ncurious engineers who love solving hard problems, thinking from first\nprinciples, and building systems that don’t exist yet.\n\nThis role is a blend of core\nsoftware engineering + applied AI, ideal for IIT-level talent who want to\nwork end-to-end: design → build → ship → impact.\n\n \n\nWhat you’ll do\n\n Build AI-powered enterprise\n systems that connect and simplify complex workflows.\n Work hands-on with LLMs,\n Knowledge Graphs, Generative AI, and ML pipelines.\n Translate business problems into scalable,\n production-grade solutions.\n Design and integrate systems across .NET,\n React, Node.js, Python, and cloud environments.\n Collaborate with a team combining enterprise\n architecture + applied AI + product engineering.\n\n \n\nWhat we’re\nlooking for\n\nWe evaluate candidates on skill\n+ thinking + learning agility.\n\nRequired Skills\n\nStrong foundation in:\n\n Strong CS fundamentals (DSA, OS, DBMS,\n Algorithms, System Design)\n Projects\n or experience in .NET / Node.js / Python / JavaScript\n Understanding\n of REST APIs, Git/GitHub, SQL/Oracle\n Comfortable with full-stack problem\n solving\n Ability to write clean, modular, testable\n code\n SQL fundamentals (Oracle experience is a\n plus)\n Testing (unit + integration)\n\n \n\nPreferred (Not\nMandatory)\n\n Cloud exposure (Azure preferred)\n Experience with enterprise systems or\n microservices\n Interest in AI, ML, or automation\n workflows\n\n \n\n \n\nEligibility:\n\n B.Tech/M.Tech in Computer Science.\n\n \n\nWho will thrive\nhere\n\nWe value mindset more than buzzwords.\n\n Owners, not operators — you see things through\n end-to-end.\n Fast learners — you pick up frameworks, tools,\n concepts quickly.\n Curiosity-driven thinkers — you enjoy breaking down problems.\n Adaptable builders — comfortable with rapid\n prototyping and iteration.\n Team players — collaborative, humble, and open\n to feedback.\n\n \n\nWhy join\nPristineAI\n\n Build at the intersection of enterprise\n systems + Generative AI + engineering\n Work with experts across applied\n AI, data, product, and architecture\n 2 weeks of annual learning leave\n Competitive salary + equity\n High-trust, inclusive, curiosity-driven\n culture\n Opportunity to shape a platform used\n by Fortune-scale enterprises\n\nIf engineering\nexcites you and AI inspires you, we’d love to meet you.",
		info: "Compensation Flexibility\nPristineAI is open to offering higher CTC within the fresher band for exceptional candidates. Students with strong internship experience, high-impact projects, outstanding GitHub portfolios, or notable presentations/publications may be considered for an enhanced starting package of ₹10–12 LPA, based on overall evaluation.",
