		details:
			"About GruveGruve is an innovative software services startup dedicated to transforming enterprises to AI powerhouses. We specialize in cybersecurity, customer experience, cloud infrastructure, and advanced technologies such as Large Language Models (LLMs). Our mission is to assist our customers in their business strategies utilizing their data to make more intelligent decisions. As a well-funded early-stage startup, Gruve offers a dynamic environment with strong customer and partner networks.Position SummaryWe are looking for bright, enthusiastic Engineers to join our AI team. As a fresher, you will work with experienced software and ML engineers to build, test, and deploy AI-based solutions—especially in the areas of Large Language Models (LLMs) and modern machine learning. This role offers a unique opportunity to learn cutting-edge AI technologies while contributing to real-world products.Key Responsibilities· AI/ML Development: Assist in designing and building scalable AI systems, focusing on LLMs and deep-learning applications.· Model Training & Fine-Tuning: Work on data preparation, model training, fine-tuning, and evaluation under senior guidance.· Experimentation & Research: Explore modern techniques like LoRA/Q-LoRA, reasoning models (e.g., DeepSeek-R1), and other emerging AI methods.· Data Engineering: Support dataset creation, preprocessing, and quality checks for model training.· Performance Optimization: Learn to improve model accuracy, inference speed, and compute efficiency.· AI Deployment: Gain exposure to deploying models on cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP) and integrating them into applications.· API & Backend Development: Help build APIs and microservices that power AI-driven products.· MLOps: Learn best practices for CI/CD, monitoring, and maintaining AI models in production.· Collaboration: Work closely with mentors, product teams, and engineers to solve real business problems using AI.· Ethical AI & Security: Understand and follow responsible AI and data privacy guidelines.Basic Qualifications· B.Tech / Dual Degree / M.Tech in Computer Science, Data Science, Electrical Engineering, Mathematics & Computing, or related fields.· Strong programming skills in Python.· Good understanding of machine learning fundamentals.· Hands-on experience with Python ML libraries (PyTorch, TensorFlow, scikit-learn) through projects, internships, or coursework.· Familiarity with frontend technologies (e.g., React) is a bonus.· Basic knowledge of LLMs or transformer models is a plus, not mandatory.Preferred Qualifications· Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.· Passion for AI/ML and eagerness to learn from senior engineers.· Ability to communicate ideas clearly and work in a collaborative team environment.· Attention to detail and curiosity to explore new technologies.Why Gruve:At Gruve, we foster a culture of innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone can thrive and contribute their best work. If you’re passionate about technology and eager to make an impact, we’d love to hear from you.Gruve is an equal opportunity employer. We welcome applicants from all backgrounds and thank all who apply; however, only those selected for an interview will be contacted.",
