			"About GruveGruve is an innovative software services startup dedicated to transforming enterprises to AI powerhouses. We specialize in cybersecurity, customer experience, cloud infrastructure, and advanced technologies such as Large Language Models (LLMs). Our mission is to assist our customers in their business strategies utilizing their data to make more intelligent decisions. As a well-funded early-stage startup, Gruve offers a dynamic environment with strong customer and partner networks.Position SummaryWe are hiring bright, motivated Software Engineers to join our development team. As a fresher, you will work with senior engineers to build high-quality backend systems, APIs, automation tools, and data-driven applications using either Java or Python. This role offers hands-on exposure to modern engineering practices, cloud technologies, and real-world product development.Key Responsibilities· Backend Development: Assist in building scalable backend services using Java (Spring Boot) or Python (Django/Flask/FastAPI).· API & Microservices: Develop and maintain RESTful APIs and microservices with proper documentation and testing.· Database Engineering: Work with SQL/NoSQL databases—schema design, queries, and performance improvements.· Automation & Scripting: Contribute to automation scripts, tools, and data workflows as required.· Code Quality: Write clean, testable code and participate in code reviews.· Cloud & Deployment: Get exposure to deploying services on AWS, Azure, or GCP and working with CI/CD pipelines.· Debugging & Optimization: Support performance tuning, troubleshooting, and improving reliability of applications.· Collaboration: Work closely with senior developers, QA, and product teams to deliver high-quality features.· Continuous Learning: Explore modern frameworks, tools, and best practices in Java/Python development.Basic Qualifications· B.Tech / Dual Degree / M.Tech in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Data Science, Mathematics & Computing, or related fields.· Strong programming skills in Java or Python.· Good understanding of data structures, algorithms, OOP, and software engineering fundamentals.· Familiarity with frameworks such as Spring Boot, Django, Flask, or FastAPI through projects or internships.· Understanding of SQL and basic database concepts.Preferred Qualifications· Problem-solving mindset and strong analytical skills.· Experience with Git, Linux, or cloud platforms (AWS/Azure/GCP).· Curiosity to explore new technologies and contribute to team discussions.· Strong communication and collaboration abilities.Why Gruve:At Gruve, we foster a culture of innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone can thrive and contribute their best work. If you’re passionate about technology and eager to make an impact, we’d love to hear from you.Gruve is an equal opportunity employer. We welcome applicants from all backgrounds and thank all who apply; however, only those selected for an interview will be contacted.",
