		details:
			"Visual/UI Designer Company: Marvin Location: Fully RemoteRole Type: Full-timeAbout the RoleWe’re looking for a passionate and motivated Visual/UI Designer to join our fast-growing team at Marvin. This is an incredible opportunity to work closely with our marketing and product teams, build real-world design experience, and contribute to projects that reach thousands of users. If you love bringing ideas to life through stunning visuals and intuitive user interfaces, you’ll feel right at home here.What You’ll DoDesign visually compelling, responsive websites and landing pages.Create wireframes, high-fidelity mockups, and interactive prototypes.Work closely with developers to ensure designs are implemented beautifully and accurately.Optimize pages for performance, accessibility, and scalability.Stay current with modern design trends, tools, and technologies.What We’re Looking ForExperience as a Visual Designer, UI Designer, or similar role.Strong grasp of Visual design principles, layout, and responsive design.Hands-on experience with no-code tools like Webflow or Framer.Basic understanding of HTML, CSS, or JavaScript (nice to have).Excellent communication, collaboration, and problem-solving skills.Bonus Points If You HaveExperience working with CMS platforms (e.g., WordPress, Webflow).Familiarity with SEO basics and accessibility best practices.You’ll Be a Great Fit If You…Are obsessed with great design and visual storytelling.Love making pixel-perfect interfaces.Enjoy researching users and understanding what makes them tick.Are excited to create something meaningful every day.Aren’t afraid of looking at data to improve your designs.About MarvinWorld's most advanced AI for researchMarvin is a research repository and qualitative data analysis platform for research, product, design and marketing teams. We have the most advanced AI in our space and operate on the cutting edge of what's possible.Backed by the most advanced AI in the industry, we help teams centralize all customer feedback, and analyze and share customer learnings. Our research assistant automates the tedious aspects of qualitative research so that product teams spend more time understanding their customers.Our customers include some of the most well-known brands including Microsoft, Chick-fil-A, BestBuy, LinkedIn, HP, VistaPrint, Twilio, Hinge, Staples, and many many others.Backed by some of the most well-known Silicon Valley investors including Sam Altman and Scott Banister. We are one of the fastest-growing companies this space has ever seen.We are a global, fully remote company that loves working with each other. We let our work speak for itself and provide you with extreme ownership and a sense of purpose.",
