		details:
			"UI/UX DesignerCompany: Marvin Location: Fully RemoteRole Type: Full-timeAbout the RoleWe’re looking for a passionate and creative UI/UX Designer to join our rapidly growing team at Marvin. This role gives you the chance to work closely with product, research, and engineering teams while designing meaningful experiences for thousands of users worldwide. If you enjoy solving problems through design, understanding user behavior, and crafting intuitive digital interfaces, this is the perfect place to grow your skills.What You’ll DoConduct user research, gather feedback, and analyze behavioral insights to inform design decisions.Create clear wireframes, user flows, and interactive prototypes that effectively communicate UX concepts.Design polished, intuitive UI screens that balance aesthetics, usability, and brand consistency.Collaborate with product managers, developers, and fellow designers to translate ideas into high-quality product experiences.Plan and run usability tests, identify pain points, and iterate on designs to continuously improve the user journey.What We’re Looking ForExperience as a UI/UX Designer, Product Designer, or similar role.Strong understanding of UX principles, design thinking, and interaction design.Ability to create clean, pixel-perfect UI designs.Experience conducting user research or usability studies.Solid communication and collaboration skills.You’ll Be a Great Fit If You…Are obsessed with design and user experience.Want to create something meaningful every single day.Enjoy understanding users through research and data.Deliver pixel-perfect UI with care and attention to detail.Aren’t afraid to dive into metrics and use insights to improve your designs.About MarvinWorld's most advanced AI for researchMarvin is a research repository and qualitative data analysis platform for research, product, design and marketing teams. We have the most advanced AI in our space and operate on the cutting edge of what's possible.Backed by the most advanced AI in the industry, we help teams centralize all customer feedback, and analyze and share customer learnings. Our research assistant automates the tedious aspects of qualitative research so that product teams spend more time understanding their customers.Our customers include some of the most well-known brands including Microsoft, Chick-fil-A, BestBuy, LinkedIn, HP, VistaPrint, Twilio, Hinge, Staples, and many many others.Backed by some of the most well-known Silicon Valley investors including Sam Altman and Scott Banister. We are one of the fastest-growing companies this space has ever seen.We are a global, fully remote company that loves working with each other. We let our work speak for itself and provide you with extreme ownership and a sense of purpose.",
