		details:
			"The Management Trainee – Analytical Development will support the development, optimization, validation, and transfer of analytical methods required for characterizing biopharmaceutical products such as proteins, monoclonal antibodies, vaccines, and other biotechnology-based entities.\nThis position provides hands-on training, exposure to advanced analytical platforms, and cross-functional collaboration within R&D, Quality, and Manufacturing teams.Key Responsibilities\n1. Analytical Method Development\n\nAssist in developing and optimizing analytical methods for raw materials, in-process samples, and finished biopharmaceutical products.\n\nSupport characterization of biomolecules using physico-chemical and bioanalytical techniques.2. Method Qualification & Validation\n\nParticipate in method qualification/validation studies as per ICH, USP, EP, and regulatory guidelines.\n\nPrepare validation protocols, reports, and data summaries.\n\n3. Documentation & Compliance\n\nMaintain laboratory notebooks, raw data, and electronic documentation in compliance with GLP/GMP standards.\n\nSupport preparation of SOPs, technical reports, COAs, and other documentation.\n\n4. Data Analysis & Reporting\n\nCompile, analyze, and interpret data from analytical experiments.\n\nPresent findings to the analytical development team and cross-functional groups.\n\n5. Technology Transfer\n\nSupport analytical method transfer to QC, manufacturing sites, or external partners.\n\nParticipate in resolving analytical challenges during scale-up and tech transfer.\n\n6. Continuous Learning\n\nLearn and adopt new analytical technologies and emerging regulatory trends.\n\nParticipate in departmental training programs and scientific discussions.",
