			"Resume filtering | Technical interview (00:20) | Personal interview (00:10)",
		details:
			"The Management Trainee – Quality Functions will undergo structured training across Quality Assurance (QA), Quality Control (QC), and Quality Systems within a biosimilar/biotechnology manufacturing environment. This role is designed to build future quality leaders with strong understanding of GxP, regulatory compliance, biosimilar development, process control, and laboratory operations. The trainee will support day-to-day quality activities while learning end-to-end processes for biologics manufacturing and release.Key Responsibilities\n\n1. Quality Assurance (QA)\n\n Support\n implementation and monitoring of cGMP, ICH, WHO, EMA,\n and US FDA compliance across the facility.\n Assist\n with review and approval of controlled documents including SOPs,\n Work Instructions, BMR/BPR, Specifications, and Logbooks.\n Participate\n in Deviation, CAPA, and Change Control initiation, documentation,\n follow-up, and closure.\n Conduct\n routine GMP compliance checks on manufacturing floors and warehouse\n operations.\n Assist\n in regulatory and internal audits (preparation, document collation,\n responses).\n Support\n vendor qualification, material approval processes, and training record\n maintenance.\n Observe\n and assist in quality risk management (FMEA, risk assessment\n tools).\n\n2. Quality Control (QC)\n\n Learn\n and assist in testing of biosimilar raw materials, in-process samples,\n drug substance (DS), and drug product (DP).\n Ensure\n compliance with ALCOA+ data integrity principles.\n Support\n instrument calibration, preventive maintenance, and laboratory\n documentation.\n\n3. Quality Systems & Compliance\n\n Participate\n in Document Control, issuance and archival of GMP documents.\n Learn\n and support LIMS / QMS software systems used in biotech\n environments.\n Assist\n in quality metrics reporting, trend analysis, and continuous improvement\n initiatives.\n Contribute\n to investigation teams for OOS, OOT, deviations, and complaints.\n\n \n\n3. Training & Development Goals\n\n Gain\n working knowledge of biosimilar product lifecycle: cell line,\n upstream, downstream, formulation, filling, and packaging.\n Understand\n comparability studies, analytical similarity, and biosimilarity\n guidelines.\n Build\n competency in Good Documentation Practices (GDP) and Good\n Laboratory Practices (GLP).\n Learn\n root cause analysis methods (Fishbone, 5 Whys, CAPA effectiveness\n checks).\n Develop\n skills in scientific communication, report writing, and cross-functional\n collaboration.",
		info: "",
