			"The Management Trainee – Project Management will\nsupport cross-functional planning, execution, and monitoring of projects within\na biosimilar/biotech organization. This role is designed to develop future\nproject managers who understand drug development pipelines, technology\ntransfer, manufacturing operations, regulatory requirements, and\ncross-functional coordination.\n\nThe trainee will work closely with project managers and\nleadership teams to learn project planning tools, timelines, documentation\nprocedures, and stakeholder communication practices essential in biosimilar\ndevelopment and commercial manufacturing.Primary Responsibilities1. Project Coordination & Planning\n\nAssist in development, tracking, and updating of project plans, timelines, and deliverables for biosimilar development, scale-up, validation, and manufacturing.\n\nSupport coordination between cross-functional teams such as:\n\nR&D / Analytical Development\n\nProcess Development (Upstream/Downstream)\n\nQuality (QA/QC)\n\nRegulatory Affairs\n\nSupply Chain & Logistics\n\nManufacturing / Operations\n\nTechnology Transfer teams\n\nParticipate in project kick-off meetings, milestone reviews, and weekly status updates.\n\n2. Documentation & Reporting\n\nHelp maintain project dashboards, status trackers, Gantt charts, and action-item logs.\n\nAssist in preparation of technical presentations, project summaries, and decision-support documents for leadership review.\n\nDraft meeting minutes, circulate follow-up actions, and track progress to closure.\n\nSupport documentation required for regulatory submissions, tech transfer packages, and process validation plans.\n\n3. Cross-Functional Collaboration\n\nShadow senior project managers and learn how to facilitate communication across departments.\n\nAssist in coordination during:\n\nTechnology transfer\n\nManufacturing readiness reviews (MRR/MRA)\n\nRisk assessments (FMEA, QRM)\n\nAnalytical method transfers\n\nFacilitate alignment on timelines, resources, and deliverables between internal teams and external partners/vendors.\n\n4. Project Execution & Risk Management\n\nHelp identify project risks, delays, and resource gaps; assist in preparing mitigation strategies.\n\nSupport tracking of critical path activities and ensuring timely escalation when deviations occur.\n\nLearn to apply project management methodologies (Waterfall, Agile concepts relevant to biotech operations).\n\n5. Data Analysis & PM Tools\n\nLearn and use project management tools such as MS Project, Smartsheet, Excel trackers, Power BI dashboards, or internal PM systems.\n\nAssist in preparing KPI dashboards, budget tracking sheets, and performance reports.\n\nTraining & Development Objectives\n\nGain end-to-end understanding of biosimilar development, from cell line development to regulatory submission and commercial launch.\n\nLearn fundamentals of CMC, process development, scale-up, and GMP manufacturing workflows.\n\nBuild competence in project governance, resource planning, and risk management techniques.\n\nDevelop strong communication, leadership, and stakeholder management skills.\n\nUnderstand regulatory expectations (ICH, WHO, US FDA, EMA) influencing project timelines and deliverables.",
