		details:
			"Job description:We are currently looking for a Manager (R&D and Production) to work in the field of dentalimplant processing.In this role, you will, Perform all activities related to titanium implant processing following CNC machining.This includes magnetic polishing, anodization, sand blasting, acid etching, ultrasoniccleaning, primary packaging, and secondary packaging. Knowledge of Orthopaedic and Dental Implant Fabrication workflows andbiocompatible material processing. Having Knowledge in Metal Additive Manufacturing and Advanced Laser MaterialProcessing. Candidate must be well aware of physical characterization techniques such as VickersHardness Test, Fatigue Test, UTM, SEM-EDAX, and AFM, and how to analyze theresults of these techniques. Candidates must be well aware of GDP, GLP, and have experience working in cleanroom environments such as ISO-5, ISO-7 classes. Besides, a candidate must know how to operate a microscope and do measurementsof the parts. Candidate must perform sterility checks post-sterilization and hence must be wellaware of microbial techniques. Candidate should strive to fine-tune the processing parameters to achieve betterosseointegration at the same time inhibiting bacterial colonization.For this, candidates must have a practical knowledge of,o Cell adhesion studieso Cell viability studieso Osteogenesis assayso Bacterial inhibition studieso Media preparation, sterilization, etc. Candidate should work on preparing and characterizing hydroxyapatite and tricalciumphosphate nano/microparticles. Candidate must coordinate with the external agencies to design and evaluate testsaccording to the ISO-13485 guidelines and regularly calibrate the instruments. The candidate must have good knowledge of metals, their processing methods,microstructure–property relationships, and suitability for biomedical applications,particularly titanium and its alloys used in dental and orthopedic implants.• Having Knowledge in Welding, Casting, Micro-machining, and HybridManufacturing/Machining processes.• Practical experience in Biomedical Analysis (In-vitro & In-vivo) including biologicalresponse evaluation.",
