		details:
			"About HOC\n\nHOC is a technology and automation company\nbuilding advanced solutions that help enterprises unify fragmented data,\nautomate workflows, and ensure compliance at scale.\n\nOur flagship product, EPIC (Enterprise\nPlatform for Integrated Compliance), is used globally across energy\ntrading, finance, and utilities to integrate data, automate processes, and\nmanage operational and regulatory risk.\n\nHOC is also developing AI-powered\ncapabilities such as Natural Language Query (NLQ) systems, Agentic\nAI frameworks, and Machine Learning models to enhance data\nintelligence, automate decision support, and drive next-generation analytics.\n\nHeadquartered in New York with offices in\nNew Jersey and Mumbai, HOC combines deep domain expertise with strong\nengineering and AI innovation.\n\nRole Overview\n\nAs a System Analyst, you will bridge\nbusiness needs and technical implementation. You will work with clients,\nproduct teams, and developers to analyze processes, design and configure\nsolutions, and ensure successful automation and deployment using HOC’s EPIC\nplatform and related AI-driven frameworks.\n\nThis role requires analytical thinking,\nstrong attention to detail, disciplined execution, and a willingness to\ncontinuously learn new technologies and business processes.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n Analyze and document business\n processes, data models, and compliance workflows.\n Perform gap analysis and design\n solutions using EPIC and related automation components.\n Configure, test, and validate\n workflows, reports, and integrations in client environments.\n Conduct end-to-end testing of\n code, data, and process configurations to ensure accuracy and quality.\n Collaborate with developers to\n integrate ML models, NLQ interfaces, and AI automation components.\n Create and maintain detailed\n documentation including BRDs, Functional Specs, SOPs, and Test Plans.\n Support user acceptance testing,\n deployment, and client training sessions.\n Follow established processes and\n ensure consistent documentation, version control, and delivery standards.\n Continuously identify\n opportunities to improve automation, AI integration, and data quality.\n Participate in internal learning\n programs, certifications, and proof-of-concept projects for professional\n growth.\n Communicate effectively with\n business and technical stakeholders to ensure alignment and clarity.\n\nRequired Skills & Competencies\n\n Strong analytical and logical\n thinking with a process-driven mindset.\n Proficiency in SQL (queries,\n stored procedures) and data analysis.\n Strong data understanding\n with the ability to interpret, validate, and troubleshoot data flows.\n Proficient in Excel for\n data analysis, validation, and reporting.\n Hands-on experience or familiarity\n with BI tools such as Power BI, Tableau, or similar platforms.\n Understanding of data\n integration, workflow automation, and reporting systems.\n Exposure to AI, ML, or NLP\n concepts preferred.\n Ability to debug through logs or\n code and work closely with technical teams.\n High attention to detail,\n documentation discipline, and adherence to process.\n Excellent communication skills and\n a collaborative working style.\n Proactive approach to learning,\n certification, and self-improvement.\n\nNice to Have\n\n Familiarity with Agentic AI,\n prompt-based automation, or low-code workflows.\n Exposure to cloud platforms\n such as AWS or Azure.\n Understanding of compliance,\n risk management, or data governance frameworks.\n\nWhat HOC Offers\n\n Opportunity to work on AI-driven\n enterprise automation and compliance technology.\n Structured onboarding and\n continuous learning through certifications and POCs.\n Transparent performance metrics\n and growth opportunities aligned with defined goals.\n Culture rooted in Integrity,\n Passion, and Joy where excellence is the standard.\n\nCompetitive compensation and a collaborative,\nhigh-performance environment.",
		info: "Rewards and Other Benefits \nAdditional financial and recognition-based benefits include: • Individual and team rewards (RnR) • Project success celebrations • Internet reimbursement • Training and Certification reimbursement • Traveling Reimbursement (applicable for specific employees or roles) • WFO Allowance • Other approved reimbursements Indirect Compensation (non-monetary): • Recognition: Acknowledgment by peers and supervisors through the R&R Program • Career Development: Technical, product, and soft-skill training programs • Paid Time Off: As per the Leave Policy • Employee Engagement: Annual events, monthly and quarterly activities • Work-Life Balance: Hybrid work environment, flexible timing, and opportunities for horizontal and \nvertical growth",
