			"Resume filtering | Technical test (03:00) | Technical interview (01:00)",
		details:
			"Mechanical Design\nEngineer\n\n \n\nTeam\nto deliver design and Integration of Aero engine components and assemblies –\nApply principles product safety, robust design, system engineering, DFX and\nproducibility. Work with the Integrated project team in a collaborative\nenvironment to mature the design through gated technical reviews, securing\nbuyoffs by demonstrating that the physical and functional solutions provided\nachieve the desired product requirements and attributes such as life, cost,\nweight, serviceability. Deliver definitions for manufacturing – this may be\ndone in the traditional drawings or Model Based Definitions whilst complying to\nthe customer operating procedures and best practices.\n\n \n\nKey\nResponsibilities\n\n• \nYou may need to Integrate physical design solution at module level\nand / or with the owners of nonphysical data functional such as Air Systems,\nOil Systems, aerothermal, Performance, etc.\n\n• \nA on need basis, address the arisings from the fleet and perform\nroute cause investigation to help improve the safety, Reliability and\nAvailability; Also assess impact on the component assemblies based on changes\nto the understanding of the engine operating conditions.\n\n• \nKnowledge of gas turbine components or an understanding of\nmaterial, thermal, mechanical, and dynamic issues associated with the core\nturbomachinery components / modules (such as Compressor, combustion, Rotative\ndiscs, casings, structures, Turbine Statics, shafts etc.) may be advantageous.\n\n• \nAchieve the Right First Time and On Time Delivery targets planned\ndeliverables in design to make. You will also work towards developing optimized\nhigh quality code deliverables, continual knowledge management and adherence to\nthe organizational guidelines and processes.\n\n• \nPrior Experience of working in the gas Turbine Product, Aviation\nindustry or within the APQP/PPAP framework (Aerospace Standard AS9145) may be\nadvantageous.\n\n• \nStrong desire for continuous self-improvement, and Improvement of\nprocesses\n\n• \nAbility to Apply analytical creative thinking to solve technical\nproblems.\n\n• \nGood communication and presentation skills; Ability to articulate\ncomplex topics with people at all levels of the organization and customers.\n\n• \nKnowledgeable on the usage of Product Lifecycle Management (e.g.,\nTeamcenter) and Modelling software (e.g.: UG NX)\n\n \n\n \n\nProduct Definition\nEngineer\n\n \n\nTo be part of the team with experience of\nmodelling, drafting and MBD on a variety of complex components and\nsub-assemblies in core turbomachinery domain (such as Compressor, combustion,\nRotative discs, casings, structures, Turbine Statics, shafts etc.) may be\nadvantageous.\n\n \n\nKey\nResponsibilities\n\n• \nDeliver Geometrical definitions for engineered product- This may\nneed you to create 3D models, Digital Assemblies, General Arrangements\ndrawings, sections, Models for stress analysis, etc.\n\n• \nDeliver the manufacturing Instructions whilst complying to the\ncustomer operating procedures and best practices. This may be done via\ntraditional drawings or Model Based Definitions \n\n• \nInteract with Designers, Manufacturing to deliver the FM\nobjectives including producibility.\n\n• \nAchieve the Right First Time and On Time Delivery targets planned\ndeliverables in design to make. You will also work towards developing optimized\nhigh quality code deliverables, continual knowledge management and adherence to\nthe organizational guidelines and processes.\n\n• \nGD&T ASME Y14.5 and Understanding of Mass Properties\n\n• \nKnowledgeable on the usage of Product Lifecycle Management (e.g.:\nTeamcenter) and Modelling software (e.g.: UG NX)\n\n• \nStrong desire for continuous self-improvement, and Improvement of\nprocesses\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\nMechanical\nIntegrity Engineer\n\n \n\nMechanical\nIntegrity (stress) engineers ensure the integrity of gas turbine products. Opportunity to work across a wide variety of\ncommodities (Fan, Compressors, Casings, Structures, Combustor, Turbines) design\nfunction by undertaking analysis of the proposed designs and in-service issues\nto ensure that they are robust and that they meet requirements. predict the\nmechanical behaviour of components and sub-systems considering various failure\nmechanisms (e.g., proof, ultimate, fatigue (low & high cycle), creep etc.)\nand contributing factors (e.g., vibration, thermal induced loads, inherent\nmanufacturing anomalies, corrosion, extreme operating conditions such as blade\nout, over-speed, over pressure and burst duct etc.).\n\n \n\nKey\nAccountabilities\n\n• \nConduct Mechanical Analysis and Design of Experiments to ensure\nthe integrity of products.\n\n• \nTo resolve problems through engineering judgements. \n\n• \nWork as part of a multi discipline teams to ensure new designs are\nfit for purpose (cost, weight, performance, manufacturability etc.).\n\n• \nTo actively promote, encourage and support the identification and\nimplementation of continuous improvements (of tools, processes, and methods)\nboth within and outside their immediate sphere of influence and take prompt\naction across the wider team.\n\n• \nThe ability to effectively communicate the method and results of\ncomplex analyses to peers, senior colleagues, and external organisations such\nas customers or regulatory bodies.\n\n• \nAn understanding of material behaviour, crack propagation,\ncontact, thermo-mechanical fatigue, and statistics.\n\n• \nExperience of, or a good appreciation of, finite element stressing\ntechniques (SC03, Abaqus, Ansys, LS-Dyna), complex meshing (Hypermesh,\nUnigraphics etc) and data storage (Teamcenter).\n\n• \nAn ability to apply logical, analytical, and innovative thinking\non a range of technical problems and make balanced decisions across technical\nand business parameters.\n\n• \nKnowledge and experience of product integrity, liability, and\naerospace certification frameworks. \n\n• \nTo be a point of contact within a given engineering discipline and\nto share subject matter knowledge across the function.\n\n \n\nRotatives Lifing\nEngineer\n\nTeam is responsible for Rotative Component Lifing for Aero Engine that\nhelps discover and define the problem statement, evaluates the solution\noptions, and makes recommendations. One will perform lifing of various\nTurbomachinery components, ownership of critical parts lifing and disc NPI\nalong with modifications.\n\nKey Accountabilities\n\n• \nConcept design and detailed design of turbo machinery components\n(especially Gas Turbine) with very good proficiency in lifing analysis.\n\n• \nExposure or Experience in CAE platforms like ABAQUS with very good\nmeshing and complex analysis capabilities.\n\n• \nExperience in mechanical integrity\nassessments, like Structural, Thermal, Transient, Creep, Fatigue, and their interactions.\n\n• \nAnalytical and Communication skills, Planning and Co-ordination\nskills",
