			"Job\nDescription- Power Programmers - Specialist Programmer\n\nInfosys has designed the Power Programmers career track\nfor polyglots who are passionate about programming and want to do more than\nprogramming as usual, who will be working on emerging and next-gen\ntechnologies. In this role, you will build platforms, marketplaces, innovative\nsolutions, contribute and develop open software. will collaborate with some of\nthe best talents in the industry to create and implement innovative high\nquality programming solutions. You will be part of a learning culture, where\nteamwork and collaboration are encouraged, excellence is rewarded, and\ndiversity is respected and valued.Technology Focus Areas - Frontier Engineering\n\n• \nExponential Engineering\n[Greenfield, Brownfield, Platforms]\n\n• \nAI & Agentic Engineering\n[Cloud AI Platforms, Open Source, S4HANA, Salesforce]\n\n• \nSoftware Resiliency Engineering\n[Experts across Enterprise stack]\n\n• \nForward Deployed Engineering\n[Services & Industry Stack]\n\n \n\n1. Specialist\nProgrammer – Level 1, you would \n\n• \nDevelop full-stack applications using\nmodern frameworks and best practices.\n\n• \nApply AI in software engineering to\nenhance productivity and quality.\n\n• \nWork collaboratively with dynamic teams to\nbuild software applications using a predictable Agile DevSecOps model.\n\n• \nLeverage cloud platforms, DevOps, and AI\ntools throughout the development lifecycle.\n\n• \nDeliver innovation in chosen technologies,\ndriving impactful solutions.\n\n• \nContribute to open-source projects to\nbuild community engagement and technical visibility.\n\n2. Specialist\nProgrammer – Level 2. In addition to Level 1, you would \n\n• \nTake on more complex challenges— develop scalable\nsystems and solve advanced technical problems.\n\n• \nProvide technical guidance to team\nmembers and apply deep technology-specific knowledge to real-world projects.\n\n• \nDevelop as an AI Master, contributing\nto the creation of Proof of Concepts (PoCs) and Minimum Viable Products (MVPs).\n\n• \nDrive innovation through open-source\ncontributions, publishing white papers, and fostering a culture of\nexperimentation.\n\n3. Specialist\nProgrammer – Level 3. In addition to Level 2, you would \n\n• \nCollaborate across teams to guide technical\ndirection and lead experimentation with emerging technologies. \n\n• \nDevelop as a Forward Deployed Engineer\n(FDE), working closely with clients and internal stakeholders. \n\n• \nDesign and develop enterprise-grade\nplatforms that scale across industries. \n\n• \nPlay a key role in strategic technology\ninitiatives, influencing architecture and innovation. \n\n• \nContribute to AI/ML innovation,\nincluding building Small Language Models (SLMs) and advanced algorithms.\n\n• \nEngage actively in open-source communities,\npublish white papers, and drive patentable innovations.\n\nAdditional Competencies\n\n• \nStrong analytical and problem-solving\nskills to tackle complex technical challenges.\n\n• \nEffective collaboration and communication\nskills for cross-functional teamwork.\n\n• \nDemonstrated consistency in competitive\ncoding platforms (e.g., HackerRank, CodeChef, LeetCode).\n\n• \nPossession of industry-recognized external\ncertifications, where applicable.\n\n• \nActive participation in technology forums\nand contributions to open-source communities.Selection process:\n\n \n\n· Eligible candidates\nwould go through an internet-based programming ability test (3 questions, 180\nminutes duration)\n\n· An in-depth technical\ninterview (60 mins) would be conducted for candidates who clear the test\nprocess.",
