		details:
			"The primary purpose of this role is to design, build, and optimize large-scale, high-performance software systems that power core business platforms across the organisation. The role requires strong fundamentals in algorithms, system design, and distributed computing, along with the ability to work on emerging technologies such as vibe coding, automation frameworks, data-driven engineering, and event-stream processing",
		info: "1. Platform & System Developmenta. Design and develop scalable, high-performance software components using modern engineering practices and clean coding principles.b. Implement system modules that handle concurrency, low-latency operations, real-time processing, and fault tolerance.c. Ensure architectural consistency, code quality, and modularity across services and components.2. Vibe Coding, Automation & Developer Productivity Toolsa. Build and enhance tools leveraging vibe coding / AI-assisted development, automated refactoring, and intelligent code generation frameworks.b. Integrate automated testing, static analysis, and continuous validation tools to reduce manual effort and improve release velocity.c. Develop internal engineering utilities that streamline workflows for debugging, environment setup, versioning, and CI/CD processes.3. Distributed Systems & Event-Driven Architecturea. Work with event-streaming systems (Kafka etc.) to build real-time data pipelines, publish/subscribe workflows, and event-driven microservices.b. Optimize system throughput, fault recovery mechanisms, and distributed state management.c. Implement robust back-pressure handling, retries, and idempotent processing for mission-critical flows.4. Integration Engineering & API Frameworksa. Develop and maintain APIs, messaging interfaces, and integration layers with third-party or internal platforms.b. Ensure compatibility with industry protocols and secure communication standards.c. Build scalable middleware and gateway components for routing, authentication, and data transformation.5. Deployment, Release Engineering & Reliabilitya. Manage containerisation, infrastructure-as-code, and automated deployment pipelines for smooth releases.b. Conduct resilience testing, latency benchmarking, and load simulations to validate system readiness.c. Improve system uptime through proactive monitoring, error-budgeting, and SRE-aligned engineering practices.6. Technical Collaboration & Continuous Improvementa. Work closely with architecture, DevOps, platform engineering, and data teams to refine system designs.b. Participate in technical reviews, design discussions, and post-incident analysis to drive platform hardening.c. Continuously evaluate new frameworks, engineering stacks, and developer tools to improve overall productivity and platform capabilities.",
