		details:
			"The incumbent will be responsible to design, develop, and deploy advanced AI and machine learning solutions across the group. The incumbent will work to architect and scalable AI systems that enhance decision-making, automation, and customer experience, while ensuring high standards of performance, reliability, and security. He/she will drive end-to-end AI development—from model design to production deployment—enabling impactful use cases across investments, operations, customer platforms, and internal processes.",
		info: "1. AI Strategy, Ideation & Use Case Discoverya. Perform feasibility assessments through data audits, workflow decomposition, and technical constraints analysis.b. Identify high-value AI/ML and LLM opportunities through quantitative impact modelling and algorithmic fit evaluation.c. Define problem statements with measurable KPIs, technical success criteria, and model performance benchmarks.2. Advanced Research, Modelling & Experimentationa. Develop and refine ML/LLM models using statistical methods, optimisation techniques, signal processing or deep learning architectures.b. Drive experimentation through controlled trials, feature engineering, model validation, and hyperparameter optimisation.c. Implement explainability methods (SHAP, LIME, feature attribution) aligned with BFSI risk and governance standards.3. Architecture, Prototyping & AI Engineeringa. Architect scalable AI pipelines including data ingestion, feature stores, vector databases, and model serving layers.b. Build POCs and production-grade systems involving RAG pipelines, embeddings, APIs, and microservices for AI workloads.c. Define and optimise MLOps/LLMOps workflows covering CI/CD for models,versioning, orchestration, and automated evaluation.4. Deployment, Testing & Operationalisationa. Lead technical deployment via containerisation, API integration, cloud provisioning, and performance tuning.b. Conduct UAT, stress tests, drift checks, and latency benchmarking to validate production readiness.c. Implement model governance controls including audit trails, security checks, and configuration management.5. Monitoring, Governance & Continuous Improvementa. Establish monitoring frameworks for model drift, data drift, inference quality, and resource utilisation.b. Implement automated retraining, periodic performance recalibration, and model lifecycle optimisation.c. Ensure compliance with Responsible AI, data privacy, and regulatory requirements through built-in controls.6. Cross-Functional Technical Collaborationa. Collaborate with Data Engineering, Cloud, and Architecture teams on data pipelines, storage design, and compute optimisation.b. Translate complex modelling constraints into system requirements for product and engineering teams.c. Provide technical mentorship on algorithms, experimentation design, and scalable AI engineering patterns.",
		reqs: "Education• Bachelor’s in Computer Science, Data Science, AI, Engineering, Mathematics, or related technical field.2. Product & Analytical Skills• Strong problem-solving skills• Comfort with data-driven decision-making.3. Technical Understanding• Understanding of ML concepts (classification, regression, evaluation metrics, model lifecycle).4. Behavioural Competencies• Curiosity, willingness to learn, and ability to operate in an emerging tech environment.• High ownership and ability to manage multiple initiatives.",
