		details:
			"Your Role in the RevolutionAt WinZO, UI/UX design goes far beyond wireframes and polished screens, it's about building seamless, rewarding, and culturally resonant experiences that keep millions of users across the globe engaged, day after day.Our team isn’t just about handing off designs; we are co-creators of the entire product journey. Every interaction you design from start to finish should feel fast, intuitive, and deeply satisfying.What You’ll do at WinZOTranslate concepts into wireframes, prototypes, and polished interfaces that balance usability and delight.Contribute to end-to-end user journeys ranging from coming up with a new feature to completing transactions in a tap.Collaborate closely with fellow designers, product managers and developers to ship pixel-perfect, responsive experiences.Participate in user research, focus group discussions, and feedback sessions to ground your designs in real behavior.Build with speed: iterate quickly, test often, and improve based on live feedback.Collaborate and experiment along with our graphic design team to create motion design, animations, and microinteractions that make every interaction more engaging and joyful.Essential Skills:A strong interest in creating delightful, functional experiences for a varied user base.Proficiency in Figma for UI design, autolayouting, prototyping, and collaboration.Confident working across mobile, web, and responsive game environments.A foundational understanding of UI/UX principles, user flows, and interaction design.Eagerness to learn from feedback, improve with iterations, and contribute to team-wide design goals.Understanding of design fundamentals: typography, color theory, layout, and iconography.Strong communication and presentation skills for sharing design rationale.Familiarity with design handoff tools like Zeplin, FigJam, or Dev Mode.Preferred Skills:A mindset of ownership and collaboration, ready to grow in a fast-paced, high-impact design environmentSkilled at exploring and adapting visual styles with creative agility.Experience with Generative AI Tools, After Effects, and Framer.Motion design for transitions or microinteractions (e.g. Lottie, Principle)",
