		details:
			"About WinZOFounded in 2018, WinZO is India’s largest social interactive entertainment platform, with 250 million global users and a portfolio of over 100 competitive games across multiple e-sports and social gaming formats. By creating an alternative distribution model for developers, content creators, and entrepreneurs, WinZO helps global creators monetize at scale, while championing the rise of ‘Made in India’ content on the world stage.At the core of our journey lies a legacy of excellence: a team composed of bright minds from top institutions and industry-leading organizations who combine strong technical foundations with creativity and strategic vision. This unique blend enables us to address complex, large-scale challenges while delivering innovative solutions that engage users across geographies.1. GRAPHIC DESIGNERWhat You’ll do as a Graphic DesignerOwn the creation of high‑impact graphics for web, app, and marketing channels by crafting layouts, typography treatments, and color palettes that speak to diverse user personas.Building digital posters, thumbnails of the TV series content, online and offline event creatives, merchandising, newsletters, emailers, brand and marketing assets, publication of reports, brochures, in-app creatives, social media assets.Rapidly iterate on designs based on stakeholder and user‑research feedback—balancing brand consistency with fresh, context‑driven creativity.Collaborate closely with motion artists, UI/UX, and content teams to embed graphics into interactive and video experiences at 250 M+ userbase scale.Conduct design research: analyze competitors, gather visual trends, and translate insights into sketches, mood‑boards, and prototypes.Evolve our asset library: renewing files, updating templates, and ensuring everyone works from the latest brand system.Essential Skills (Graphic Design):Experienced as a graphic designer, with a polished portfolio demonstrating digital and print work.Expert in Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, and InDesign for pixel‑perfect execution.Strong foundations in layout, typography, color theory, and user‑centric visual hierarchy.Excellent communication and collaboration skills, thriving on cross‑team feedback loops.Preferred Skills (Graphic Design):Proficiency in Figma for rapid wireframes and UI handoffs.Illustration chops, should be able to sketch icons or custom art assets without needing a specialist.Basic motion‑graphics know‑how (After Effects) to support animated banners or social clips.Research‑driven mindset: comfortable diving into data dashboards or user interviews to inform design choices.2. ILLUSTRATION DESIGNERWhat You’ll do as an Illustration DesignerDesign and deliver high‑impact icons, 2D art, character, elements and environment illustrations, compositions, infographics, and storyboards that translate narratives, data and UX insights into clear visual stories.Collaborate with product, research, and motion teams to identify illustration opportunities that solve real user problems.Rapidly prototype concepts, sketching, wireframing, and producing polished visuals to validate ideas with stakeholders.Dive into user‑research findings and analytics to inform your style choices, color palettes, and composition.Essential Skills (Illustration Designer):Have expertise in Photoshop or Procreate.Strong fundamentals in drawing, composition, color theory and typography.Adaptable across digital and print formats, with a user‑centric mindset.Strong portfolio with varied artwork, quick turnarounds in designs.Clear communicator who thrives on feedback and iteration.Have a knack for illustrations and drawing of various art styles.Preferred Skills (Illustration Designer):Experience exporting vector and raster assets optimized for diverse platforms.Layering knowledge to support handoff into motion pipelines.Portfolio showing research‑driven, culturally aware illustrations.Understanding and use of AI tools and proficiency in using the AI tools is a plus. 3. MOTION DESIGNERWhat You’ll do as a motion designer-Craft Engaging Micro‑Animations: Design and animate in‑app interactions like loaders, transitions, and feedback states, that elevate user delight and reinforce brand personality.Prototype & Iterate Quickly: Build interactive motion prototypes in After Effects or Figma to validate timing, easing, and visual impact with stakeholders and users.Maintain & Evolve Motion Library: Curate a shared repository of animation presets, easing curves, and asset templates, ensuring consistency and rapid reuse.Drive Research‑Led Creativity: Monitor motion trends, test new tools or techniques, and propose innovative treatments that keep WinZO at the forefront of animated UX.Storytelling & Educational Content: Creating engaging videos that showcase products, highlight features, and communicate brand narratives effectively, while educating and connecting with the audience.Marketing & Campaign Assets: Design motion graphics for campaigns, social ads, and app store previews, ensuring assets are optimized for multiple formats and markets (India, US, etc.).Cross team collaboration: Work closely with product managers, designers, and developers, marketing teams to design solutions.Essential Skills (motion designer):Proficiency in Adobe After Effects and Premiere Pro for high‑fidelity motion work.Strong grounding in 12 principles of animations: timing, anticipation, staging, stretch and squash etc.Exceptional strategic and storytelling abilities, translating data and user research into compelling motion experiences.Excellent communication and collaboration, thriving in feedback‑driven sprints.Preferred Skills (motion designer):Basic 3D motion skills (Cinema 4D, Blender) for simple scene builds or camera moves.Scripting know‑how (Expressions in After Effects) to automate repetitive tasks.Exposure to Lottie or JSON‑based export for mobile‑optimized micro‑animations.Understanding and use of AI tools and proficiency in using the AI tools is a plus. 4. 3D & Animation DesignerWhat You’ll do as a 3D & Animation DesignerTranslate concept art and sketches into polished 3D models and textures that bring our campaigns to life.Prototype animated sequences like character gestures, environmental effects, simple camera moves to validate creative direction.Collaborate with UI/UX, motion, and engineering teams to integrate 3D assets seamlessly into gameplay and marketing surfaces.Research and experiment with emerging tools and techniques such as PBR workflows, procedural modeling, or real‑time shaders to push our visual quality forward.Essential Skills (3D & Animation):Proficiency in Blender or Maya for modeling, texturing, and basic animation.Solid grasp of PBR texturing, topology, and UV layout principles.Keen eye for form, lighting, and visual storytelling in 3D space.Strong communication and willingness to iterate based on feedback.Preferred Skills (3D & Animation):Basic scripting (Python) to automate routine tasks or batch processes.Exposure to Substance Painter/Designer or similar for advanced material creation.Experience with Generative AI ToolsA portfolio that demonstrates both creative flair and technical understanding of 3D assets.",
