		details:
			"RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT (R&D)R&D at Maruti Suzuki India Limited is a cornerstone of the company’s strategy to maintain its position as a leading automotive manufacturer in India and to enhance its global presence. Maruti Suzuki’s R&D roles are in three broad areas, each focusing on different aspects of vehicle development and innovationA. Product Planning AreaThis area is responsible for transforming visionary ideas into market leading products, combining strategic planning, cutting edge design, cost effectiveness and innovative management.B. Engineering AreaThis area is responsible for conceptualization & development of new models. They oversee vehicle engineering aspects of the body, chassis, advance powertrain systems (ICE, BEVs, Hybrid Powertrains) and other critical aspects such as infotainment systems, telematics, ADAS. etc. of new models for India and other export markets.C. Homologation & Regulation AreaThis area is responsible for ensuring that every MSIL car meets both national and international safety, environment, and quality standards and that it adheres to latest automotive regulations, before it reaches the customer. Also representing the company in various technical committees for formation of regulations.R&D at MSIL is growing rapidly and Maruti is investing in new products, people, technology and facilities to become a world class R&D center. The R&D facility at Rohtak houses a world class test track which is one of the best in Asia. The Rohtak R&D facility will help Maruti Suzuki engineers to Experiment, Develop & Test products and technologies for not only Indian markets but for Global markets as well.The Engineering Top Management interact regularly with young people for mentoring. A world class R&D facility with challenging opportunities awaits young engineers to be a part of The Maruti Story.",
