			"Resume filtering | Technical test (24:00) | Technical interview (00:30) | Personal interview (00:20)",
		details:
			"About Bajaj AutoBajaj Auto is one of the world's most admired manufacturers of two- and three-wheelers. As India’s top motorcycle exporter, the company operates in over 70 countries, with more than 18 million motorcycles on roads globally. Bajaj Auto has achieved a significant milestone by becoming the first company in its category to reach a market capitalization of INR one trillion.Job Title: Graduate Trainee Engineer (GTE) Role: Automotive\nStyling Job Purpose: \nSupport the Styling Design team in creating visually engaging, innovative, and user-friendly \ndesigns across vehicles (motorcycles, scooters, three-wheelers, EVs, etc.), concepts, and \ndigital interfaces. This role offers exposure to diverse design domains for building strong \ncreative, technical, and visualization skills. Key Responsibilities: • Develop creative styling concepts for Bajaj and partner brands across automotive \nsegments. • Work on color, graphics, surfacing, and visual compositions to improve product \naesthetics. • Collaborate with designers, engineers, and brand teams to deliver consistent \nexperiences. • Contribute to UX/UI for rider and driver interfaces (instrument clusters, HMI screens). • Create wireframes, mockups, and prototypes to communicate design intent. • Apply typography, color theory, and layout for visually balanced outputs. • Stay updated with design trends, technologies, and best practices in automotive and \ndigital design. • Support clay modelling and visualization activities as needed. • Participate in brainstorming to deliver fresh, innovative design ideas. Tools & Software Exposure: \nAlias, Blender, V-Red, Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, Figma, Adobe XD, InDesign, KeyShot, 3D \nscanning systems, clay modelling tools. Key Skills Required: • Basic understanding of automotive styling, form, and aesthetics. • Proficiency in Adobe Creative Suite, Alias, Blender, V-Red, Figma. • Knowledge of 3D rendering, digital modelling, surface graphics, and HMI design. • Strong grasp of UX/UI design fundamentals and user-centered design thinking. • Visualization and storytelling ability for presentations. • Teamwork, time management, and attention to detail. Preferred Attributes: • Passion for automotive design and emerging mobility trends. • Curiosity to learn across styling, CAS modelling, UX/UI, and clay modelling. • Creative mindset with technical understanding.",
