		details:
			"About Bajaj AutoBajaj Auto is one of the world's most admired manufacturers of two- and three-wheelers. As India’s top motorcycle exporter, the company operates in over 70 countries, with more than 18 million motorcycles on roads globally. Bajaj Auto has achieved a significant milestone by becoming the first company in its category to reach a market capitalization of INR one trillion.Graduate Trainee Engineer Role- CAS\nModelling Job Purpose: \nJoin the digital modelling team to create high-quality, production-ready surfacing and CAS \n(Class-A Surfacing) models for future Bajaj and partner vehicles. Enable the translation of \ncreative concepts into manufacturable digital assets. Key Responsibilities: • Work closely with design and engineering teams to develop surface data for vehicles. • Create Class-A quality digital models using Alias, Blender, V-Red, and related software. • Support design visualization and physical model development (clay, rapid prototyping). • Optimize surface geometry for manufacturability, aesthetic appeal, and engineering \nfeasibility. • Collaborate on iterative design refinement based on feedback from styling and \nengineering. • Prepare visualizations and renderings for design reviews and management \npresentations. • Maintain model fidelity throughout the design development process. Tools & Software Exposure: \nAlias, Blender, V-Red, Autodesk Maya, 3D scanning tools, clay modelling reference, rapid \nprototyping software. Key Skills Required: • Strong fundamentals in digital surface modelling and Class-A surfacing principles. • Proficiency in Alias and other industry-standard surfacing tools. • Understanding of automotive form, proportion, and surface aesthetics. • Visualization and presentation skills using rendering tools. • Attention to detail, ability to work iteratively and meet tight deadlines. Preferred Attributes: \n• Passion for precision modelling and digital craftsmanship. \n• Ability to collaborate effectively across design and engineering teams. \n• Curiosity for new tools and techniques in digital modelling.",
