		details:
			"Key ResponsibilitiesArchitect and develop highly scalable, fault-tolerant backend systems using Node.js, TypeScript, and NestJS.Design and implement robust data models with PostgreSQL, including schema design, indexing, and performance optimization.Drive system design discussions focusing on scalability, distributed architecture, observability, and maintainability.Provide technical leadership to the team through mentorship, architecture reviews, and ownership of key systems.Own the CI/CD pipeline setup for fast, reliable, and secure deployments using modern DevOps practices.Implement and maintain caching and queuing mechanisms using Redis (with queues) in production-grade projects.Design and manage search capabilities using Elasticsearch, including indexing strategies and relevance tuning.Integrate and maintain graph databases (Neo4j or AWS Neptune) for graph-based data processing and querying.Lead and conduct comprehensive code reviews that uphold engineering excellence and knowledge sharing.Drive the implementation of secure coding practices and ensure compliance with security and privacy standards.Contribute to system observability using tools like Prometheus, Grafana, or other logging/monitoring stacks.Collaborate closely with product managers, frontend teams, and stakeholders to align technical decisions with business goals.Continuously evaluate and adopt new technologies to improve scalability, performance, and developer productivity.Required Skills and QualificationsB.E./B.Tech or M.Tech in Computer Science or a related technical field.Must have built production-grade applications end-to-end from scratch — projects cloned, learned from tutorials, or modified from GitHub do not qualify.Expert-level proficiency in Node.js, TypeScript, and backend architecture patterns.Strong experience in debugging complex distributed systems — able to isolate, analyze, and resolve issues effectively.Must have production experience with Redis queues in a real application context.Must have hands-on experience with Elasticsearch and have used it for real-world search and analytics use cases.Must have hands-on experience with a graph database such as Neo4j or Amazon Neptune in production.Experience with AWS or similar cloud infrastructure, including setting up cloud-native architectures and services.Proven record of setting up CI/CD pipelines using tools like GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Jenkins, or CircleCI.Demonstrated ability to perform rigorous code reviews and maintain high standards for code quality and documentation.Strong understanding of microservices, event-driven architecture, REST, and GraphQL APIs.Excellent communication skills — able to collaborate with stakeholders and mentor junior engineers.Bonus: Contributions to open-source projects, participation in tech conferences, or leadership in engineering communities.",
